th=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font size=\"3\"><font size=\"4\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">date command</span></b></font></font> </p><div> <font size=\"3\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">1. Function</span></b></font> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display or modify the system time and date. Only the super user can use the date command to set the time, the average user can only use date command to display the time. date syntax is as follows:</span> </div><div> <font size=\"+0\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">date [options] displays the time format (+ start, followed by time format)</span></font></font> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Date command options and their descriptions are as follows.</span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">--S - set: Set the system time.</span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">--D - date: display description date.</span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Time display format shown in Table 4.3.</span> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Table 4.3 Time Display Format</span></font> </div><p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"97%\"><tbody><tr><td width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Format</span></font> </div></td><td width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Meaning that</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% H</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Show hours, said the range is 00 to 23</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% I</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Show hours, said the range is 01 to 12</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% K</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Show hours, said the range of 0 to 23</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% L</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Show hours, said the range of 1 to 12</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% M</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Shown in minutes, the display format for the 00 ~ 59</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% S</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Show seconds, the display format for the 00 ~ 59</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% P</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display is the AM (morning) or PM (afternoon)</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% R</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display time in the format hh: mm: ss AM or PM, where hh for hours, mm the minutes, ss for seconds</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% T</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display time in the format hh: mm: ss</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% X</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display the year and date in the format mm / dd / yyyy, where yyyy represents the year</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% X</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display time format, equivalent to% H:% M:% S\'s portfolio</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% A</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display of the week</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% B or% B</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Displays the month,% b is a short month,% B is to show the full name of month</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% M</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Displays the month, said the format is from 01 to 12</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% Z</span></font> </div&gt; </td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Time Zone Display</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% D</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Shows the first few days a month</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% D</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display the year and month, in the format mm / dd / yy, where yy the last two digits representing the year</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% Y or% y</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display the year,% Y display the full year,% y last two digits of the year show</span></font> </div></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"23%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">% C</span></font> </div></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"76%\"><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Display the date and time format, equivalent to &quot;% a% d% b% Y% r% Z&quot; a combination of</span></font> </div></td></tr></tbody></table></p><div><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Ã‚Â </span></div><div> <font size=\"3\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">2. Example</span></b></font> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">(1) with the specified time and date format.</span> </div><div> <font size=\"+0\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"># Date \'+ This date now is:% x, time is now:% X, thanks!\'</span></font></font> </div><div> <font size=\"+0\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">This date now is: 07/15/2008, time is now: 07:41:35 PM, thanks!</span></font></font> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">(2) to modify the system time.</span> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux /] # date-s 20080715</span></font> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Tue Jul 15 00:00:00 CST 2008</span></font> </div><div> <font size=\"+0\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux /] # date-s 17:25</span></font></font> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Tue Jul 15 17:25:00 CST 2008</span></font> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">The above two can be merged together.</span> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux /] # date-s &quot;20080715 17:25&quot;</span></font> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Tue Jul 15 17:25:00 CST 2008</span></font> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\">(3) shows the time two days ago.</span> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux /] # date \'+% Y-% m-% d\'</span></font> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">2008-07-15</span></font> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ server108 /] # date-d &quot;2 days ago&quot; +% Y-% m-% d</span></font> </div><div> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">2008-07-13</span></font> </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','date command1. FunctionDisplay or modify the system time and date. Only the super user can use the date command to set the time, the average user can only use date command to display the time. date syntax is as follows:date [options] displays the time format (+ start, followed by time format)Date...'),(68,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0725/357.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Linux system management and maintenance of the-ls command','Linux_system_management_and_maintenance_of_thels_command','2010-07-25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">ls command</span></span></b> </p><div> <b><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><spa