run: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">options:</span></font> options for the command said.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-char-type: symbol; mso-symbol-font-family: &apos;Wingdings 2&apos;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Wingdings 2&quot;; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-char-type: symbol; mso-symbol-font-family: &apos;Wingdings 2&apos;\">-</span></span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">arguments:</span></font> that command.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">At the command line, options are one or more letter code, mainly used to change the command executed. Options generally preceded by a <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;-&quot;</span></font> symbol used to distinguish between parameters. For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls-a</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ls</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command with <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">the-a</span></font> option lists all the files in the current directory (including hidden files). If</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ls</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">without <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;-a&quot;</span></font> option, only display the current directory the file names and directories (Do not show hidden files).</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">General commands have many options, you can list them separately, you can also <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;-&quot;</span></font> behind the need of the options listed, for example,</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ls-a-l</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Can also be written:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ls-al</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Many commands can accept parameters. Parameter is the option followed by one or more strings that specify the operation of the command object, such as files or directories. For example, to display</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ etc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory of all documents and information, using the following command:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls-al <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> / Etc</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Special circumstances, some command with no arguments, such as</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ls</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command, and some have parameters. When the parameter is not enough,</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">will give error. For example,</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">mv</span></font><html> ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\' &quot;&gt; command at least two parameters. </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # mv <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> mylinux1.txt <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> mylinux.txt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">In a command line <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell,</span></font> you can enter multiple commands, separate each command with a semicolon, for example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls-al; cp mylinux1.txt <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> mylinux2.txt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Instead multi-line can also enter a command, use the <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;\\&quot;</span></font> will continue to the next line of a command:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # cp-i \\</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; Mylinux1.txt \\</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; Mylinux2.txt</span></font> </p><h4 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: Ã©Â»Â‘Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial\">2.</span> shell</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã©Â»Â‘Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial\">wildcards</span> </h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Wildcard mainly to user description of file or directory, for example, the user only needs to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;. Sh&quot;</span></font> at the end of the file, you can easily use the wildcard to achieve. Various versions of the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">has a wildcard, the wildcard characters are special characters, users can use command line parameters of these characters, the file name or path name of the match.</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">with the command line will match the rules specified in line with all the file names or path names as the order parameter, and then execute this command.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">bash</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">wildcard commonly used with <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;*&quot;, &quot;?&quot;, &quot;[].&quot;</span></font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(1) &quot;*&quot;</span></font> - match any one or more characters</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"><html> style = &quot;background-color: # d9d9d9&quot;&gt; [root @ WEBServer ~] # ls *. txt </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">This command is to list all of the current directory to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;. Txt&quot;</span></font> at the end of the file (remove the <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;.&quot;</span></font> At the beginning of the file).</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # cp doc / * <span style=\"mso-tab-count: 1\"> </span> / Opt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">That the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">doc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory of all files (except with <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;.&quot;</span></font> At the beginning of the file) copy to the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ opt</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory.</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls-al / etc /*/*. conf</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Listed in</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ etc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">subdirectory of the directory of all the <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;. Conf&quot;</span></font> at the end of the file. In the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ etc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;. Conf&quot;</span></font> at the end of the file will not be listed.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(2) &quot;?&quot;</span></font> - Matches any single character</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls ab?. Txt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Will be listed at the beginning of the current directory to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ab,</span></font> then a letter is any character, followed by <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;. Txt&quot;</span></font> at the end of the file.</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls ab??. Txt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><html> os; &quot;&gt; will be listed <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">at the beginning of</span> the current directory to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ab</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">then any character of the two letters, followed <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">by&quot;.</span></font></span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">txt</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">&quot;at the end of the file.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(3) &quot;[]&quot;</span></font> - is included in square brackets matches any single character within the</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls / dev / sda [12345]</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ Dev/sda1 <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> / Dev/sda2 <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> / Dev/sda3 <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> / Dev/sda4 <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> / Dev/sda5</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Listed above in the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ dev</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory to</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">sda</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">beginning, the first <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">4</span></font> characters are <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">1, 2, 3,</span></font></span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">4</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">or <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">5,</span></font> all the files.</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls / dev / sda [1-5]</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">In square brackets,</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&quot;1-5&quot;</font></span> shows the range of matches, with the above command completely equivalent.</span></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(4)</span></font> the combined use of wildcards</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><html> ; Mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\' &quot;&gt; In <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux,</span></font> the wildcard can also be used in combination, for example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls [0-9]?. Conf</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Lists the current directory to begin with a number, followed by an arbitrary character, and then to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;. Conf&quot;</span></font> all files ending in.</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls [xyz] *. txt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Lists the current directory to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">x,</span></font></span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">y</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">or</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">z</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">at the beginning, and finally to <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;. Txt&quot;</span></font> at the end of the file.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\"></span></p><h4 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: Ã©Â»Â‘Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial\">3.</span> shell</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã©Â»Â‘Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial\">redirect</span> </h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Under the system,</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Open <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">3</span></font> files, standard input, standard output and standard error output. The user\'s default</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">to the standard keyboard input, the default standard output and standard error output screen. That is, the user input commands from the keyboard, and then the results and error messages output to the screen.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">The so-called redirect, just do not use the system default standard input and output, but the re-designation, therefore redirected into the input redirection, output redirection, and error output redirection. Need to know to achieve the redirection redirection operator,</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">redirection operator is determined according to redirect operations.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(1)</span></font> input redirection</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Enter the redirection command used to change the input source, using the input redirection to the contents of a file can be input as a command, rather than from the keyboard input.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Enter the redirection operator for the <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;&lt;&quot;</span></font> and <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;&lt;&lt;</span></font></span>pos;; mso-ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'&quot;&gt;&quot;Ã£Â€Â‚ For example: </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # wc &lt;/ etc / inittab</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">53 <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> 2291666</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Statistics with the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">wc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command file input to it</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ etc / inittab</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">the number of lines, words, numbers and characters.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">There is an input redirection <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;&lt;&lt;&quot;,</span></font> which redirects to tell <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell,</span></font> the standard input for the current command from the command line between a pair of numbers separated by the content. For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # wc &lt;&lt;aa</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # Default runlevel. The runlevels used by RHS are:</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> 0 - halt (Do NOT set initdefault to this)</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> 1 - Single user mode</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> 2 - Multiuser, without NFS (The same as 3, if you do not have networking)</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> 3 - Full multiuser mode</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> 4 - unused</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> 5 - X11</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; # <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> 6 - reboot (Do NOT set initdefault to this)</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&gt; Aa</span></font> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\"><font style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> 8 <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â  </span> 65303</span></font></font></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">The above command</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">aa</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">a pair of numbers separated by the content between the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">wc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command as input. No separation can be any character.</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">will be separated by number in the first reading after the content until the end of another vertical bar to read, and then send the content</span><font face=\"Times New Roman\">wc</font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command processing.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">(2)</font></span> output redirection</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Redirect the output is the output of the command is not in the screen output, but output to a specified file.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">In <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Linux,</font></span> redirect the output quite a lot, for example, the output of a command is very long, a screen can not display complete, we can specify the output of the command to a file, then use</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">more</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command to view the file, resulting in the command output complete information.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Operator for output redirection with <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&quot;&gt;&quot;</font></span> and <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&quot;&gt;&gt;.&quot;</font></span> For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ps-ef&gt; ps.txt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Ps-ef</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">output of the system operation process information entered into the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">ps.txt</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">all files, not output to the screen, you can use the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">more</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command to view</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">ps.txt</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">file system, running processes information.</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # more file1 file2 file3&gt; file</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">more</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command is to check the contents of the file, the above command is to <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">file1,</font></span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">file2</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">and</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">file3</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">output to</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">file</font></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">all the contents of the file, similar to the combined contents of the file.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">If <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&quot;&gt;</font></span></span> <spa<html> n style = &quot;font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'&quot;&gt; &quot;after the specified file does not exist, <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">will automatically rebuild a; If the file exists, then the contents of this file will be overwritten the original; if you do not overwrite existing file, use the <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;&gt;&gt;&quot;</span></font> operator. For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls-al / etc / *&gt;&gt; / root / install.log</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">The</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ etc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory and its subdirectories for all file information is appended to the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ root / install.log</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">file behind.</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ Root / install.log</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">file the original content still exists.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(3)</span></font> Error Redirection</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Error redirection and redirect standard output, like, you can use the operator <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;2&gt;&quot;</span></font> and <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;2&gt;&gt;&quot;</span></font> to achieve the redirection of error output. For example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # tar zxvf text.tar.gz 2&gt; error.txt</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">tar</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">command is packaged, you can see on the screen</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">tar</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">decompression process. If the <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;text.tar.gz&quot;</span></font> is a corrupted compressed, will the error message output to</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">error.txt</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">file.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\"></span></p><h4 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã©Â»Â‘Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">4.</span> pipe</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span> </h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Pipe can connect many of the command, the first <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">one</span></font> command can be input as the first <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">two</span></font> command output,</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">2</span></font><html> hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\' &quot;&gt; command\'s output as the first <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">three</span></font> command input, and so on. Therefore, the pipeline\'s role is to the output of a command as the next command input, without going through any intermediate files.</span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">Through the pipe symbol <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;|&quot;</span></font> can create a pipe connection, for example:</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ls-al / etc / * | more</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">That the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">/ etc</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory and all files in subdirectories under the split-screen display.</span> </p><p class=\"a\" style=\"margin: 1.2pt 0cm\"> <font face=\"Courier New\" size=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #d9d9d9\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">[Root @ WEBServer ~] # ps-ef | grep httpd | wc-l</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">This command is to check the system is running the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">httpd</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">process and the process of calculating the number of <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">httpd.</span></font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\"></span></p><h4 style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: Ã©Â»Â‘Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial\">5.</span> shell</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã©Â»Â‘Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial\">in the reference</span> </h4><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">In <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">bash,</span></font> there are many special characters, which itself has a special meaning. If the parameters of the</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">shell</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">to use them, there will be problems.</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span></font> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-ascii-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">uses the &quot;reference&quot; technology to ignore the special meaning of these characters, the reference technology is notified of these special characters</span> <font face=\"Times New Roman\"><s','What is a shellshell are intended to be \"shell\" means, in fact, very vivid description of the shell in the Linux system role. shell around the Linux kernel that is outside of a \"shell\" program, the user operating system, all tasks are completed through the shell interaction with the Linux kernel to...'),(71,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0719/327.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Red Hat Linux6 Beta 2 new tests to look forward to!','Red_Hat_Linux6_Beta_2_new_tests_to_look_forward_to','2010-07-19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p style=\"text-align: left\"> Back in April, following the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.0 version of the first test, the first time with CentOS 5. 4 and Fedora 12.0 test comparison. RedHat is published in the July 1 edition of its Enterprise Linux 6 of the second Beta version, modified in this version from a large number of Beta 1, including the installation manager, after adjustment, and add a new package. Enterprise Linux 6 blurred virtual, physical, and the boundaries between cloud computing to adapt to contemporary changes occurring in IT environments. After these changes, the new version of the Linux system performance, how, where and Ubuntu, CentOS, and test the latest version of openSUSE its comparison can gain comparison. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604H93-0.jpg&apos;);}\" onload=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=&apos;hand&apos;; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604H93-0.jpg\" /><br /><br /> View: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Beta 2 Release Notes <br /> <b>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Beta</b> <br /> For this RHEL 6.0 Beta 2, was tested in the repair of the Beta 1 pm and Bug and updated the Anaconda installer and many packages. This version uses the 2.6.32-37.el6 kernel, Gnome 2.28.2 Desktop, X. Org Server 1.7.7, Mesa 7.7.1, GCC 4.4.4, the default file system used EXT4. <br /> For comparison of this test Ubuntu, CentOS, OpenSUSE versions is the latest release of Ubuntu 10.04, the latest version of CentOS 5.5 and OpenSUSE 11.3 RC2, all those involved in the test are 64-bit Linux distributions. <br /> Depending on the application environment, test tools are Phoronix Test Suite, including Apache, PostMark, LZMA compression, CompileBench, TTSIOD 3D rendering, C-Ray ,7-Zip compression, FFmpeg, John The Ripper, NAS parallel test and Loopback TCP network performance testing, Test System Platform with Intel Core processor i7 920, clocked at 3.60GHz, 8 logical core, the motherboard is SuperComputer the ASRock 58, RAM 3GB, 320GB Seagate ST3320620AS, Nvidia GeForce 9800GTX graphics cards, directly through various benchmark tests to compare the first Second, the performance version of Linux 6. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100719/0S6041204-1.jpg&apos;);}\" onload=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=&apos;hand&apos;; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S6041204-1.jpg\" /><br /> Apache test results <br /><br /> The first is to begin testing by the Apache, the results can be seen from the test data, leading the CentOS 5.5, the transaction per second than the RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 leading nearly 70%. The Ubuntu 10.04 LTS also good performance. In this test RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 a little behind compared to OpenSUSE 11.3 RC2, CentOS leading reason may be that it defaults to using the EXT3 file system on the other three have used EXT4 file system. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604B26-2.jpg&apos;);}\" onload=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=&apos;hand&apos;; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604B26-2.jpg\" /><br /> PostMark disk test results but PostMark disk test, CentOS system because it is using EXT3 file system data is not as EXT4 file system using the operating system. OpenSUSE 11.3 has obvious advantages in the test, RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 Despite the use of EXT4 file system, but the results are not satisfactory. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100719/0S60443b-3.jpg&apos;);}\" onload=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmouseover=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.style.cursor=&apos;hand&apos;; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmousewheel=\"return imgzoom(this);\" src=\"/uploads/allimg/100719/0S60443b-3.jpg\" /><br /> LZMA compression test results even though the three test before the performance is not very good, but the RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 was in the LZMA compression test has advantages, LZMA compression test using a 256MB size file, RHEL 6.0 Beta 2 of the compression speed was faster than OpenSUSE , Ubuntu and CentOS, the compression time of the three systems are roughly equal. <br /><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onclick=\"if(!this.resized) {return true;} else {window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100719/0S604EI-4.jpg&apos;);}\" onload=\"if(this.width&gt;screen.width*0.7) {this.resized=true; this.width=screen.width*0.7; this.alt=&apos;Click here to open new window\\nCTRL+Mouse wheel to zoom in/out&apos;;}\" onmouse