ct to your ftp, then start uploading. </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\"><font color=\"#000000\">Problem symptoms and error message:</font></span> </p><p class=\"code\"> Fatal error: Class \'aut\' not found in d: \\ test \\ cmsware \\ include \\ xxxx.php on line 418 </p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> the problem may occur because the server version installed ZEND Optimizer too old, you may webhost upgraded their ZEND Optimizer </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\"><font color=\"#000000\">Problem symptoms and error message:</font></span> </p><p class=\"code\"> Fatal error: Incompatible file format: The encoded file has format major ID 2, whereas the Optimizer expects 1; The encoded file was probably encoded by the Zend Encoder for PHP 5 (zendenc5), and therefore cannot be run on PHP 4 in C: \\ usr \\ local \\ www \\ data \\ install.php on line 0 </p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> You will php5 php4 package used in the environment. Thinking (CMSware) start from the version 2.5 release is divided into two packages php4 and php5. Please use the php4 php4 environment release package, php5 php5 under Please release package. </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\"><font color=\"#000000\">Problem symptoms and error message:</font></span> </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: main (/ CMSware/include/functions.php5.php) [function.main]: failed to open stream: No such file or directory in / CMSware / include / functions.php on line 3 </p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> You will php5 php4 package used in the environment. Thinking (CMSware) start from the version 2.5 release is divided into two packages php4 and php5. Please use the php4 php4 environment release package, php5 php5 under Please release package. </p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Fatal error: Incompatible file format: The encoded file has format ID 2003120701, whereas the Optimizer can read to 2002062301 in E: \\ Inetpub \\ wwwroot \\ touyi \\ wwwroot \\ cmsware \\ install \\ xxxx.php on line0 </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> the problem may occur because the server version installed ZEND Optimizer too old, can not support the thinking (CMSware), you can contact with the hosting provider to upgrade their ZEND Optimizer <br /><br /> <b>Download Zend Optimizer</b> <br /><br /> Please download and install to the following website: <font color=\"#333399\" face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><a href=\"http://downloads.zend.com/optimizer/\" target=\"_blank\">http://downloads.zend.com/optimizer/</a></font> <br /></p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Zend 2003120701 1 5784 21721x QM \\ Gv? F? New CDXXXXXXX </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p> (Where N k is omitted, garbled) </p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> ZEND Optimizer not installed <br /><br /> Please download and install to the following website: <font color=\"#333399\" face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><a href=\"http://downloads.zend.com/optimizer/\" target=\"_blank\">http://downloads.zend.com/optimizer/</a></font> </p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Fatal error: Incompatible file format: The encoded file has format ID 3120701, which is too old </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> installation file date, please go to the official replacement of the trial program </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"code\"> Fatal error: This file has expired. In / / cmsware/public_html/cmsware2.1RC1_plus/install.php on line 0 </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> file date, please go to the official website to download new programs </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code\"> parse error: parse error, unexpected T_DNUMBER in D: \\ usr \\ local \\ www \\ data \\ cms \\ install.php on line 3 </p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> <span style=\"font-size: 12px\">Zend Optimizer</span> not be installed or configured correctly, the proposed reconfiguration. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Problem symptoms and error message:  Fatal error: Incompatible file format: The encoded file has format ID 2004072201, whereas the Optimizer can read to 2004040401 in / / vhost / u / s / b / lonmo.com / www / cmsware / www / install.php on line 0 Possible causes and solutions: zend Optimizer...'),(75,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0630/262.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Very good AWStats log analysis tool','Very_good_AWStats_log_analysis_tool','2010-06-30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p><br /><br /> Home <font color=\"#000000\"><a href=\"http://awstats.sourceforge.net\">: http://awstats.sourceforge.net</a></font> <br /><br /> Note: This article documents the basic operation at the official step by step, whether in reference to the relevant installation process made the necessary changes to the document. <br /><br /> Environment: <br /> redhat 9 <br /> Apache/2.0.54 source installation path is / usr/local/apache2 <br /> Host IP 192.168.0.111 domain s1.domain1.com <br /> The version used by awstats-6.5.tar.gz <br /> Function: <br /> Statistics s1.domain1.com by awstats access information, and provide web page view <br /> AWStats many functions, specific, you can visit the official website of the above, I use it to analyze the main apache server logs. Be still talk about the general principle: awstats perl script providing a range of implementation: service configuration, log reader , report generation and other functions. The function of the specific implementation process to achieve is: first of all, the visits recorded in the apache logs, AWStats updates are performed each time to read these logs, analysis of log data and the results stored in the database, ( This database is awstats own and do not need third-party software support.), the last AWStats cgi program by providing a web page to display statistical data in the database. <br /><br /> First look at the current configuration of apache, vi httpd.conf <br /> &lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt; <br /> ServerAdmin <a href=\"mailto:yahoon@xxx.com\">yahoon@xxx.com</a> <br /> DocumentRoot / var/www/html/s1 <br /> ServerName s1.domain1.com <br /> ErrorLog logs/s1_web-error_log <br /> TransferLog logs/s1_web-access_log <br /> &lt;/ VirtualHost&gt; <br /> Access s1.domain1.com logging to / usr/local/apache2/logs/s1_web-access_log <br /><br /> Package installation process will extract the following as / usr / local / awstats <br /> The first step is to generate configuration files for the site, there are actually many ways, according to the instructions of official documents recommend using a script, but this is relatively simple way. <br /> Go to / usr / local / awstats / tools, the directory features many different perl scripts. Executive <br /> [Root @ server1 tools] # perl awstats_configure.pl <br /> Will enter an interactive configuration program, the process will ask you some questions to answer, of course, these are the configuration files can be modified in the future. I will list all of the content and comments as follows <br /> ----- AWStats awstats_configure 1.0 (build 1.6) (c) Laurent Destailleur ----- <br /> This tool will help you to configure AWStats to analyze statistics for <br /> one web server. You can try to use it to let it do all that is possible <br /> in AWStats setup, however following the step by step manual setup <br /> documentation (docs / index.html) is often a better idea. Above all if: <br /> - You are not an administrator user, <br /> - You want to analyze downloaded log files without web server, <br /> - You want to analyze mail or ftp log files instead of web log files, <br /> - You need to analyze load balanced servers log files, <br /> - You want to \'understand\' all possible ways to use AWStats ... <br /> Read the AWStats documentation (docs / index.html). <br /> --- ÃƒÂ€ Running OS detected: Linux, BSD or Unix <br /> I detect the current operating system <br /> -----&gt; Check for web server install <br /> Found Web server Apache config file \'/ usr/local/apache2/conf/httpd.conf\' <br /> Detected my current apache configuration file <br /> -----&gt; Check and complete web server config file \'/ usr/local/apache2/conf/httpd.conf\' <br /> Warning: You Apache config file contains directives to write \'common\' log files <br /> This means that some features can\'t work (os, browsers and keywords detection). <br /> Do you want me to setup Apache to write \'combined\' log files [y / N]? Y <br /> AWStats is recommended combined log format, apache common format used by default. So this place prompted to modify the apache configuration files do not, the log format to combined, of course replied yes. <br /> Add \'Alias / awstatsclasses &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / classes /&quot;\' <br /> Add \'Alias / awstatscss &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / css /&quot;\' <br /> Add \'Alias / awstatsicons &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / icon /&quot;\' <br /> Add \'ScriptAlias / awstats / &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / cgi-bin /&quot;\' <br /> Add \'&lt;Directory&gt;\' directive <br /> AWStats directives added to Apache config file. <br /> Inside the apache configuration file to the increase of the above, there are some directory and alias settings. This part of the general added to the file last. <br /> -----&gt; Update model config file \'/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / cgi-bin / awstats.model.conf\' <br /> File awstats.model.conf updated. <br /> Updated template file <br /> -----&gt; Need to create a new config file? <br /> Do you want me to build a new AWStats config / profile <br /> file (required if first install) [y / N]? y <br /> The need to create a new profile, choose y <br /> -----&gt; Define config file name to create <br /> What is the name of your web site or profile analysis? <br /> Example: [url] www.mysite.com [/ url] <br /> Example: demo <br /> Your web site, virtual server or profile name: <br /> ÃƒÂ˜ s1.domain1.com <br /> This place filled site\'s domain name <br /> -----&gt; Define config file path <br /> In which directory do you plan to store your config file (s)? <br /> Default: / etc / awstats <br /> Directory path to store config file (s) (Enter for default): <br /> &gt; Enter configuration files generated by the path, the default is / etc / awstats, I will not modify, directly enter. <br /> -----&gt; Create config file \'/ etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf\' <br /> Config file / etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf created. <br /> Can see that the file has been created, path is / etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf \' <br /> -----&gt; Restart Web server with \'/ sbin / service httpd restart\' <br /> Stopping httpd: [OK] <br /> Starting httpd: httpd: Could not determine the server\'s fully qualified domain name, using 127.0.0.1 for ServerName <br /> [OK] <br /> Due to the modification of the httpd.conf, so it will automatically restart apache to make the configuration file take effect, but there is a problem here, because I did not use the system comes with apache, but source code is installed, it does not add service, so Although the successful start here, but not what I need. is very simple, and so will close it and open my own. <br /> -----&gt; Add update process inside a scheduler <br /> Sorry, configure.pl does not support automatic add to cron yet. <br /> You can do it manually by adding the following command to your cron: <br /> / Usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / cgi-bin / awstats.pl-update-config = s1.domain1.com <br /> Or if you have several config files and prefer having only one command: <br /> / Usr / local / awstats / tools / awstats_updateall.pl now <br /> Press ENTER to continue ... <br /> Due to new information obtained, we must update the database, that is to re-do read the log. Analysis of the log extract inside the new part of the analysis, the updated data into the database. The best time to perform it. This If section is to remind you that you need to achieve this function manually to the top two lines in bold to write any line of crontab, it regularly executed. The first one is to update the s1.domain1.com, while the second is case of multiple sites, all of the sites for updates. I do not do this operation. Enter. <br /> A SIMPLE config file has been created: / etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf <br /> You should have a look inside to check and change manually main parameters. <br /> You can then manually update your statistics for \'s1.domain1.com\' with command: <br /> &gt; Perl awstats.pl-update-config = s1.domain1.com <br /> You can also read your statistics for \'s1.domain1.com\' with URL: <br /> ÃƒÂ˜ [url] http://localhost/awstats/awstats.pl?config=s1.domain1.com [/ url] <br /> Press ENTER to finish ... <br /> Press Enter to complete the installation. These words to write very clear, the next job is to check the configuration file execution perl awstats.pl-update-config = s1.domain1.com to update the database through the [url] http:// localhost / awstats / awstats.pl? config = s1.domain1.com [/ url] to see the statistics of the information this script, and we are in the httpd.conf are updated, here is some of the major changes it will CustomLog logs / access_log common to <br /> CustomLog logs / access_log combined <br /> The final face in the file increases <br /> # Directives to allow use of AWStats as a CGI <br /> Alias / awstatsclasses &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / classes /&quot; <br /> Alias / awstatscss &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / css /&quot; <br /> Alias / awstatsicons &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / icon /&quot; <br /> ScriptAlias / awstats / &quot;/ usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / cgi-bin /&quot; <br /> # This is to permit URL access to scripts / files in AWStats directory. <br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/awstats/wwwroot&quot;&gt; <br /> Options None <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /><br /> Before the change, or first turning off the script to start apache, apache will start right <br /> [Root @ server1 tools] # service httpd stop <br /> [Root @ server1 tools] # / usr/local/apache2/bin/apachectl start <br /><br /> Visit s1.domain1.com display properly, this visit should be recorded to a log inside. <br /> Visit [url] http://192.168.0.111t/awstats/awstats.pl?config=s1.domain1.com [/ url], prompted <br /> Forbidden <br /> You don\'t have permission to access / awstats / awstats.pl on this server <br /> Understand is a permissions issue, to the / usr / local execute chmod-R 777 awstats (should be 755 on the line, because I just tested it) <br /><br /> Check the configuration file of the key projects <br /> vi / etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf <br /> Check and make the following changes <br /> # LogFile = &quot;/ var / log / httpd / mylog.log&quot; <br /> LogFile = &quot;/ usr/local/apache2/logs/s1_web-access_log&quot; <br /> Refers to the log apche <br /> LogType = W <br /> That is the web log analysis <br /> LogFormat = 1 <br /> Expressed as a combined log format <br /> SiteDomain = &quot;s1.domain1.com&quot; <br /> Domain name <br /> HostAliases = &quot;s1.domain1.com [url] www.s1.domain1.com [/ url] 127.0.0.1 localhost&quot; <br /> The meaning of this variable is the domain alias. That multiple domain names corresponding to the same website of the sentence is automatically generated. I do not have to use so there is no change. <br /><br /> Update the database <br /> cd / usr / local / awstats / wwwroot / cgi-bin <br /> perl awstats.pl-config = s1.domain1.com-update <br /> Get the following error <br /> Error: AWStats database directory defined in config file by \'DirData\' parameter (/ var / lib / awstats) does not exist or is not writable. <br /> Setup (\'/ etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf\' file, web server or permissions) may be wrong. <br /> Check config file, permissions and AWStats documentation (in \'docs\' directory). <br /> Also visit [url] http://192.168.0.111t/awstats/awstats.pl?config=s1.domain1.com [/ url] tips <br /> Error: AWStats database directory defined in config file by \'DirData\' parameter (/ var / lib / awstats) does not exist or is not writable. <br /> Setup (\'/ etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf\' file, web server or permissions) may be wrong. <br /> Check config file, permissions and AWStats documentation (in \'docs\' directory). <br /> It is clear that / var / lib / awstats directory does not exist here need help, this path is a configuration file / etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf inside the DirData parameters determined that the database storage areas. So I did not modify the default value is still DirData = &quot;/ var / lib / awstats&quot; <br /> Since the prompt does not exist, it is now to create a new <br /> cd / var / lib <br /> mkdir awstats <br /><br /> Update the database <br /> [Root @ server1 cgi-bin] # perl awstats.pl-config = s1.domain1.com-update <br /> Information is as follows <br /> Update for config &quot;/ etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf&quot; <br /> With data in log file &quot;/ usr/local/apache2/logs/s1_web-access_log&quot; ... <br /> Phase 1: First bypass old records, searching new record ... <br /> Searching new records from beginning of log file ... <br /> Jumped lines in file: 0 <br /> Parsed lines in file: 1 total number of rows processed (apache log is a line representing a record) <br /> Found 0 dropped records, <br /> Found 1 corrupted records, found a broken record Found 0 old records, <br /> Found 0 new qualified records. <br /><br /> View the contents of the log <br /> [Root @ server1 cgi-bin] # less / usr/local/apache2/logs/s1_web-access_log <br /> 192.168.0.28 - - [30/Aug/2007: 10:19:59 +0800] &quot;GET / HTTP/1.1&quot; 200 23 <br /><br /> Visit [url] http://192.168.0.111/awstats/awstats.pl?config=s1.domain1.com [/ url] view statistics very strange, why is it so? Open the httpd.conf virtual host part of that does not change, so the record does not change the log type, you need to use a single set of log types. <br /> &lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt; <br /> ServerAdmin <a href=\"mailto:yahoon@xxx.com\">yahoon@xxx.com</a> <br /> DocumentRoot / var/www/html/s1 <br /> ServerName s1.domain1.com <br /> LogFormat &quot;% h% l% u% t \\&quot;% r \\ &quot;%&gt; s% b \\&quot;% {Referer} i \\ &quot;\\&quot;% {User-Agent} i \\ &quot;&quot; combined1 <br /> CustomLog logs/s1_web-access_log combined1 <br /> ErrorLog logs/s1_web-error_log <br /> &lt;/ VirtualHost&gt; <br /> I can see this log format here will be named combine1, just name it, you can easily play. Modified to restart apache <br /><br /> Clear the log, then visit s1.domain1.com, produced the following log <br /> [Root @ server1 cgi-bin] # less / usr/local/apache2/logs/s1_web-access_log <br /> 192.168.0.28 - - [30/Aug/2007: 13:04:05 +0800] &quot;GET / HTTP/1.1&quot; 304 - &quot;-&quot; &quot;Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; <br /> SV1; TencentTraveler) &quot; <br /> 192.168.0.28 - - [30/Aug/2007: 13:05:30 +0800] &quot;GET / HTTP/1.1&quot; 304 - &quot;-&quot; &quot;Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; <br /> SV1; TencentTraveler) &quot; <br /> 192.168.0.28 - - [30/Aug/2007: 13:05:30 +0800] &quot;GET / HTTP/1.1&quot; 304 - &quot;-&quot; &quot;Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; <br /> SV1; TencentTraveler) &quot; <br /> 192.168.0.28 - - [30/Aug/2007: 13:05:30 +0800] &quot;GET / HTTP/1.1&quot; 304 - &quot;-&quot; &quot;Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; <br /> SV1; TencentTraveler) &quot; <br /> 192.168.0.28 - - [30/Aug/2007: 13:05:31 +0800] &quot;GET / HTTP/1.1&quot; 304 - &quot;-&quot; &quot;Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; <br /> SV1; TencentTraveler) &quot; <br /> 192.168.0.28 - - [30/Aug/2007: 13:05:31 +0800] &quot;GET / HTTP/1.1&quot; 304 - &quot;-&quot; &quot;Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; <br /> SV1; TencentTraveler) &quot; <br /> ... ... <br /><br /> Update the database again <br /> [Root @ server1 cgi-bin] # perl awstats.pl-config = s1.domain1.com-update <br /> Update for config &quot;/ etc/awstats/awstats.s1.domain1.com.conf&quot; <br /> With data in log file &quot;/ usr/local/apache2/logs/s1_web-access_log&quot; ... <br /> Phase 1: First bypass old records, searching new record ... <br /> Direct access to last remembered record has fallen on another record. <br /> So searching new records from beginning of log file ... <br /> Phase 2: Now process new records (Flush history on disk after 20000 hosts) ... <br /> Jumped lines in file: 0 <br /> Parsed lines in file: 6 <br /> Found 0 dropped records, <br /> Found 0 corrupted records, <br /> Found 0 old records, <br /> Found 6 new qualified records. <br /><br /> Visit [url] http://192.168.0.111/awstats/awstats.pl?config=s1.domain1.com [/ url] <br /><br /> Finally note that, in the text has been repeatedly mentioned, to be able to respond to the latest information to update the database. That you may have made many visits to it, but that did not change the page view statistics. This is because These logs have not been updated to the database. The simplest way is to regularly perform. <br /> Of course, now written by the software only the basic installation and use, its use far beyond that. In particular, which pertain to the apache log of the relevant knowledge, for example, rotate log cycle, load balancing, log consolidation and so on. I also new to, I hope you valuable advice. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Home : http://awstats.sourceforge.net Note: This article documents the basic operation at the official step by step, whether in reference to the relevant installation process made the necessary changes to the document.  Environment:  redhat 9  Apache/2.0.54 source installation path is /...'),(76,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0623/251.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Installation and Configuration nagios3.2.0 combat Raiders','Installation_and_Configuration_nagios320_combat_Raiders','2010-06-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> First, install the support package </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Yum-y install gcc gcc-c + + gd gd-devel php httpd openssl-devel <br /> # Yum-y install gcc gcc-c + + gd gd-devel php httpd openssl-devel <br /></p><p> Second, install nagios </p><p> Create User </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Useradd nagios # passwd nagios <br /> # Useradd nagios # passwd nagios <br /></p><p> Create Group </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Groupadd nagcmd # usermod-G nagcmd nagios # usermod-G nagcmd apache <br /> # Groupadd nagcmd # usermod-G nagcmd nagios # usermod-G nagcmd apache <br /></p><p> Installation </p><p> Bash code <br /> # Tar xzf nagios-3.2.0.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-3.2.0 <br /> #. / Configure - with-command-group = nagcmd - prefix = / usr / local / nagios <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install # make install to install the main program to use, CGI and HTML files <br /> # Make install-init # make install-init to use in / etc / rc.d / init.d install the startup script # make install-config # make install-cofig used to install the sample configuration file, the installation path is / usr / local / nagios / etc. <br /> # Make install-commandmode # make install-commandmode used to configure the directory permissions <br /> # Tar xzf nagios-3.2.0.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-3.2.0 <br /> #. / Configure - with-command-group = nagcmd - prefix = / usr / local / nagios <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install # make install to install the main program to use, CGI and HTML files <br /> # Make install-init # make install-init to use in / etc / rc.d / init.d install the startup script # make install-config # make install-cofig used to install the sample configuration file, the installation path is / usr / local / nagios / etc. <br /> # Make install-commandmode # make install-commandmode used to configure the directory permissions </p><p> nagios directory features a brief description: <br /> execution directory bin Nagios, nagios file is the main program <br /> etc Nagios configuration file location <br /> sbin Nagios Cgi file directory, execute external command is the directory where the required documents <br /> Share Nagios web directory where the file <br /> var Nagios log file, spid and other file\'s directory <br /> var / archives log archive directory <br /> var / rw external command file used to store </p><p> Configuring apache </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / etc / httpd / conf / httpd.conf # add the end of the <br /> # Vi / etc / httpd / conf / httpd.conf # add the end of the </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p> Bash code <br /> ScriptAlias / nagios / cgi-bin &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / sbin&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/sbin&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options ExecCGI <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /><br /> Alias / nagios &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / share&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/share&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options None <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /> ScriptAlias / nagios / cgi-bin &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / sbin&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/sbin&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options ExecCGI <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /><br /> Alias / nagios &quot;/ usr / local / nagios / share&quot; <br /><br /> &lt;Directory &quot;/usr/local/nagios/share&quot;&gt; <br /> # SSLRequireSSL <br /> Options None <br /> AllowOverride None <br /> Order allow, deny <br /> Allow from all <br /> # Order deny, allow <br /> # Deny from all <br /> # Allow from 127.0.0.1 <br /> AuthName &quot;Nagios Access&quot; <br /> AuthType Basic <br /> AuthUserFile / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users <br /> Require valid-user <br /> &lt;/ Directory&gt; <br /></p><p> Create a verification file apache directory </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Htpasswd-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users nagiosadmin <br /> New password: (Enter password) <br /> Re-type new password: (enter a password) <br /> Adding password for user nagiosadmin <br /><br /> # Service httpd restart <br /> # Htpasswd-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / htpasswd.users nagiosadmin <br /> New password: (Enter password)<br /> Re-type new password: (enter a password) <br /> Adding password for user nagiosadmin </p><p> # Service httpd restart <br /></p><p> Configure nagios configuration files </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / contacts.cfg # will be inside the email address to your email address <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / contacts.cfg # will be inside the email address to your email address </p><p> Third, install nagios plugins </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Tar xzf nagios-plugins-1.4.13.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-plugins-1.4.13 <br /> #. / Configure - with-nagios-user = nagios - with-nagios-group = nagios - prefix = / usr / local / nagios <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Tar xzf nagios-plugins-1.4.13.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-plugins-1.4.13 <br /> #. / Configure - with-nagios-user = nagios - with-nagios-group = nagios - prefix = / usr / local / nagios <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /></p><p> Fourth, starting nagios </p><p> Add Service </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Chkconfig - add nagios <br /> # Chkconfig nagios on <br /> # Chkconfig - add nagios <br /> # Chkconfig nagios on <br /></p><p> Check the configuration file </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nagios-v / usr / local / nagios / etc / nagios.cfg <br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nagios-v / usr / local / nagios / etc / nagios.cfg <br /></p><p> Start nagios </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Service nagios start <br /> # Service nagios start <br /></p><p> Start apache </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Service httpd start <br /> # Service httpd start <br /></p><p> Access <a href=\"http://localhost/nagios\">http://localhost/nagios</a> username password </p><p></p><p> Fifth, install the nrpe </p><p><br /> Bash code <br /> # Tar xzvf nrpe-2.12.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nrpe-2.12 <br /> #. / Configure <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install-plugin # server-side plug-ins as long as the installation of nrpe on-line monitoring <br /> # Tar xzvf nrpe-2.12.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nrpe-2.12 <br /> #. / Configure <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install-plugin # server-side plug-ins as long as the installation of nrpe on-line monitoring </p><p> In / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / commands.cfg check_nrpe commands defined </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / commands.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / commands.cfg <br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p> Commands.cfg code <br /> # \'Check_nrpe\' command definition <br /> define command { <br /> command_name check_nrpe <br /> command_line $ USER1 $ / check_nrpe-H $ HOSTADDRESS $-c $ ARG1 $ <br /> } <br /> # \'Check_nrpe\' command definition <br /> define command { <br /> command_name check_nrpe <br /> command_line $ USER1 $ / check_nrpe-H $ HOSTADDRESS $-c $ ARG1 $ <br /> } <br /></p><p> Sixth, in the monitored machine and plug-ins installed nrpe nagios </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Useradd nagios <br /> # Tar xzvf nagios-plugins-1.4.13.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-plugins-1.4.13 <br /> #. / Configure <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Chown nagios.nagios / usr / local / nagios / <br /> # Chown-R nagios.nagios / usr / local / nagios / libexec / <br /><br /><br /><br /> # Tar xzvf nrpe-2.12.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nrpe-2.12 <br /> #. / Configure <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install-plugin # install the nrpe plugin can not install the monitoring client <br /> # Make install-daemon # install the nrpe daemon <br /> # Make install-daemon-config # install the nrpe configuration file <br /> # Useradd nagios <br /> # Tar xzvf nagios-plugins-1.4.13.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nagios-plugins-1.4.13 <br /> #. / Configure <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Chown nagios.nagios / usr / local / nagios / <br /> # Chown-R nagios.nagios / usr / local / nagios / libexec / <br /><br /><br /><br /> # Tar xzvf nrpe-2.12.tar.gz <br /> # Cd nrpe-2.12 <br /> #. / Configure <br /> # Make all <br /> # Make install-plugin # install the nrpe plugin can not install the monitoring client <br /> # Make install-daemon # install the nrpe daemon <br /> # Make install-daemon-config # install the nrpe configuration file <br /></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / nrpe.cfg # modify the nrpe configuration file, which allows Nagios monitoring server (192.168.0.19) monitoring <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / nrpe.cfg # modify the nrpe configuration file, which allows Nagios monitoring server (192.168.0.19) monitoring </p><p> Nrpe.cfg code <br /> allowed_hosts = 127.0.0.1,192.168.0.19 # multiple machines separated by commas <br /> allowed_hosts = 127.0.0.1,192.168.0.19 # multiple machines separated by commas </p><p> Bash code <br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nrpe-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / nrpe.cfg-d as a separate daemon start nrpe, you can use xinetd start nrpe, specifically clear view nrpe official document. <br /><br /> # Cat&gt;&gt; / etc / rc.d / rc.local &lt;&lt;EOF # Boot automatically start nrpe <br /> / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nrpe-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / nrpe.cfg-d <br /><br /> EOF <br /><br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_nrpe-H localhost # check nrpe is installed properly <br /> NRPE v2.12 <br /><br /> # Netstat-tln # view port <br /><br /> tcp 0 0 0.0.0.0:5666 0.0.0.0: * <br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nrpe-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / nrpe.cfg-d as a separate daemon start nrpe, you can use xinetd start nrpe, specifically clear view nrpe official document. <br /><br /> # Cat&gt;&gt; / etc / rc.d / rc.local &lt;&lt;EOF # Boot automatically start nrpe <br /> / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nrpe-c / usr / local / nagios / etc / nrpe.cfg-d <br /><br /> EOF <br /><br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_nrpe-H localhost # check nrpe is installed properly <br /> NRPE v2.12 <br /><br /> # Netstat-tln # view port <br /><br /> tcp 0 0 0.0.0.0:5666 0.0.0.0: * <br /></p><p> We need to / usr / local / nagios / etc / nrpe.cfg defined in the monitoring of local resources that we use the command. <br /> The following commands are defined by default: </p><p> command [check_users] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_users-w 5-c 10 <br /> command [check_load] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_load-w 15,10,5-c 30,25,20 <br /> command [check_hda1] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_disk-w 20%-c 10%-p / dev/hda1 <br /> command [check_zombie_procs] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_procs-w 5-c 10-s Z <br /> command [check_total_procs] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_procs-w 150-c 200 </p><p> The following commands are defined their own: <br /> # Monitor swap usage, use of more than 20% of the state for the warning, more than 10% of the critical state when </p><p></p><p> Nrpe.cfg code <br /> command [check_swap] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_swap-w 20%-c 10% <br /> command [check_swap] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_swap-w 20%-c 10% </p><p> # Root partition disk usage monitoring </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p> Java code <br /> command [check_disk_root] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_disk-w 20%-c 10%-p / <br /> command [check_disk_root] = / usr / local / nagios / libexec / check_disk-w 20%-c 10%-p / <br /></p><p> VII, nagios monitoring process </p><p> NRPE total consists of two parts: <br /> (1). Check_nrpe plug-in, running on the monitoring host. <br /> (2). NRPE daemon, running on a remote linux host (usually the machine being monitored) <br /> In accordance with the above, the whole monitoring process is as follows: <br /> When Nagios need to monitor a remote linux host of services or resources when: <br /> 1). Nagios will run check_nrpe plug-in, we in the nagios configuration file to tell it what to check. <br /> 2). Check_nrpe plugin via SSL to connect to the remote NRPE daemon. <br /> 3). NRPE daemon will run the appropriate nagios plug-in to carry out inspections of local resources or services. <br /> 4). NRPE daemon will check the results back to check_nrpe plug-in, plug-in will be submitted to the nagios to do its processing. <br /> Note: NRPE daemon nagios plug-in needs to be monitored linux installed on the remote host, or, daemon can not do any monitoring. </p><p> VIII, nagios configuration files </p><p> # Control access to the configuration file cgi <br /> cgi.cfg <br /> # Nagios main configuration file <br /> nagios.cfg <br /> # Resource.cfg defines some variables in order to be reference to other documents, such as the $ USER1 $ <br /> resource.cfg <br /> # Objects is a directory for Nagios object definitions <br /> objects <br /> # Servers to create a directory on their own, Nagios can load a directory of all the configuration files (you need to configure nagios.cfg) <br /> servers </p><p> . / Objects: <br /> # Command to define the configuration file, which can be defined in other documents referenced commands <br /> commands.cfg <br /> # Contacts and contact groups profile <br /> contacts.cfg <br /> # Monitor the local machine\'s configuration file <br /> localhost.cfg <br /> # An example of monitoring the printer configuration file (not enabled by default) <br /> printer.cfg <br /> # An example of monitoring the router configuration file (not enabled by default) <br /> switch.cfg <br /> # Template configuration file can be defined in this template, referenced in other documents <br /> templates.cfg <br /> # Define time profile control <br /> timeperiods.cfg <br /> # An example of monitoring Windows configuration file (not enabled by default) <br /> windows.cfg </p><p> . / Servers: <br /> # Create your own profile host group <br /> hostgroup.cfg <br /> # Create your own monitor remote Linux host configuration file <br /> sectop.cfg </p><p> What is the reference configuration file? <br /></p><p> Mainly with the nagios monitoring a host of various information, including local resources and external services. These are the nagios which is defined as one item (nagios call services, the services provided to the host with distinction, I use the word project), but each monitor project implementation, you need to file by commands.cfg defined commands. <br /> In order to define some of the projects do not have to repeat, Nagios configuration file into a template (templates.cfg), will define some common template properties for the multiple references. <br /> We now have a monitoring program is to monitor a machine\'s web service is normal, what elements do we need? The most important are the following three points: first, control which machine, and then what is the command control Yaoyong last, the implementation is a problem which to be notified when the contact. </p><p><br /> We should first define the commands.cfg monitor remote services and resources command, and how to send mail order. Monitor remote services and resources most of the order of the commands through the / usr / local / nagios / libexec under the scripting, such as the ping command check_ping. <br /> / Usr / local / nagios / libexec script command under the law through the use of hair-h parameter View </p><p> Then we define the contacts.cfg file contacts and contact groups, as defined in the timeperiods.cfg monitoring time period. </p><p> Finally, we monitor in the server configuration file referenced in the previously defined elements to monitor the server status. </p><p> The following section refer to the configuration file configuration to do that: </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / resource.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / resource.cfg <br /></p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Define $ USER1 $ variable, set the plugin path $ USER1 $ = / usr / local / nagios / libexec <br /> # Define $ USER1 $ variable, set the plugin path $ USER1 $ = / usr / local / nagios / libexec <br /></p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / commands.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / commands.cfg <br /></p><p></p><p> Command.cfg code <br /> # Define check-host-alive command <br /> define command { <br /> command_name check-host-alive # command name <br /> command_line $ USER1 $ / check_ping-H $ HOSTADDRESS $-w 3000.0,80%-c 5000.0,100%-p 5 <br /> } <br /> # Above $ USER1 $ and $ HOSTADDRESS $ defined by reference to their own configuration files. No variable is defined to be referenced. <br /><br /> # \'Check_nrpe\' command definition <br /> define command { <br /> command_name check_nrpe <br /> command_line $ USER1 $ / check_nrpe-H $ HOSTADDRESS $-c $ ARG1 $ <br /> } <br /> # Define check-host-alive command <br /> define command { <br /> command_name check-host-alive # command name <br /> command_line $ USER1 $ / check_ping-H $ HOSTADDRESS $-w 3000.0,80%-c 5000.0,100%-p 5 <br /> } <br /> # Above $ USER1 $ and $ HOSTADDRESS $ defined by reference to their own configuration files. No variable is defined to be referenced. <br /><br /> # \'Check_nrpe\' command definition <br /> define command { <br /> command_name check_nrpe <br /> command_line $ USER1 $ / check_nrpe-H $ HOSTADDRESS $-c $ ARG1 $ <br /> } <br /></p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / contacts.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / contacts.cfg <br /></p><p></p><p> Contacts.cfg code <br /> # Define contacts <br /> define contact { <br /> contact_name nagiosadmin; Short name of user <br /> use generic-contact; Inherit default values from generic-contact template (defined above) <br /> alias Nagios Admin; Full name of user <br /><br /> Email <a href=\"mailto:test@gmaile.com\">test@gmaile.com</a> ; &lt;&lt;***** CHANGE THIS TO YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS ****** <br /> } <br /> # The above generic-contact is defined in templates.cfg. <br /> # Define contact groups <br /> define contactgroup { <br /> contactgroup_name admins <br /> alias Nagios Administrators <br /> members nagiosadmin # where you can add multiple contacts, separated by commas <br /> } <br /> # Define contacts <br /> define contact { <br /> contact_name nagiosadmin; Short name of user <br /> use generic-contact; Inherit default values from generic-contact template (defined above) <br /> alias Nagios Admin; Full name of user <br /><br /> Email <a href=\"mailto:test@gmaile.com\">test@gmaile.com</a> ; &lt;&lt;***** CHANGE THIS TO YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS ****** <br /> } <br /> # The above generic-contact is defined in templates.cfg. <br /> # Define contact groups <br /> define contactgroup { <br /> contactgroup_name admins <br /> alias Nagios Administrators <br /> members nagiosadmin # where you can add multiple contacts, separated by commas <br /> } <br /></p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / timeperiods.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / timeperiods.cfg <br /></p><p></p><p> Timeperiods.cfg code <br /> # Define time monitoring <br /> define timeperiod { <br /> timeperiod_name 24x7 # monitor all time (7 * 24 hours) <br /> alias 24 Hours A Day, 7 Days A Week <br /> sunday 00:00-24:00 <br /> monday 00:00-24:00 <br /> tuesday 00:00-24:00 <br /> wednesday 00:00-24:00 <br /> thursday 00:00-24:00 <br /> friday 00:00-24:00 <br /> saturday 00:00-24:00 <br /> } <br /> # Define time monitoring <br /> define timeperiod { <br /> timeperiod_name 24x7 # monitor all time (7 * 24 hours) <br /> alias 24 Hours A Day, 7 Days A Week <br /> sunday 00:00-24:00 <br /> monday 00:00-24:00 <br /> tuesday 00:00-24:00 <br /> wednesday 00:00-24:00 <br /> thursday 00:00-24:00 <br /> friday 00:00-24:00 <br /> saturday 00:00-24:00 <br /> } <br /></p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / templates.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / templates.cfg <br /></p><p></p><p> Templates.cfg code <br /> Contact # define generic-contact template, not a real contact, real contact is defined in the contacts.cfg <br /> define contact { <br /> name generic-contact <br /> service_notification_period 24x7 <br /> host_notification_period 24x7 <br /> service_notification_options w, u, c, r, f, s <br /> host_notification_options d, u, r, f, s <br /> service_notification_commands notify-service-by-email <br /> host_notification_commands notify-host-by-email <br /> register 0 <br /> } <br /> Contact # define generic-contact template, not a real contact, real contact is defined in the contacts.cfg <br /> define contact { <br /> name generic-contact <br /> service_notification_period 24x7 <br /> host_notification_period 24x7 <br /> service_notification_options w, u, c, r, f, s <br /> host_notification_options d, u, r, f, s <br /> service_notification_commands notify-service-by-email <br /> host_notification_commands notify-host-by-email <br /> register 0 <br /> } </p><p> -------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- -------------- <br /> service_notification_period 24x7 <br /> Service out of the state notice period, the time period is defined above in the timeperiods.cfg. <br /> host_notification_period 24x7 <br /> Notify the host out of the situation of the time period, the time period is defined above in the timeperiods.cfg <br /> service_notification_options w, u, c, r <br /> When the service there w-alarm (warning), u-Unknown (unkown), c-serious (critical), or r-normal from the abnormal situation, in these four cases, notify the contact. <br /> host_notification_options d, u, r <br /> When the hostD-When the machine there (down), u-back is not up to (unreachable), r-normal from the abnormal situation, in which three kinds of contacts, inform <br /> service_notification_commands notify-service-by-email <br /> Notice a problem with the command service notify-service-by-email, the command is defined in the commands.cfg, the role is to give contact email. <br /> host_notification_commands notify-host-by-email <br /> Above, the host is used when things go wrong the way email notification contacts <br /> -------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- -------------- </p><p></p><p> Templates.cfg code <br /> # Define generic-host host template <br /> define host { <br /> name generic-host; The name of this host template <br /> notifications_enabled 1; Host notifications are enabled <br /> event_handler_enabled 1; Host event handler is enabled <br /> flap_detection_enabled 1; Flap detection is enabled <br /> failure_prediction_enabled 1; Failure prediction is enabled <br /> process_perf_data 1; Process performance data <br /> retain_status_information 1; Retain status information across program restarts <br /> retain_nonstatus_information 1; Retain non-status information across program restarts <br /> notification_period 24x7; Send host notifications at any time <br /> register 0; DONT REGISTER THIS DEFINITION - ITS NOT A REAL HOST, JUST A TEMPLATE! <br /> } <br /><br /> # Define Linux host template <br /> define host { <br /> name linux-server; The name of this host template <br /> use generic-host; This template inherits other values from the generic-host template <br /> check_period 24x7; By default, Linux hosts are checked round the clock <br /> check_interval 5; Actively check the host every 5 minutes <br /> retry_interval 1; Schedule host check retries at 1 minute intervals <br /> max_check_attempts 10; Check each Linux host 10 times (max) <br /> check_command check-host-alive; Default command to check Linux hosts <br /> notification_period workhours; Linux admins hate to be woken up, so we only notify during the day <br /> ; Note that the notification_period variable is being overridden from <br /> ; The value that is inherited from the generic-host template! <br /> notification_interval 120; Resend notifications every 2 hours <br /> notification_options d, u, r; Only send notifications for specific host states <br /> contact_groups admins; Notifications get sent to the admins by default <br /> register 0; DONT REGISTER THIS DEFINITION - ITS NOT A REAL HOST, JUST A TEMPLATE! <br /> } <br /> # Define generic-host host template <br /> define host { <br /> name generic-host; The name of this host template <br /> notifications_enabled 1; Host notifications are enabled <br /> event_handler_enabled 1; Host event handler is enabled <br /> flap_detection_enabled 1; Flap detection is enabled <br /> failure_prediction_enabled 1; Failure prediction is enabled <br /> process_perf_data 1; Process performance data <br /> retain_status_information 1; Retain status information across program restarts <br /> retain_nonstatus_information 1; Retain non-status information across program restarts <br /> notification_period 24x7; Send host notifications at any time <br /> register 0; DONT REGISTER THIS DEFINITION - ITS NOT A REAL HOST, JUST A TEMPLATE! <br /> } <br /><br /> # Define Linux host template <br /> define host { <br /> name linux-server; The name of this host template <br /> use generic-host; This template inherits other values from the generic-host template <br /> check_period 24x7; By default, Linux hosts are checked round the clock <br /> check_interval 5; Actively check the host every 5 minutes <br /> retry_interval 1; Schedule host check retries at 1 minute intervals <br /> max_check_attempts 10; Check each Linux host 10 times (max) <br /> check_command check-host-alive; Default command to check Linux hosts <br /> notification_period workhours; Linux admins hate to be woken up, so we only notify during the day <br /> ; Note that the notification_period variable is being overridden from <br /> ; The value that is inherited from the generic-host template! <br /> notification_interval 120; Resend notifications every 2 hours <br /> notification_options d, u, r; Only send notifications for specific host states <br /> contact_groups admins; Notifications get sent to the admins by default <br /> register 0; DONT REGISTER THIS DEFINITION - ITS NOT A REAL HOST, JUST A TEMPLATE! <br /> } </p><p> # Open the configuration file in the nagios.cfg on / usr / local / nagios / etc / servers / in the configuration file reference. </p><p></p><p> Nagios.cfg code <br /> cfg_dir = / usr / local / nagios / etc / servers <br /> cfg_dir = / usr / local / nagios / etc / servers </p><p> # Host monitoring remote Linux files, if the monitoring multiple hosts can simply copy the modified. <br /> # We should bear in mind the order used in the commands.cfg sectop.cfg defined commands.cfg defined in order to use / usr / local / nagios / libexec plug-ins under the (command). </p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / servers / sectop.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / servers / sectop.cfg <br /></p><p></p><p> Sectop.cfg code <br /> # Define host <br /> define host { <br /> use linux-server; Name of host template to use <br /> ; This host definition will inherit all variables that are defined <br /> ; In (or inherited by) the linux-server host template definition. <br /> host_name sectop <br /> alias Docs <br /> address 192.168.99.200 <br /> } <br /> # Define Ping remote Linux host <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description PING <br /> check_command check_ping! 100.0,20%! 500.0,60%; check_ping commands.cfg defined command, followed by two parameters, commands and parameters to use! segmentation. <br /> } <br /> # Check the root partition to use the remote Linux host situation, check_nrpe command must be in / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / commands.cfg defined (default undefined) <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Root Partition <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_disk_root <br /> } <br /> # Check the number of the remote Linux host login <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Current Users <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_users <br /> } <br /> # Check the load on the remote Linux host <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Current Load <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_load <br /> } <br /> # Check remote Linux swap partitions use the host <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Swap Usage <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_swap <br /> } <br /> # Check remote host\'s SSH service Linux <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description SSH <br /> check_command check_ssh <br /> notifications_enabled 0 <br /> } <br /> # Check remote Linux host HTTP service <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description HTTP <br /> check_command check_http <br /> notifications_enabled 0 <br /> } <br /> # Define host <br /> define host { <br /> use linux-server; Name of host template to use <br /> ; This host definition will inherit all variables that are defined <br /> ; In (or inherited by) the linux-server host template definition. <br /> host_name sectop <br /> alias Docs <br /> address 192.168.99.200 <br /> } <br /> # Define Ping remote Linux host <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description PING <br /> check_command check_ping! 100.0,20%! 500.0,60%; check_ping commands.cfg defined command, followed by two parameters, commands and parameters to use! segmentation. <br /> } <br /> # Check the root partition to use the remote Linux host situation, check_nrpe command must be in / usr / local / nagios / etc / objects / commands.cfg defined (default undefined) <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Root Partition <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_disk_root <br /> } <br /> # Check the number of the remote Linux host login <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Current Users <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_users <br /> } <br /> # Check the load on the remote Linux host <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Current Load <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_load <br /> } <br /> # Check remote Linux swap partitions use the host <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description Swap Usage <br /> check_command check_nrpe! check_swap <br /> } <br /> # Check remote host\'s SSH service Linux <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description SSH <br /> check_command check_ssh <br /> notifications_enabled 0 <br /> } <br /> # Check remote Linux host HTTP service <br /> define service { <br /> use generic-service; Name of service template to use <br /> host_name sectop <br /> service_description HTTP <br /> check_command check_http <br /> notifications_enabled 0 <br /> } <br /></p><p></p><p> Bash code <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / servers / hostgroup.cfg <br /> # Vi / usr / local / nagios / etc / servers / hostgroup.cfg <br /></p><p></p><p> Hostgroup.cfg code <br /> # Define host group (localhost.cfg host group in a similar setting, I have it commented out, otherwise there may be conflicts) <br /> define hostgroup { <br /> hostgroup_name linux-servers; The name of the hostgroup <br /> alias Linux Servers; Long name of the group <br /> members localhost, sectop; Comma separated list of hosts that belong to this group <br /> } <br /><br /> # Define hostgroup { <br /> # Hostgroup_name windows-servers; The name of the hostgroup <br /> # Alias Windows Servers; Long name of the group <br /> # Members print; Comma separated list of hosts that belong to this group <br /> #} <br /> # Define host group (localhost.cfg host group in a similar setting, I have it commented out, otherwise there may be conflicts) <br /> define hostgroup { <br /> hostgroup_name linux-servers; The name of the hostgroup <br /> alias Linux Servers; Long name of the group <br /> members localhost, sectop; Comma separated list of hosts that belong to this group <br /> } <br /><br /> # Define hostgroup { <br /> # Hostgroup_name windows-servers; The name of the hostgroup <br /> # Alias Windows Servers; Long name of the group <br /> # Members print; Comma separated list of hosts that belong to this group <br /> #} </p><p> ================================================ <br /> # Complete the monitoring host configuration configuration files configuration file using the following command to check the correctness: </p><p><br /> Bash code <br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nagios-v / usr / local / nagios / etc / nagios.cfg <br /> # / Usr / local / nagios / bin / nagios-v / usr / local / nagios / etc / nagios.cfg <br /></p><p><br /></p><p> # Determine the correct restart Nagios: </p><p> Bash code <br /> # Service nagios restart </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' First, install the support package  Bash code  # Yum-y install gcc gcc-c + + gd gd-devel php httpd openssl-devel  # Yum-y install gcc gcc-c + + gd gd-devel php httpd openssl-devel  Second, install nagios  Create User  Bash code  # Useradd nagios # passwd nagios  # Useradd nagios # passwd nagios ...'),(77,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0623/250.html','http://www.ixdba.net','sendmail problem of slow start','sendmail_problem_of_slow_start','2010-06-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> This is nothing new, the problem is the host name resolution, but see your / etc / hosts, still do not see why there will be problems parsing: <br /> 127.0.0.1 localhost localhost.localdomain <br /> 192.168.12.246 ixdba.net </p><p> Explain here, my host name is ixdba.net </p><p> In my / etc / mail / sendmail.cf in <br /> O DaemonPortOptions = Port = smtp, Addr = 127.0.0.1, Name = MTA </p><p> This address is 127.0.0.1, should be concerned with this, to read: <br /> 127.0.0.1 localhost localhost.localdomain <br /> 127.0.0.1 ixdba.net <br /> Still not work, it appears that the new line did not play a role in the following, try the following </p><p> 127.0.0.1 localhost localhost.localdomain ixdba.net </p><p> Try again, Oh, start the flash, the problem should be solved, in fact, read sendmail start / etc / hosts of the first line. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' This is nothing new, the problem is the host name resolution, but see your / etc / hosts, still do not see why there will be problems parsing:  127.0.0.1 localhost localhost.localdomain  192.168.12.246 ixdba.net  Explain here, my host name is ixdba.net  In my / etc / mail / sendmail.cf in  O...'),(78,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0422/36.html','http://www.ixdba.net','locale: Cannot set the problem','locale_Cannot_set_the_problem','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">System</a></u> environment:</span></span></font></strong> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ host conf] # more / etc / issue</span></span> </p><div> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 5 (Tikanga)</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Kernel \\ r on an \\ m</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </div><div> <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Problem phenomenon:</span></span></font></strong> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><font color=\"#000000\">[Root @ ha] # locale <br /></font> <font color=\"#ff6600\">locale: Cannot set LC_CTYPE to default locale: No such file or directory <br /> locale: Cannot set LC_MESSAGES to default locale: No such file or directory <br /> locale: Cannot set LC_ALL to default locale: No such file or directory</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\">LANG = en_US.UTF-8 <br /> LC_CTYPE = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_NUMERIC = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_TIME = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_COLLATE = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_MONETARY = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_MESSAGES = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_PAPER = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_NAME = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_ADDRESS = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_TELEPHONE = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_MEASUREMENT = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_IDENTIFICATION = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; <br /> LC_ALL = en_US.UTF-8</font></span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Enter the locale command, the phenomenon appears as shown above, at the same time, the system for no reason the Chinese to change the encoding of this document, why?</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">Address:</font></strong> <br /></span></span> </div><div style=\"text-indent: 21pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">This problem occurs in redhat system, the final analysis, because the system lacks the corresponding result of glibc package, this problem is the lack of glibc-common cause, you can see at this time the system is not / usr / lib / locale / locale-archive file The.</span></span> </div><div style=\"text-indent: 21pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Version of the system, install the glibc-commo package to solve the problem, I installed version is: glibc-common-2.5-12.i386.rpm.</span></span> </div><div style=\"text-indent: 21pt\"> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">After installation, problem solving, locale, the display is normal.</span></span> </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','System environment:[Root @ host conf] # more / etc / issueRed Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 5 (Tikanga)Kernel \\ r on an \\ mÃ‚Â Problem phenomenon:[Root @ ha] # locale  locale: Cannot set LC_CTYPE to default locale: No such file or directory  locale: Cannot set LC_MESSAGES to default locale: No...'),(79,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0422/34.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Talk about the Red Hat Linux, rhel, and Fedora Core as well as differences and relations between Centos','Talk_about_the_Red_Hat_Linux_rhel_and_Fedora_Core_as_well_as_differences_and_relations_between_Centos','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' (Editor: South African Ant)...'),(80,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0421/9.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Linux performance analysis and adjustment of actual articles','Linux_performance_analysis_and_adjustment_of_actual_articles','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">We are talking not just to expand what <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%B3%BB%E7%BB%9F\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">the system</span> cache, such as <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%B0%83%E6%95%B4\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">adjusting</span> the control page, in fact, these operations can really solve the system <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">performance</span> problem or a problem. We mainly discuss how to get the system resources and performance of the current situation, and then targeted based on these data, adjusted to obtain the final result. <br /><br /> 1, those measures can indeed offer performance? <br /> 1) Make sure system has sufficient memory. <br /> 2) the use of cluster; <br /> 3) to optimize the disk (including the <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%96%87%E4%BB%B6\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">file</span> system), increased I / O throughput; <br /> 4) <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%BD%91%E7%BB%9C\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">network</span> bandwidth; <br /><br /> 2, general factors that affect system performance: <br /> 1) CPU <br /> 2) memory <br /> 3) The disk I / O bandwidth <br /> 4) Network I / O bandwidth in general, and now the network <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%9C%8D%E5%8A%A1%E5%99%A8\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">server</span> for the services provided, the CPU speed is enough to provide processing capabilities; hence affects the performance of the disk and memory. Memory is not enough, then the virtual memory <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%AE%A1%E7%90%86\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">management</span> systems for memory pages to be frequently written to disk, memory, disk write operation. This is the swapping process, greatly affects the performance. <br /><br /> The network I / O, in general he is not independent. Therefore, other factors to be considered comprehensive. <br /><br /> 3, check the system performance situation. <br /> 1) CPU usage analysis <br /><br /> The following indicators to measure the CPU <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%B4%9F%E8%BD%BD\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">load</span> conditions. <br /><br /> Overall Utilization: <br /><br /> [Root @ linux stone] sar-u 5 5 <br /> <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=Linux\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Linux</span> 2.4.21-4.ELsmp (linux1) 01/04/05 <br /><br /> 18:00:17 CPU% user% nice% system% idle <br /> 18:00:22 all 1.50 0.00 0.93 97.57 <br /> 18:00:27 all 16.02 0.00 4.74 79.24 <br /> 18:00:32 all 5.69 0.00 3.77 90.53 <br /> 18:00:37 all 0.79 0.00 1.10 98.11 <br /> 18:00:42 all 2.69 0.00 1.21 96.10 <br /> Average: all 5.15 0.00 2.24 92.61 <br /><br /> CPU access to the specified number (multiple CPU case) the use of <br /> [Root @ linux stone] sar-U 0 <br /> Linux 2.4.21-4.ELsmp (linux1) 01/04/05 <br /> 00:00:00 CPU% user% nice% system% idle <br /> 0 1.10 0.00 0.83 98.36 00:10:00 <br /> 0 0.55 0.00 0.78 97.52 00:20:00 <br /> 0 0.97 0.00 0.77 98.57 00:30:00 <br /> 0 1.15 0.00 0.93 97.09 00:40:00 <br /> 0 1.88 0.00 1.33 95.96 00:50:00 <br /> 0 1.20 0.00 1.11 96.66 01:00:00 <br /> 0 0.78 0.00 1.26 97.96 01:10:00 <br /> 0 1.07 0.00 1.04 96.91 01:20:00 <br /> 0 1.24 0.00 1.01 97.29 01:30:00 <br /><br /> Can get <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%BF%90%E8%A1%8C\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">to run</span> user <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%BF%9B%E7%A8%8B\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">process%</span> user,% system kernel process and free state is the percentage of CPU time. <br /> Observational data, the conclusions: <br /> % User greater that the server is running normally;% system that the server is in the larger system calls or I / O operations. If there is a lot of time CPU is idle (% idle), it shows CPU enough. <br /><br /> We also get the kernel to switch on every time the number of the current process, if this number is high, that the server hardware. <br /> [Root @ linux stone] sar-w <br /> 07:50:00 cswch / s <br /> 08:00:00 285.49 <br /> 08:10:00 259.64 <br /> 08:20:00 387.54 <br /> 08:30:00 359.15 <br /> 08:40:00 504.29 <br /> 08:50:00 762.73 <br /> 09:00:00 572.93 <br /> 09:10:01 885.75 <br /> 09:20:00 1159.97 <br /> 09:30:00 1101.83 <br /> 09:40:00 1095.72 <br /> 09:50:00 1052.89 <br /> 10:00:00 961.75 <br /> 10:10:00 861.31 <br /> 10:20:00 501.76 <br /> 10:30:00 370.81 <br /> 10:40:00 736.26 <br /> 10:50:00 635.93 <br /> 11:00:00 399.51 <br /> 11:10:00 873.58 <br /> 11:20:00 741.14 <br /> 11:30:00 776.49 <br /> 11:40:00 641.55 <br /> Average: 416.97 <br /><br /> Average load: <br /> Average system load is defined as running at a specific time interval, the average number of processes in the queue, in general, as long as each CPU is the current number of active processes is less than 3 the performance of the system is good, and if the number of tasks for each CPU greater than 5, then the performance of the machine that has serious problems. <br /><br /> [Root @ linux stone] uptime <br /> 18:07:22 up 10 days, 8:05, 1 user, load average: 0.49, 0.31, 1.18 <br /> That in the last 1,5,15 minutes in the run queue, the average number of processes. <br /><br /> [Root @ linux stone] sar-q <br /> 07:50:00 runq-sz plist-sz ldavg-1 ldavg-5 <br /> 08:00:00 0214 0.01 0.08 <br /> 08:10:00 0222 0.37 0.21 <br /> 08:20:00 1 229 0.41 0.42 <br /> 08:30:00 0239 0.45 1.10 <br /> 08:40:00 0242 0.24 0.36 <br /> 08:50:00</font>1 253 1.55 1.98 <br /> 09:00:00 0248 0.45 0.55 <br /> 09:10:01 0273 8.17 3.85 <br /> 09:20:00 0295 0.62 0.99 <br /> 09:30:00 0279 0.87 0.79 <br /> 09:40:00 1 284 0.62 0.68 <br /> 09:50:00 0302 0.38 0.51 <br /> 10:00:00 0277 0.98 0.79 <br /> 10:10:00 2 289 0.60 0.55 <br /> 10:20:00 2 264 0.28 0.33 <br /> 10:30:00 0269 0.28 0.31 <br /> 10:40:00 0284 0.58 0.46 <br /> 10:50:00 0324 1.18 0.62 <br /> 11:00:00 0311 0.43 0.31 <br /> 11:10:00 0330 0.65 0.54 <br /> 11:20:00 1 335 0.45 0.45 <br /> 11:30:00 1 345 0.39 0.47