pan> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">Be modified to find these lines:</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><br /> $ Cfg [\'Servers\'] [$ i] [\'auth_type\'] = \'http\'; / / Authentication method (valid choices: config, http, HTTP, signon or cookie) <br /> $ Cfg [\'Servers\'] [$ i] [\'user\'] = \'root\'; / / MySQL user <br /> $ Cfg [\'Servers\'] [$ i] [\'password\'] = \'PASSWORD\'; / / MySQL password (only needed <br /><br /></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">After these steps, we a safer environment for basic</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">LAMP</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">server set up on the success of friends.</span> </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','RPM packages and source packages storage location / usr / local / src  Source package compile install location (prefix) / usr / local / xxx  Storage location, and maintenance procedures for the script / usr / local / sbin  MySQL database location / var / lib / mysql  Apache web root directory /...'),(87,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/2010/0423/64.html','http://www.ixdba.net','The default security bjpeg-6b...','The_default_security_bjpeg6b','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">The default security bjpeg-6b</span></strong> <br /><br /> shell&gt; wget <a href=\"ftp://ftp.uu.net/graphics/jpeg/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz\">ftp://ftp.uu.net/graphics/jpeg/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz</a> <br /><br /> tar zxvf jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz <br /> cd jpeg-6b <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/jpeg6-enable-shared-enable-static <br /> make <br /> make install <br /></p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">Specify the installation directory install jpeg-6b</span></strong> </p><p><br /> If you choose the default installation, you may very well, but to specify a path, first create the following folder, or will be error: <br /><br /> <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">Error</a></u> prompted :...... / usr / bin / install-c-m 644 jconfig.h / usr/local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h <br /><br /> / Usr / bin / install: can not create a general file \'/ usr/local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h\': No such file or directory <br /><br /> make: *** [install-headers] Error 1 <br /></p><p> Create the following folders need to <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6 <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/include <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/lib </p><p> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/bin <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/man <br /> # Mkdir / usr/local/jpeg6/man/man1 </p><p> # Make install-lib <br /> # Make install <br /><br /> Then compile setting: <br /><br /> . / Configure - enable-shared - enable-static <br /><br /> Followed by make, start to go wrong: <br /><br /> . / Libtool - mode = compile gcc-O2-I.-C. / Jcapimin.c <br /><br /> make:. / libtool: command not found <br /><br /> make: *** [jcapimin.lo] Error 127 <br /><br /> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">First, see if there is not installed libtool and libtool-ltdl-devel <br /><br /> rpm-qa | grep libtool <br /><br /> Jpeg-6b then enter the source directory, and then perform the following steps, remember! <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.sub. <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.guess.</span> <br /></strong> <br /> Libtool which is to bring the two configuration files jpeg-6b overwrite the corresponding file directory <br /><br /> make clean and then re-configure <br /><br /> When the first does not have permission to establish the corresponding folder, make install on the line again <br /><br /> <strong>Installing GD</strong> <br /><br /> Error <br /><br /> make [2]: *** [gd_png.lo] Error 1 <br /><br /> make [2]: Leaving directory `/ usr/local/file/gd-2.0.26gif \' <br /><br /> make [1]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1 <br /><br /> make [1]: Leaving directory `/ usr/local/file/gd-2.0.26gif \' <br /><br /> make: *** [all] Error 2 <br /><br /> (Such as where there is an error, please vi gd_png.c, find the &quot;png.h&quot; changed to &quot;/ usr/local/libpng2/include/png.h&quot;) </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','The default security bjpeg-6b shell> wget ftp://ftp.uu.net/graphics/jpeg/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz tar zxvf jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz  cd jpeg-6b  . / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/jpeg6-enable-shared-enable-static  make  make install Specify the installation directory install jpeg-6b If you choose the default...'),(88,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0423/62.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' I: Preparation Package,...','_I_Preparation_Package','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> I: Preparation Package, storage / home / xiutuo / software / directory. </p><p> Main package </p><p> 1. Httpd-2.2.6.tar.gz </p><p> 2. Mysql-5.0.45-linux-i686-glibc23.tar.gz (this version is already compiled compressed, slightly after decompression configured to use) </p><p> 3. Php-5.2.5.tar.gz </p><p> Packages needed to install php (where libxml2 is installed php5 required.) </p><p> 1. Libxml2-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxm2\">http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxm2</a> </p><p> 2. Libxslt-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxslt\">http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/sources/libxslt</a> </p><p> 3. Curl-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://curl.haxx.se/download\">http://curl.haxx.se/download</a> </p><p> GD library requires package (some say PHP source code package comes GD2.0.28 and zlib, as long as the three support packages to install GD: jpg, png and freetype, but we still download) </p><p> 1. Gd-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://www.libgd.org/Main_Page\">http://www.libgd.org/Main_Page</a> or <a href=\"http://www.libgd.org/releases/\">http://www.libgd.org/releases/</a> </p><p> 2. Freetype-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/freetype\">http://sourceforge.net/projects/freetype</a> </p><p> 3. Jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://ijg.org/files/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz\">http://ijg.org/files/jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz</a> </p><p> 4. Libpng-(Version). Tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html\">http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html</a> </p><p> 5. Zlib-1.2.3.tar.gz ---&gt; <a href=\"http://www.zlib.net\">http://www.zlib.net</a> </p><p> All of the above packages to download to: / root / Software / directory. </p><p> Second: Install mysql </p><p> # Tar-zvxf mysql-5.0.45-linux-i686-glibc23.tar.gz </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Cp-r mysql-5.0.45 / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Cp / usr / local / mysql / support-files / mysql.server / etc / rc.d / init.d / mysql / / mysql boot </p><p> # Cp / usr / local / mysql / support-files / my-medium.cnf / etc / my.cnf </p><p> Add mysql user and group </p><p> # Groupadd mysql </p><p> # Useradd-g mysql mysql </p><p> Modify the mysql directory permissions </p><p> # Chown-R root / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Chgrp-R mysql / usr / local / mysql </p><p> # Chown-R mysql / usr / local / mysql / data </p><p> Mysql system database generated </p><p> # / Usr / local / mysql / scripts / mysql_install_db - user = mysql &amp; / / start the mysql service </p><p> # / Usr / local / mysql / bin / mysqld_safe - user = mysql &amp; </p><p> If there Starting mysqld daemon with databases from / usr / local / mysql / data representative of normal start mysql service. </p><p> Press Ctrl + C out of mysql Ã§ÂšÂ„ root password change </p><p> # / Usr / local / mysql / bin / mysqladmin-u root-p password &quot;123456&quot; </p><p> Third: Install GD library (for PHP support GIF, PNG, JPEG) </p><p> <strong>a. Create a directory to install jpeg6:</strong> </p><p> If you choose the default installation, you may very well specify the path, please create the following folder, if you do not create the folder, it will error </p><p> Error :...... / usr / bin / install-c-m 644 jconfig.h / usr/local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h / usr / bin / install: can not create a general file \'/ usr / local/jpeg6/include/jconfig.h \': No such file or directory and then began to compile <br /> jpeg-6b./configure - enable-shared - enable-static <br /> make may be wrong <br /> . / Libtool - mode = compile gcc-O2-I.-C. / Jcapimin.cmake:. / Libtool: command not found <br /> make: *** [jcapimin.lo] Error 127 <br /> First, see if there is not installed libtool and libtool-ltdl-devel <br /> rpm-qa | grep libtool <br /> Jpeg-6b then enter the source directory, and then perform the following steps, remember! <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.sub. <br /> cp / usr / share / libtool / config.guess. <br /> Libtool which is to bring the two configuration files jpeg-6b overwrite the corresponding file directory make clean <br /> Not have permission to re-configure the time to first establish the corresponding folder, make install on the line again </p><p> Installation is as follows: </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6 </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/bin </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/lib </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/include </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/man </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/man1 </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/jpeg6/man/man1 </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd jpeg6 </p><p> <strong>#. / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/jpeg6 / - enable-shared - enable-static</strong> </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p> <strong>b.libpng package (support for PNG)</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf libpng-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Cd libpng-(version) </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / libpng </p><p> # Make </p><p> #&gt; Make install </p><p> <strong>c. Install freetype</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf freetype-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Cd freetype-(version) </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr / local / freetype </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / freetype </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p></p><p> <strong>d. Install zlib</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zxvf zlib-1.2.3.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd zlib.1.2.3 </p><p> # Mkdir / usr / local / zlib </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / zlib </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p></p><p> <strong>e. Install GD Library</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf gd-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/gd2 </p><p> # Cd gd-(version) </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/gd2 - with-jpeg = / usr/local/jpeg6 - with-zlib-dir = / usr / local / zlib - with-png = / usr / local / libpng - with-freetype = / usr / local / freetype </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p> <strong>e. Install Curl library</strong> </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zxf curl-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr / local / curl </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / curl </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p></p><p> <strong>Four: Install apache2</strong> </p><p> # Cd / roo / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf httpd-2.2.6.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd httpd-2.2.6 </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/apache2 </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / apache - enable-modules = so - enable-rewrite </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p> # / Usr/local/apache2/bin/apachectl-k start / / start apahce </p><p> View with a browser <a href=\"http://localhost\">http://localhost</a> , be it works, that apache is configured successfully. </p><p> # / Usr/local/apache2/bin/apachectl-k stop / / stop apache </p><p></p><p> Five: Install php5, php5 must have libxml2 support! </p><p> a. Install libxml2 </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf libxml2-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Cd libxml2-(version) </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/libxml2 </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/libxml2 </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p></p><p> b. Install libxslt (optional install, you can not install) </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf libxslt-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr / local / libxslt </p><p> # Cd libxslt-(version) </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / libxslt - with-libxml-prefix = / usr/local/libxml2 </p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p></p><p> c. install php5 </p><p> # Cd / root / Software / </p><p> # Tar-zvxf php-(version). Tar.gz </p><p> # Mkdir-p / usr/local/php5 </p><p> # Cd php-(version) </p><p> #. / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/php5 - with-apxs2 = / usr/local/apache2/bin/apxs \\ </p><p> &gt; - With-gd = / usr/local/gd2 - with-jpeg-dir = / usr/local/jpeg6 \\ </p><p> &gt; - With-zlib-dir = / usr / local / zlib \\ </p><p> &gt; - With-png-dir = / usr / local / libpng \\ </p><p> &gt; - With-freetype-dir = / usr / local / freetype - \\ </p><p> &gt; - Enable-trace-vars - with-mysql = / usr / local / mysql \\ </p><p> &gt; - Enable-mbstring = all - with-curl = / usr / local / curl - enable-mbregex \\ </p><p> &gt; - With-config-file-path = / usr/local/php5 - enable-ftp \\ </p><p> &gt; - Enable-soap - with-xsl = / usr / local / libxslt </p><p></p><p> # Make </p><p> # Make install </p><p> # Cp php.ini-dist / usr/local/php5/php.ini (Do not forget Oh) </p><p></p><p> VI: Re-configure apache2 so that he supports php </p><p></p><p> # Cd / usr/local/apache2/conf </p><p> # Vim httpd.conf </p><p> In the LoadModule php5_module modules/libphp5.so </p><p> Add AddType application / x-httpd-php. Php </p><p></p><p> OK, the basic installation has been completed. </p><p> Restart APACHE: </p><p> # / Usr/local/apache2/bin/apachectl start </p><p> If you re-start APACHE appears: </p><p> Syntax error on line 232 of / usr/local/apache2/conf/httpd.conf: Cannot load / usr/local/apache2/modules/libphp5.so into server: </p><p> / Usr/local/apache2/modules/libphp4.so: cannot restore segment prot after reloc: Permission denied </p><p> It should be in accordance with the following solutions: </p><p></p><p> 1.chcon-t texrel_shlib_t / usr/local/apache2/modules / *. so </p><p></p><p> 2. Edit / etc / selinux / config, find this: </p><p> # This file controls the state of SELinux on the system. </p><p> # SELINUX = can take one of these three values: </p><p> # Enforcing - SELinux security policy is enforced. </p><p> # Permissive - SELinux prints warnings instead of enforcing. </p><p> # Disabled - SELinux is fully disabled. </p><p> SELINUX = enforcing </p><p></p><p> The SELINUX = enforcing commented: # SELINUX = enforcing, and then add a new behavior: </p><p> SELINUX = disabled </p><p> Save and close. </p><p></p><p> Edit / etc / sysconfig / selinux, found: </p><p> # This file controls the state of SELinux on the system. </p><p> # SELINUX = can take one of these three values: </p><p> # Enforcing - SELinux security policy is enforced. </p><p> # Permissive - SELinux prints warnings instead of enforcing. </p><p> # Disabled - SELinux is fully disabled. </p><p> SELINUX = enforcing </p><p></p><p> If SELINUX already SELINUX = disabled, then do not change, otherwise put SELINUX = enforcing commented out, the new add a line: </p><p> SELINUX = disabled </p><p> Save and exit. </p><p> ok, web environment apache2 + mysql5 + php5 to introduce here. More detailed configuration of apache2 and mysql configuration and the corresponding php.ini configuration reference documentation. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' I: Preparation Package, storage / home / xiutuo / software / directory.  Main package  1. Httpd-2.2.6.tar.gz  2. Mysql-5.0.45-linux-i686-glibc23.tar.gz (this version is already compiled compressed, slightly after decompression configured to use)  3. Php-5.2.5.tar.gz  Packages needed to install php...'),(89,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0422/51.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Select prefork or worker can...','_Select_prefork_or_worker_can','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Select prefork or worker can be compiled using the-with-mpm = MPM parameters specified, the default is prefork, prefork child process derived by way of pre with a separate child process to handle the different requests, processes independent of each other. Compile and make install in make install, use httpd-l to determine the current use of the MPM is prefork.c. View httpd-mpm.conf configuration file, which contains the following default configuration section: <br /> &lt;IfModule Prefork.c&gt; <br /> StartServers 5 <br /> MinSpareServers 5 <br /> MaxSpareServers 10 <br /> MaxClients 150 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; <br /> prefork <br /> Control of the process in the initial establishment of &quot;StartServers&quot; sub-process, in order to meet the needs of MinSpareServers set to create a process, wait a second, to create two, wait a second, to create four ... ... so created by the exponential increase number of processes, up to 32 per second, until the value set to meet MinSpareServers up. This model comes in the request can not re-spawn a new process, which reduces the system overhead in order to increase performance. MaxSpareServers set the maximum number of idle processes, and if this value is greater than the number of idle process, Apache will automatically kill off some redundant process. Do not set this value too large, but if MinSpareServers smaller than the value set, Apache will automatically adjust it to MinSpareServers +1. <br /> If the site loads more, consider the same time increase MinSpareServers and MaxSpareServers. MaxRequestsPerChild set is that each child process to handle the requests. Each child in dealing with the &quot;MaxRequestsPerChild&quot; requests will be automatically destroyed. 0 means unlimited, and that the child will never be destroyed. Although the default is set to 0, so that each child process can handle more requests, but set to a nonzero value if there are two important advantages: 1, prevents accidental memory leaks. 2, in the server load down at the right time will automatically reduce the number of child processes. Therefore, according to the load on the server to adjust this value. MaxClients is the most important of these instructions, a set that Apache can handle the request, the greatest impact is the performance parameters of Apache. The default value of 150 is not enough, if the total number of requests has reached this value (via ps-ef | grep http | wc-l to confirm), then subsequent requests will queue until the completion of a request has been processed . This is a lot of system resources while remaining the main reason for HTTP access is very slow. Although theoretically the higher the value, the more requests can be handled, but the restrictions can not be greater than the default Apache 256. ServerLimit recompile Apache directive can not increase the MaxClients. <br /> &lt;IfModule Prefork.c&gt; <br /> ServerLimit 10000 <br /> StartServers 5 <br /> MinSpareServers 5 <br /> MaxSpareServers 10 <br /> MaxClients 10000 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p> Worker </p><p> Relative to the prefork, worker support for the new multi-threaded and multi-process mixture model MPM. The use of threads to handle, so it can handle the request of the relative mass, and the system resources is less than the cost of process-based server. However, worker also uses a number of processes, each process has generated more than one thread to get the stability of the server-based process. In the configure-with-mpm = worker after the make build, make install to install. Generated in the default httpd-mpm.conf has the following default configuration section: </p><p> &lt;IfModule Worker.c&gt; <br /> StartServers 2 <br /> MaxClients 150 <br /> MinSpareThreads 25 <br /> MaxSpareThreads 75 <br /> ThreadsPerChild 25 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p> Worker process generated by the master control &quot;StartServers&quot; sub-processes, each child process ThreadsPerChild contains a fixed number of threads, each thread independently handle the request. Similarly, in order to not generate thread again when a request comes, MinSpareThreads and MaxSpareThreads set the minimum and maximum number of idle threads; while at the same time MaxClients set the maximum number of incoming clients. If the existing number of threads in the child process can not meet the load, the control process will derive a new child process. MinSpareThreads and MaxSpareThreads default maximum of 75 and 250, respectively. These two parameters did not affect the performance of Apache can be adjusted accordingly in accordance with the actual situation. <br /> ThreadsPerChild worker MPM is most closely associated with the performance of the instruction. The default value is the maximum ThreadsPerChild 64, if the load the larger, 64 is not enough. Explicitly use this time to ThreadLimit directive, which is the default value of the maximum 20,000. Worker mode, the total number of requests can be processed simultaneously by ThreadsPerChild value multiplied by the total number of child processes of decision, should be greater than equal to MaxClients. If the load is large, the number of existing child process can not meet, the control process will derive a new child process. The largest number of child processes by default is 16, increase the need to explicitly declare when ServerLimit (maximum is 20,000). Note that, if explicitly declared ServerLimit, then it must be multiplied by a value greater than or equal ThreadsPerChild MaxClients, and MaxClients ThreadsPerChild must be an integer multiple, otherwise Apache will automatically adjust to an appropriate value. <br /> &lt;IfModule Worker.c&gt; <br /> ServerLimit 25 <br /> ThreadLimit 200 <br /> StartServers 3 <br /> MaxClients 2000 <br /> MinSpareThreads 50 <br /> MaxSpareThreads 200 <br /> ThreadsPerChild 100 <br /> MaxRequestsPerChild 0 <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p> The following is built using Apache ab testing tools to test the situation on the Server (set the requested index page is 6bytes), cpu% occupancy rate for the cpu, mem for the memory usage (M units), RequestsPerSecond per second processing number of requests. </p><p> 1, Prefor way (ServerLimit, StartServer, MinSpareServers, MaxSpareServers, MaxClients, MaxRequestPerChild) </p><p> -n/-c (ab parameter) Cpu% Mem Requestspersecond <br /> (-, 5,5,10,150,0) <br /> 100000/100 28.8 2,858,434 <br /> 100000/200 29.2 3,048,032 <br /> 100000/500 25.3 3,237,348 <br /> 100000/1000 24.4 3,305,886 <br /> (10000,5,5,10,500,0) <br /> 100000/100 28.7 3,718,345 <br /> 100000/200 27.4 3,897,929 <br /> 100000/500 24.9 4,177,229 <br /> 100000/1000 23.4 4,376,676 <br /> (10000,5,5,10,1000,0) <br /> 100000/100 28.8 4,088,517 <br /> 100000/200 27.0 4,228,045 <br /> 100000/500 24.2 4,557,236 <br /> 100000/1000 22.5 4,706,570 <br /> (10000,5,5,10,1500,0) <br /> 100000/100 29.6 3,308,407 <br /> 100000/200 28.1 3,498,014 <br /> 100000/500 26.4 3,807,290 <br /> 100000/1000 24.0 4,006,686 </p><p> 2, Worker mode </p><p> (ServerLimt, Threadlimt, Startservers, MaxClients, MinspareThread, MaxspareThread, ThreadperChild, MaxRequestPerChild) <br /> -n/-c (ab parameter) cpu% mem RequestsperSecond <br /> (50,500,5,10000,50,200,200,0) <br /> 100000/100 18.6 1,886,020 <br /> 100000/200 20.1 1,955,892 <br /> 100000/500 19.8 2,095,708 <br /> 100000/1000 22.2 2,186,081 <br /> (100,500,5,10000,50,200,100,0) <br /> 100000/100 24.5 2,406,919 <br /> 100000/200 23.6 2,476,798 <br /> 100000/500 24.6 2,546,827 <br /> 100000/1000 22.3 2,716,114 <br /> (200,500,5,10000,50,200,50,0) <br /> 100000/100 27.3 3,017,781 <br /> 100000/200 27.4 3,077,789 <br /> 100000/500 26.0 3,207,141 <br /> 100000/1000 21.8 3,446,110 <br /> Relatively speaking, prefork mode speed to slightly higher than the worker, but it requires the cpu and memory resources are also slightly more than woker. </p><p> How to know the current application mode apache </p><p> httpd-l If you have prefork.c prefork way that is, if it is worker.c that work mode. <br /> Reason busy site requires you to conduct your analysis. Generally of logs. And then make judgments based on the actual situation. </p><p> I have done to optimize a friend. He was a machine every night basically scores LOAD. Is very slow. I analyzed the log. There are many reptiles found in the dynamic accessPage and have many malicious IP theft in the picture data. Lead to a lot of resources are consumed. Finally, I take the appropriate measures. LOAD is now basically in 1 below. Therefore, access behavior analysis of the blind is important to adjust the connection parameters of APACHE is not really meaningful. I hope my words can correct some of your incorrect thoughts. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Select prefork or worker can be compiled using the-with-mpm = MPM parameters specified, the default is prefork, prefork child process derived by way of pre with a separate child process to handle the different requests, processes independent of each other. Compile and make install in make install,...'),(90,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/tomcat/2010/0422/45.html','http://www.ixdba.net','tomcat directory browsing is...','tomcat_directory_browsing_is','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">tomcat</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">directory browsing is enabled by default, but usually do not want to have this feature, and to prohibit directory browsing. This feature can be achieved by configuring</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">web.xml</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">file achieve.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\"><br /> &lt;servlet&gt; <br /> &lt;servlet-name&gt; default &lt;/ servlet-name&gt; <br /> &lt;servlet-class&gt; <br /> org.apache.catalina.servlets.DefaultServlet <br /> &lt;/ Servlet-class&gt; <br /> &lt;init-param&gt; <br /> &lt;param-name&gt; debug &lt;/ param-name&gt; <br /> &lt;param-value&gt; 0 &lt;/ param-value&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Init-param&gt; <br /> <span style=\"color: red\">&lt;init-param&gt; <br /> &lt;param-name&gt; listings &lt;/ param-name&gt; <br /> &lt;param-value&gt; false &lt;/ param-value&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Init-param&gt; <br /></span> &lt;load-on-startup&gt; 1 &lt;/ load-on-startup&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Servlet&gt; <br /></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">And the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">listings</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">property to <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">false.</span> But this is a complete directory can not be <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;\">viewed.</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\"></span></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','tomcat directory browsing is enabled by default, but usually do not want to have this feature, and to prohibit directory browsing. This feature can be achieved by configuring web.xml file achieve.  <servlet>  <servlet-name> default </ servlet-name>  <servlet-class> ...'),(91,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/2010/0422/44.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' A: Unison Introduction ...','_A_Unison_Introduction_','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> A: Unison Introduction </p><p><br /> Unison is a windows and unix platforms can use file synchronization tool that can make two folders (local or network) to keep the content consistent. unison with other file system synchronization tools or the same characteristics, but also has its own characteristics: </p><p> Cross-platform; </p><p> Kernel and user rights for no special requirements; </p><p> unison is a two-way, two points can automatically copy the update processing is not part of the conflict, some conflict will be displayed to the user to select update strategy; </p><p> IXDBA.NET Technical Community </p><p> Can be connected as long as two hosts, you can run unison, can use secure socket connection or ssh connection, less demanding on the bandwidth, the use of the compression protocol similar to rsync. </p><p> Unison with text and graphical interface, here only how to use the text interface. </p><p><br /> Second: Install unison </p><p><br /> Download various versions of unison: </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/unison//download.html\">http://www.seas.upenn.edu/ ~ bcpierce / unison / / download.html</a> </p><p> unison compiler Download: </p><p> <a href=\"http://caml.inria.fr/pub/distrib/ocaml-3.10\">http://caml.inria.fr/pub/distrib/ocaml-3.10</a> </p><p> Other useful links; </p><p> <a href=\"http://worldhello.net/doc/bcp/unison.html\">http://worldhello.net/doc/bcp/unison.html</a> </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/unison//contrib.html\">http://www.seas.upenn.edu/ ~ bcpierce / unison / / contrib.html</a> </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.cis.upenn.edu/~bcpierce/unison/download/releases/stable/unison-manual.html#rshmeth\">http://www.cis.upenn.edu/ ~ bcpierce / unison / download / releases / stable / unison-manual.html # rshmeth</a> </p><p> <a href=\"http://linux.chinaunix.net/bbs/viewthread.php?tid=888250&amp;extra=page%3D1%26amp%3Bfilter%3Dreward\">http://linux.chinaunix.net/bbs/viewthread.php?tid=888250&amp;extra=page% 3D1% 26amp% 3Bfilter% 3Dreward</a> </p><p> Can be downloaded from the above address a variety of platforms, various versions of unison, are based on source code installed, there are binary, I downloaded the binary can be used directly. Here are source code installation: </p><p> Source install unison </p><p> Linux, compile and install packages from source, you need a tool called the Objective Caml compiler, version 3.0.7 at least, you can download from here: <a href=\"http://caml.inria.fr/\">http://caml.inria.fr/</a> </p><p> Ocaml installation script as follows: </p><p> # Tar-zxf ocaml-3.09.3.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd ocaml-3.09.3 </p><p> #. / Configure </p><p> # Make world opt </p><p> # Make install </p><p> Demanding on the version of Unison to synchronize the two hosts need the same version of unison, so the same is used here and the windows version 2.13.16, unison-2.13.16.tar.gz </p><p> The installation script as follows: </p><p> # Tar-zxf unison-2.13.16.tar.gz </p><p> # Cd unison-2.13.16 </p><p> # Make UISTYLE = text </p><p> # Make install </p><p> Executable file will be generated after the unison, to the system PATH will be to their cp. </p><p> # Cp. / Unison / usr / local / bin </p><p><br /> Three: Configure ssh double trust </p><p><br /> As unison to synchronize folders in the remote login a remote server, so you want to configure the two machines trust each other </p><p> This example assumes the local machine is: 10.178.1.132 (linux) </p><p> Remote machine: 10.178.1.110 (solaris) </p><p> 1. In the two machines to create RSA keys </p><p> The following actions to the local machine and remote machine is executed again </p><p> (1) to root user login </p><p> (2) in the root user\'s home directory to create. Ssh directory and set the correct permissions </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # mkdir ~ /. Ssh </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # chmod 700 ~ /. Ssh </p><p> (3) the use of ssh-keygen command to generate the first version of the SSH protocol 2 RSA key </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # ssh-keygen-t rsa </p><p> Generating public / private rsa key pair. </p><p> Enter file in which to save the key (/ root / .ssh / id_rsa): </p><p> Enter passphrase (empty for no passphrase): </p><p> Enter same passphrase again: </p><p> Your identification has been saved in / root / .ssh / id_rsa. </p><p> Your public key has been saved in / root / .ssh / id_rsa.pub. </p><p> The key fingerprint is: </p><p> 17: E4: 7C: 79:8 d: A0: 00:3 b: D9: F7: 7A: 56: F3: AC: 54:4 d <a href=\"mailto:oracle@gsgatzhapp1\">@ gsgatzhapp1 Oracle</a> </p><p> In prompted to save the private key (key) and public key (public key) of the location, use the default values. If the private key password (passphrase), then enter a private key password (if using the private key password when using ssh to execute remote commands to enter the private key password, so, in this case the private key password is not used), therefore, directly back to cars can be. </p><p> 2. Add the key to the authorized key file (authorized key file) in the </p><p> (1) to root user login </p><p> (2) the implementation of the local machine </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # cd ~ /. Ssh </p><p> [Root@gsgatzhapp1.ssh] # ssh 10.178.1.132 cat / root / .ssh / id_rsa.pub&gt;&gt; authorized_keys </p><p> [Oracle@gsgatzhapp1.ssh] # ssh 10.178.1.110 cat / root / .ssh / id_rsa.pub&gt;&gt; authorized_keys </p><p> [Oracle@gsgatzhapp1.ssh] # scp authorized_keys 10.178.1.110: / root / .ssh / </p><p> [Oracle @ gsgatzhapp1. Ssh] # chmod 600 / root / .ssh / authorized_keys </p><p> (3) on the remote machine 10.178.1.110: </p><p> bash-2.05 # chmod 600 / root / .ssh / authorized_keys </p><p> (4) Test </p><p> After running in the gsgatzhapp1: </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # ssh 10.178.1.132 date </p><p> [Root @ gsgatzhapp1 ~] # ssh 10.178.1.110 date </p><p> If you do not need to enter a password to a system date, indicating that SSH configuration is successful. </p><p><br /> IV: unison use </p><p><br /> Unison can be used in a host, synchronize two folders, can also be used on the network. </p><p> 1: for local use </p><p> Usage: </p><p> # Unison 111 222 # 111 and 222 synchronize the local folder </p><p> Contacting server ... </p><p> Looking for changes </p><p> Warning: No archive files were found for these roots. This can happen either </p><p> because this is the first time you have synchronized these roots, </p><p> or because you have upgraded Unison to a new version with a different </p><p> archive format. </p><p> Update detection may take a while on this run if the replicas are </p><p> large. </p><p> Unison will assume that the \'last synchronized state\' of both replicas </p><p> was completely empty. This means that any files that are different </p><p> will be reported as conflicts,and any files that exist only on one </p><p> replica will be judged as new and propagated to the other replica. </p><p> If the two replicas are identical, then no changes will be reported. </p><p> Press return to continue. [&lt;spc&gt;] Reconciling changes </p><p> 111,222 </p><p> &lt;---- File aaaaaaaaaaaaa [f]? </p><p> Commands: </p><p> &lt;ret&gt; or f or &lt;spc&gt; follow unison\'s recommendation (if any) </p><p> I ignore this path permanently </p><p> E permanently ignore files with this extension </p><p> N permanently ignore paths ending with this name </p><p> m merge the versions </p><p> d show differences </p><p> x show details </p><p> l list all suggested changes </p><p> p or b go back to previous item </p><p> g proceed immediately to propagating changes </p><p> q exit unison without propagating any changes </p><p> / Skip </p><p> &gt; Or. Propagate from left to right </p><p> &lt;Or, propagate from right to left </p><p></p><p> &lt;---- File aaaaaaaaaaaaa [f] f </p><p></p><p> Proceed with propagating updates? [] Y </p><p> Propagating updates </p><p></p><p> UNISON started propagating changes at 15:06:08 on 27 Aug 2007 </p><p> [BGN] Copying aaaaaaaaaaaaa </p><p> from / 222 </p><p> to / 111 </p><p> [END] Copying aaaaaaaaaaaaa </p><p> UNISON finished propagating changes at 15:06:08 on 27 Aug 2007 </p><p> Saving synchronizer state </p><p> Synchronization complete (1 item transferred, 0 skipped, 0 failures) </p><p> If detected, two folders are different, unison will be prompted to let you select the appropriate action. The example above. </p><p> The right of the folder that has 222 new file, whether to the left of the 111 synchronized folder, f said the force, and then confirmed to be updated, if you enter? Will be described in more detail. </p><p> 2: unison remotely </p><p> Usage: </p><p> # Unison &lt;local directory&gt; ssh: / / remotehostname (IP) / &lt;remote directory\'s absolute path&gt; </p><p> For example: </p><p> # Unison / home / AAA ssh: / / username @ remotehostname (ip) / / DB / path / BBB </p><p> Said the unit\'s directory / home / AAA and the remote host / DB / path / BBB synchronization. In general, two functions need to ssh connection. </p><p> Note that between the host and the directory also added a &quot;/&quot; </p><p> 3: unison Parameter Description </p><p> Unison has many parameters, here only a few frequently used, please refer to the detailed manual unison: </p><p> &quot;-Testserver </p><p> Test connectivity, connect to the server to exit. Example: </p><p> $ Unison / ssh: / / opensou1 @ bluehost /-servercmd = ~ / bin / unison-testserver </p><p> If the server executable file is not in unison under the default directory, or even unison command (need you to build an upload to the server), you need to use-servercmd parameter tells the server to execute unison command position. </p><p> Use-testserver parameter, the link that is out successfully, it will not perform directory comparison to subsequent operations. </p><p> &quot;-Servercmd xxx </p><p> Tells unison, unison server command is. See example above. </p><p> &quot;-Auto </p><p> Accept the default action, and then waits for the user to confirm whether implementation. </p><p> &quot;-Batch </p><p> batch mode, automatic mode, accept the default action and implementation. </p><p> &quot;-Ignore xxx </p><p> Increase in xxx to ignore list </p><p> &quot;-Ignorecase [true | false | default] </p><p> Whether to ignore the file name case </p><p> &quot;-Follow xxx </p><p> Whether to support the contents of the synchronous symbolic link </p><p> &quot;Owner = true (to keep pace over the file owner) </p><p> &quot;Group = true (to synchronize files over the group information) </p><p> &quot;Perms = -1 (sync over the files read-write permissions) </p><p> &quot;Repeat = 1 (interval 1 second after the start of a Sync Check) </p><p> &quot;Retry = 3 (failed again) </p><p> &quot;Sshargs =-C (using ssh\'s compression and transmission mode) </p><p> &quot;Xferbycopying = true </p><p></p><p> &quot;-Immutable xxx </p><p> The same directory, can be ignored when scanning </p><p> &quot;-Silent </p><p> Quiet mode </p><p> &quot;-Times </p><p> Sync modified </p><p> &quot;-Path xxx parameter </p><p> Synchronous-path parameter specifies only the subdirectories and files, not the entire directory. -Path can appear multiple times, for example, </p><p> unison / home / username ssh: / / remotehost / / home / username \\ </p><p> -Path shared \\ </p><p> -Path pub \\ </p><p> -Path .netscape / bookmarks.html </p><p> 4: unison through the configuration file to use </p><p> Although you can entirely through the command line to specify the parameters needed to run unison, but we recommend using the configuration file to configure the use of unison, the reason is very simple to see the configuration file easier to understand than looking at the command line, and a more manageable . </p><p> Folder is located in the default configuration file ~ currentuser / .unison, that the current user\'s home directory, windows are located in C: \\ Documents and Settings \\ currentuser \\. Unison, the default configuration file name is default.prf. </p><p> Run this command: </p><p> # Unison exitgogo </p><p> Unison will default to read ~ currentuser / .unison / exitgogo.prf file configuration information. My configuration information in / root / .unison / exitgogo.prf, so we can introduce the above parameters, configuration information for all the parameters written to a. prf file. </p><p> Here is one of my web application to synchronize two folders in the configuration information: </p><p> root = / sina / webdata </p><p> root = ssh: / / root@192.168.60.121 / / sina / webdata </p><p> # Force = / sina / webdata </p><p> ignore = Path as / * </p><p> # Prefer = ssh: / / root@192.168.60.121 / / sina / webdata </p><p> batch = true </p><p> # Repeat = 1 </p><p> # Retry = 3 </p><p> owner = true </p><p> group = true </p><p> perms = -1 </p><p> fastcheck = false </p><p> rsync = false </p><p> # Debug = verbose </p><p> sshargs =-C </p><p> xferbycopying = true </p><p> log = true </p><p> logfile = / root/.unison/sina_122.1547.log </p><p> As follows: </p><p> Root expressed the need to synchronize two folders </p><p> force that the local / var / www / bbsnew folder as the standard, the directory synchronization to the remote. Note that if the force parameter is specified, then becomes a single synchronized unison, and that force will be subject to the specified folder synchronization. </p><p> Unison itself is two-way sync, but to do two-way synchronization, do not set the force parameter, if the force parameter is set to become the single sync, unison at this time similar to sync. </p><p> Unison is the basic principle of two-way synchronization: if there are two folders AB, A folder to synchronize their changes to B, B folder also synchronize their own changes to the A, the final contents of AB the same two folders, the file is AB Collection folder. </p><p> Unison, a disadvantage of two-way synchronization for a file in two folders are synchronized modified, unison is not to synchronize, because unison could not determine with that subject. </p><p> ignore = Path to omit / sina / webdata following WEB-INF/tmp directory, that synchronization does not synchronize it. </p><p> batch = true, said automatic mode, accept the default action, and implement </p><p> -Fastcheck true that the use of synchronous file creation time to compare two files, if this option is false, unison will compare the two files. BuiltMeeting is set to true </p><p> log = true, said the output in the terminal operation information. </p><p> logfile is specified, while the output written to log file. </p><p><br /> Five: unison FAQ </p><p><br /> How to synchronize large amounts of data and the remote server, upload some of the data, the time-out: </p><p> 9% 559:15 ETARead from remote host bluehost: Connection reset by peer </p><p> Fatal error: Lost connection with the server </p><p> In practice, the best way is for the first time to upload the files first branded package, with ftp upload, and then expand into the server, then you can perform a unison synchronization. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' A: Unison Introduction  Unison is a windows and unix platforms can use file synchronization tool that can make two folders (local or network) to keep the content consistent. unison with other file system synchronization tools or the same characteristics, but also has its own characteristics: ...'),(92,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0422/42.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Download module:  To the...','_Download_module__To_the','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Download module: </p><p> To the official website: <a href=\"http://www.nowhere-land.org/programs/mod_vhost_limit/\">http://www.nowhere-land.org/programs/mod_vhost_limit/</a> download module </p><p> <a href=\"http://www.nowhere-land.org/prog\">http://www.nowhere-land.org/prog</a> ... st_limit-0.4.tar.gz </p><p> Installation: <br /> apxs-c mod_vhost_limit.c-o / path / to / libexec / mod_vhost_limit.so </p><p> In httpd.conf add: <br /> LoadModule vhost_limit_module libexec / mod_vhost_limit.so <br /> AddModule mod_vhost_limit.c </p><p> Configuration: </p><p> MaxClients 150 <br /> ExtendedStatus On </p><p> NameVirtualHost * </p><p> &lt;VIRTUALHOST * /&gt; <br /> ServerName server1 <br /> DocumentRoot / some/where/1 <br /> MaxVhostClients 100 </p><p><br /> &lt;VIRTUALHOST * /&gt; <br /> ServerName server2 <br /> DocumentRoot / some/where/2 <br /> MaxVhostClients 30 </p><p><br /> &lt;VIRTUALHOST * /&gt; <br /> ServerName server3 <br /> DocumentRoot / some/where/3 </p><p><br /> Where: server1 is limited to 100 concurrent threads. server2 is limited to 30 concurrent threads. server3 is not limited. </p><p> Note: the need to support mod_status the ExtendedStatus On! ! </p><p> Exceed the limit as the number of concurrent client will appear in the error 503 </p><p> -------------------------------------------------- ----------------------------------------- </p><p> Limit the number of IP connections </p><p> Here to download the module <a href=\"http://dominia.org/djao/limit/mod_limitipconn-0.04.tar.gz\">http://dominia.org/djao/limit/mod_limitipconn-0.04.tar.gz</a> </p><p> Installation: <br /> tar zxvf mod_limitipconn-0.04.tar.gz <br /> cd mod_limitipconn-0.04 <br /> make APXS = / usr / local / apache / bin / apxs ÃƒÂŸ ----- Here the path is set according to your own <br /> make install APXS = / usr / local / apache / bin / apxs ÃƒÂŸ ----- Here the path is set according to your own </p><p> Editing httpd.conf <br /> Add a global variable: <br /> &lt;IfModule mod_limitipconn.c&gt; <br /> &lt;Location /&gt; # of all virtual hosts / directory MaxConnPerIP 3 # 3 for each IP only allows concurrent connections NoIPLimit image / * # IP restrictions on the pictures do not do &lt;/ Location&gt; </p><p> &lt;Location / mp3&gt; # all the hosts of the / mp3 directory MaxConnPerIP 1 # IP allows only one connection per request <br /> OnlyIPLimit audio / mpeg video # The limit is only for video and audio format file &lt;/ Location&gt; <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; </p><p></p><p> Or virtual host: <br /> &lt;VirtualHost xx.xxx.xx.xx&gt; # # ip address <a href=\"mailto:ServerAdmineasy@phpv.net\">ServerAdmineasy@phpv.net</a> <br /> DocumentRoot / home / easy <br /> ServerNamewww.phpv.net <br /> &lt;IfModule mod_limitipconn.c&gt; <br /> &lt;Location /&gt; </p><p></p><p> MaxConnPerIP 5 <br /> NoIPLimit image / * <br /> &lt;/ Location&gt; <br /> &lt;Location / mp3&gt; # all the hosts of the / mp3 directory MaxConnPerIP 2 # IP allows only one connection per request <br /> OnlyIPLimit audio / mpeg video # The limit is only for video and audio format file &lt;/ Location&gt; <br /> &lt;/ IfModule&gt; <br /> &lt;/ VirtualHost&gt; </p><p><br /> -------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------- </p><p> Bandwidth restrictions: </p><p> Download module <a href=\"ftp://ftp.cohprog.com/pub/apache/module/1.3.0/mod_bandwidth.c\">ftp://ftp.cohprog.com/pub/apache/module/1.3.0/mod_bandwidth.c</a> <br /> Installation: <br /> / Usr / local / apache / bin / apxs-c. / Mod_bandwidth.c-o / usr / local / apache / libexec / mod_bandwidth.so </p><p><br /> &lt;------- More / usr / local / apache set the path for you </p><p> Editing httpd.conf <br /> Add: <br /> LoadModule bandwidth_module libexec / mod_bandwidth.so <br /> AddModule mod_bandwidth.c </p><p> Restart your apache </p><p> Related documents: </p><p> Global configuration directives: </p><p> * BandWidthDataDir <br /> Syntax: BandWidthDataDir &lt;directory&gt; <br /> Default: &quot;/ tmp / apachebw&quot; <br /> Context: server config </p><p> Sets the name of the root directory usedby mod_bandwidth to store its internal temporary information. Don\'t forget to create the needed directories: &lt;directory&gt; / master and &lt;directory&gt; / link </p><p> * BandWidthModule <br /> Syntax: BandWidthModule &lt;On|Off&gt; <br /> Default: Off <br /> Context: per server config </p><p> Enable or disable totaly the whole module. By default, the module is disable so it is safe to compile it in the server anyway. </p><p> PLEASE, NOTE THAT IF YOU SET A BANDWIDTH LIMIT INSIDE A VIRTUALHOST BLOCK, YOU ALSO __NEED__ TO PUT THE &quot;BandWidthModule On&quot; DIRECTIVE INSIDE THAT VIRTUALHOST BLOCK! </p><p> IF YOU SET BANDWIDTH LIMITS INSIDE DIRECTORY BLOCKS (OUTSIDE OF ANY VIRTUALHOST BLOCK), YOU ONLY NEED TO PUT THE &quot;BandWidthModule On&quot; DIRECTIVE ONCE, OUTSIDE OF ANY VIRTUALHOST OR DIRECTORY BLOCK. </p><p> * BandWidthPulse <br /> Syntax: BandWidthPulse &lt;microseconds&gt; <br /> Default: <br /> Context: per server config </p><p> Change the algorithm used to calculate bandwidth and transmit data. In normal mode (old mode), the module try to transmit data in packets of 1KB. That mean that if the bandwidth available is of 512B, the module will transmit 1KB, wait 2 seconds, transmit another 1KB and so one. </p><p> Seting a value with &quot;BandWidthPulse&quot;, will change the algorithm so that the server will always wait the same amount of time between sending packets but the size of the packets will change. The value is in microseconds. For example, if you set &quot;BandWidthPulse 1000000 &quot;(1 sec) and the bandwidth available is of 512B, the sever will transmit 512B, wait 1 second, transmit 512B and so on. </p><p> The advantage is a smother flow of data. The disadvantage is a bigger overhead of data transmited for packet header. Setting too small a value (bellow 1 / 5 of a sec) is not realy useful and will put more load on the system and generate more traffic for packet header. </p><p> Note also that the operating system may do some buffering on it\'s own and so defeat the purpose of setting small values. </p><p> This may be very useful on especialy crowded network connection: In normal mode, several seconds may happen between the sending of a full packet. This may lead to timeout or people may believe that the connection is hanging. Seting a value of 1000000 (1 sec ) would guarantee that some data are sent every seconds ... </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Download module:  To the official website: http://www.nowhere-land.org/programs/mod_vhost_limit/ download module http://www.nowhere-land.org/prog ... st_limit-0.4.tar.gz  Installation:  apxs-c mod_vhost_limit.c-o / path / to / libexec / mod_vhost_limit.so  In httpd.conf add:  LoadModule...'),(93,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0421/3.html','http://www.ixdba.net','php-fpm to manage the FastCGI mode ph','phpfpm_to_manage_the_FastCGI_mode_ph','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Run php with FastCGI in time, if we change the php.ini settings, you must restart the fastcgi php daemon. If your system is relatively large load, then this process may restart your system will interrupt service for some time. php-fpm is born to solve this problem, it\'s in the php fastcgi process does not interrupt the circumstances had changed to reload your php.ini. <br /> Php-fpm and can no longer rely on other fastcgi initiator, such as lighttpd\'s spawn-fcgi, for me to finally get rid of the shadow of lighttpd. <br /> So what, go! <br /> My php version is 5.2.6, and the first official website to download the corresponding php version php-fpm patch: PHP-FPM <br /> Assumptions: php source directory in: / usr/local/src/php-5.2.6, php-fpm downloaded to the / usr / local / src <br /> cd / usr / local / src <br /> gzip-cd php-5.2.6-fpm-0.5.9.diff.gz | patch-d php-5.2.6-p1 </p><p></p><p> After the patch lay, when compiling php several parameters to increase the following: </p><p> -Enable-fpm fpm activated fastcgi mode support-with-fpm-conf php-fpm in the configuration file (default PREFIX / etc / php-fpm.conf) <br /> -With-fpm-log php-fpm log file (default PREFIX / logs / php-fpm.log) <br /> -With-fpm-pid php-fpm in the pid file (default PREFIX / logs / php-fpm.pid) </p><p> Compile time-enable-fpm, of course is necessary, several other conditions can adjust your own. <br /> Compilation parameters: <br /> cd / usr/local/src/php-5.2.6 <br /> . / Configure - enable-fastcgi - enable-fpm - prefix = / usr/local/php5 - with-config-file-path = / usr/local/php5/etc - THE-OTHERS <br /> make <br /> make install </p><p><br /> One-THE-OTHERS represent some other php build parameters, omitted here. <br /> After a while, so php built and installed, the following start configuring php-fpm. <br /> vi / usr/local/php5/etc/php-fpm.conf </p><p><br /> php-fpm.conf xml format is a plain text file, you can open it yourself to see the details, basically a look to understand. Here special attention to what these configuration fields: <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;listen_address&quot;&gt; 127.0.0.1:9000 &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Php in fastcgi process of this that the ip address and port monitoring <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;user&quot;&gt; nobody &lt;/ value&gt; <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;group&quot;&gt; nobody &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Php fastcgi process that\'s what users and user groups to run <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;display_errors&quot;&gt; 0 &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Php error message is displayed <br /> &lt;value name=&quot;max_children&quot;&gt; 5 &lt;/ value&gt; </p><p><br /> Here the largest number of child processes to run php-fpm: <br /> / Usr/local/php5/bin/php-cgi - fpm </p><p><br /> Php-fastcgi process is already running in the background, and monitor port 9000 of 127.0.0.1. <br /> Can use ps and netstat to see the results: <br /> ps aux | grep php-cgi </p><p><br /> netstat-tpl | grep php-cgi </p><p><br /> Installed the php-fpm, then it is how to achieve our original objective of it? <br /> Fortunately, php-fpm we are prepared to give yourself a program to control the fastcgi process, the file in $ PREFIX / sbin / php-fpm <br /> Run it: <br /> / Usr/local/php5/sbin/php-fpm </p><p><br /> The program has the following parameters: </p><p> php-fastcgi start the process of starting <br /> php in fastcgi stop the process of forced termination <br /> php in fastcgi quit to terminate the process smooth <br /> php in fastcgi restart the process of restarting <br /> reload to reload the php.ini php <br /> re-enable the log files logrotate </p><p> In other words, to modify the php.ini, we can use <br /> / Usr/local/php5/sbin/php-fpm reload </p><p><br /> Thus, to maintain the fastcgi php process in continuous operation in the state, and reload the php.ini. <br /> After the words: This file can be slightly modified, making it the CentOS / Redhat services, reducing the number of management overhead. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Run php with FastCGI in time, if we change the php.ini settings, you must restart the fastcgi php daemon. If your system is relatively large load, then this process may restart your system will interrupt service for some time. php-fpm is born to solve this problem, it\'s in the php fastcgi process...'),(94,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0422/41.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Under the original Linux build environment to build Nginx','Under_the_original_Linux_build_environment_to_build_Nginx','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> A,) to install Nginx <br /> 1.) Installation <br /> Pronounced Nginx [engine x], is established by the Russian Igor Sysoev project, based on the BSD license. F5 said that he is a member of the original, the English home page: <a href=\"http://nginx.net\">http://nginx.net</a> . Some large sites in Russia have been using it for more than two years, and has been doing a great job. </p><p></p><p> Need to be installed before installing nginx and zlib pcre package to support the override, and web compression, and so regular. </p><p></p><p> Installing pcre </p><p> Download: <a href=\"http://www.pcre.org/\">http://www.pcre.org/</a> </p><p> Download for their own version, and then install: </p><p> tar zxvf pcre-7.7.tar.gz </p><p> cd pcre-7.7 </p><p> make </p><p> make install </p><p></p><p> Installing zlib </p><p> Download: <a href=\"http://www.zlib.net/\">http://www.zlib.net/</a> </p><p> Download for their own version, and then install: </p><p> tar zxvf zlib-1.2.3.tar.gz </p><p> cd zlib-1.2.3 </p><p> make </p><p> make install </p><p> Download: <a href=\"http://www.nginx.net/\">http://www.nginx.net/</a> </p><p></p><p> Wait pcre and zlib installed, start the installation nginx </p><p></p><p> Download for their own version, and then compile and install: </p><p></p><p> Nginx compile parameters are as follows: </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 /] # tar zxvf nginx-0.6.31 </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cd nginx-0.6.31 </p><p></p><p> Special Note: Nginx requires PCRE module support, but in the next RHEL, even if the PCRE module has been installed, Nginx compile time still can not find the correct library files, so need to do the following modifications. </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # mkdir / usr / include / pcre </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / libpcre.a </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / libpcre.la </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / oracle/pcre-7.7/pcre.h / usr / include / pcre / pcre.h </p><p></p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # mkdir / usr / include / pcre / .libs </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / .libs / libpcre.a </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / usr / local / lib / libpcre.a / usr / include / pcre / .libs / libpcre.la </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # cp / oracle/pcre-7.7/pcre.h / usr / include / pcre / .libs / pcre.h </p><p></p><p> The above modifications are finished, then began to compile the installation. </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] #. / Configure - with-pcre = / usr / include / pcre - with-http_stub_status_module </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # vi. / Objs / Makefile (Note: 1006 OK to delete this file &quot;. / Configure - disable-shared&quot;) </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # make </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # make install </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 nginx-0.6.31] # </p><p> Installed, the default nginx installed in / usr / local /, enter nginx folder, open the configuration file! </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 conf] # pwd </p><p> / Usr / local / nginx / conf </p><p></p><p> 2) nginx Detailed profile </p><p></p><p> [Root @ oracle132 conf] # vi nginx.conf </p><p> user nobody nobody; # run the user </p><p> worker_processes 1; # start the process </p><p></p><p> # Global error log and PID file </p><p> # Error_log logs / error.log; </p><p> error_log logs / error.log notice; </p><p> # Error_log logs / error.log info; </p><p></p><p> pid logs / nginx.pid; </p><p></p><p> # Maximum number of working patterns and connections </p><p> events { </p><p> use epoll; </p><p> worker_connections 1024; </p><p> } </p><p></p><p> # Set http server using its capabilities to provide load balancing reverse proxy support </p><p> http { </p><p></p><p> # Set mime type </p><p> include mime.types; </p><p> default_type application / octet-stream; </p><p></p><p> # Set the log format </p><p> # Log_format main \'$ remote_addr - $ remote_user [$ time_local] $ request\' </p><p> # \'&quot;$ Status&quot; $ body_bytes_sent &quot;$ http_referer&quot;\' </p><p> # \'&quot;$ Http_user_agent&quot; &quot;$ http_x_forwarded_for&quot;\'; <br /><br /> # Access_log logs / access.log main; <br /><br /> # Set the request buffer <br /> client_header_buffer_size 1k; <br /> large_client_header_buffers 4 4k; <br /><br /> # Set the access log <br /> sendfile on; </p><p> tcp_nopush on; <br /> keepalive_timeout 65; <br /><br /> # Enable Web compression gzip on; <br /> gzip_http_version 1.0; <br /> gzip_comp_level 2; <br /> gzip_proxied any; <br /> gzip_types text / plain text / html text / css application / x-javascript text / xml application / xml application / xml + rss text / javascript; <br /> gzip_min_length 1100; <br /> gzip_buffers 4 8k; <br /> # Set the list of servers load balancing <br /> upstream ixdba { <br /> # Weigth parameter that weights are assigned to the higher weight the greater the chances <br /> # Squid on the machine open port 3128 <br /> server 192.168.8.1:3128 weight = 5; <br /> server 192.168.8.2:80 weight = 1; <br /> server 192.168.8.3:80 weight = 6; <br /> } <br /> # The following is to configure the virtual host include / usr / local / nginx / conf / proxy.conf; <br /> include / usr / local / nginx / conf / vhosts / www.test.com.conf; <br /><br /> 3) Detailed virtual host configuration file <br /> Because each virtual host to specify a file, the following example, a virtual host configuration is as follows: <br /> [Root @ oracle132 vhosts] # <br /> vi / usr / local / nginx / conf / vhosts / www.test.com.conf; <br /><br /> server { <br /> listen 80; # virtual host using port server_name <a href=\"http://www.test.com\">www.test.com</a> ; # virtual host access to domain name charset UTF-8; # set the default character encoding nginx # access_log logs / host.access.log main; <br /> # All jpg format pictures have nginx to handle the location ~ \\. Jpg $ { <br /> root / cicro/cws3/vhosts/www.test.com/ROOT; <br /> expires 30d; <br /> } <br /> # All gif format images have nginx to handle location ~ \\. Gif $ { <br /> root / cicro/cws3/vhosts/www.test.com/ROOT; <br /> expires 30d; <br /> } <br /> # Upload all the files and the html have to deal with nginx </p><p> location ~ ^ / (upload | html) / { </p><p> root / cicro/cws3/vhosts/www.test.com/ROOT; </p><p> expires 30d; </p><p> } </p><p> # Remove the above file, all the rest are agents to <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8009\">http://127.0.0.1:8009</a> to access </p><p> location / { </p><p> root / cicro/cws3/vhosts/www.test.com/ROOT; </p><p> index index.html; </p><p> proxy_pass <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8009\">http://127.0.0.1:8009</a> ; </p><p> } <br /> # Set the view state of the address Nginx </p><p> location / NginxStatus { </p><p> access_log on; </p><p> auth_basic &quot;NginxStatus&quot;; </p><p> auth_basic_user_file .. / htpasswd; </p><p> } </p><p> # Error_page 404 / 404.html; </p><p> # Redirect server error pages to the static page / 50x.html </p><p> # </p><p> error_page 500 502 503 504 / 50x.html; </p><p> location = / 50x.html { </p><p> root html; </p><p> } </p><p> } </p><p> In the above state has set the address of view Nginx, you need to apache\'s htpasswd to generate a login verification file, so generate a htpasswd file: </p><p> [Root @ oracle132 vhosts] # / usr / local / bin / htpasswd-c htpasswd gaojf </p><p> New password: (Enter your password) <br /> Re-type new password: (re-enter your password) <br /> Adding password for user gaojf </p><p></p><p> The above / usr / local / bin / htpasswd htpasswd file is the execution path, if not the file can be copied from the apache\'s bin directory to a come! </p><p> -C is to create a file </p><p> -C back httpasswd is to create a verification file name. </p><p> gaojf is to create the user </p><p></p><p> # View nginxstatus: <br /> <a href=\"http://www.test.com/nginxstatus/\">http://www.test.com/nginxstatus/</a> , enter the username and password authentication, you can see something like the following: <br /> Active connections: 328 <br /> server accepts handled requests <br /> 9309898228890 <br /> Reading: 1 Writing: 3 Waiting: 324 <br /> The first line that is now the third line of active connections of the third number indicates the current time is running Nginx total number of requests received, if the ceiling is reached soon, we need to increase the upper limit. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' A,) to install Nginx  1.) Installation  Pronounced Nginx [engine x], is established by the Russian Igor Sysoev project, based on the BSD license. F5 said that he is a member of the original, the English home page: http://nginx.net . Some large sites in Russia have been using it for more than two...'),(95,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0422/40.html','http://www.ixdba.net','nginx configuration anti-hotlinking','nginx_configuration_antihotlinking','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">I, for different file types <br /> location ~ .* \\. (wma | wmv | asf | mp3 | mmf | zip | rar | jpg | gif | png | swf | flv) $ { <br /> valid_referers none blocked *. admin99.net admin99.net; <br /> if ($ invalid_referer) { <br /> # Rewrite ^ / http://www.admin99.net/403.html; <br /> return 403; <br /> } <br /> } <br /><br /> Second, for a different directory <br /> location / img / { <br /> root / data / img /; <br /> valid_referers none blocked *. admin99.net admin99.net; <br /> if ($ invalid_referer) { <br /> rewrite ^ / http://www.admin99.net/images/error.gif <br /> # Return 403; <br /> } <br /> } <br /><br /> Third, these are anti-hotlinking features built nginx, nginx also can be used to achieve third-party modules ngx_http_accesskey_module download anti-hotlinking not discussed.</font> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','I, for different file types  location ~ .* \\. (wma | wmv | asf | mp3 | mmf | zip | rar | jpg | gif | png | swf | flv) $ {  valid_referers none blocked *. admin99.net admin99.net;  if ($ invalid_referer) {  # Rewrite ^ / http://www.admin99.net/403.html;  return 403;  }  }  Second, for a different...'),(96,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0422/39.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Nginx error page redirection method','Nginx_error_page_redirection_method','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In the nginx configuration file, you can place <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">the error</a></u> page redirection is configured, the nginx.conf file has the following configuration information:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">error_page 404 / 404.html;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This 404.html ensure html nginx home directory to the directory, if necessary, after 404 in the event of a direct jump to another address, you can directly set as follows:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> error_page 404 http://www.ixdba.net;</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Can be defined the same way as the 403,500 other common errors.</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Special attention is paid 404.html file page size to more than 512k, otherwise the browser will be replaced ie ie default error page. I have had in the past this problem.</font> </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','In the nginx configuration file, you can place the error page redirection is configured, the nginx.conf file has the following configuration information:error_page 404 / 404.html;This 404.html ensure html nginx home directory to the directory, if necessary, after 404 in the event of a direct jump to...'),(97,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/nginx/2010/0421/5.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Compile the linux install nginx + php (fastcgi)','Compile_the_linux_install_nginx__php_fastcgi','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> connected with nginx fastcgi php, install the linux compile the following support to compile php fastcgi mode, some other things, according to the way the original installed on it. <br /> Divided into the following steps: <br /> 1, install the fastcgi version of php <br /> 2, the use of spawn-fcgi php-fastcgi start engine <br /> 3, configure php to fastcgi engine connection nginx <br /> 1, install the fastcgi version of php <br /> mkdir / usr / local / modules <br /> # Jpeg directory <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/bin <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/lib <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/include <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/man <br /> mkdir / usr/local/modules/jpeg6/man/man1 <br /> A1, install zlib <br /> tar xzvf zlib-1.2.1.tar.gz <br /> cd zlib-1.2.1 <br /> # Do not use - prefix custom installation directory, the installation of gd <br /> . / Configure <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> A2, install freetype <br /> tar xzvf freetype-2.1.5.tar.gz <br /> cd freetype-2.1.5 <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / modules / freetype <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> A3, install libpng <br /> tar xzvf libpng-1.2.5.tar.gz <br /> # Do not use - prefix custom installation directory, the installation of gd <br /> cd libpng-1.2.5 <br /> cp scripts / makefile.std makefile <br /> make test <br /> make install <br /> A3, install jpeg <br /> tar xzvf jpegsrc.v6b.tar.gz <br /> cd jpeg-6b <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 - enable-shared - enable-static <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> A4, install GD <br /> tar xzvf gd-2.0.28.tar.gz <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / modules / gd - with-jpeg = / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 - with-png - with-zlib - with-freetype = / usr / local / modules / freetype <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> Then compile and install php, note with - enable-fastcgi parameters and - enable-force-cgi-redirect parameter <br /> . / Configure - prefix = / usr / local / php - with-gd = / usr / local / modules / gd - with-jpeg-dir = / usr/local/modules/jpeg6 - with-zlib - with-png - with-freetype-dir = / usr / local / modules / freetype - enable-magic-quotes - enable-fastcgi - with-mysql = / usr / local / mysql - enable-track-vars - enable-ftp - with-config-file-path = / usr / local / php / etc - with-zip - enable-force-cgi-redirect <br /> make-j10 <br /> make install <br /> 2, the use of spawn-fcgi php-fastcgi start after engine build in / usr / local / php / bin / php-cgi will have following the executable program, the use of spawn-fcgi php-fastcgi start the engine: <br /> / Data / nginx / sbin / spawn-fcgi-a 127.0.0.1-p 9000-u nobody-f / usr / bin / php-cgi-C 20 <br /> Means fastcgi ip and port to use the machine 9000 to provide services, permissions nobody, start 20 process. The main attention-C this parameter, the general process of 20, sufficient, and that not enough can turn up on my machine every php-cgi process will take 7-8 megabytes of memory, opening 100 is 700-800 MB . </p><p> spawn-fcgi nginx in this program does not provide, you can <br /> <a href=\"http://www.sudone.com/download/spawn-fcgi\">http://www.sudone.com/download/spawn-fcgi</a> <br /> Downloaded to the general on the nginx the sbin directory, and then added to give it executable permissions: <br /> chmod + x / data / nginx / sbin / spawn-fcgi <br /> 3, configure php to fastcgi engine connection nginx get a fastcgi-params first configuration, in the conf directory of nginx build a text file, reads: <br /> # Fastcgi-params <br /> fastcgi_param QUERY_STRING $ query_string; <br /> fastcgi_param REQUEST_METHOD $ request_method; <br /> fastcgi_param CONTENT_TYPE $ content_type; <br /> fastcgi_param CONTENT_LENGTH $ content_length; <br /> fastcgi_param SCRIPT_NAME $ fastcgi_script_name; <br /> fastcgi_param REQUEST_URI $ request_uri; <br /> fastcgi_param DOCUMENT_URI $ document_uri; <br /> fastcgi_param DOCUMENT_ROOT $ document_root; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_PROTOCOL $ server_protocol; <br /> fastcgi_param GATEWAY_INTERFACE CGI/1.1; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_SOFTWARE nginx; <br /> fastcgi_param REMOTE_ADDR $ remote_addr; <br /> fastcgi_param REMOTE_PORT $ remote_port; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_ADDR $ server_addr; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_PORT $ server_port; <br /> fastcgi_param SERVER_NAME $ server_name; <br /> # PHP only, required if PHP was built with - enable-force-cgi-redirect <br /> fastcgi_param REDIRECT_STATUS 200; <br /> # End <br /> This is the most primitive fastcgi-params, the Internet may have a more optimized version, you can access accordingly. <br /> Then configure nginx.conf, such as <a href=\"http://www.sudone.com\">www.sudone.com</a> , this configuration can be used by: <br /> server { <br /> include port.conf; <br /> server_name <a href=\"http://www.sudone.com\">www.sudone.com</a> sudone.com; <br /> location / { <br /> index index.html index.php; <br /> root / data / sudone / php /; <br /> } <br /> location ~. php $ { <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME / data / sudone / php $ fastcgi_script_name; <br /> include fastcgi_params; <br /> } <br /> } <br /> Brought down after a few need to change the place: <br /> 1, server_name <br /> 2, location / inside the root <br /> 3, location ~. Php $ inside fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME <br /> The parameters of which fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME, $ fastcgi_script_name php file path in front of the general and the same root, and finally do not have to write /, seemingly would be a problem, not superfluous. <br /> Note: <br /> The administrator may have always forget to start nginx start after the spawn-fcgi, so it is best to write a script to start, and then to cultivate the habit of testing services available. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' connected with nginx fastcgi php, install the linux compile the following support to compile php fastcgi mode, some other things, according to the way the original installed on it.  Divided into the following steps:  1, install the fastcgi version of php  2, the use of spawn-fcgi php-fastcgi start...'),(98,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/apache/2010/0422/38.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Now the so-called Web crawler...','Now_the_socalled_Web_crawler','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Now the so-called Web crawler search engine, also known as the spider is too much like some of the search engine algorithms is poor, to climb the serious consumption of server resources, but also may cause memory overflow. Can set the robots.txt to ban reptiles to climb the server. Online search for the next data, the default web root directory is not placed under the robots.txt file, to allow all web crawlers search all documents. Khan! ! <br /><br /> Put a file in the root directory robots.txt, but if not immediately. <br /> To prohibit sogou reptiles, set in the robots.txt so that User-agent: Sogou web spider <br /> Disallow: /</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">There is a stupid way to view the log, observation of the browser features, such as sogou is characterized by &quot;Sogou web spider&quot;, which can be set in the apache setenvif User-Agent &quot;Sogou web spider *&quot; den <br /> Order deny, allow <br /> deny from env = den <br /> Look at the apache log information, are reported to 403</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The most practical way to view apache log to see the source IP, confirmation, letters, the most effective</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">These operations are a temporary solution, but now the search engine too much, sometimes affect the normal operation of the server, it is necessary, you can make some restrictions on their operation.</font> </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','Now the so-called Web crawler search engine, also known as the spider is too much like some of the search engine algorithms is poor, to climb the serious consumption of server resources, but also may cause memory overflow. Can set the robots.txt to ban reptiles to climb the server. Online search for...'),(99,'Oracle','Database','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/1012/796.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Recently discovered this...','_Recently_discovered_this','2010-10-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Recently discovered this problem, reproduced eygle article, once again recorded! </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Recently a new database on the line Oracle10gR2 warning log file (alert.log) persists following <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> : <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:22 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:23 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:25 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:09:30 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /> Tue Jul 18 23:12:15 2006 <br /> WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136) <br /><br /> Recorded at the same time sqlnet.log the following errors: <br /><br /> Fatal NI connect error 12170. <br /><br /> VERSION INFORMATION: <br /> TNS for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> Oracle Bequeath NT Protocol Adapter for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> TCP / IP NT Protocol Adapter for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production <br /> Time: 19-JUL-2006 11:25:26 <br /> Tracing not turned on. <br /> Tns error struct: <br /> ns main err code: 12535 <br /> TNS-12535: TNS: operation timed out <br /> ns secondary err code: 12606 <br /> nt main err code: 0 <br /> nt secondary err code: 0 <br /> nt OS err code: 0 <br /> Client address: (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = tcp) (HOST = 192.168.1.123) (PORT = 58147)) <br /><br /> This is related to network connection and an error, Metalink is given the following solution: <br /><br /> 1.set INBOUND_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_ &lt;listenername&gt; = 0 in listener.ora <br /> 2. Set SQLNET.INBOUND_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 0 in sqlnet.ora of server. <br /> 3. Stop and start both listener and database. <br /> 4. Now try to connect to DB and observe the behaviour <br /><br /> Here restart the database and the Listener I think it is not necessary, and we look Listner should reload it. <br /><br /> [Oracle @ order admin] $ lsnrctl <br /><br /> LSNRCTL for Linux: Version 10.2.0.2.0 - Production on 19-JUL-2006 15:26:33 <br /><br /> Copyright (c) 1991, 2005, Oracle. All rights reserved. <br /><br /> Welcome to LSNRCTL, type &quot;help&quot; for information. <br /><br /> LSNRCTL&gt; reload <br /> Connecting to (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP) (HOST = 172.16.9.11) (PORT = 1521))) <br /> The command completed successfully <br /> LSNRCTL&gt; services <br /> Connecting to (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP) (HOST = 172.16.9.11) (PORT = 1521))) <br /> Services Summary ... <br /> Service &quot;order&quot; has 2 instance (s). <br /> Instance &quot;order&quot;, status UNKNOWN, has 1 handler (s) for this service ... <br /> Handler (s): <br /> &quot;DEDICATED&quot; established: 0 refused: 0 <br /> LOCAL SERVER <br /> Instance &quot;order&quot;, status READY, has 1 handler (s) for this service ... <br /> Handler (s): <br /> &quot;DEDICATED&quot; established: 0 refused: 0 state: ready <br /> LOCAL SERVER <br /> The command completed successfully <br /><br /> LSNRCTL&gt; show inbound_connect_timeout <br /> Connecting to (DESCRIPTION = (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP) (HOST = 172.16.9.11) (PORT = 1521))) <br /> LISTENER parameter &quot;inbound_connect_timeout&quot; set to 0 <br /> The command completed successfully <br /> LSNRCTL&gt; exit <br /><br /> Changes, observed a period of time, the current normal. <br /><br /> About SQLNET.INBOUND_CONNECT_TIMEOUT parameters, Oracle proposed to modify the parameters in order to avoid denial-of-service attacks.</span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Recently discovered this problem, reproduced eygle article, once again recorded! Recently a new database on the line Oracle10gR2 warning log file (alert.log) persists following error :  Tue Jul 18 23:09:22 2006  WARNING: inbound connection timed out (ORA-3136)  Tue Jul 18 23:09:23 2006  WARNING:...'),(100,'Mysql','Database','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0810/431.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Under linux mysql database...','_Under_linux_mysql_database','2010-08-10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Under linux <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/mysql/\">mysql</a></u> database table name by default is case-sensitive, to ignore the table names case, add a configuration to: <br /></p><p> vi / etc / my.cnf <br /> In the [mysqld] to increase column: <br /> lower_case_table_names = 0 </p><p> Can ignore case, if you set </p><p> lower_case_table_names = 1 Ã¥ÂˆÂ™ case sensitive. </p><p> The default mysql is case sensitive. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Under linux mysql database table name by default is case-sensitive, to ignore the table names case, add a configuration to:  vi / etc / my.cnf  In the [mysqld] to increase column:  lower_case_table_names = 0  Can ignore case, if you set  lower_case_table_names = 1 Ã¥ÂˆÂ™ case sensitive.  The default...'),(101,'Oracle','Database','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0806/418.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' This problem not only with...','_This_problem_not_only_with','2010-08-06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> This problem not only with the parameters shared_servers, dispatchers, but also with the server, the client\'s TNSname.ora documents are related. </p><p> In the DB server side shared_servers parameter controls whether to accept share server connection, but, client can be set by TNSname.ora mandatory DEDICATED <br /> As follows, 4 kinds of situations: <br /> DB shared_servers = 0, TNSname.ora server = shared, or not set ==&gt; DEDICATED connection <br /> DB shared_servers = 0, TNSname.ora server = DEDICATED ==&gt; DEDICATED connection <br /> DB shared_servers&gt; 0, TNSname.ora server = DEDICATED ==&gt; DEDICATED connection <br /> DB shared_servers&gt; 0, TNSname.ora server = shared, or not set ==&gt; Shared Connection </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' This problem not only with the parameters shared_servers, dispatchers, but also with the server, the client\'s TNSname.ora documents are related.  In the DB server side shared_servers parameter controls whether to accept share server connection, but, client can be set by TNSname.ora mandatory...'),(102,'Oracle','Database','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0806/416.html','http://www.ixdba.net','An AIX system, memory, 16G,...','An_AIX_system_memory_16G','2010-08-06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">An AIX system, memory, 16G, install the oracle database, just apply on-line to find the problem.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">1. Question the phenomenon of clients can not connect to the database, listener is running normally, but after restart the listener reported the following <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> : <br /> TNS-12549: TNS: operating system resource quota exceeded <br /> TNS-12560: TNS: protocol adapter error <br /> TNS-00519: Operating system resource quota exceeded <br /> IBM / AIX RISC System/6000 Error: 11: Resource temporarily unavailable</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">jianting not start, observe the background session to connect to the database are not many.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">2. Deal with the problem since the tips of resources beyond the amount of ideas, and nothing less than the pressures and constraints related to the new system is deployed, the equipment performance OK, not the overall control down pressure. <br /> Therefore, from another angle, since the new system to do, and whether certain &quot;limit&quot; parameter is not relevant to adjust?</span></span> </p><p></p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Since it is a new deployment environment, simply stop and study the need to modify the parameters of the maxuproc AIX parameters gradually emerged. This maxuproc parameter can be interpreted as &quot;max user processes&quot;, to limit each user a maximum number of processes available (similar to Oracle\'s processes limit the number of parameters on the session.) The parameter default value is 128, that something that enough? !</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">3. Solve the fault since the discovery of the problem, it will be more successful the treatment. <br /> 1) Check the current value of the parameter maxuproc <br /> # Lsattr-E-l sys0 | grep maxuproc <br /> 2) using the command chdev parameters will be adjusted as large as 1024 maxuproc <br /> # Chdev-l sys0-a maxuproc = 1024</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Parameters can be dynamically modified, that change will come into force.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Get the fault has been eliminated, call it a day.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">chdev command using the method of reference connection <br /> http://www.kuqin.com/aixcmds/aixcmds1/chdev.htm</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">4. Summary Fortunately, finding problems early, if only to find the problem on the line, the price will be heavy. <br /> Plans and programs is important, such issues need to accumulate and to always remember it. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','An AIX system, memory, 16G, install the oracle database, just apply on-line to find the problem.1. Question the phenomenon of clients can not connect to the database, listener is running normally, but after restart the listener reported the following error :  TNS-12549: TNS: operating system...'),(103,'Mysql','Database','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0707/282.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Problem symptoms and error...','Problem_symptoms_and_error','2010-07-07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> </p><p> <font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"code\">Database connection failed! Please check the database server, user name, password is correct</span> <br /><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> If the installation is mysql4.1 above, and just installed the password algorithm change will occur without this problem, the solution detailed in this article <br /> Client does not sport authentication protocol requested by server section <br /> <span style=\"font-size: 12px\">But if the problem is in the virtual hosting business devices appears, it must be really wrong your database server, user name, password</span></font> </p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"code\"> Client does not sport authentication protocol requested byserver </p><p><br /> Above all users to install Mysql4.1 see this !!!!!!!!! <b><br /></b> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> <br /> Mysql 4.1 and above to use the new cryptographic algorithms, and php does not support the new algorithm, so the new user, need to use the following solution to log in Mysql php can not connect the problem <span style=\"font-size: 12px\">(which some_user, some_host, newpwd are your database user name, host, password) <br /><br /> The first solution: <br /> mysql&gt; SET PASSWORD FOR <br /> -&gt; \'Some_user\' @ \'some_host\' = OLD_PASSWORD (\'newpwd\'); <br /><br /> For example, the database user is admin, host localhost, the password is 123456 <br /><br /> Enter the command at this time should be: <br /> mysql&gt; SET PASSWORD FOR admin @ localhost = OLD_PASSWORD (\'123456 \'); <br /> [Thanks henrykim do this example] <br /><br /> The second solution: <br /> mysql&gt; DATE mysql.user SET password = OLD_PASSWORD (\'newpwd\') <br /> -&gt; WHERE Host = \'some_host\' AND User = \'some_user\'; <br /> mysql&gt; FLUSH pRIVILEGES; <br /><br /><br /> The third solution (not recommended) <br /> With the - old-passwords option is enabled mysqld, then use the above method to change the original user <br /><br /> From Mysql official website: <font color=\"#333399\" face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><a href=\"http://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql/en/old-client.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql/en/old-client.html</a></font></span> <br /></p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_fetch_array (): supplied argument is not a valid MySQL result resource in / home / lonmo.com / install.php on line 405 </p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> mysql and php version mysql version of the library to use that much difference. If not look into the same </p><div class=\"Mjb598\"></div><p></p><p class=\"code-comment\"> Problem symptoms and error message: </p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_connect (): Too many connections in C: \\ web \\ www.lonmo.com \\ include \\ lib \\ kDB \\ lib \\ mysql.php on line 11 kDB Error: Connecting to MySQL failed, please contact to your administrator </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> server reached the maximum number of mysql connections. Just occasionally, look up the log to see if there is a lot of search engine spiders access to the records of spiders crawling sometimes this is like. <br /> Best to check your configuration file my.cnf file mysql max_connections value, if set too small to larger </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> </p><p> <font color=\"#000000\"><span class=\"code\">To the final step to establish an administrator always says &quot;the administrator to create failed&quot;</span> <br /><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions: It</span> may be a database permissions problem, such as user name or password error</font> </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> </p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_connect (): Access denied for user: \'root @ localhost\' (Using password: NO) in C: \\ usr \\ local \\ www \\ data \\ install.php on line 383 </p><p><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> current user (root) do not have permission to connect to the mysql database. May be connected user name, password is not correct, here is you are not prompted to specify the connection password for the root account </p><p> <span class=\"code-comment\">Problem symptoms and error message:</span> When prompted to create a database </p><p class=\"Mjb598\"></p><p></p><p class=\"code\"> Warning: mysql_connect (): Access denied for user: \'cmsware @ localhost\' (Using password: YES) in C: \\ usr \\ local \\ www \\ data \\ install.php on line 383 </p><p><br /> <span class=\"important\">Possible causes and solutions:</span> current user (cmsware) do not have permission to connect to the mysql database. May be connected user name, password is not correct, here is your permission to lack of prompt or password. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','Problem symptoms and error message:Database connection failed! Please check the database server, user name, password is correctPossible causes and solutions: If the installation is mysql4.1 above, and just installed the password algorithm change will occur without this problem, the solution detailed...'),(104,'Oracle','Database','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0604/172.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' PL / SQL block can only be...','_PL__SQL_block_can_only_be','2010-06-04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> PL / SQL block can only be directly embedded SELECT, DML (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE), and transaction control statements (COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT), but not directly embedded DDL statements (CREATE, ALTER, DROP) and DCL statements (GRANT, REVOKE) </p><p> 1. Retrieve a single row of data <br /> 1.1 use a scalar variable to accept the data v_ename emp.ename% type; <br /> v_sal emp.sal% type; <br /> select ename, sal into v_ename, v_sal from emp where empno = &amp;no; </p><p> 1.2 accept data using record variables type emp_record_type is record ( <br /> ename emp.ename% type, sal emp.sal% type); <br /> emp_record emp_record_type; <br /> select ename, sal into emp_record from emp where empno = &amp;no; </p><p> 1.3 embedded SELECT statement Note: <br /> When using the SELECT INTO statement, we must return to a data, and can only return one data <br /> no_date_found: <br /> select into returns no data too_many_rows: <br /> select into multiple data returned <br /> where clause to use NOTE: <br /> Variable name used in the same column name can not otherwise trigger TOO_MANY_ROWS exception. <br /></p><p> 2. Manipulate data using the VALUES clause 2.1 insert data v_deptno dept.deptno% type; <br /> v_dname dept.dname% type; <br /> v_deptno: = no; <br /> v_dname: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> insert into dept (deptno, dname) values (v_deptno, v_dname); </p><p> 2.2 Inserting Data using subqueries v_deptno emp.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> insert into employee select * from emp where deptno = v_deptno; <br /><br /> Update 2.3 updates the data column values using the expression v_deptno dept.deptno% type: = no; <br /> v_loc dept.loc% type: = \'&amp; loc\'; <br /> update dept set loc = v_loc where deptno = v_deptno; </p><p> 2.4 update using subquery column value v_ename emp.ename% type: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> update emp set (sal, comm) = (select sal, comm from emp where ename = v_ename) where job = (select job from emp where ename = v_ename) </p><p> 2.5 delete data delete data using variables v_deptno dept.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> delete from dept where deptno = v_deptno; <br /><br /> 2.6 delete data using subqueries v_ename emp.ename% type: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> delete from emp where deptno = (select deptno from emp where ename = v_ename); </p><p><br /> 3.SQL cursor cursor is a pointer pointing to the context area, including the implicit cursor (SQL cursor) and two types of explicit cursor SQL cursor used to process SELECT INTO, INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE statements. <br /> Explicit cursor to handle multiple lines of SQL cursor SELECT statement includes: SQL% FOUND, SQL% NOTFOUND, SQL% ROWCOUNT, SQL% ISOPEN other four properties <br /> 3.1 SQL% ISOPEN: execution, will implicitly open and close the cursor. So the value of the property is always FALSE <br /><br /> 3.2 SQL% FOUND: used to determine the successful implementation of SQL statements. When SQL have a role in rows, for TRUE, FALSE otherwise <br /> v_deptno emp.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> update emp set sal = sal * 1.1 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> if sql% found then dbms_output.put_line (\'the implementation of successful\'); else dbms_output.putline (\'failed\'); endif <br /><br /> 3.3 sql% notfound: SQL statement is executed to determine the success of a role when the SQL rows to false, otherwise true <br /><br /> 3.4 sql% rowcount: returns the SQL statement, the total effect of the number of rows v_deptno emp.deptno% type: = &amp;no; <br /> update emp set sal = sal * 1.1 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> dbms_output.put_line (\'modify\' | | sql% rowcount | | \'rows\'); </p><p><br /> 4. Transaction control statements, including transaction control statements COMMIT, ROLLBACK, and SAVEPOINT three kinds of statements <br /> v_sal emp.sal% type: = &amp;salary; <br /> v_ename emp.ename% type: = \'&amp; name\'; <br /> update emp set sal = v_sal where ename = v_ename; <br /> commit; <br /> exception <br /> when others then <br /> rollback; </p><p> insert into temp values (1); <br /> savepoint a1; <br /> insert into temp values (2); <br /> savepoint a2; <br /> insert into temp values (3); <br /> savepoint a3; <br /> rollback to a2; <br /> commit; </p><p><br /> 5. Control structures conditional branch statement <br /> 5.1 Simple conditional v_sal number (6,2); <br /> select sal into v_sal from emp where lower (ename) = lowe (\'&amp; &amp; name\'); <br /> if v_sal &lt;2000 then update emp set sal = v_sal +200 where lower (ename) = lower (\'&amp; name\') <br /> end if </p><p> 5.2 The double conditional branch v_comm number (6,2); <br /> select comm into v_comm from emp where empno = &amp; &amp;no; <br /> if v_comm &lt;&gt; 0 then update emp set comm = v_comm +100 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> else update emp set comm = 200 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> end if </p><p> 5.3 Multiple conditional branch v_job varchar2 (10); <br /> v_sal number (6,2); <br /> select job, sal into v_job, v_sal from emp where empno = &amp; &amp;no; <br /> if v_job = \'president\' then update emp set sal = v_sal +1000 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> elseif v_job = \'manager\' then update emp set sal = v_sal +500 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> else update emp set sal = v_sal +200 where empno = &amp;no; <br /> end if; </p><p><br /> 5.4 CASE statement: <br /> CASE statement in a single selector for comparing equivalent declare <br /> v_deptno emp deptno% type; <br /> begin <br /> v_deptno: = &amp;no; <br /> case v_deptno <br /> when 10 then update emp set comm = 100 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> when 20 then update emp set comm = 80 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /> when 30 then update emp set comm = 50 where deptno = v_deptno; <br /&gt; else <br /> dbms_output.put_line (&quot;does not exist \'); <br /> end case; <br /> end; </p><p> 5.5 In the CASE statement uses a variety of conditions are declare <br /> v_sal emp.sal% type; <br /> v_ename emp.ename% type; <br /> begin <br /> select ename, sal into v_ename, v_sal from emp where empno = &amp;no; <br /> case <br /> when v_sal &lt;1000 then update emp set comm = 100 where ename = v_ename; <br /> when v_sal &lt;2000 then update emp set comm = 80 where ename = v_ename; <br /> when v_sal &lt;6000 tehn update emp set comm = 50 where ename = v_ename; <br /> end case; <br /> end; </p><p><br /> 5.6 basic cycle loop, WHILE loop, FOR loop <br /> Basic cycle: Be sure to include EXIT statement, the definition of loop control variable create table temp (cola int); <br /> declare <br /> i int: = 1; <br /> begin <br /> loop <br /> insert into temp values (i); <br /> exit when i = 10; <br /> i: = i +1; <br /> end loop; <br /> end; </p><p> 5.7 WHILE loop: the definition of loop control variable, and changes in the body of the loop declare the loop control variable <br /> i int: = 1; <br /> begin <br /> while i &lt;= 10 loop <br /> insert into temp values (i); <br /> i: = i +1; <br /> end loop; <br /> end; </p><p> 5.8 for loop: Using FOR loop, ORACLE implicitly define the loop control variable. <br /> for counter in [reverse] <br /> lower_bound .. upper_bound loop <br /> statement1; <br /> statement2; <br /> ....... <br /> end loop; <br /> 5.9 counter is a loop control variable, and the variable is implicitly defined by the ORACLE, not explicitly defined; lower_bound and upper_bound loop control variable corresponding to the value of upper and lower bounds. By default, FOR loop will automatically increase each time a designated REVERSE option, each loop control variable will begin by a <br /> for i in reverse 1 .. 10 loop <br /> insert into temp values (i); <br /> end loop; <br /> end; </p><p><br /> 5.10 nested loops and labels: The label used in the nested loop, you can distinguish the inner loop and outer loop and inner loop can exit the outer loop declare <br /> result int; <br /> begin <br /> &lt;&lt;outer&gt;&gt; <br /> for i in 1 .. 100 loop <br /> &lt;&lt;inter&gt;&gt; <br /> for j in 1 .. 100 loop <br /> result: = i * j; <br /> exit outer when result = 1000; <br /> exit when result = 500; <br /> end loop inner; <br /> dbms_ouput.put_line (result); <br /> end loop outer; <br /> dbms_output.put_line (result); <br /> end; </p><p><br /> 6. Sequence control statements PL / SQL not only provides a conditional branch statements and loop control statements, but also provides a sequence of control statements GOTO and NULL. Generally do not use <br /> 6.1 GOTO: jump to a specific label for the Department to enforce the statement. <br /> GOTO LABEL_NAME; <br /><br /> declare <br /> i int: = 1; <br /> begin <br /> loop <br /> insert into temp values (i); <br /> if i = 10 then <br /> goto end_loop <br /> end if; <br /> i: = i +1; <br /> end loop; <br /> &lt;&lt;end_loop&gt;&gt; <br /> dbms_output.put_line (\'end of the loop\'); <br /> end; </p><p><br /> 6.2 null: will not do anything, and will directly transfer control to the next statement. <br /> declare <br /> v_sal emp.sal% type; <br /> v_ename emp.ename% type; <br /> begin <br /> select ename, sal into v_ename, v_sal from emp where empno = &amp;no; <br /> if v_sal &lt;3000 then update emp set comm = sal * 0.1 where ename = v_ename; <br /> else <br /> null; <br /> end if; <br /> end; </p><p> Continued </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' PL / SQL block can only be directly embedded SELECT, DML (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE), and transaction control statements (COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT), but not directly embedded DDL statements (CREATE, ALTER, DROP) and DCL statements (GRANT, REVOKE)  1. Retrieve a single row of data  1.1 use a scalar...'),(105,'Mysql','Database','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0520/105.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' (Editor: South African...','_Editor_South_African','2010-05-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' (Editor: South African Ant)...'),(106,'Oracle','Database','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0521/112.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Since the oracle is not...','_Since_the_oracle_is_not','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Since the oracle is not added, this configuration, you must manually write a method or sequence or with a trigger </p><p> Or a sequence of easy to use (personal habits) </p><div class=\"dp-highlighter\"><ol class=\"dp-j\"><li> <span>create sequence salary_seq</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>increment by</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> <span>--- plus a few each</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>start with</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> <span>- start counting from</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>nonmaxvalue - do not set the maximum</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>nocycle - has been incremental, not cycle</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>cache</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">10</span></font> <span>- a buffer</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>eg create sequence salary_seq</span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>minvalue</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">100</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>maxvalue</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">9999999999</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>start with</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">560</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>increment by</span> <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">1</span></font> <span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>cache <font color=\"#c00000\"><span class=\"number\">20;</span></font></span> </li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li><span>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span></li><li> <span>using: insert into tableName value <font color=\"#0000ff\"><span class=\"string\">(salary_seq.nextval,\'\',\'\');</span></font></span> </li></ol></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Since the oracle is not added, this configuration, you must manually write a method or sequence or with a trigger  Or a sequence of easy to use (personal habits) create sequence salary_seqÃ‚Â Ã‚Â increment by 1 --- plus a few eachÃ‚Â Ã‚Â start with 1 - start counting from 1Ã‚Â Ã‚Â nonmaxvalue - do not set the...'),(107,'Oracle','Database','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0521/111.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Primary key:  1. The primary...','_Primary_key__1_The_primary','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Primary key: <br /> 1. The primary key constraint: a table can have only one primary key constraint. Primary key can be a single field, there can be multiple fields. In either case, all of its fields are NOT NULL. <br /> 2.Unique constraint: A table can have multiple Unique constraint, Unique field can be NULL. <br /> 3. The primary key and Unique: The difference is a table can have only one primary key constraint, but can have multiple Unique Constraints; all primary key fields are not null, unique can be </p><p> null; the same point is guaranteed unique. <br /> 4. The primary key, Unique and Index: Unique constraints and primary key constraint will be indexed by default. Unique primary key and when there are multiple fields, there is an index prefix problem, that is, where language </p><p> Conditions of the sentence must have a primary key or unique in the first field, it would not use the index. <br /> 5. Foreign key and primary key, Unique: foreign key to one table to another (the parent table) the primary key or unique index. If you want to add a record, while the parent table is not the error. Conversely, if </p><p> If you want to delete the parent records in the table, and the child table has records, will be an error. However, if the foreign key constraint is created, if you use on delete cascade, then delete the parent table data </p><p> Does not directly handle error data associated with the table removed. <br /> If you want to delete the parent table, you need to add cascade constraints, then the child table\'s foreign key is removed, the table records remain unchanged. <br /> Foreign key: </p><p> Foreign key is the table is another table join between the foreign key field must be the primary key in another table is the use of foreign keys to ensure data integrity. It usually includes the following: <br /> Physical integrity, to ensure that each entity is unique (by primary key to the implementation). </p><p> Set the primary key oracle There are 2 ways: <br /> One is to set the primary key from the growth, and the other is to generate unique sequence; <br /> 1. Since the growth of the primary key </p><p> SQL&gt; create table Prim_key_Increase_Test ( <br /> 2 id number (10) primary key, <br /> 3 name varchar2 (30) <br /> 4); </p><p> Table has been created. </p><p> SQL&gt; create sequence Prim_key_Incre_Sequence <br /> 2 minvalue 1 <br /> 3 nomaxvalue <br /> 4 start with 1 <br /> 5 increase by 1 <br /> 6 nocycle <br /> 7 nocache; <br /> increase by 1 <br /> * <br /> Error Line 5: <br /> ORA-00933: SQL command not properly ended </p><p><br /> SQL&gt; 5 <br /> 5 * increase by 1 <br /> SQL&gt; c / increase / increment / <br /> 5 * increment by 1 <br /> SQL&gt; r <br /> 1 create sequence Prim_key_Incre_Sequence <br /> 2 minvalue 1 <br /> 3 nomaxvalue <br /> 4 start with 1 <br /> 5 increment by 1 <br /> 6 nocycle <br /> 7 * nocache </p><p> Sequence has been created. </p><p> SQL&gt; create trigger Prim_key_trigger before <br /> 2 insert on Prim_key_Increase_Test for each row <br /> 3 begin <br /> 4 select Prim_key_Incre_Sequence.nextval into: New.id from dual; <br /> 5 end; <br /> 6 / </p><p> Trigger has been created </p><p> SQL&gt; commit; </p><p> Submit completed. </p><p> SQL&gt; insert into Prim_key_Increase_Test (id) values (\'181 \'); </p><p> 1 row created. </p><p> SQL&gt; select * from Prim_key_Increase_Test; </p><p> ID NAME <br /> ---------- ------------------------------ <br /> 1 </p><p> SQL&gt; insert into Prim_key_Increase_Test (id) values (\'181 \'); </p><p> 1 row created. </p><p> SQL&gt; insert into Prim_key_Increase_Test (id) values (\'181 \'); </p><p> 1 row created. </p><p> SQL&gt; select * from Prim_key_Increase_Test; </p><p> ID NAME <br /> ---------- ------------------------------ <br /> 1 <br /> 2 <br /> 3 </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Primary key:  1. The primary key constraint: a table can have only one primary key constraint. Primary key can be a single field, there can be multiple fields. In either case, all of its fields are NOT NULL.  2.Unique constraint: A table can have multiple Unique constraint, Unique field can be...'),(108,'Mysql','Database','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0521/110.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' First, you have a table! ...','_First_you_have_a_table_','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> First, you have a table! <br /> CREATE TABLE example ( <br /> ID Number (4) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY, <br /> NAME VARCHAR (25), <br /> PHONE VARCHAR (10), <br /> ADDRESS VARCHAR (50)); <br /> If you build the table for the above statement is also in doubt, we recommend that you do not continue it! Has those times you do not like to see Jin Qiong Yao read! <br /> Then, you need a custom sequence <br /> CREATE SEQUENCE emp_sequence <br /> INCREMENT BY 1 - plus a few each <br /> START WITH 1 - start counting from 1 <br /> NOMAXVALUE - do not set the maximum <br /> NOCYCLE - has been incremental, not cycle <br /> NOCACHE - do not build a buffer to complete the above code sequence (sequence) of the building process, the name emp_sequence, the range is from 1 to infinity (infinite extent is determined by your machine), nocycle the decision not to cycle If you set the maximum you can use the cycle to the largest circulation, would seq. For nocache By the way if you give a cache value of the system will automatically read the value of your cache size of a seq <br /> This will speed up the repeated operation speed, but if circumstances such as when an accident or the oracle of the dead machine, then the next value will be removed and the last seq incoherent. (It does not matter if even suggested incoherent cache, Because time is money it! beside the point!) <br /> Connected to the text book, you have only a table and the sequence is not enough, you also need a trigger to execute it! Code: <br /> CREATE TRIGGER &quot;trigger name&quot; BEFORE <br /> INSERT ON example FOR EACH ROW WHEN (new.id is null) <br /> begin <br /> select emp_sequence.nextval into: new.id from dual; <br /> end; <br /> Once on shore, call it a day! Here you try to insert data into it! <br /> INSERT INTO example (Name, phone, address) Values (\'\'Cao\'\',\'\' 56498543\'\',\'\' Heibei\'\'); <br /></p><p> ================================================== =========== <br /> ORACLE SEQUENCE brief introduction (from the growth of field) - - </p><p> In the oracle in the serial number sequence is called each time when it will be automatically taken to increase, generally required by the serial number used in the sort of place. <br /> 1, CreateSequence <br /> You must first have CREATESEQUENCE or CREATEANYSEQUENCE permissions <br /> CREATESEQUENCEemp_sequence <br /> INCREMENTBY1 - plus a few each <br /> STARTWITH1 - start counting from 1 <br /> NOMAXVALUE - do not set the maximum <br /> NOCYCLE - has been incremental, not cycle <br /> CACHE10; </p><p> Once you have defined emp_sequence, you can use CURRVAL, NEXTVAL <br /> CURRVAL = returns the current value of sequence <br /> NEXTVAL = the value added sequence, and then return sequence values such as: <br /> emp_sequence.CURRVAL <br /> emp_sequence.NEXTVAL </p><p> Can use the sequence of places: <br /> - Does not contain a sub-query, snapshot, VIEW of the SELECT statement <br /> -INSERT statement in a subquery <br /> -NSERT statement in the VALUES <br /> -UPDATE\'s SET in </p><p> Can see the following example: <br /> INSERTINTOempVALUES <br /> (Empseq.nextval,\'\'LEWIS\'\',\'\' CLERK\'\', 7902, SYSDATE, 1200, NULL, 20); </p><p> SELECTempseq.currvalFROMDUAL; </p><p> However, to note are: <br /> - The first returns the initial value NEXTVAL; subsequent NEXTVAL will automatically increase your INCREMENTBY defined value, then return to the increased value. SEQUENCE CURRVAL always returns the current value, but only after the first use initialization NEXTVAL CURRVAL, otherwise it will go wrong. NEXTVAL will increase once the value of a SEQUENCE, so if you are in the same statement, which use multiple NEXTVAL, its value is not the same. Understand? </p><p> - If you specify CACHE value, ORACLE memory which can be placed in a number of pre-sequence, so that faster access. After the cache inside the access, oracle and then take a group to automatically cache. No use of cache may jump, such as abnormal down suddenly off the database (shutdownabort), cache in the sequence will be lost. Therefore, when used in the createsequence nocache to prevent this situation. </p><p> 2, AlterSequence <br /> Is the sequence you or the owner, or have ALTERANYSEQUENCE permission to change sequence. You can start to alter than all the other sequence parameters. If you want to change the start value, you must dropsequence then re-create. <br /> Altersequence example <br /> ALTERSEQUENCEemp_sequence <br /> INCREMENTBY10 <br /> MAXVALUE10000 <br /> CYCLE - to 10,000 from scratch after <br /> NOCACHE; </p><p><br /> Sequence of the initialization parameters: <br /> SEQUENCE_CACHE_ENTRIES = cache settings can also be the sequence number. </p><p> Can be very simple DropSequence <br /> DROPSEQUENCEorder_seq; </p><p><br /> All right, here. </p><p><br /> -------------------------------------------------- ----------- <br /> Since the growth and triggers: </p><p> How to implement Oracle features like automatic increase ID? <br /> Finishing editor: ChinaASP </p><p> We often used in the design of the database when the ID is automatically assigned a system as our primary key, but there is no such ORACLE </p><p> Function, we can take the following functions automatically increase the ID of the function <br /> 1. First, create a sequence <br /> createsequenceseqmaxincrementby1 <br /> 2. Use <br /> selectseqmax.nextvalIDfromdual <br /> To get a ID <br /> If this statement is on the trigger, you can achieve the automatic increase in ID and mssql the same functionality! </p><p><br /> -------------------------------------------------- ----------------------- </p><p> Create table # # # # # # </p><p> CREATETABLE &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP&quot; (&quot;ID&quot; NUMBERNOTNULL, &quot;TYPE&quot; <br /> NUMBER (3) NOTNULL, &quot;BODY&quot; VARCHAR2 (100) NOTNULL, &quot;HITS&quot; NUMBER ( <br /> 10) DEFAULT0NOTNULL, PRIMARYKEY (&quot;ID&quot;)) <br /> TABLESPACE &quot;TS_SPORTS&quot; </p><p> Construction sequence # # # # # # </p><p> CREATESEQUENCE &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;SPORTS_LINEUP_ID_SEQ&quot; INCREMENTBY1 <br /> STARTWITH1MAXVALUE1.0E28MINVALUE1NOCYCLE <br /> CACHE50NOORDER </p><p> # # # Build triggers automatic update # # # </p><p> CREATEORREPLACETRIGGER &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;SPORTS_LINEUP_ID_TRIGGER&quot; <br /> BEFOREINSERT <br /> ON &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP&quot; <br /> FOREACHROW <br /> DECLARE <br /> next_idNUMBER; <br /> BEGIN <br /> - Getthenextidnumberfromthesequence <br /> SELECTsports_lineup_id_seq.NEXTVAL <br /> INTOnext_id <br /> FROMdual; </p><p> - Usethesequencenumberastheprimarykey <br /> - Fortherecordbeinginserted. <br /> : New.id: = next_id; <br /> END; </p><p> # # # Build protection PRIMARYKEY trigger # # # </p><p> CREATEORREPLACETRIGGER &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP_ID_UPDATE_TRIGGER&quot; <br /> BEFOREUPDATEOF &quot;ID&quot; ON &quot;SPORTS&quot;. &quot;LINEUP&quot; <br /> FOREACHROW <br /> BEGIN <br /> RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR (-20000, <br /> \'\'Sports_lineup_id_update_trigger: UpdatesoftheIDfield\'\' <br /> | |\'\'Arenotallowed .\'\'); <br /> END; </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table&gt;',' First, you have a table!  CREATE TABLE example (  ID Number (4) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,  NAME VARCHAR (25),  PHONE VARCHAR (10),  ADDRESS VARCHAR (50));  If you build the table for the above statement is also in doubt, we recommend that you do not continue it! Has those times you do not like to see...'),(109,'Mysql','Database','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0521/108.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Growth of the primary key automatically in Mysql, SqlServer','Growth_of_the_primary_key_automatically_in_Mysql_SqlServer','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> 1, the automatic growth of the primary key identifier type is defined as </p><p> <font color=\"#333399\">In mysql, if the table is set to <font color=\"#ff0000\">auto_increment</font> primary key type, the database will automatically assign the primary key.</font> For example: </p><p> create table customers (id int auto_increment primary key not null, name varchar (15)); </p><p> insert into customers (name) values (&quot;name1 &quot;),(&quot; name2&quot;); </p><p> select id from customers; </p><p> Sql statement to be created over the customers table, then insert two records in the inserted field, just set the value name. Finally, the field id lookup table, the query results: </p><p> id </p><p> 1 </p><p> 2 </p><p> Thus, once the type of id is set to auto_increment, mysql database by increments automatically assign the primary key. </p><p> <font color=\"#333399\">In the MS SQLServer, if the table\'s primary key is set to <font color=\"#ff0000\">identity</font> the type, the database will automatically assign the primary key.</font> For example: </p><p> create table customers (id int identity (1,1) primary key not null, name varchar (15)); </p><p> insert into customers (name) values (&quot;name1 &quot;),(&quot; name2&quot;); </p><p> select id from customers; </p><p> Mysql query results and the same. Thus, if the id is set to identity the type, MS SQLServer database automatically by increments as the primary key assignment. identity contains two parameters, the first argument that the initial value, said second parameter increments. </p><p> 2, obtained from the automatic growth of the sequence identifier </p><p> <font color=\"#333399\">In Oracle, for the primary key of each table to create a separate sequence, and then get automatic increases in the sequence identifier, assign it to the primary key.</font> For example, what statement creates a named customer_id_seq sequence, the sequence of the starting value is 1, in increments of 2. </p><p> create sequence customer_id_seq increment by 2 start with 1 </p><p> Once you have defined customer_id_seq sequence, you can access the sequence curval and nextval properties. </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\">curval: Returns the current value of sequence</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\">nextval: first increase the value of the sequence, and then return the sequence value</font> </p><p> The following sql statement, first create the customers table, then insert two records in the insertion set the value of id and name fields, in which the value of the id field from the customer_id_seq sequence. Last queries customers table id field. </p><p> create table customers (id int primary key not null, name varchar (15)); </p><p> insert into customers values (customer_id_seq.curval, &quot;name1&quot;), (customer_id_seq.nextval, &quot;name2&quot;); </p><p> select id from customers; </p><p> If the oracle in the implementation of the above statement, the query results: </p><p> id </p><p> 1 </p><p> 3 </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' 1, the automatic growth of the primary key identifier type is defined as In mysql, if the table is set to auto_increment primary key type, the database will automatically assign the primary key. For example:  create table customers (id int auto_increment primary key not null, name varchar (15)); ...'),(110,'Oracle','Database','en','/a/db/oracle/2010/0422/21.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Alibaba DBA interview questions, Cece from','Alibaba_DBA_interview_questions_Cece_from','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> A: SQL tuning category </p><p> 1: The table lists some connection </p><p> 2: without the help of third-party tools, how to view sql of the implementation plan </p><p> 3: How to use the CBO, CBO and the difference RULE </p><p> 4: how to locate the important (and consume more resources) of the SQL </p><p> 5: How to track a session of the SQL </p><p> 6: SQL adjust what is most concerned about </p><p> 7: Tell me about your understanding of the index (index of the structure, dml impact on the query of why improve query performance) </p><p> 8: Use the index lookup will be able to improve query performance? Why </p><p> 9: What is bind variables? What are the advantages and disadvantages bind variables? </p><p> 10: How stable (fixed) implementation plan </p><p> 11: and the sort of memory-related, respectively, in 8i and 9i how to adjust, temporary table space What is the role </p><p> 12: there is Table T (a, b, c, d), sorted according to the field c to take the first 21-30 records show, please give sql </p><p> II: basic concepts of database classes </p><p> 1: pctused and pctfree What is the meaning of what that role </p><p> 2: a brief description of table / segment / extent / block the relationship between </p><p> 3: Describe the relationship between the tablespace and datafile </p><p> 4: locally managed tablespaces and dictionary managed tablespaces feature, ASSM What are the characteristics </p><p>