> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' This article discusses the parameters involved are:  log_archive_dest  log_archive_dest_n  log_archive_start  db_recovery_file_dest  Oracle version:  SQL> select * from v $ version;  BANNER  -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------  Oracle Database 10g...'),(118,'Mysql','Database','en','/a/db/mysql/2010/0521/109.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Hibernate does not use a long...','Hibernate_does_not_use_a_long','2010-05-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span>Hibernate</span> does not use a long time and I wanted to do a little hands-on example of <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/\">the database</a></u> using <span>Oracle. Oracle</span> intends to use the sequence as the primary key, but do not know how to use <span>Hibernate</span> associated together. Ask colleagues, was told to use a query such as <span>select</span> statement <span>&quot;select</span></span> <span>sequence.nextval from <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">dual&quot;,</span></span> </p><p> <span><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">As follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span>1,</span> first create a <span>sequence</span> in <span>oracle <br /></span></span> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">2. <span>Hbm.xml</span> in the configuration of your <span><br /></span> This data, when re-inserted, <span>Hibernate</span> automatically returns the following statement: <span><br /></span></span> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </span> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Automatically generate the next sequence value, then insert an object into the table. <br /> Solutions to this problem was! <br /> <span><br /> <span style=\"color: black; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-k