rvers in the...','_I_have_two_servers_in_the','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> I have two servers in the dmesg in the following <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">errors</a></u> , ask why? </p><p> os: rhel4.4 </p><p><br /> Server Model: hp dl380 g4, g5 </p><p><br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> hw_random hardware driver 1.0.0 loaded <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: \\ _SB_.PCI0 evaluate _BBN fail = 0x5 <br /> shpchp: acpi_shpchprm: get_device PCI ROOT HID fail = 0x5 </p><p> Resolution: </p><p> Startup option to add parameters: <br /> Modify / boot / grub / menu.lst file, the line started the final with the core kernel <br /> acpi = off noapic or acpi = noapic or acpi = off </p><p><br /> 1) acpi = off against a number of advanced power management features, the application has no effect. <br /> 2) noapic change interrupt, the application would not be affected. </p><p><br /> If your linux system can send and receive data card, optical card can not access the disk array, disk, boot times and then stop errors such as ACPI, you can try the above method, there will be an unexpected effect! </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' I have two servers in the dmesg in 