lobal Area 76619308 bytes <br /> Fixed Size 454188 bytes <br /> Variable Size 50331648 bytes <br /> Database Buffers 25165824 bytes <br /> Redo Buffers 667648 bytes</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database mounted completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">SQL&gt; ALTER DATABASE OPEN; <br /> ALTER DATABASE OPEN <br /> * <br /> ERROR</span> at line</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1:</font> <br /> ORA-01122:</span> database file <span lang=\"EN-US\">2</span> failed verification</font></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-01110:</span> data file</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">2: \'F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS01.DBF\' <br /> ORA-01200: 25600</span> of <span lang=\"EN-US\">26880</span> actual file size is less than the correct size</font></font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Try the following to open the database using <span lang=\"EN-US\">_corrupted_rollback_segments</span> use <span lang=\"EN-US\">_offline_rollback_segments</span> parameters, <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle</span> will attempt to remove the delay block, and for <span lang=\"EN-US\">_corrupted_rollback_segments</span> it, <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle</span> assumes the transaction is rolled back, not to carry out other checks. General loss of or damage <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> table space when you can try to use the implicit parameter:</span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; ALTER DATABASE DATAFILE \'F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS01.DBF\' OFFLINE DROP;</font></span> </p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database has changed.</font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The following initialization parameters to create <span lang=\"EN-US\">PFILE:</span></span></font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SHUTDOWN IMMEDIATE <br /> ORA-01109:</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">database not open</span></font></font> </p><p><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database dismounted.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ORACLE</span> instance shut down.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; CREATE PFILE = \'F: INITTEST.ORA\' FROM SPFILE;</font></span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">File has been created.</font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Manually add the following initialization parameters:</span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">*. Undo_management = \'MANUAL\' <br /> _corrupted_rollback_segments = (_SYSSMU1 $, _SYSSMU2 $, _SYSSMU3 $, _SYSSMU4 $, _SYSSMU5 $, _SYSSMU6 $, _SYSSMU7 $, _SYSSMU8 $, _SYSSMU9 $, _SYSSMU10 $)</font></span> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Community Forums</a></font></strong> <br /><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Can be given in an article on ways to open a database query to get the rollback list <span lang=\"EN-US\">DBA_ROLLBACK_SEGS</span> view.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The database does not start, you can <span lang=\"EN-US\">linux</span> operating system command <span lang=\"EN-US\">strings</span> from the <span lang=\"EN-US\">system</span> tablespace rollback segment data file to obtain information.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Windows</span> environment for <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle,</span> can be data files through <span lang=\"EN-US\">ftp,</span> copied to the <span lang=\"EN-US\">linux</span> system, then execute the command <span lang=\"EN-US\">strings:</span></span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">strings system01.dbf | grep _SYSSMU</font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The following <span lang=\"EN-US\">PFILE</span> using the modified open the database:</span></font> </p><p>S &quot;style =&quot; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt &quot;&gt; SQL&gt; STARTUP PFILE = F: INITTEST.ORA <br /> ORACLE <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">instance started.</span> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Total System Global Area 76619308 bytes <br /> Fixed Size 454188 bytes <br /> Variable Size 50331648 bytes <br /> Database Buffers 25165824 bytes <br /> Redo Buffers 667648 bytes</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Database mounted completed. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span> Database has been opened.</span></font></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The following approach to and described in an article on the relatively similar, and remove rollback segments, then delete the rollback table space and then create a new <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace:</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SELECT SEGMENT_NAME, OWNER, TABLESPACE_NAME, STATUS <br /> 2 FROM DBA_ROLLBACK_SEGS;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SEGMENT_NAME OWNER TABLESPACE_NAME STATUS <br /> --------------- ------ -------------------- --------- ------- <br /> SYSTEM SYS SYSTEM ONLINE <br /> _SYSSMU1 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU2 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU3 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU4 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU5 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU6 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU7 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU8 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU9 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY <br /> _SYSSMU10 $ PUBLIC UNDOTBS1 NEEDS RECOVERY</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">11</span> rows selected.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; DROP ROLLBACK SEGMENT &quot;_SYSSMU1 $&quot;;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Back section has been removed.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; DROP ROLLBACK SEGMENT &quot;_SYSSMU2 $&quot;;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Back section has been removed.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; DROP ROLLBACK SEGMENT &quot;_SYSSMU3 $&quot;;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Back section has been removed.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; DROP ROLLBACK SEGMENT &quot;_SYSSMU4 $&quot;;</span></font> </p>','The topic of the immediately preceding...'),(194,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/20/1356.html','http://www.ixdba.net','UNDO tablespace ORA-1122 error solution (b)','UNDO_tablespace_ORA1122_error_solution_b','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Some time ago to solve an <span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-1122</span> error, just the local database environment because automatic restart <span lang=\"EN-US\">Windows,</span> resulting in the database can not open, error message is <span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-1122.</span></span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The error is <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> table space table space.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Introduced on a method to recover use of Beijing, this attempt to <span lang=\"EN-US\">re-UNDO</span> table space approach.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">UNDO</span> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">tablespace <span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-1122</span> error solution (a): http://www.ixdba.net/article/cb/1355.html <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span></font></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"><font color=\"#007799\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font color=\"#007799\"><br /><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Because there is a database backup, so you can easily restore the database, but rarely get an error situation, try to see if you can back up in the absence of a database on the basis of the recovery:</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Look again at the problem, try to open the database, it will error:</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; CONN / @ TEST AS SYSDBA</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Connected to an idle instance.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">SQL&gt; STARTUP MOUNT <br /> ORACLE</span> instance started.</font></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Total System Global Area 76619308 bytes <br /> Fixed Size 454188 bytes <br /> Variable Size 50331648 bytes <br /> Database Buffers 25165824 bytes <br /> Redo Buffers 667648 bytes</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database mounted completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">SQL&gt; ALTER DATABASE OPEN; <br /> ALTER DATABASE OPEN <br /> * <br /> ERROR</span> at line</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1:</font> <br /> ORA-01122:</span> database file <span lang=\"EN-US\">2</span> failed verification</font></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-01110:</span> data file</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">2: \'F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS01.DBF\' <br /> ORA-01200: 25600</span> of <span lang=\"EN-US\">26880</span> actual file size is less than the correct size</font></font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">If there is no backup, then only alternative way to recover, if a problem occurs the contents of the data file is not the key content, then you can consider using the <span lang=\"EN-US\">ALTER DATABASE DATAFILE OFFLINE</span> way.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Method can refer to a similar case: a <span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-1122</span> error <font color=\"#0000ff\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">solution:</span></font> http://www.ixdba.net/article/05/1353.html</span></font></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">But the problem here is the <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace, <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> table space if there is no data to roll back, then the problem is rather simple, because <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle</span> can replace <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> table space, only directly to the <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace data file <span lang=\"EN-US\">OFFLINE,</span> start the database create a new <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace, and switch to the current <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace.</span></font> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Community Forums</a></font></strong> <br /><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">However, if the <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace to rollback the data recorded, then the recovery will be more complicated.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Try <span lang=\"EN-US\">OFFLINE</span> data file in question:</span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; ALTER DATABASE DATAFILE \'F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS01.DBF\' OFFLINE;</font></span> </p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database has changed.</font></span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; ALTER DATABASE OPEN;</font></span> </p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database has changed.</font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Here the system can create a new <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace, and to achieve change:</span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; CREATE UNDO TABLESPACE UNDOTBS2 DATAFILE \'F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS02.DBF\' SIZE 200M;</font></span> </p><p>= &quot;Verdana&quot; size = &quot;2&quot;&gt; table space has been created. </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SHOW PARAMETER UNDO_TABLESPACE</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">NAME TYPE VALUE <br /> ------------------------------------ ----------- --- --------------------------- <br /> undo_tablespace string UNDOTBS1 <br /> SQL&gt; ALTER SYSTEM SET UNDO_TABLESPACE = UNDOTBS2;</span></font> </p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">System has been changed.</font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Although the database has been launched to complete, <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> table space has also been switched, but the problem does not end, if you try to delete the <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDOTBS1</span> will be error:</font></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; DROP TABLESPACE UNDOTBS1 INCLUDING CONTENTS AND DATAFILES; <br /> DROP TABLESPACE UNDOTBS1 INCLUDING CONTENTS AND DATAFILES <br /> * <br /> ERROR</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">at line</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1:</font> <br /> ORA-01548:</span> active rollback segment has been found <span lang=\"EN-US\">\'_SYSSMU1 $\',</span> stop the removal table space</font></font></span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; SELECT COUNT (*) FROM YANGTK.T; <br /> SELECT COUNT (*) FROM YANGTK.T <br /> * <br /> ERROR</font></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">at line</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1:</font> <br /> ORA-00376:</span> file <span lang=\"EN-US\">2</span> can not be read at this time <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /> ORA-01110:</span> data file <span lang=\"EN-US\">2: \'F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS01.DBF\'</span></font></font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In the query including the need to rollback the table, it will also encounter an error. And no problem for the other tables, you can normally visit:</font></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SELECT COUNT (*) FROM YANGTK.T1;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">COUNT (*) <br /> ---------- <br /> 20</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Now the problem is the previously mentioned, <span lang=\"EN-US\">OFFLINE</span> the <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> tablespace holds the records need to roll back, and these records will not result in the database part of the final restoration is complete, before the affected part of the object is not a normal visit The.</font></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SELECT SEGMENT_NAME, OWNER, TABLESPACE_NAME, STATUS <br /> 2 FROM DBA_ROLLBACK_SEGS;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SEGMENT_NAME OWNER TABLESPACE_NAME STATUS <br /> -------------------- ------ -------------------- ---- ------------</span></font> </p>','Some time ago to solve an ORA-1122 error, just the local database environment because automatic restart Windows, resulting in the database can not open, error message is...'),(195,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/cb/1355.html','http://www.ixdba.net','UNDO tablespace ORA-1122 error solution (a)','UNDO_tablespace_ORA1122_error_solution_a','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div class=\"storytext\"><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Some time ago to solve an <span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-1122</span> error, just the local database environment because automatic restart <span lang=\"EN-US\">Windows,</span> resulting in the database can not open, error message is <span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-1122.</span></span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The error is <span lang=\"EN-US\">UNDO</span> table space table space.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><br /><font size=\"2\"></font></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">First look at the problem, try to open the database, it will error:</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; CONN / @ TEST AS SYSDBA</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Connected to an idle instance.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">SQL&gt; STARTUP MOUNT <br /> ORACLE</span> instance started.</font></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Total System Global Area 76619308 bytes <br /> Fixed Size 454188 bytes <br /> Variable Size 50331648 bytes <br /> Database Buffers 25165824 bytes <br /> Redo Buffers 667648 bytes</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database mounted completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">SQL&gt; ALTER DATABASE OPEN; <br /> ALTER DATABASE OPEN <br /> * <br /> ERROR</span> at line</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1:</font> <br /> ORA-01122:</span> database file <span lang=\"EN-US\">2</span> failed verification</font></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">ORA-01110:</span> data file</font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">2: \'F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS01.DBF\' <br /> ORA-01200: 25600</span> of <span lang=\"EN-US\">26880</span> actual file size is less than the correct size</font></font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Database is in archive mode:</span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; SELECT LOG_MODE FROM V $ DATABASE;</font></span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">LOG_MODE <br /> ------------ <br /> ARCHIVELOG</font></span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The easiest way to solve the problem than the use of backup and archive logs for database recovery. Because it is the unit test database, so there is no set backup strategy, but still in the local database to find a cold backup a year ago, and found that all archived database exists, then use the archive recovery is the most convenient and secure methods.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">First, backup the current environment is still the one hand, in order for a recovery if there is an accident, at least not before the operation can be restored to the state, will not cause the database to further complicate the issue. On the other hand is the site to preserve the error, so after trying to restore the normal method environment can also try other recovery methods.</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Backup completed on-site environment, the database can be restored:</span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; HOST COPY F: ORACLEBACKUPTEST20061110UNDOTBS01.DBF F: ORACLEORADATATESTUNDOTBS01.DBF</font></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; RECOVER TABLESPACE UNDOTBS1 <br /> ORA-00279:</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">change <span lang=\"EN-US\">55747341 (generated</span> at <span lang=\"EN-US\">11/11/2006 22:11:26)</span> is required for thread <span lang=\"EN-US\">1</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Community Forums</a></font></strong> <br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">ORA-00289:</font></span> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">proposed:</font> F: ORACLEORADATATESTARCHIVEARC00306.001 <br /> ORA-00280:</span> change <span lang=\"EN-US\">55747341</span> for thread <span lang=\"EN-US\">1</span> is carried out by sequence <span lang=\"EN-US\"># 306</span></font></font></span> </p><p><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"></span> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Specify <span lang=\"EN-US\">log: {&lt;RET&gt; = suggested | filename | AUTO | CANCEL}</span></font></span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">ORA-00279:</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">change <span lang=\"EN-US\">55773423 (generated</span> at <span lang=\"EN-US\">11/12/2006 08:34:23)</span> is required for thread <span lang=\"EN-US\">1</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">ORA-00289:</font></span> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">proposed:</font> F: ORACLEORADATATESTARCHIVEARC00307.001 <br /> ORA-00280:</span> change <span lang=\"EN-US\">55773423</span> for thread <span lang=\"EN-US\">1</span> is in a sequence <span lang=\"EN-US\">#</span></font></font></span>Conducted 307 <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">ORA-00278:</font></span> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">log file is no longer needed for this recovery <span lang=\"EN-US\">\'F: ORACLEORADATATESTARCHIVEARC00306.001\'</span></font></font> </p><p><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Specify <span lang=\"EN-US\">log: {&lt;RET&gt; = suggested | filename | AUTO | CANCEL}</span></font></font></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">ORA-00279:</span></font> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">change <span lang=\"EN-US\">55793564 (generated</span> at <span lang=\"EN-US\">11/12/2006 23:24:46)</span> is required for thread <span lang=\"EN-US\">1