»\">2</a> * <a href=\"/article/cb/1355$2.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">Next&gt;&gt;</a> </center><br />','Some time ago to solve an ORA-1122 error, just the local database environment because automatic restart Windows, resulting in the database can not open, error message is...'),(196,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/2c/1352.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle 11g backup and recovery enhancements','Oracle_11g_backup_and_recovery_enhancements','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle 11g backup and recovery in a lot of new features, whether it is performance, functionality, security and operational aspects of the different levels of increase.</font> <p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This article describes RMAN delete Archive log validation.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In the previous version 11g, Oracle\'s rman log does not, and other application systems closely integrated, so, rman delete archive log when the log does not judge whether the other system is still useful.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">When rman delete the log, you may find that other systems such as DATA GUARD, STREAMS such as the log is deleted and can not work properly.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Starting from 11g, rman will first judge in the deletion, the log is still needed other systems, when the other needs still need the log, rman will alarm, and will not delete the log.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Look at the situation under 10g:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; conn <a href=\"mailto:sys/test@testrac_standby\">sys / test @ testrac_standby connected as SYSDBA.</a></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; select sequence # from v $ managed_standby where status = \'WAIT_FOR_LOG\';</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SEQUENCE #</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">----------</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">577</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; shutdown immediate</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">ORA-01109: database not open</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database dismounted.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">ORACLE instance shut down.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; exit from the Oracle Database 10g Enterprise Edition Release 10.2.0.3.0 - 64bit Production</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">With the Partitioning, OLAP and Data Mining options off</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">$ Rman target /</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Recovery Manager: Release 10.2.0.3.0 - Production on Thursday September 13 04:14:09 2007</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Copyright (c) 1982, 2005, Oracle. All rights reserved.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Connected to target database: TESTRAC (DBID = 4291216984)</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">RMAN&gt; delete archivelog sequence 577;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Using target database control file instead of recovery catalog allocated channel: ORA_DISK_1 channel ORA_DISK_1: sid = 286 instance = testrac1 devtype = DISK allocated channel: ORA_DISK_2 Channel ORA_DISK_2: sid = 308 instance = testrac2 devtype = DISK</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A copy of the archived log key Thrd Seq S list the name of the time limit</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">------- ---- ------- ------------ ----</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">May 1981 1 577 A 31-8 -07 / data1/archivelog/1_577_626291662.dbf</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Are you sure you want to delete the above objects (enter YES or NO)? no</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In 10g,, rman does not check the logs if other systems are still needed, and in 11g, this problem is resolved:</font> </p><p align=\"center\"><table bgcolor=\"#cccccc\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"1\" width=\"80%\"><tbody><tr><td bgcolor=\"#f2f2f2\"><pre> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">[Oracle @ yangtk ~] $ rman target / <br /> Recovery Manager: Release 11.1.0.6.0 - Production on <br /> Sun Oct 21 09:02:08 2007 <br /> Copyright (c) 1982, 2007, Oracle. All rights reserved. <br /> connected to target database: ORA11G (DBID = 4026820313) <br /> RMAN&gt; delete archivelog all; <br /> using target database control file instead of recovery catalog <br /> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Community Forums</a></font></strong> <br /> allocated channel: ORA_DISK_1 <br /> channel ORA_DISK_1: SID = 128 device type = DISK <br /> RMAN-08137: WARNING: archived log not deleted as it is still needed <br /> archived log file name = / data/oracle/oradata/ora11g/archivelog / <br /> 1_212_630620185.dbf thread = 1 sequence = 212 <br /> RMAN-08137: WARNING: archived log not deleted as it is still needed <br /> archived log file name = / data/oracle/oradata/ora11g/archivelog / <br /> 1_213_630620185.dbf thread = 1 sequence = 213</font> </pre></td></tr></tbody></table></p>','This article describes RMAN delete Archive log...'),(197,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/03/1230.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle database remote replication and disaster recovery of remote','Oracle_database_remote_replication_and_disaster_recovery_of_remote','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Ã‚Â </font><p> <strong><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">1, based on the storage layer replication disaster recovery solution</font></font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Replication of this technology is the storage area network SAN-based replication, replication IO conducted for each copy of the data than the larger; system can achieve synchronous or asynchronous data replication in two ways. Large amount of data the system has great advantages for the (daily log volume in 60G and above), but the host, operating system, database versions and other requirements consistent with, and environmental requirements of the network is relatively high.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Target system does not need a host, as long as storage devices can be, read the target system if necessary, require additional configuration and equipment, more trouble.</font> </p><p> <strong><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">2, disaster recovery replication solutions based on logical volume</font></font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Mechanism of this technology-based TCP / IP network environment to copy, the logical volume by the operating system to capture changes in the process of replication. Characterized by replication-based storage solutions quite similar, synchronous or asynchronous can also choose two ways, the host of software and hardware environment of the consistency requirement is relatively high, a large amount of data on the application of an advantage. If you want to achieve the target system readable, you need to create third-party image. Personally think that this technology and the above-mentioned storage-based replication technology more suitable for large amounts of data in the system, or application system disaster recovery replication.</font> </p><p> <strong><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">3, based on the logic of oracle redo log replication</font></font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The main use of this approach has some third-party software, as well as their own DATAGUARD in oracle logical Standby. At present, foreign countries have had a lot more mature products and success stories, China has a similar product, but in the product on the maturity and success stories there is a gap with the foreign.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The principle of such products is basically the same, its work process can be divided into the following process:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Use a separate process outside the oracle to capture redo log file information will be translated into sql statement, and then transmitted through the network to the target client database, perform the same database on the target side of the sql. If the process can not keep up oracle log switch, you can capture the contents of the archive logs. And some products to services in the source unit, when a transaction is completed, then it is transferred to the target side. All the products are generally copied to the table as a unit, but also supports most of the DDL replication (mainly in oracle9i environment).</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Technical characteristics of this technology and the advantages are the following:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Target has been a client database can access the database; to ensure consistency across the database of the transaction; because the process used to capture other than oracle, and its priority lower than the oracle process, so the performance of the source system database has little effect; Based on the realization principle and the use of multiple queue files, copy the environment can provide network failure, database failure, host failure fault tolerance; because such software to copy only the sql statement or transaction, so he can fully support the replication of heterogeneous environments hardware models, oracle version, operating system type, version and so did not ask.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This approach can also support multiple replication methods, such as data sets, distribution of such copy, or a copy of such multi-layer test.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">As the transmission of the content is redolog or archive log part, so it takes a very small network resources, can achieve remote replication between different cities.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The logic-based replication products redolog have many advantages, but with the other programs mentioned above comparison, there are also some disadvantages:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Throughput of the database is too large, in fact, there will be greater, according to delay the day when the database reached 60G per day or more, this feasibility cross; implementation process may have some down time to data synchronization and configuration of the activation; replication environment, set up after the database structure needs some changes on the operational processes in accordance with the provisions, there are some maintenance costs.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">However, the current rapid development of such products, the above issues, in the latest version of most products have greatly improved.</font> </p>','1, based on the storage layer replication disaster recovery...'),(198,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/4c/2154.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle Flashback operations available','Oracle_Flashback_operations_available','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Starting</span> from <span lang=\"EN-US\">9i, Oracle provides Flashback (FLASHBACK) function. Find the current time is a point in time before the system or the state of the table.</span></span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">The maximum time you can flash back and roll back the space-related. If you use the automatic management of rollback table space, then <span lang=\"EN-US\">flash back to the support given UNDO_RETENTION the minimum time. In other words, FLASHBACK UNDO_RETENTION can support at least the time given, if the system is relatively idle, you can flash back to a longer time. (Of course, if the rollback table space, lack of space allocation, when the system is busy, it may not yet reached UNDO_RETENTION reuse time limit of data space)</span></span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">A prerequisite for using the flash back to the table <span lang=\"EN-US\">DDL operations</span> can not <span lang=\"EN-US\">be. Not only can not flash back DDL operations, but also can not flash back DDL operations before the data.</span></span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Ã‚Â  </font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\"><br /><font size=\"2\"></font></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Oracle provides two ways to support Flashback:</font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">One is to use <span lang=\"EN-US\">DBMS_FLASHBACK package, which is SESSION flashback level. Implementation of the package ENABLE_AT_TIME or ENABLE_AT_SYSTEM_CHANGE_NUMBER DBMS_FLASHBACK process, the current session state in flashback, this time the query returns any ENABLE_AT_TIME specified time or SCN ENABLE_AT_SYSTEM_CHANGE_NUMBER time corresponding to the specified state. When the process of implementation of DISABLE, the system returns to the current state.</span></span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">This method is <span lang=\"EN-US\">SESSION level, since any form of any query are returned the results of a previous point in time. But disadvantage is that flash back to the state, does not support DML statement. If an earlier point in time data recovery current data, you must ENABLE_AT_TIME, open a cursor, and then DIABLE flashback state, and then read data from the cursor and insert into the current table.</span></span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">The second way is to use <span lang=\"EN-US\">AS OF statement, which is statement-level flashback. AS OF TIMESTAMP can be followed, or SCN. Directly behind the table in the query by adding AS OF point in time the way, you can query the data to that moment. This method is intuitive, easy to use in the recovery of individual tables, or on a table provides time-based access.</span></span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Here\'s an example:</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; alter session set nls_date_format = \'yyyy-mm-dd hh24: mi: ss\';</font></span> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IXDBA.NET Technical Community</font></a></font></strong> <br /><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Session has been changed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; create table t (id number, name varchar2 (30));</font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Table has been created.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; insert into t values (1, \'yangtingkun\');</font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">1 row created.</span></font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; commit;</font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </span<html> &gt; </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; select sysdate from dual;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SYSDATE <br /> ------------------- <br /> 2005-01-24 23:21:23</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; commit;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; commit;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; commit;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; commit;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; commit;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; select sysdate from dual;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SYSDATE <br /> ------------------- <br /> 2005-01-24 23:26:05</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; delete t;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Deleted <span lang=\"EN-US\">1 rows.</span></font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; commit;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; commit;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Submit completed.</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; exec dbms_flashback.enable_at_time (to_timestamp (\'2005-1-24 23:26:5 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd hh24: mi: ss\'))</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">PL / SQL procedure successfully completed.</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; select * from t;</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">ID NAME <br /> ---------- ------------------------------ <br /> 1 yangtingkun</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">SQL&gt; exec dbms_flashback.disable</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">PL / SQL procedure successfully completed.</span></font> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p>size = &quot;2&quot;&gt; SQL&gt; select * from t; </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The line is not selected</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"> </font></span></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">SQL&gt; select * from t as of timestamp to_timestamp (\'2005-1-24 23:26:5 \',\' yyyy-mm-dd hh24: mi: ss\');</font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">ID NAME <br /> ---------- ------------------------------ <br /> 1 yangtingkun</font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 24pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-char-indent-size: 12.0pt\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size: 8.5pt\">The above two methods is given by flashback queries. In the above example, I <span lang=\"EN-US\">insert</span> in the implementation of <span lang=\"EN-US\">direct command and delete command interval of 5 minutes or so, and submitted a number of air services. This is due to the time Oracle is mapped to SCN on the map about every 5 minutes followed. Therefore, both operating interval of 5 minutes, and between the SCN to ensure that two operations have changed, so that the correct Oracle timestamp can be mapped to the different SCN.</span></span></font> </p>','Starting from 9i, Oracle provides Flashback (FLASHBACK) function. Find the current time is a point in time before the system or the state of the...'),(199,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/83/985.html','http://www.ixdba.net','SPFILE RMAN backup and recovery of the recovery (c)','SPFILE_RMAN_backup_and_recovery_of_the_recovery_c','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Lack of initialization files, the database is not started. If the initialization parameters through the <span lang=\"EN-US\">RMAN</span> backup, then <span lang=\"EN-US\">RMAN</span> can recover the initialization parameters.</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">SPFILE</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">RMAN</span> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">backup and recovery of the recovery <span lang=\"EN-US\">(a):</span> http://yangtingkun.itpub.net/post/468/300061</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">UNION ALL</span> of the pages on the query execution plan problem <span lang=\"EN-US\">(b):</span> http://yangtingkun.itpub.net/post/468/303523</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">This article describes a simple way <span lang=\"EN-US\">NOCATALOG</span> another recovery method.</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"><br /></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Described above do not exist <span lang=\"EN-US\">autobackup</span> situation, <span lang=\"EN-US\">SPFILE</span> recovery rather complicated issues.</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">If only the <span lang=\"EN-US\">SPFILE</span> is lost, the control file still exists, then there is a recovery method is relatively simple. First of all initialization parameters manually edit a file, specify the database name and control file location. Relative to an article on the <span lang=\"EN-US\">DBID,</span> these information is very easy to get.</span> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">[Oracle @ demo2 oracle] $ vi init.ora</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">db_name = testdata <br /> instance_name = testdata <br /> control_files = \'/ data/oradata/testdata/control01.ctl\' <br /> db_block_size = 8192</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Note that if the value of <span lang=\"EN-US\">DB_BLOCK_SIZE alert</span> file can be found, if the <span lang=\"EN-US\">alert</span> file is missing, you can try many times when the find the following error, shutting down the instance, re-modify the <span lang=\"EN-US\">INIT.ORA</span> file, start again.</span> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">RMAN&gt; startup mount pfile = / home / oracle / init.ora</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Oracle instance started <br /> RMAN-00571: ============================================== ============= <br /> RMAN-00569: =============== ERROR MESSAGE STACK FOLLOWS =============== <br /> RMAN-00571: =========