ted channel: ORA_DISK_1 <br /> channel ORA_DISK_1: sid = 9 devtype = DISK <br /> allocated channel: ORA_DISK_2 <br /> channel ORA_DISK_2: sid = 10 devtype = DISK <br /> Channel <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/a9/919.html\">ORA_DISK_1:</a> starting datafile backupset Restore <br /> Channel <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/a9/919.html\">ORA_DISK_1:</a> Restoring SPFILE <br /> output filename = / opt/ora9/product/9.2/dbs/spfiletestdata.ora <br /> Channel <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/a9/919.html\">ORA_DISK_1:</a> restored Backup piece 1 <br /> piece handle = / data1/backup/testdata/4jim5c2n_1_1 tag = TAG20070706T130423 params = NULL <br /> channel ORA_DISK_1: restore complete <br /> Finished restore at 06-7</font></span> </p>','Lack of initialization files, the database is not started. If the initialization parameters through the RMAN backup, then RMAN can recover the initialization...'),(200,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/22/984.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle Tip of the highest priority? - A detailed record of dealing with bad blocks','Oracle_Tip_of_the_highest_priority__A_detailed_record_of_dealing_with_bad_blocks','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">All documents referring to <span lang=\"EN-US\">ORACLE HINT,</span> he will point out, <span lang=\"EN-US\">HINT</span> highest priority. But today they found an unexpected situation.</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"><br /></p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Developer testing library today reported an error:</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">ORA-01578: ORACLE data block corrupted (file # 39, block # 24961)</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">ORA-01110: data file 39: \'/ oracle/oradata/test/ndmain09.dbf\'</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">As a test database, so do not do hot backup. Test data in the database itself is not very important, a <span lang=\"EN-US\">BLOCK</span> of data loss is acceptable. So I plan to discard the bad blocks directly to the data.</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Since there is no need to try to fix the data, no need to use <span lang=\"EN-US\">DBMS_REPAIR</span> package, using three methods to set the export <span lang=\"EN-US\">EVENT</span> relatively trouble, intends to use the most simple way <span lang=\"EN-US\">ROWID</span> around bad blocks to rebuild the table.</span> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">First, find the table in question:</span> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SELECT SEGMENT_TYPE, OWNER, SEGMENT_NAME FROM DBA_EXTENTS <br /> 2 WHERE FILE_ID = 39 <br /> 3 AND 24961 BETWEEN BLOCK_ID AND BLOCK_ID BLOCKS -1 <br /> 4;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SEGMENT_TYPE OWNER SEGMENT_NAME <br /> ------------------ ------------------------------ - ---------------------------- <br /> TABLE DATA CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The following tectonic blocks <span lang=\"EN-US\">ROWID:</span></span> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; CONN DATA <br /> Enter password: <br /> Connected. <br /> SQL&gt; SELECT DATA_OBJECT_ID FROM USER_OBJECTS WHERE OBJECT_NAME = \'CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT\';</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">DATA_OBJECT_ID <br /> -------------- <br /> 54649</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SELECT DBMS_ROWID.ROWID_CREATE (1, 54649, 39, 24961, 0) FROM DUAL;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">DBMS_ROWID.ROWID_C <br /> ------------------ <br /> AAANV5AAnAAAGGBAAA</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">We have found the <span lang=\"EN-US\">ROWID</span> of the bad block, following addition to the <span lang=\"EN-US\">BLOCK</span> than just to read out the data on it:</span> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; CREATE TABLE CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT_BAK AS <br /> 2 SELECT / * ROWID (CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT) * / * FROM CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT <br /> 3 WHERE ROWID &lt;CHARTOROWID (\'AAANV5AAnAAAGGBAAA\') <br /> 4 OR ROWID&gt; = CHARTOROWID (\'AAANV5AAnAAAGGCAAA\') <br /> 5; <br /> CREATE TABLE CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT_BAK AS <br /> * <br /> ERROR at line 1: <br /> ORA-01578: ORACLE data block corrupted (file # 39, block # 24961) <br /> ORA-01110: data file 39: \'/ oracle/oradata/test/ndmain09.dbf\'</span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 21pt\"> <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Strange, obviously has been told by prompting <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle</span> to skip bad blocks, and how has reported this error? Implementation plan to see it:</span> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; EXPLAIN PLAN FOR <br /> 2 SELECT / * ROWID (CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT) * / * FROM CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT <br /> 3 WHERE ROWID &lt;CHARTOROWID (\'AAANV5AAnAAAGGBAAA\') <br /> 4 OR ROWID&gt; = CHARTOROWID (\'AAANV5AAnAAAGGCAAA\') <br /> 5;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Explained.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SELECT * FROM TABLE (DBMS_XPLAN.DISPLAY ());</span></font> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Community Forums</a></font></strong> <br /><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">PLAN_TABLE_OUTPUT <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">-------------------------------------------------- ------------------------ <br /> | Id | Operation | Name | Rows | Bytes | Cost | <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------ <br /> | 0 | SELECT STATEMENT | | 164K | 1175M | 1985 | <br /> | 1 | TABLE ACCESS FULL | CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT | 164K | 1175M | 1985 | <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Note: cpu costing is off, PLAN_TABLE \'is old version</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">9 rows selected.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; ALTER SESSION SET OPTIMIZER_MODE = FIRST_ROWS;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Session a</span></font>ltered. </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; EXPLAIN PLAN FOR <br /> 2 SELECT / * ROWID (CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT) * / * FROM CAT_ZONE_PRODUCT <br /> 3 WHERE ROWID &lt;CHARTOROWID (\'AAANV5AAnAAAGGBAAA\') <br /> 4 OR ROWID&gt; = CHARTOROWID (\'AAANV5AAnAAAGGCAAA\') <br /> 5;</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">Explained.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">SQL&gt; SELECT * FROM TABLE (DBMS_XPLAN.DISPLAY ());</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt\">PLAN_TABLE_OUTPUT <br /> ------------------------------------