><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This is the end of the video, then there are Oracle 9i DBA fundamentals of exercise to explain the two parts 1,2, welcomed the attention ixdba.net!</font> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font size=\"6\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><strong>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â </strong> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/ixdba037\"><strong>Online Play</strong></a> <strong>Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </strong> <a href=\"http://blog.ixdba.net/ixdba/1z0_031_18.zip\"><strong>Download</strong></a></font></font> </p>','This course is a classic official standard Oracle DBA training tutorial, each and every door is about to enter Oracle DBA students exposure to the first course. During the courses, you will learn the basics of Oracle architecture, including the Oracle Instance and the basic management concepts, how...'),(210,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/68/1165.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Resize datafile one case led to ASM Crash','Resize_datafile_one_case_led_to_ASM_Crash','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Yesterday, while maintaining an Oracle 10.1.0.3.0 database, the ASM instance led to Crash, a database switch.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This is an early opening of the Oracle10g database, has been running very stable, very low failure rate. <br /> View the log and found the following error message: <br /></font> </p><blockquote> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Wed Aug 29 12:05:24 2007 <br /> <strong>alter database datafile \'+ DATADG/mmsdb/datafile/gateway.295.1\' resize 12000M</strong> <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:05:25 2007 <br /> Completed: alter database datafile \'+ DATADG / mmsdb / datafile / ga <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:10:14 2007 <br /> create tablespace dodd datafile size 100M <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:10:15 2007 <br /> Starting control autobackup <br /> Created Oracle managed file / msflsh/MMSDB/autobackup/2007_08_29/o1_mf_n_631887015_3f9wf82j_.bkp <br /> Control autobackup written to DISK device <br /> handle \'/ msflsh/MMSDB/autobackup/2007_08_29/o1_mf_n_631887015_3f9wf82j_.bkp\' <br /> Completed: create tablespace dodd datafile size 100M <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:11:24 2007 <br /> drop tablespace dodd <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:11:25 2007 <br /> Deleted Oracle managed file + DATADG/mmsdb/datafile/dodd.313.5 <br /> Starting control autobackup <br /> Created Oracle managed file / msflsh/MMSDB/autobackup/2007_08_29/o1_mf_n_631887085_3f9whfv1_.bkp <br /> Control autobackup written to DISK device <br /> handle \'/ msflsh/MMSDB/autobackup/2007_08_29/o1_mf_n_631887085_3f9whfv1_.bkp\' <br /> Completed: drop tablespace dodd <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:21:48 2007 <br /> <strong>alter database datafile \'+ DATADG/mmsdb/datafile/gateway.295.1\' resize 15000M</strong> <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:21:48 2007 <br /> Errors in file / opt/oracle/admin/mmsdb/bdump/mmsdb_asmb_8036.trc: <br /> ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [kffmXpResize], [26], [32], [], [], [], [], [] <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:21:51 2007 <br /> Errors in file / opt/oracle/admin/mmsdb/bdump/mmsdb_asmb_8036.trc: <br /> ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [kffmXpResize], [26], [32], [], [], [], [], [] <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:21:51 2007 <br /> ASMB: terminating instance due to error 486 <br /> Wed Aug 29 12:21:51 2007 <br /> Errors in file / opt/oracle/admin/mmsdb/bdump/mmsdb_pmon_7990.trc: <br /> ORA-00486: ASMB process terminated with error <br /> Instance terminated by ASMB, pid = 8036</font> </blockquote><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Note the log, the first data file is reduced Resize, and then Resize enlarged file. <br /> This is just a totally fits with the Oracle Bug: 3952778</font></strong> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">This Bug\'s described as: <br /> <strong>Shrinking and then growing an ASM file can result in an internal error ORA-600 [kffmxpresize].</strong> <br /> Effects have been identified Version: <strong>10.1.0.3</strong></font></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">See not, and colleagues of our database environment operation and fully consistent with the Bug, so the ASM instance Crash, the database crashed. <br /> Really makes people fainted!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">As to whether the shot hits the target Bug, friends who are interested can try: D</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><strong>The lesson of the accident are: DBA also need to see the luck!</strong> <br /> <strong>The accident DBA lesson is: If I\'m feeling good always, be sure to find out why.</strong></font></font> </p>','Yesterday, while maintaining an Oracle 10.1.0.3.0 database, the ASM instance led to Crash, a database...'),(211,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/0a/2147.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle database via JDBC connection Ten Tips','Oracle_database_via_JDBC_connection_Ten_Tips','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Java Database Connectivity (JDBC) API is a series that allows Java programmers to access the database interface, the interface is not identical to each developer. In the use of Oracle\'s JDBC years, I accumulated a lot of skills that will enable us to play better system performance and achieve more.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>1, in the development of client development using the Thin driver</strong></font> &lt;br /&gt; in the development of Java software, Oracle\'s database provides four types of drivers, two kinds of application software used, applets, servlets and other client software, other two for the database stored procedures and other server-side Java software. The client-side software development, we can choose to OCI driver or the Thin driver. OCI driver localization of the interface using Java (JNI), through the Oracle client software to communicate with the database. Thin driver is a pure Java driver that communicates directly with the database. In order to obtain the highest performance, Oracle recommends the development of client software to use OCI driver, which seems to be correct. But I recommend using Thin drivers, because through several tests found that in normal circumstances, Thin driver performance more than the OCI driver.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>2, turn off auto-commit feature to improve system performance</strong></font></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /></font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> 3, dynamic SQL commands or time-limited objects using Statement</font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> In the implementation of SQL commands, we have two choices: You can use PreparedStatement object, you can use Statement objects. No matter how many times using the same SQL command, PreparedStatement parsing and compiling it only once. When using the Statement object, each execution of a SQL command, it will be parsed and compiled. This may make you think, use PreparedStatement objects than using Statement objects faster. However, I conducted the tests show that the client software, this is not the case. Therefore, time-bound SQL operations, unless the bulk to handle SQL commands, we should consider using the Statement object. <br /> In addition, the use of Statement objects also makes it easier to write dynamic SQL command, because we can string together to create a valid SQL command. Therefore, I think, Statement objects can dynamically create and execute SQL commands easier.</font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> 4, the use of helper functions to format the dynamic SQL commands</font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> Use of Statement object to execute to create a dynamic SQL command, we need to address some formatting problems. For example, if we want to create a table to insert the name of O\'Reilly\'s SQL commands, you must use two connected &quot;\'\'&quot; was replaced by O\'Reilly in the &quot;\'&quot; number. Completion of these work the best way is to create a helper method to complete replacement operation, and then taking the formula in the connection string to express a heart SQL command used to create the helper method. Similarly, we can make helper method accepts a value of type Date, then let it out based on Oracle\'s to_date () function of the string expression.</font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> 5, the use of PreparedStatement object to improve the overall efficiency of the database</font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> Using the PreparedStatement object to execute SQL commands, the command is parsed and compiled the database, and then was placed in command buffer. Then, whenever the implementation of the same PreparedStatement object, it will be parsed once again, but will not be re-compiled. Can be found in the buffer precompiled commands, and can be re-used. A large number of users in the enterprise application software, often repeated the same SQL commands, use the PreparedStatement object is to reduce the number of compilation brought to improve the overall performance of the database. If it is not in the client creation, preparation, implementation of PreparedStatement Statement task requires the task longer than I would recommend Dynamic SQL commands in addition to all the circumstances of use outside the PreparedStatement object.</font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> 6, in the repeated batch operation to insert or update the object using the PreparedStatement</font></strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><br /> If the bulk to handle insert and update operations, we can significantly reduce the time they need. Oracle provides the Statement and CallableStatement does not really support the batch, only the PreparedStatement object is really to support batch processing. We can use addBatch () and executeBatch () method of selection criteria JDBC batch, or through the use of PreparedStatement object setExecuteBatch () method and standard executeUpdate () method of selection of the Oracle proprietary faster method. To use Oracle\'s proprietary batch processing mechanism can be invoked as follows setExecuteBatch (): <br /> PreparedStatement pstmt3D null; try {((OraclePreparedStatement) pstmt). SetExecuteBatch (30 );... pstmt.executeUpdate ();}</font></strong></font> </p>','Java Database Connectivity (JDBC) API is a series that allows Java programmers to access the database interface, the interface is not identical to each developer. In the use of Oracle\'s JDBC years, I accumulated a lot of skills that will enable us to play better system performance and achieve...'),(212,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/43/2041.html','http://www.ixdba.net','How to find the oracle system processes the SQL statement being executed','How_to_find_the_oracle_system_processes_the_SQL_statement_being_executed','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 17.85pt; TEXT-INDENT: -17.85pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 18.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; mso-fareast-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">1 <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span><