yle=\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">This parameter name suggests, it is used to control the <span lang=\"EN-US\">SGA</span> to use the maximum size of <span style=\"COLOR: blue\">virtual memory,</span> where the meaning of virtual memory may be fuzzy, the first can be understood, that <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle</span> can <span style=\"COLOR: blue\">allocate in memory to the maximum size of <span lang=\"EN-US\">SGA.</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span></font></font> </p><p style=\"MARGIN: 7.8pt 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 21pt; mso-para-margin-top: .5gd\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Now I am here to explain the &quot;virtual memory&quot; means, exactly should say: The actual memory and virtual memory. We know that when the <span lang=\"EN-US\">OS</span> is not enough memory in the actual use of the time, <span lang=\"EN-US\">OS</span> would be to use virtual memory. <span lang=\"EN-US\">oracle os</span> is running on a system with software, it is also a program, it requests <span lang=\"EN-US\">os</span> how much memory it used as its <span lang=\"EN-US\">sga</span> (for example, <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle</span> Application <span lang=\"EN-US\">500M</span> memory for <span lang=\"EN-US\">SGA,</span> which <span lang=\"EN-US\">SGA_MAX_SIZE = 500M), os</span> is generally <span lang=\"EN-US\">oracle</span> does not give it all started when the actual memory, but may only to <span lang=\"EN-US\">200M.</span> With the program running, <span lang=\"EN-US\">Oracle</span> constantly need memory, and assume that all the computer\'s real memory is only <span lang=\"EN-US\">500M,</span> then it is certain that the <span lang=\"EN-US\">OS</span> can not put all <span lang=\"EN-US\">500M</span> of real memory allocated to the <span lang=\"EN-US\">oracle</span> of <span lang=\"EN-US\">sga,</span> may also give a maximum of <span lang=\"EN-US\">350M,</span> left <span lang=\"EN-US\">150M</span> under virtual memory.</span></font></font> </p>','Oracle\'s SGA includes the following sections, you can show sga command or by looking at v $ sga view to see the SGA\'s probably consists of:...'),(214,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/bc/2009.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle Server-specific patterns and problems in shared mode','Oracle_Serverspecific_patterns_and_problems_in_shared_mode','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><h2 align=\"center\" style=\"MARGIN: 13pt 0cm; TEXT-ALIGN: center\"></h2><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Difference between the concept and</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------- <br /><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Sharing model for a similar connection pool concept, but the practical application of the effect is not very good, did not know there is no improvement in</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">10g <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------- <br /><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%