plication datafile <br /> \'/ Usr / oracle / dbs / application.dbf\' size 3M <br /> Increase in specific situations, and temporary tablespace rollback command example: <br /> SVRMGR&gt; create rollback tablespace rbs8 datafile <br /> \'/ Usr/oracle/dbs/rbs8.dbf\' size 4M <br /> SVRMGR&gt; create tablespace tmp8 datafile <br /> \'/ Usr/oracle/dbs/tmp8.dbf\' size 550K <br /> Rollback and temporary table space is exhausted, it can be deleted or offline <br /> SVRMGR&gt; drop tablespace rbs8; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; drop tablespace tmp8; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; alter tablespace rbs offline; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; alter tablespace tmp8 offline;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Create rollback segment Example:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SVRMGR&gt; create rollback segment rs11 tablespace tmp8; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; alter rollback segment rs11 online; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; alter rollback segment rs11 offline;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2, increasing the size of a table space</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">When the size of a table space can not meet operational needs, it should expand the table space. <br /> For example: <br /> SVRMGR&gt; alter tablespace system <br /> add datafile \'/ usr/oracle/dbs/sys338.dbf\' size 3M; <br /> Ten, increasing oracle user and the user authorization <br /> 1, increasing oracle user and the user license example: <br /> SVRMGR&gt; create user newuser identified by userpasswd default tablespace application temporary tablespace tmp8; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; grant connect to newuser; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; grant resource to newuser; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; grant update on emp to newuser; <br /> 2, increasing the role of oracle <br /> oracle default roles connect, resource, dba. It is a group can be assigned to another role <br /> Or the sum of the user\'s permissions, connect with 8 rights, resource rights of 5, dba 77 <br /> A privilege. Connecting users to the general Fu connect, enabling programmers to connect to the general increase resource, <br /> Only database administrators have dba privileges. <br /> Ã¢Â‘Â  Create a role <br /> SVRMGR&gt; create role newrole identified by rolepasswd; <br /> Ã¢Â‘Â¡ assign permissions to roles <br /> SVRMGR&gt; grant select on all table to newrolle; <br /> SVRMGR&gt; grant connect to newrole with admin option; <br /> 3, interrupt the connection when the user oracle with the oracle database to shutdown or possession of a large amount of resources the user needs to be released, dba <br /> Need to interrupt the user\'s connection with the oracle. <br /> Ã¢Â‘Â , SVRMGR&gt; select sid, serial #, username from v $ session; <br /> Ã¢Â‘Â¡, SVRMGR&gt; alter system kill session \'interger1, interger2\'; <br /> interger1, interger2 correspond to the sid and serial #</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">XI, SQL syntax</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> 1) Connection number: | | <br /><br /> 2) connect the two characters eg: select game_card_type_id | | name from game_card_type; <br /> 3) order by desc (descending) <br /> order by asc (ascending) <br /> 4) like \'_a%\' _ to represent a character. % Indicated that the number of characters</font> </p>',' A: Database startup...'),(270,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/04/1172.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle10g (10.2) in Redhat AS4','Oracle10g_102_in_Redhat_AS4','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 7.5pt 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 2\"> <strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"></span></strong> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 7.5pt 0cm; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Ora