n example: <br /> Original / usr size of 32 (PPs) * 32M (PP SIZE) = 1G <br /> # Lslv hd2 <br /> LOGICAL VOLUME: hd2 VOLUME GROUP: rootvg <br /> LV IDENTIFIER: 0006faaa00004c0000000111fd3878b2.5 PERMISSION: read / write <br /> VG STATE: active / complete LV STATE: opened / syncd <br /> TYPE: jfs WRITE VERIFY: off <br /> MAX LPs: 32512 PP SIZE: 32 megabyte (s) <br /> COPIES: 1 SCHED POLICY: parallel <br /> LPs: 32 PPs: 32 <br /> STALE PPs: 0 BB POLICY: relocatable <br /> INTER-POLICY: minimum RELOCATABLE: yes <br /> INTRA-POLICY: center UPPER BOUND: 32 <br /> MOUNT POINT: / usr LABEL: / usr <br /><br /> The / usr size into 2G <br /> # Chfs-a size = 2048M / usr <br /> Filesystem size changed to 4194304 <br /><br /> # Df-k <br /> Filesystem 1024-blocks Free% Used Iused% Iused Mounted on <br /> / Dev/hd4 32768 15632 53% 1724 11% / <br /> / Dev/hd2 2097152 865732 59% 31825 7% / usr <br /> / Dev/hd9var 32768 23884 28% 369 5% / var <br /> / Dev/hd3 65536 63396 4% 30 1% / tmp <br /> / Dev/hd1 32768 31684 4% 18 1% / home <br /> / Proc - - - - - / proc <br /> / Dev/hd10opt 65536 14304 79% 981 6% / opt <br /><br /> # Lslv hd2 <br /> LOGICAL VOLUME: hd2 VOLUME GROUP: rootvg <br /> LV IDENTIFIER: 0006faaa00004c0000000111fd3878b2.5 PERMISSION: read / write <br /> VG STATE: active / complete LV STATE: opened / syncd <br /> TYPE: jfs WRITE VERIFY: off <br /> MAX LPs: 32512 PP SIZE: 32 megabyte (s) <br /> COPIES: 1 SCHED POLICY: parallel <br /> LPs: 64 PPs: 64 <br /> STALE PPs: 0 BB POLICY: relocatable <br /> INTER-POLICY: minimum RELOCATABLE: yes <br /> INTRA-POLICY: center UPPER BOUND: 32 <br /> MOUNT POINT: / usr LABEL: / usr <br /><br /> Other file systems are set according to their own needs can be, here are my settings: <br /> Filesystem 1024-blocks Free% Used Iused% Iused Mounted on <br /> / Dev/hd4 32768 16708 50% 1777 11% / <br /> / Dev/hd2 2097152 811420 62% 32230 7% / usr <br /> / Dev/hd9var 262144 245636 7% 380 1% / var <br /> / Dev/hd3 1048576 796292 25% 457 1% / tmp <br /> / Dev/hd1 262144 253744 4% 27 1% / home <br /> / Proc - - - - - / proc <br /> / Dev/hd10opt 2097152 1938404 8% 2302 1% / opt <br /><br /> oracle installation required a larger space, so plan a separate file system. <br /> # Crfs-v jfs-g rootvg-m / oracle-a size = 8196M-a bf = true</font></span>','empty\n'),(278,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/69/1248.html','http://www.ixdba.net','oracle 9i database upgrade to oracle10','oracle_9i_database_upgrade_to_oracle10','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div class=\"storytext\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Upgrade to 10G ORACLE9I brief description: <br /> How to Win the next upgrade to the Oracle10.2.0.1 Oracle9208 <br /> 1, close the original 9208 database, perform a full cold-prepared. <br /> 2, the installation ORACLE10g, select a different with the 9208 Home, the time of installation chose not to install the database. <br /> 3, the SYSDBA logged into SQLPLUS, run: <br /> Sql&gt; spool upgrade.info <br /> Sql&gt; @ oracle10G_HOMErdbmsadminutlu102i.sql <br /> Sql&gt; spool off <br /> Note that the output of the screen <br /> 4, in the Tablespace column prompted some additional space for the table space: <br /> Autoextend Additional space required: 165mb. <br /> The original query the original database size and free space of space. <br /> Sql&gt; select tablespace_name, bytes from dba_data_files; <br /> Sql&gt; select tablespace_name, sum (bytes) from dba_free_space group by tablespace_name; <br /> Expansion prompted the need to increase space for the table space. <br /> Sql&gt; alter database tablespace system add datafile <br /> \'D: oracleoradatatestsystem02.dbf\' size 200m; <br /> Sql&gt; alter database datafile <br /> \'D: oracleoradatatestxdb01.dbf\' resize 50m \'; <br /> 4, copy the file to the 9i\'s initsid.ora 10gHomedatabase directory. <br /> Run menu, Database Upgrade Assistant, follow the prompts step by step operation. If not successful, the manual upgrade, followed the following order. <br /> 5, copy the password file pwdsid.ora 9i to 10gHomedatabase directory. <br /> 6, under the copy 9iHomenetworkadmin tnsname.ora, listerna.ora, sqlnet.ora to 10GHomenetworkadmin directory. <br /> 7, according to upgrade.info tips, modify 10GHomedatabaseinitSid.ora parameter file. <br /> 8, close 9I database <br /> 9, at the command line with a cmd&gt; oradim-delete-sid sid removed under the WINDOWS service instance. <br /> 10, at the command line using cmd.&gt; Oradim-new-sid sid pfile = \'path\' to create a new instance. <br /> 11, to stop the original 9i the listerner services <br /> 12, with sysdba to login as sqlplus, the way to start the database upgrade. <br /> Startup upgrade <br /> Startup tips LRM-00116: \'D: ORACLELOGSDB followed by\' = \'Syntax error <br /> ORA-01078: failure of treatment system parameters prompted, change 10GHomedatabaseinitsid.ora, will utl_file_dir = d: oraclelogs <br /> Commented out. Re-run the sql&gt; startup upgrade success. <br /> 13, creating sysaux table space. <br /> Sql&gt; create tablespace sysaux <br /> Datafile \'d: oracleoradatatestsysaux01.dbf\' size 500m <br /> Extent management local <br /> Segment space management auto <br /> Online; <br /> 15, @ d: oracle10.2rdbmsadmincatupgrd.sql; (on my computer this process took about 1 Ã‚Â½ hours). <br /> 16, sql&gt; shutdown immediate; <br /> 17, sql&gt; startup <br /> 18, sql&gt; @ d: oracle10.2rdbmsadminutlrp.sql <br /> To recompile any invalid application object <br /> After the implementation of all the re-run the query compilation errors <br /> Sql&gt; select * from utl_recomp_errors; <br /><br /> 19 10G Start the listerner service test, upgrade is completed.</font> </div>','empty\n'),(279,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/e4/1618.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Linux performance analysis and adjustment of the basic principles of','Linux_performance_analysis_and_adjustment_of_the_basic_principles_of','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"></p><p