; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">must be carried out. ideological shift is more than the temporary use of technology to <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">improve,</span> because he can help you speed up the learning speed.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /><br /></span> <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAM','empty\n'),(282,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/5c/2177.html','http://www.ixdba.net','On the linux file system inode and related concepts','On_the_linux_file_system_inode_and_related_concepts','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>One. inode size defined</strong> <br /><br /></font> </p><div class=\"wp-caption alignnone\" id=\"attachment_141\" style=\"WIDTH: 448px\"><p align=\"center\"> <a href=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/de/de22412dc430b1380d45c3aa0d1c4444.gif\"><font size=\"2\"><img alt=\"inode table sample\" border=\"0\" class=\"size-full wp-image-141\" height=\"314\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/de/de22412dc430b1380d45c3aa0d1c4444.gif\" title=\"inode table sample\" width=\"438\" /></font></a> </p><font size=\"2\"> </font><p class=\"wp-caption-text\"> <font size=\"2\">inode table sample</font> </p></div><p><font size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font size=\"2\">inode table is the data area of the index table.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Inode inode into memory and file system inode, we have said here is the file system inode.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>1.</strong> Linux FS inode table can be simply divided into two parts with the data area. inode table has many of the inode, inode were recorded for each attribute of a file distributed with this file which datablock on (that is, we say that the pointer.) <br /> inode two functions: the log file attributes and pointers</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>2.</strong> Inode table in the red area that inode size, is 128Byte, in liunx system through the command we can see, the system is so defined. <br /> Inode size is assigned to an inode to record the document properties of the disk block size. <span id=\"more-140\"></span></font> </p><div class=\"hl-surround\"><div class=\"hl-main\"> <font size=\"2\">dumpe2fs-h / dev/hda6 | grep node <br /> Inode size: 128</font> </div></div><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>3.</strong> Data ares in the purple zone block size, is our general concept of disk blocks. This area is where we used to store data.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>4.</strong> There is also a logical concept: FS 2048 byte assigned to each data area, to assign an inode. But one is not necessarily spent on inode 2048 byte, does not mean that files allocation of a minimum of 2048 byte, it simply represents the filesystem in inode table / data area allocated space ratio is 128/2048, which is 1 / 16 .</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>mkfs.ext3-i 2048</strong> of this command-i parameter is what we call the logic of the concept, and its size determines the size of inode count, redhat5 default-i minimum can be set to 1024.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Many online articles introduced on the inode, the inode size of the definition of a mistake, they put-i parameter or the value of the inode size block size read as many articles so confusing.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>5.</strong> Inode <strong>mkfs.ext3</strong> command parameters can be changed:</font> </p><div class=\"hl-surround\"><div class=\"hl-main\"> <font size=\"2\">mkfs.ext3-i 2048-b 8192-f 1024 / dev/sdb2</font> </div></div><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>-I 2048</strong> inode for every change creates a 2KB <br /> <strong>-B 8192</strong> to set the size of 8kB block size <br /> <strong>-F 1024</strong> to set the size of fragments 1KB</font> </p><div class=\"hl-surround\"><div class=\"hl-main\"> <font size=\"2\">mkfs.ext3-N 2939495 / dev/sdb2</font> </div></div><p> <strong><br /></strong> <font size=\"2\"><strong>-N 2939495</strong> change inode count.</font> </p><p> <strong><font size=\"2\">II. Inode change a partition\'s complete operation parameters:</font></strong> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>1.</strong> Uninstall hard disk partition:</font> </p><div class=\"hl-surround\"><div class=\"hl-main\"> <font size=\"2\">[Root @ localhost ~] # umount / dev/hda7</font> </div></div><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>2.</strong> Inode parameter adjustment</font> </p><div class=\"hl-surround\"><div class=\"hl-main\"> <font size=\"2\">[Root @ localhost ~] # mkfs.ext3-i 1024-b 8192 / dev/hda7 <br /><br /> mke2fs 1.39 (29-May-2006) <br /> Filesystem label = <br /> OS type: Linux <br /> Block size = 4096 (log = 2) <br /> Fragment size = 4096 (log = 2) <br /> 2048256 inodes, 512064 blocks <br /> 25603 blocks (5.00%) reserved for the super user <br /> First data block = 0 <br /> Maximum filesystem blocks = 525250560 <br /> 63 block groups <br /> 8240 blocks per group, 8240 fragments per group <br /> 32512 inodes per group <br /> Superblock backups stored on blocks: <br /> 8240, 24720, 41200, 57680, 74160, 206000, 222480, 403760 <br /><br /> Writing inode tables: done <br /> <font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\"><strong>IXDBA.NET Community Forums</strong></a></font> <br /> Creating journal (8192 blocks): done <br /> Writing superblocks and filesystem accounting information: done <br /><br /> This filesystem will be automatically checked every 30 mounts or <br /> 180 days, whichever comes first. Use tune2fs-c or-i to override.</font> </div></div><p> <font size=\"2\">3. To modify / etc / fstab <br /> Before the amendment</font> </p><div class=\"hl-surround\"><div class=\"hl-main\"> <font size=\"2\">[Root @ localhost ~] # vi / etc / fstab <br /><br /> LABEL = / / ext3 defaults 1 1 <br /> LABEL = / boot / boot ext3 defaults 1 2 <br /> devpts / dev / pts devpts gid = 5, mode = 620 0 0 <br /> tmpfs / dev / shm tmpfs defaults 0 0 <br /> LABEL = / opt / opt ext3 defaults 1 2</font> </div><br /><br /><center> <b><font color=\"red\">Read more:</font> <font color=\"red\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">1</font></b> <a href=\"/article/5c/2177$2.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">2</a> * <a href=\"/article/5c/2177$3.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">3</a> * <a href=\"/article/5c/2177$4.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">4</a> * <a href=\"/article/5c/2177$2.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">Next&gt;&gt;</a> </center><br /></div>','One. inode size...'),(283,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/2b/2151.html','http://www.ixdba.net','PXE + TFTP + DHCP network automatically install the Linux boot','PXE__TFTP__DHCP_network_automatically_install_the_Linux_boot','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">His earlier written an article to share with you the next! <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">Overview</font> <br /><br /> PXE (preboot execute environment), developed by Intel\'s latest technology, working in the Client / Server network model to support the station through the network from a remote server to download images, and thus support from the network operating system boot process, and its During startup, the terminal requires the server to assign IP addresses, then TFTP (trivial file transfer protocol) or MTFTP (multicast trivial file transfer protocol) protocol to download a boot package to a local memory and executed by the end of this startup software package basic software settings to guide the pre-installed in the server terminal operating system. PXE can boot multiple operating systems, such as: Windows 95/98/2000/xp/2003/vista/2008, linux and so on. <br /><br /> Most direct expression of PXE, the stations in the network environment can save hard drive, but not usually refer to the concept of diskless stations, since the use of the technology in the network mode PC running speed faster than the PC with disk 3 times. Of course, the PC using the PXE is not in the traditional sense TERMINAL terminal, because the PC using the PXE server is not consuming CPU, RAM and other resources, so the server hardware requirements low. <br /> Cloning PXE network is now the most widely used one is the cafe of the diskless technology. The field in a disk in the PXE network maintenance and installation can be the best system to use Internet cafes to install and maintain a unified guidance technology, PXE boot speed and stability are the best! <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">A: Installation Environment</font> <br /><br /> A Linux server, linux service, need to install the tftp + dhcp. As a remote installation of network servers. <br /> Client host, which is the need to install the Linux system, the host, the host motherboard must support boot from network. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">II: Installation and Configuration Linux software on a network server to tftp and dhcp</font> <br /><br /> 1: Check for installed tftp <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # rpm-qa tftp * <br /> tftp-server-0.42-3.1.el5.centos <br /> tftp-0.42-3.1.el5.centos <br /> If not, that is not installed, if your system supports yum, direct execution <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # yum install * tftp * <br /> 2: Check whether the service in accordance with the dhcp <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # rpm-qa dhcp * <br /> dhcpv6-client-1.0.10-16.el5 <br /> dhcp-3.0.5-18.el5 <br /> If you do not dhcp, also perform yum install. <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # yum install dhcp * <br /> 3: Configuring tftp service dhcp service (1) configuration tftp service <br /> Tftp is bound by default under the xinetd service, therefore, will want to modify the file to the tftp / etc / xinetd.d to complete, the modified tftp file as follows, where &quot;disable&quot; option from the &quot;yes&quot; is amended as &quot;no&quot;, an increase in the server_args option &quot;-u nobody&quot; parameter, so that any user can access. <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # more / etc / xinetd.d / tftp <br /> # Default: off <br /> # Description: The tftp server serves files using the trivial file transfer \\ <br /> # Protocol. The tftp protocol is often used to boot diskless \\ <br /> # Workstations, download configuration files to network-aware printers, \\ <br /> # And to start the installation process for some operating systems. <br /> service tftp <br /> { <br /> socket_type = dgram <br /> protocol = udp <br /> wait = yes <br /> user = root <br /> server = / usr / sbin / in.tftpd</font>','empty\n'),(284,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/b4/2150.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Talk about the Red Hat Linux, rhel, and Fedora Core as well as differences and relations between Centos','Talk_about_the_Red_Hat_Linux_rhel_and_Fedora_Core_as_well_as_differences_and_relations_between_Centos','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"><font size=\"2\">The content is &quot;gradual <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/d4/444.html\">Linux</a> &quot;chapter excerpt, and more, please visit this link: <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/article/ac/2144.html\">http://www.ixdba.net/article/ac/2144.html</a></font></font></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\"><font size=\"2\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">1. Red Hat Linux <br /><br /></font> Red Hat <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/d4/444.html\">Linux</a> is the first release redhat personal version of linux, the 1.0 version on November 3, 1994 issue. Although its history is less than other linux releases a long, but compared to a lot of <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/d4/444.html\">Linux</a> distributions, Red Hat\'s long history and much more. Since Red Hat 9. 0 after release, RedHat is no longer developing the company\'s Linux desktop distributions, Red Hat Linux to stop the development, and will be fully concentrate on the development of the server version, which is Red Hat Enterprise Linux version. April 30, 2004, Red Hat the company official to stop Red Hat 9. 0 version of the support, marking the official end of the Red Hat Linux. The original Red Hat Linux desktop distributions are Fedora open source community and from the plan to merge into Fedora Core release. <br /> Red Hat is currently divided into two series: the Red Hat provides technical support and updates fee Red Hat Enterprise Linux, as well as community development free from the Fedora Core. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">2. Fedora Core</font> <br /><br /> Fedora Core (abbreviated as FC) is targeting Red Hat\'s experimental site for the new technology, many new technologies will be tested in the FC, if stable, then Red Hat will consider joining the Red Hat Enterprise Linux. <br /> Fedora Core 1 was released in late 2003, and FC is the positioning of desktop users. FC provides the latest package, while its version of the update cycle is very short, only 6 months. Since version update frequently, performance and stability can not be guaranteed, therefore, generally not recommended on the server Fedora Core. <br /> In fact, so to that, Fedora is Red Hat released Red Hat Enterprise linux version of an experiment, take the user to do the test for Red Hat Enterprise Edition released as a foundation. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">3. Red Hat Enterprise Linux</font> <br /><br /> Red Hat Enterprise Linux (abbreviated to RHEL, Red Hat Enterprise Edition.) Red Hat is now the main job of the server version of linux development, in the version of emphasis on the performance and stability as well as hardware support. Enterprise Edition operating system, because the development cycle is longer, pay attention to performance, stability, and server software support, version updates are relatively slow. <br /> RedHat Enterprise Linux version is divided into 4 Advanced Server (AS), ES Workstation (WS), Desktop, their difference is not large, only a function of the difference. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">4. Centos</font> <br /><font color=\"#ff0000\"></font><br /> CentOS full name of the &quot;Community Enterprise Operating System&quot; (Community Enterprise Operating System) <br /> CentOS background: <br /> Redhat released Redhat 9. 0, no longer develop redhat 10,11 ... ..., a comprehensive shift Redhat enterprise linux (abbreviated as rhel) development, and different from the past, the new redhat Enterprise Edition requires users to first purchase lisence, redhat same time commitment to ensure the stability, security. rhel binary code is no longer available for download, but as part of redhat service, but the source code remains open. In this case, there has been centos, whitebox, dao, and so a number of open source in the enterprise version, which centos most active. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">Here is how to make about centos generated:</font> <br /><br /> CentOS community on the Redhat web site download all the source code, recompile. As AS / ES / WS is a commercial product, therefore, must be all the Redhat\'s Logo CentOS and logo into their own identity. Such as the AS4. 0 SRPM original source compiled and put on Centos community logo, so that became the CentOS 4. 0. Redhat Enterprise Linux AS4 Update1 the source compiled to become a CentOS4. 1. AS4 Update2 source code compiled to become a CentOS4. 2 and so on. CentOS is produced.</font></font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Therefore, it can be said of CentOS is Redhat AS / ES / WS free version can be obtained using the centos redhat enterprise linux with the same features and performance. Centos while also providing free long-term upgrade and update services. Thus, in many versions of RHEL clone, CentOS is a very outstanding very good. <br /> Although it is a RHEL clone centos, but not exactly the same, said cloning is a 100% interchangeability. In fact, different for centos, RHEL on CentOS software can not guarantee 100% above normal.</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">To understand the difference between Redhat version series, after all. In fact, we found Why Redhat linux as a beginner to learn the reason.</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">First of all: in the country, and even the world\'s Linux users are most familiar with, the most heard details of the distribution can be sure it is a Red Hat. Red Hat is the linux community as the &quot;boss&quot;, the U.S. company Red Hat released Red Hat linux is a commercial operation of the most successful Linux distributions, Red Hat, so trust linux release, Red Hat linux functionality and performance There is no doubt.</font> </p>','The content is \"gradual Linux \"chapter excerpt, and more, please visit this link:...'),(285,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/26/2149.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Customize your Linux system installation disk','Customize_your_Linux_system_installation_disk','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The following are carried out under a virtual machine environment. <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"></font></font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">1, V M install linux system</font> <font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"> </font></font> <br /><font color=\"#000000\"></font><br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\">2, the installation of custom tools anaconda repodata createrepo mkisofs</font> <font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"> </font></font> <br /><font color=\"#000000\"></font><br /></font> <p align=\"left\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\"><font size=\"2\"><font style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"><font color=\"#000000\">Too much associated with yum install / / customization process need to generate comps.xml iso file and generates</font></font></font></font> </p><p align=\"left\"> <font color=\"#000000\"><font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt\"></font></font> </p><br /><