ont size=\"3\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-fareast; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin\">After installation, problem solving, <font face=\"Calibri\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">locale,</span></font> the display is normal.</span></font> </p>','...'),(289,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/0c/2112.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Linux virtual machines into VMware Server2.0.1 environment error','Linux_virtual_machines_into_VMware_Server201_environment_error','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Today downloaded Vmware Server2.0.1, installed under the previous VMware1.0 linux virtual machine import in, but always an error:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">SCSI reservation for virtual device &quot;scsi1: 0&quot; cannot be enabled because the disk &quot;share-disk.vmdk&quot; is being used by another virtual machine running on a different host machine. SCSI reservation under VMware Server is only available for machines running on the same host machine. <br /> Failed to configure virtual device scsi1.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">As the imported virtual machine environment is a double, while use of the shared disk, share-disk.vmdk is a shared disk configuration file, the installation error that should be the other host also load the virtual disk, do not configure Shared disk settings? ?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Open one of the virtual machine\'s configuration files: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 4.vmx</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">disk.locking = &quot;false&quot; <br /> diskLib.dataCacheMaxSize = &quot;0&quot; <br /> diskLib.dataCacheMaxReadAheadSize = &quot;0&quot; <br /> diskLib.DataCacheMinReadAheadSize = &quot;0&quot; <br /> diskLib.dataCachePageSize = &quot;4096&quot; <br /> diskLib.maxUnsyncedWrites = &quot;0&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Shared disk is configured, why it was error, hesitation on the occasion, seen a few lock files, are the problem here?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">share-disk.vmdk.RESLCK, 564d06b1-1836-79ac-7fd9-b024b42335c1.vmem.lck</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">share-disk.vmdk.RESLCK this is a shared disk lock when opening the file, because the environment does not exist before, so, delete this file, re-start the VMware Server2.0, normally launched!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">At the same time starts, you can see the share-disk.vmdk.RESLCK in the new environment, but also re-generated, so it is, ignore it!</font> </p>','Today downloaded Vmware Server2.0.1, installed under the previous VMware1.0 linux virtual machine import in, but always an...'),(290,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/dc/2111.html','http://www.ixdba.net','OS community and the tycoon: Google announced Chrome OS Web Operating System','OS_community_and_the_tycoon_Google_announced_Chrome_OS_Web_Operating_System','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Start from the search, then the network application services, followed by an accident to launch the browser and mobile phone operating system Android, is now, Google brings us unexpected, in order to make Chrome play all of the energy (fart), today launched Google Google Chrome OS!</font> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/e1/e1631fff8ab020350817775583fcc680.jpg\" /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Initially, Chrome OS is designed as a lightweight open-source Internet OS, Google will be open later this year, its source code, and Google claims that Chrome OS using a netbook on sale in the second half of next year.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Chrome as a browser extension, Google said it will redefine the way the operating system. But also for the Internet, people had the hope is to make Android running on a netbook, but it is not necessary.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Chrome OS most of the applications will be completed in the Web. Google said the speed, simplicity, security will be Chrome OS features, you will in a few seconds into the Web world. Users no longer need to worry about viruses, malware, trojans and other security issues. Chrome OS can be said to be a Web operating system.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Chrome OS based on Linux kernel, and can run on x86 and ARM platforms. Web is the platform for all Web applications can run perfectly in Chrome OS, and developers can also develop applications for different languages. At the same time, these applications can also run on Windows, Mac OS and Linux.</font> </p><blockquote><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Google Chrome OS is a new project, separate from Android. Android was designed from the beginning to work across a variety of devices from phones to set-top boxes to netbooks. Google Chrome OS is being created for people who spend most of their time on the web, and is being designed to power computers ranging from small netbooks to full-size desktop systems. While there are areas where Google Chrome OS and Android overlap, we believe choice will drive innovation for the benefit of everyone, including Google.</font> </p></blockquote><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Currently, chromeOS.org on July 7, U.S. time is Google up, interested in children\'s shoes can go to check whois. ChromeOS.com, ChromeOS.cn, ChromeOS.com.cn has been registered in advance.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Google formal involvement of the PC operating systems, Microsoft do not know how to look.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">For this message, you excited?</font> </p>','Start from the search, then the network application services, followed by an accident to launch the browser and mobile phone operating system Android, is now, Google brings us unexpected, in order to make Chrome play all of the energy (fart), today launched Google Google Chrome...'),(291,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/0d/2101.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Talk shell of the &quot;&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1&quot;','Talk_shell_of_the_quotgt__dev__null_2gt_amp_1quot','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Today, a technology in their own group so they were asked a question, so he explained a bit popular, to be a record, we look to explain it clearly!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">shell may often see:&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The results can command%&gt; to define the output in the form of</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Decomposition of this combination: &quot;&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1&quot; is in five parts.</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff6600\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">1:&gt; redirected to where the representative, for example: echo &quot;123&quot;&gt; / home/123.txt <br /> 2: / dev / null device file on behalf of Air <br /> 3:2&gt; &quot;means standard error stderr <br /> 4: &amp; that is equivalent to the mean, 2 &quot;&amp; 1, 2, redirect the output that is equivalent to 1 <br /> 5:1 that stdout standard output, the system default value is 1, so &quot;&gt; / dev / null&quot; equivalent to &quot;1&gt; / dev / null&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Thus,&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1 can also be written as &quot;1&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Then the execution of this statement in the title is: <br /> 1&gt; / dev / null: first that the standard output redirected to a null device file, which is not output any information to the terminal, it means do not display any information. <br /> 2 &quot;&amp; 1: Then, the standard error output redirected to standard output, because before the standard output has been redirected to a null device file, so the standard error output are redirected to a null device file.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">That clear to you, we understand, are you!</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff6600\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Under such a contrast with the way the benefits of telling!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The most common methods are:</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">command&gt; file 2&gt; file with the command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">What is different place?</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">First command&gt; file 2&gt; file means that the standards produced by the command output, and errors in the information to the file. Command&gt; file 2&gt; file that is written, stdout and stderr are sent directly to the file in, file will be opened twice, so stdout and stderr will overwrite each other so very used to write both FD1 and FD2 at the same time to seize the file in the pipeline. <br /> The command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1 This command will be sent directly to the stdout file, stderr inherited FD1 pipe, and then was sent to file, time, file is opened only once, only use a pipe FD1, it includes the contents of stdout and stderr. <br /> From the IO efficiency, the efficiency of a command before the back of a command than less efficient, so when writing shell scripts, more time, we will command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1 this writing.</font> </p>','Today, a technology in their own group so they were asked a question, so he explained a bit popular, to be a record, we look to explain it...'),(292,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/b5/2100.html','http://www.ixdba.net','How to restart the Linux not recognize the new LUN','How_to_restart_the_Linux_not_recognize_the_new_LUN','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Some Linux database server comparison with low-end storage, because the business changes, sometimes need to add some LUN. <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/d4/444.html\">Linux</a> servers have to be re-added after the start LUN? engineers sometimes say storage vendors, but this seems to be a message had been misunderstood.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Colleagues from the learned store specializing in the use QLogic FC HBA LUN Scan Utility This script can be identified without re-booting the system and the newly added LUN. QLogic FC driver has no need to re-Load.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Scene: <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/d4/444.html\">Linux</a> Server + QLogic\'s HBA card. QLogic\'s Qla2340 HBA cards with an example. Download <font color=\"#ff6600\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/article/down/ql-dynamic-tgt-lun-disc-2.3.rar\">the script</a></font> (by the way, the page QLogic FC HBA Information Utility is also useful.) Then look at the script <a href=\"http://filedownloads.qlogic.com/files/ms/56615/readme_dynamic_lun_22.html\"><u><font color=\"#800080\">documentation</font></u></a> .</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The simplest usage only need to run:</font> </p><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">#. / Ql-dynamic-tgt-lun-disc.sh</font> </pre><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Script prompts in the case of no activity <acronym title=\"Input Output\">IO</acronym> operation. In fact, much of the problem. After the <acronym title=\"Operating System\">OS</acronym> recognize the new device is recognized:</font> </p><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"># Fdisk-l</font> </pre><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">If the system has PowerPath, also need to run:</font> </p><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"># Powermt config</font> </pre><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">OK. A bit much to improve system availability, you can not apply to the owners maintained the downtime.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">PS: Also a <a href=\"http://www.dice.inf.ed.ac.uk/groups/services/file_service/docs/adding-luns.html\"><font color=\"#ff6600\">reference document</font></a> .</font> </p>','Some Linux database server comparison with low-end storage, because the business changes, sometimes need to add some LUN. Linux servers have to be re-added after the start LUN? engineers sometimes say storage vendors, but this seems to be a message had been...'),(293,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/5a/2098.html','http://www.ixdba.net','The correct way to restore EXT3 Superblock (bad superblock)','The_correct_way_to_restore_EXT3_Superblock_bad_superblock','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div class=\"asset-body\"><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">A few days ago met a Linux Ext3 file system super block (Superblock) errors. <br /></font> </p><blockquote><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">.... Bad superblock on / dev/hdc1</font> </pre></blockquote> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">A colleague to do the recovery, the results of the data are erased. Then think, then the recovery of direct fsck is wrong. The correct approach should be like this:</font> <p></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">An error for the wrong <strong>disk (or device) block size.</strong> <br /> There are many ways you can get. For example, <br /></font> </p><blockquote><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"># Tune2fs-l / dev/hdc1</font> </pre></blockquote> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">In fact, in most cases is 1 K.</font> <p></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Two pairs of the current error disk <strong>backup.</strong> <br /> Recover superblock (Superblock) process is actually a risky process. Do the backup to make backups. If there are other free equipment, use the dd command to back up the contents of the device.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">3 In general, the super-block wrong is the primary superblock is basically wrong in the Ext2/Ext3 file system is created, the screen will also prompt us to have in several places in the backup superblock. So how did you find these super block in place? help us see: <br /></font> </p><blockquote> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">-B superblock <br /> Instead of using the normal superblock, use an alternative <br /> superblock specified by superblock. This option is normally <br /> used when the primary superblock has been corrupted. The loca- <br /> tion of the backup superblock is dependent on the filesystem\'s <br /> blocksize. For filesystems with 1k blocksizes, <font color=\"#ff6600\">a backup <br /> superblock can be found at block 8193; for filesystems with 2k <br /> blocksizes, at block 16384; and for 4k blocksizes, at block <br /> 32768. <br /></font> <br /> Additional backup superblocks can be determined by using the <br /> mke2fs program using the-n option to print out where the <br /> superblocks were created. The-b option to mke2fs, which spec- <br /> ifies blocksize of the filesystem must be specified in order for <br /> the superblock locations that are printed out to be accurate. <br /><br /> If an alternative superblock is specified and the filesystem is <br /> not opened read-only, e2fsck will make sure that the primary <br /> superblock is updated appropriately upon completion of the <br /> filesystem check.</font> </blockquote><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">4 began to recover. If the file system block size is 1K, then we can use the following command to recover: <br /></font> <blockquote><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"># / Sbin/fsck.ext3-b 8193 / dev/hda4</font> </pre></blockquote><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">If the alternate block (8193) also have problems, you can try 24577 (8192 * 3 +1) or 40961 (8192 * 5 +1).</font> <p></p></div><div class=\"asset-more\" id=\"more\"><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#ff6600\">Maybe you will see it, save the super-block location is in accordance with the laws of such 1,3,5,7. The specific location in BlockSize (8192) * N +1.</font> In more than 500M of space is such a law. less than 500M, I do not know. who know tell me, thank you.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Also a guide:</font> <font color=\"#0082ff\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://edseek.com/archives/2004/02/25/ext3-filesystem-bad-superblock-recovery/\">Bad ext3 filesystem superblock Recovery</a></font> </p></div>','A few days ago met a Linux Ext3 file system super block (Superblock) errors....'),(294,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/a0/2072.html','http://www.ixdba.net','openBSD under Nginx + MySQL + PHP environment to build manual Raiders','openBSD_under_Nginx__MySQL__PHP_environment_to_build_manual_Raiders','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Preface</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Thank ChinaUnix and many experts ChinaUnix forum, learned a lot here! <br /> This manual is ONMP series of the second edition, in the first edition of the manual, but simply illustrates the basic construction methods ONMP environment, and not too much consideration to the production system applies. The second edition will be bigger amended to allow the manual to build the production environment can play a useful reference. <br /> I is limited, inevitable flaws in the manual, the actual production of your application if there are any problems found, or have any better suggestions, please ChinaUnix forum venue to BSD version, or to even a personal blog ( http://onmp.cublog.cn), thread to correct me. Hope that our concerted efforts, be able to perfect as far as possible the manual! <br /> The manual environment in OpenBSD 4.4 build Nginx, MySQL, PHP environment as an example to explain. By convention, root <br /> Permission.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> <strong>A, OpenBSD Installation and Precautions</strong></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> The installation of OpenBSD is not to say here, mainly the choice of system components during installation, partition and system services section. Part of the system components, as production systems, even not recommended to install comp44.tgz this component. Because comp44.tgz is in fact a compiler, do not install this, can largely prevent the installation of unauthorized software, to improve the security of the remote host. If you really need to install any software can also be important in the non-compiled on the machine and then use software such PSFTP uploaded to the remote host to use. PSFTP use of the software on the second floor are described in detail. <br /> System partition, it is recommended to / usr, / usr / local, / var, / var / mysql, / var / mail, / var / log, / var / nginx other points out of a separate partition, that is, detailed comparison partition, to prevent the files in a directory partition fill the entire expansion and other issues led to the deadlock. Suppose you have a 80G hard drive, a partition in the following example: <br /> / 200M <br /> (Swap) 1G <br /> / Tmp 200M <br /> / Usr 500M <br /> / Usr / local 200M <br /> / Var 100M <br /> / Var / mysql 10G <br /> / Var / mail 100M</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">/ Var / log 5G ~ 10G <br /> / Home 200M <br /> / Var / nginx some free space The system services, recommended that all services are selected &quot;n&quot;, which does not start with the system.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> <strong>Second, system performance tuning</strong></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> For multi-core machines, the use of bsd.mp the core. <br /> mv / bsd / obsd <br /> mv / bsd.mp / bsd <br /> Ã¢Â…Â , / etc / fstab tuning <br /> vi / etc / fstab <br /> Descriptor part in the file system, add &quot;noatime&quot; and &quot;softdep&quot;. Examples are as follows: <br /> / Dev/wd0a / ffs rw, noatime, softdep 1 1 <br /> / Dev/wd0l / home ffs rw, nodev, nosuid, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0d / tmp ffs rw, nodev, nosuid, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0e / usr ffs rw, nodev, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0f / usr / local ffs rw, nodev, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0g / var ffs rw, nodev, nosuid, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0i / var / log ffs rw, nodev, nosuid, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0j / var / mail ffs rw, nodev, nosuid, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0h / var / mysql ffs rw, nodev, nosuid, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> / Dev/wd0k / var / nginx ffs rw, nodev, nosuid, noatime, softdep 1 2 <br /> Friendly reminder: softdep is an asynchronous file system, power-down may result in unexpected data loss / damage, production systems, please use caution! <br /> After saving changes quit, reboot, see if I can not start correctly. <br /> There is no problem under normal circumstances, the individual machine or virtual machine may be because of compatibility reasons, can not start. Then put the root directory of the softdep removed, other directories reservations, there will still be effect. <br /> More on OpenBSD environment, the contents of the disk performance tuning, see the article even blog, address below: <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">vi / etc / sysctl.conf <br /> Skip to the end, add the following: <br /> # Increase file system cache to 1M <br /> kern.maxvnodes = 131072 <br /> # Allowed to process up to 65,536 <br /> kern.maxproc = 65536 <br /> # 65536 at the same time open up the file <br /> kern.maxfiles = 65536 <br /> Maximum concurrent connections # 65536 <br /> kern.somaxconn = 65536 <br /> # Minimum number of connections reserved <br /> kern.sominconn = 256 <br /> kern.maxclusters = 32768 <br /> # Increase TCP receive / send buffer to 64K <br /> net.inet.tcp.recvspace = 65536 <br /> net.inet.tcp.sendspace = 65536 <br /> # Increase the UDP receive / send buffer to 64K <br /> net.inet.udp.recvspace = 65536</font> </p>','empty\n'),(295,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/db/2064.html','http://www.ixdba.net','And debug the Linux core files generated under','And_debug_the_Linux_core_files_generated_under','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">I used to look at is what the machine:</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">$ Uname-a <br /> Linux dev 2.4.21-9.30AXsmp # 1 SMP Wed May 26 23:37:09 EDT 2004 i686 i686 i386 GNU / Linux</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">The default look at some of the parameters, note that core file size is 0, the program will not produce an error core file.</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">$ Ulimit-a <br /> <span class=\"style2\">core file size (blocks,-c) 0</span> <br /> data seg size (kbytes,-d) unlimited <br /> file size (blocks,-f) unlimited <br /> max locked memory (kbytes,-l) 4 <br /> max memory size (kbytes,-m) unlimited <br /> open files (-n) 2048 <br /> pipe size (512 bytes,-p) 8 <br /> stack size (kbytes,-s) 10240 <br /> cpu time (seconds,-t) unlimited <br /> max user processes (-u) 7168 <br /> virtual memory (kbytes,-v) unlimited</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">Write a simple program to see if core files are not being generated.</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">$ More foo.c</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\"># Include &lt;stdio.h&gt;</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">static void sub (void);</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">int main (void) <br /> { <br /> sub (); <br /> return 0; <br /> }</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">static void sub (void) <br /> { <br /> int * p = NULL;</font> </p><p> <font size=\"3\"><font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\"><span class=\"style2\">/ * Derefernce a null pointer, expect core dump. * / <br /> printf (&quot;% d&quot;, * p);</span> <br /> }</font></font> </p><p> <font size=\"3\"><font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\">$ Gcc-Wall-g foo.c <br /> $. / A.out <br /> <span class=\"style2\">Segmentation fault</span></font></font> </p><p> <font size=\"3\"><font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\">$ Ls-l core .* <br /> <span class=\"style2\">ls: core .*: No such file or directory</span></font></font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">Core file is not found, we change the settings to change ulimit, it generated. 1024 is taken lightly, and if core files larger than 1024 blocks to produce does not come out.</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">$ Ulimit-c 1024 (transferred by Note: Use the-c unlimited unlimited core file size) <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">$ Ulimit-a <br /> <span class=\"style2\">core file size (blocks,-c) 1024</span> <br /> data seg size (kbytes,-d) unlimited <br /> file size (blocks,-f) unlimited <br /> max locked memory (kbytes,-l) 4 <br /> max memory size (kbytes,-m) unlimited <br /> open files (-n) 2048 <br /> pipe size (512 bytes,-p) 8 <br /> stack size (kbytes,-s) 10240 <br /> cpu time (seconds,-t) unlimited <br /> max user processes (-u) 7168 <br /> virtual memory (kbytes,-v) unlimited</font> </p><p> <font size=\"3\"><font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\">$. / A.out <br /> <span class=\"style2\">Segmentation fault (core dumped)</span> <br /> $ Ls-l core .* <br /> <span class=\"style2\">-Rw ------- 1 uniware uniware 53248 Jun 30 17:10 core.9128</span></font></font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">Note the above output, more than one <span class=\"style2\">(core dumped).</span> Does have a core file, 9128 is the process PID. We use GDB to look at the core.</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">$ <span class=\"style2\">Gdb - core = core.9128</span> <br /> GNU gdb Asianux (6.0post-0.20040223.17.1AX) <br /> Copyright 2004 Free Software Foundation, Inc. <br /> GDB is free software, covered by the GNU General Public License, and you are <br /> welcome to change it and / or distribute copies of it under certain conditions. <br /> Type &quot;show copying&quot; to see the conditions. <br /> There is absolutely no warranty for GDB. Type &quot;show warranty&quot; for details. <br /> This GDB was configured as &quot;i386-asianux-linux-gnu&quot;. <br /> Core was generated by `. / A.out \'. <br /> Program terminated with signal 11, Segmentation fault. <br /> # 0 0x08048373 in?? () <br /> (Gdb) <span class=\"style2\">bt</span> <br /> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Community Forums</a></font></strong> <br /> # 0 0x08048373 in?? () <br /> # 1 0xbfffd8f8 in?? () <br /> # 2 0x0804839e in?? () <br /> # 3 0xb74cc6b3 in?? () <br /> # 4 0x00000000 in?? () <br /><br /> At this point do not see bt with <span class=\"style2\">b</span> ack <span class=\"style2\">t</span> race, that is the call stack, the original symbol information GDB do not know where. We tell it about:</font> </p><p> <font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\" size=\"3\">(Gdb) <span class=\"style2\">file. / A.out</span> <br /> Reading symbols from. / A.out...done. <br /> Using host libthread_db library &quot;/ lib/tls/libthread_db.so.1&quot;. <br /> (Gdb) <span class=\"style2\">bt</span> <br /></font> <font size=\"3\"><font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\"><span class=\"style2\"># 0 0x08048373 in sub () at foo.c: 17 <br /> # 1 0x08048359 in main () at foo.c: 8</span> <br /><br /> Backtrace this time out.</font></font> </p> <font size=\"3\"><font face=\" Ã¦Â¥Â·Ã¤Â½Â“_GB2312\">(Gdb) l <br /> <span class=\"style2\">8 sub ();</span> <br /> 9 return 0; <br /> 10}</font></font>','I used to look at is what the...'),(296,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/4f/2063.html','http://www.ixdba.net','IBM AIX Core files generated in the method','IBM_AIX_Core_files_generated_in_the_method','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font size=\"2\">Environment: (product, platform, model, software version, etc.) <br /> Platform: RS <br /> Software version: AIX4.3 or later</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Problem description: <br /> If you need an application process to produce a complete core file for analysis, how to do?</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Answer:</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><br /> 1. Preconditions</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Generating core files, have to configure the system parameters to verify that the system can produce a complete core file. In addition, the file system also need to have enough free space for the storage of the resulting core file. core files are usually stored in the process is the main user\'s home directory.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><br /> 2. When the file to produce the complete Core</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">By default, the process will not produce a complete core file. If you need to trace debug an application in a shared memory segment data, particularly data on the thread stack, you need to produce a complete core dump file for analysis.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><br /> 3. If you need to produce a complete core file information, you first need to execute the following commands as root:</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"># Chdev-l sys0-a fullcore = true</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">The command can also be done by smitty: <br /> smitty -&gt; System Environments -&gt; Change / Show Characteristics of Operating System</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Change / Show Characteristics of Operating System <br /> Maximum number of PROCESSES allowed per user [128] <br /> Maximum number of pages in block I / O BUFFER CACHE [20] <br /> Maximum Kbytes of real memory allowed for MBUFS [0] <br /> Automatically REBOOT system after a crash false <br /> Continuously maintain DISK I / O history false <br /> HIGH water mark for pending write I / Os per file [33] <br /> LOW water mark for pending write I / Os per file [24] <br /> Amount of usable physical memory in Kbytes 262144 <br /> State of system keylock at boot time normal <br /> <font color=\"#cc0000\">Enable full CORE dump true</font> <br /> Use pre-430 style CORE dump false <br /> Enable CPU Guard disable</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">The above list &quot;Enable full CORE dump&quot; entry is set to &quot;true&quot;.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><br /> 4. Use the following command to generate a core file: <br /> # Kill -11 <br /> Note: The above command will also kill the specified process.</font> </p><p></p><p> <font size=\"2\"><font size=\"4\">Appendix B. How to view C program generated by CORE DUMP (from IBM cn)</font> <br /> Document #: 1317181000005</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Environment</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Product: IBM C and C + + Compiler <br /> Platform: AIX4.3.0 above: C for AIX version 3 or above</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Problem Description</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">How to view C program generated by CORE DUMP, and find the root of a problem?</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">Answers</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\">View the AIX operating system produced by C programs CORE DUMP, you can use the AIX operating system commands: dbx. If you find no such command in use, you need to install the operating system package: bos.adt.debug. <br /> Specific use dbx commands as follows: <br /> 1. First, during the C program compiled to use the-g option. <br /> cc-g-o samp1.o samp1.c <br /> 2. After performing procedures, and produce CORE DUMP core file, use: dbx samp1.o core command to view the CORE DUMP. <br /> To find the function or statement which caused problems in the dbx command line and enter where, to display the required information. dbx command line can also perform a variety of commands to perform different view, users can help order to understand these commands.</font> </p>','Environment: (product, platform, model, software version, etc.)  Platform: RS  Software version: AIX4.3 or...'),(297,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/ed/986.html','http://www.ixdba.net','You are very strange but it applies to the 10 linu','You_are_very_strange_but_it_applies_to_the_10_linu','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In general, you may take years or even decades to master Linux shell commands. Here are 10 you may never have heard of or used commands. <br /><br /> 1.pgrep, generally as follows: <br /><br /> # Ps-ef | egrep ^ root | awk {print $ 2} <br /> 1 <br /> 2 <br /> 3 <br /> 4 <br /> 5 <br /> 20 <br /> 21 <br /> 38 <br /> 39 <br /> ... <br /><br /> In fact, you can: <br /> # Pgrep-u root <br /> 1 <br /> 2 <br /> 3 <br /> 4 <br /> 5 <br /> 20 <br /> 21 <br /> 38 <br /> 39 <br /> ... <br /><br /> 2.pstree, in a tree format to list the process. This command has been running for WebSphere, or other large tasks very useful application. <br /><br /> # Pstree <br /> init-+-acpid <br /> |-Atd <br /> |-Crond <br /> |-Cups-config-dae <br /> |-Cupsd <br /> |-Dbus-daemon-1 <br /> |-Dhclient <br /> | -events/0- +-Aio / 0 <br /> | |-Kacpid <br /> | |-Kauditd <br /> | |-Kblockd / 0 <br /> | |-Khelper <br /> | |-Kmirrord <br /> | `-2 * [Pdflush] <br /> |-Gpm <br /> |-Hald <br /> |-Khubd <br /> | -2 * [Kjournald] <br /> |-Klogd <br /> |-Kseriod <br /> |-Ksoftirqd / 0 <br /> |-Kswapd0 <br /> |-Login --- bash <br /> | -5 * [Mingetty] <br /> |-Portmap <br /> |-Rpc.idmapd <br /> |-Rpc.statd <br /> | -2 * [Sendmail] <br /> |-Smartd <br /> |-Sshd --- sshd --- bash --- pstree <br /> |-Syslogd <br /> |-Udevd <br /> |-Vsftpd <br /> |-Xfs <br /> `-Xinetd <br /><br /> 3.bc is a very accurate calculator language. I find it allows you to use shell scripts to perform square root operations. And expr <br /> Does not support the square root. <br /> #. / Sqrt <br /> Usage: sqrt number <br /> #. / Sqrt 64 <br /> 8 <br /> #. / Sqrt 132112 <br /> 363 <br /> #. / Sqrt 1321121321 <br /> 36347 <br /> Here is the script: <br /> # Cat sqrt <br /> #! / Bin / bash <br /> if [$ #-ne 1] <br /> then <br /> echo Usage: sqrt number <br /> exit 1 <br /> else <br /> echo-e &quot;sqrt ($ 1) \\ nquit \\ n&quot; | bc-q-i <br /> fi <br /><br /> 4.split, you want a large file into smaller chunks it? May be exported file mysqldump? Split is to help you complete the task order. <br /> Now I will be a 250MB file into many months to LF_ prefix 2MB file size. <br /><br /> # Ls-lh largefile <br /> -Rw-r - r - 1 root root 251M Feb 19 10:27 largefile <br /> # Split-b 2m largefile LF_ <br /> # Ls-lh LF_ * | head-n 5 <br /> -Rw-r - r - 1 root root 2.0M Feb 19 10:29 LF_aa <br /> -Rw-r - r - 1 root root 2.0M Feb 19 10:29 LF_ab <br /> -Rw-r - r - 1 root root 2.0M Feb 19 10:29 LF_ac <br /> -Rw-r - r - 1 root root 2.0M Feb 19 10:29 LF_ad <br /> -Rw-r - r - 1 root root 2.0M Feb 19 10:29 LF_ae <br /> # Ls-lh LF_ * | wc-l <br /> 126 <br /><br /> 5.nl shows the number of rows. I have been found previously in the nl command with the head to get my program files like the first. <br /><br /> # Head spider.h <br /> / * <br /> * This file define a set of standard spider extensions <br /> * <br /> * Version: 20 18.2.07 <br /> * <br /> * Authors: Equal Null <br /> * Copyright (c) 2003-2007 Equal Null, All Rights Reserved. <br /> * / # Ifndef _LINUX_SPIDER_H <br /><br /> # Nl wireless.h | head <br /> 1 / * <br /> 2 * This file define a set of standard spider extensions <br /> 3 * <br /> 4 * Version: 20 18.2.07 <br /> 5 * <br /> 6 * Authors: Equal Null <br /> 7 * Copyright (c) 2003-2007 Equal Null, All Rights Reserved. <br /> 8 * / # ifndef _LINUX_SPIDER_H <br /></font> <p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">www.ixdba.net</font></a></font></strong> </p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /><br /> 6.mkfifo command is the coolest one. You sure know how to grep or perl to create a pipeline output (pipeline). <br /> But you know how to use a command pipeline (named pipe) to Unicom, the two commands? First, let us create a pipe, and write the following: <br /><br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/mkfifo-write-to-pipe_2008_1_24_15_44_33.png\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"117\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/mkfifo-write-to-pipe_2008_1_24_15_44_33.png\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Then read from: <br /><br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/read-from-pipe_2008_1_24_15_44_40.png\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"117\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/read-from-pipe_2008_1_24_15_44_40.png\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">7.ldd, want to know what java is connected to the Linux thread library? <br /><br /> # Ldd / usr/java/jre1.5.0_11/bin/java <br /> libpthread.so.0 =&gt; / lib/tls/libpthread.so.0 (0x00bd4000) <br /> libdl.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libdl.so.2 (0x00b87000) <br /> libc.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libc.so.6 (0x00a5a000) <br /> / Lib/ld-linux.so.2 (0x00a3c000) <br /><br /> 8.col, want to help man the page is saved as a text file file? <br /><br /> # PAGER = cat <br /> # Man less | col-b&gt; less.txt <br /><br /> 9.xmlwf, need to know whether an xml document format? (Or possibly a configuration file ...) <br /><br /> # Curl-s http://www.wbwb.net&gt; bnn.html <br /> # Xmlwf bnn.html <br /> # Perl-i-pe s @ <br /> @ <br /> @ G bnn.html <br /> # Xmlwf bnn.html <br /> bcc.html: 104:2: mismatched tag <br /><br /> 10.lsof lists the open files. You can do many things with it. For example to find out which ports are open: <br /><br /> # Lsof | grep TCP <br /> portmap 2587 rpc 4u IPv4 5544 TCP *: sunrpc (LISTEN) <br /> rpc.statd 2606 root 6u IPv4 5585 TCP *: 668 (LISTEN) <br /> sshd 2788 root 3u IPv6 5991 TCP *: ssh (LISTEN)</font> <br/&gt; Sendmail 2843 root 4u IPv4 6160 TCP badhd: smtp (LISTEN) <br /> vsftpd 9337 root 3u IPv4 34949 TCP *: ftp (LISTEN) <br /> cupsd 16459 root 0u IPv4 41061 TCP badhd: ipp (LISTEN) <br /> sshd 16892 root 3u IPv6 61003 TCP wbwb.net: ssh-&gt; wbwb.net: 4661 (ESTABLISHED) <br /><br /> Use lsof-i TCP command also get the same information. <br /><br /> Or to identify a user opens a file number. Run this command for Oracle, DB2, or WebSphere application is so large is very important: <br /><br /> # Lsof | grep root | awk {print $ NF} | sort | uniq | wc-l <br /> 179 <br /><br /> Here\'s sort | uniq can also write sort-u, operating results are the same.','empty\n'),(298,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/d3/1008.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle patch 3028673 to resolve a single process','Oracle_patch_3028673_to_resolve_a_single_process','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','This issue should be gototop first discovered, that was something many years ago, but, until now, in fact, there is no final solution to this problem, so this patch or have been crushed. bug description: <p></p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # Bugs resolved by this patch in conjunction with APAR IY49415:\r\n    # ------------------------------------------------- ------------\r\n    # 3028673: ORACLE ON AIX DOES NOT SHARE MANY CONST STRUCTS - PER\r\n    # PROCESS MEMORY OVERHEAD\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> More detailed information can refer to metalink Note: 259983.1, in fact, in earlier aix 4.3 and 5.1, when the solution is: </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> $ <font color=\"#0000ff\">AIXTHREAD_SCOPE = S; export AIXTHREAD_SCOPE</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font color=\"#0000ff\">$</font> NUM_SPAREVP = <font color=\"#0000ff\">1; export NUM_SPAREVP</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> However, starting from the aix 5.2, the above solution is no longer valid, so, in order to solve this problem, aix 5.2 launched an APAR IY49415, in aix 5.3 is not find the APAR information, but does not mean aix 5.3 does not support but because aix 5.3 has been fully included now. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> AIX 5.2 # <font color=\"#0000ff\">instfix-a-ivk IY49415</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> IY49415 Abstract: read-only reloc linking / loading support \r\n\r\n    IY49415 Symptom Text:\r\n     Programs having large amounts of read-only address constants\r\n     (Compared to our competitors binaries of the same programs),\r\n     consume excessive amounts of memory under AIX since it has no\r\n     support to place address constants in read-only memory (text).\r\n\r\n    ----------------------------\r\n        Fileset bos.64bit: 5.2.0.12 is applied on the system.\r\n        Fileset bos.mp: 5.2.0.18 is applied on the system.\r\n        Fileset bos.mp64: 5.2.0.18 is applied on the system.\r\n        Fileset bos.rte.bind_cmds: 5.2.0.13 is applied on the system.\r\n        Fileset bos.up: 5.2.0.18 is applied on the system.\r\n        All filesets for IY49415 were found.\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> There is the APAR for aix 5.2 system, or all of the aix 5.3 system, oracle released a patch 3028673. Way to fight this patch is very strange, is not the traditional way Opatch play, but re-relink a new Oracle executable file, the ultimate purpose is to directly modify the source file so that oracle can be shared between multiple processes as part of the original can not share resources, this part of the general resources of space occupied by more than 1M. Therefore, the patch can be reduced so that each oracle process a little more than 1M of memory usage, particularly if in the process, and the system memory and more intense, this patch is very effect. relink the methods are: </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Relink the oracle binary\r\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n\r\n     1 save your current version of $ ORACLE_HOME / oracle\r\n     2 create a working directory $ ORACLE_HOME / relink\r\n     3 cd to $ ORACLE_HOME / relink\r\n     4 unzip the relinking package\r\n     5 link $ ORACLE_HOME / bin / oracle to ./oracle0\r\n     6 run the script. / Genscript to generate some required files and scripts\r\n     7 run. / Relink.sh to generate the new oracle binary oracle0.new. $ $\r\n     8 copy oracle0.new. $ $ To $ ORACLE_HOME / bin / oracle and verify that the\r\n     permissions match the original oracle binary.\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> In addition, special attention is needed, patch described in the </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # Patch Special Instructions\r\n    # ---------------------------\r\n    # This patch is for AIX 5.2 systems only.\r\n    #\r\n    # It is valid for all 920 * AIX 5.2 systems.\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> This is because there was no aix 5.3 system, in fact, virtually all systems aix 5.2/5.3 oracle 920 can use this patch, the following is a comparison table before and after use, attention SIZE column, patch the basic difference between before and after the patch more than 1M, If the process 1000 to save 1-2G of memory. </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Patch before the $ <font color=\"#0000ff\">ps gx | grep oracle</font>\r\n        PID TTY STAT TIME PGIN SIZE RSS LIM TSIZ TRS% CPU% MEM COMMAND\r\n     483436 - A 199:48 12 4804 2587 6 xx 49801 21136 0.5 0.0 oracletb\r\n     602170 - A 198:55 0 4804 25940 xx 49801 21136 0.5 0.0 oracletb\r\n     610420 - A 209:55 6 4844 25980 xx 49801 21136 0.5 0.0 oracletb\r\n     630988 - A 145:18 9 4860 25932 xx 49801 21136 0.4 0.0 oracletb\r\n     639154 - A 199:59 10 4828 2590 0 xx 49801 21136 0.5 0.0 oracletb\r\n     643276 - A 191:42 4 4792 25864 xx 49801 21136 0.5 0.0 oracletb\r\n     651494 - A 193:13 6 4844 25916 xx 49801 21136 0.5 0.0 oracletb\r\n     671756 - A 204:38 10 4776 2584 8 xx 49801 21136 0.5 0.0 oracletb\r\n     ... ...\r\n\r\n    $ Patch </pre>','empty\n'),(299,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/0d/1009.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Recently aix 5305 to toss dead','Recently_aix_5305_to_toss_dead','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','The last few machines, the installation of 5305 as a result, still in beta, it was agonizing death, serious physical and mental exhaustion ing, smooth on-line do not know. <p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Oslevel-s</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> 5300-05-CSP </p><p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> First, in the case of large memory usage (108G), such as the SGA open to a certain extent (about 73% of total memory), OS would be inexplicable HANG live in, what commands are executed can not, found later, found a document , said that by default, SGA can not exceed the amount of memory for 70% of total memory. If you want more than 70%, must be modified maxpin% kernel parameter, the default 80%, but the total SGA only maxpin% -10%. Had always thought as long as no more than maxpin% on it, evidently right or wrong, but only in the 5.3 to the wrong wrong, I set off on the 5.2 SGA total of more than maxpin% -10% of the. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Topas very obedient and then find the disk busy% is always 0%, modify the chdev-l sys0-a iostat = \'true\' also demonstrates that when good or bad, later learned that although some changes chdev show successful, but not modify the actual success, resulting in lsattr-El sys0 pstat-T and the results actually are different, I faint, the solution is several times more than modify, change successfully (that is, the results of these two commands after the reunification) about re-starting , then Kuangyun. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Finally found, OS serious instability, such as repeated testing Oracle database connections, found to have a machine oracle connections to more than 200 point on the connection does not go in, client-side report ORA-12500 error. Ah can not think of any reason to analyze it also seems to still have relationship with the OS\'s memory, then re-starting what OS, does not make any changes, this time with more than 4,000 into the process without any error. </p><p> IBM analysis of the dump for so long, did not analyze a result, serious contempt. AIX version of the development of a more than a difference, it is despised. . . </p><p> God, save me, even if I RPWT, you will not be more than clouds (blue_prince) is even worse now. It appears that in the last line before, really going to Temple, and someone to accompany me to go with it? </p>','empty\n'),(300,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/e9/1010.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Configured on the AIX 5L NFS Server / Cli','Configured_on_the_AIX_5L_NFS_Server__Cli','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong>First, configure the NFS Server</strong> <p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> First need to start the NFS Server, you can smit nfs-&gt; Network File System (NFS) -&gt; Configure NFS on This System start or stop the nfs service group. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> You can view lssrc-g nfs service nfs situation </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Lssrc-g nfs</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Subsystem Group PID Status\r\n     biod nfs 712706 active\r\n     nfsd nfs 635260 active\r\n     rpc.mountd nfs 462932 active\r\n     rpc.lockd nfs 639418 active\r\n     rpc.statd nfs 757914 active\r\n     nfsrgyd nfs inoperative\r\n     gssd nfs inoperative\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Of course, the above can also startsrc-g nfs and stopsrc-g nfs start and stop the service unit subsystem. Whenever the system starts, / etc / rc.nfs run exportfs command to read the server / etc / exports file, and then tell the kernel which directories to be exported with the corresponding permissions. And above and rpc.mountd daemons to / etc / rc.nfs start. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> / Etc / exports nfs server is specified the directory with permissions to export the file as follows, such as </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">More / etc / exports</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> / U01/logs-sec = sys: krb5p: krb5i: krb5: dh: none, rw, access = host_name\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Note: This is the access must write the machine name, the machine name corresponding to the ip in / etc / hosts is reflected </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The directory can be exported by exportfs, such as: </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">/ Usr / sbin / exportfs-a</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">/ Usr / sbin / exportfs</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> / U01/logs-sec = sys: krb5p: krb5i: krb5: dh: none, rw, access = host_name\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Exportfs on the use of more, you can view the help, also, / etc / xtab you and / ext / exports has the same format when running exportfs, / etc / xtab will be updated, so you can export a directory and the temporary exports file is not updated. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> On the / etc / exports of updates, you can also use the smit nfs-&gt; Network File System (NFS) -&gt; Add a Directory to Exports List or Change / Show Attributes of an Exported Directory to achieve, such as </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Smit chnfsexp</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> * Pathname of directory to export / u01/logs\r\n      Anonymous UID [-2]\r\n      Public filesystem? [No]\r\n    * Change export now, system restart or both both\r\n      Pathname of alternate exports file []\r\n      Allow access by NFS versions []\r\n      External name of directory (NFS V4 access only) []\r\n      Referral locations (NFS V4 access only) []\r\n      Replica locations []\r\n      Ensure primary hostname in replica list yes\r\n      Allow delegations? []\r\n      Security method [sys, krb5p, krb5i, krb5, dh, none]\r\n          Mode to export directory [read-write]\r\n          Hostname list. If exported read-mostly []\r\n          Hosts &amp; netgroups allowed client access [host_name1, host_name2]\r\n          Hosts allowed root access []\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Authentication server in the / etc / exports file lists the client wants to install the file system name and the file system is exported. Enter the following command to operate: </p><p> <font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><strong>www.ixdba.net</strong></a></font> </p><br /><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Showmount-e server_name</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The command in NFS Server / client can be running on, listing all currently exported by the server_name file system. </p><p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <strong>Second, configure nfs client</strong> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> nfs of client configuration is relatively simple, normal to need portmap service. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Lssrc-s portmap</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Subsystem Group PID Status\r\n     portmap portmap 225506 active\r\n 					  </pre>','empty\n'),(301,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/0c/1011.html','http://www.ixdba.net','AIX 5L on the routing configuration and management','AIX_5L_on_the_routing_configuration_and_management','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Here comes the route, I have a brief look at the role of routing in TCP / IP network, when a packet sent from one computer to another computer, when the two may be unrelated to the computer IP address However, the source sends data packets through the computer how to know the correct &quot;path&quot; to send this packet it, this is the role of the route. A brief description of the route can be, is a predetermined IP address, may be a router or a routing function of a computer, can tell you connect to the target address (or subnet) the correct path, route target generally host, subnet and default of the points. If a destination address (or subnet) do not specify a particular route, then the default route (that is, we say that the gateway). <p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Usually, if there is no route (including the default gateway), this time, only through the broadcast of a segment of the computer to access the same, but through the route, you may be able to access any computer around the world (as long as their network the same, there Ip address and the correct route point) and, of course, but also it allows you to access. From an IP address to another IP address, may be through layers of routing, such as the first router may only send messages one to the next router, a router, put down more the next level of information transmitted to the router, so far has been to target . Through the unix / linux or windows of the traceroute tracert, we can know the routing path to the right: </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> C:&gt; <font color=\"#0000ff\">tracert-d 71.5.7.191</font>\r\n\r\n    Tracing route to 71.5.7.191 over a maximum of 30 hops\r\n\r\n      1 * * * Request timed out.\r\n      2 16 ms 16 ms 16 ms 220.191.142.165\r\n      3 17 ms 17 ms 17 ms 61.130.125.73\r\n      4 20 ms 21 ms 21 ms 61.130.126.149\r\n      5 41 ms * 41 ms 202.97.43.177\r\n      6 40 ms 41 ms 42 ms 202.97.33.138\r\n      7 231 ms * 231 ms 202.97.51.174\r\n      8 1115 ms 1111 ms 1105 ms 202.97.49.130\r\n      9 230 ms 231 ms 230 ms 205.158.79.29\r\n     10 1115 ms 1122 ms 1123 ms 65.106.5.45\r\n     11 1127 ms * 1122 ms 65.106.2.158\r\n     12 463 ms 464 ms * 205.158.60.170\r\n     13 473 ms 472 ms 473 ms 71.5.7.191 </pre><p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The following matters, I will introduce a view in AIX, configure the routing list, such as query command: </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Netstat-rn</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Routing tables\r\n    Destination Gateway Flags Refs Use If PMTU Exp Groups\r\n    Route Tree for Protocol Family 2 (Internet):\r\n    <font color=\"#ff0000\">default 10.0.100.250 UGc</font> 0 0 en0 - - -\r\n    10.0.100.0 10.0.100.150 UHSb 0 0 en0 - - - =&gt;\r\n    10.0.100/24 10.0.100.150 U 2 2 en0 - - -\r\n    10.0.100.255 10.0.100.150 UHSb 0 3 en0 - - -\r\n    127 / 8 127.0.0.1 U 0 353 lo0 - - -   \r\n\r\n    Route Tree for Protocol Family 24 (Internet v6):\r\n    :: 1:: 1 UH 0 0 lo0 16896 - - </pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The red section indicates the default route, which is the gateway address. Can use the following command to add the default route: </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Route add default 10.0.100.250</font> or </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Route add 0 10.0.100.250</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Expressed not specified, or the address of the target path is 0, that is, all addresses, use the route 10.0.100.250, in fact, this is the gateway IP address. However, this route has only increased the increase in the routing table (dynamic routing), but not written in the ODM database, if you want to write in the ODM database, simply by </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Smit route</font> to complete, or similar order </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Chdev-l inet0-a route = &quot;net,-hopcount, 0,, 0,10.0.100.250&quot;</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> With the same meaning as above, that the target address of 0, will use the route 10.0.100.250, in fact, the default route, this route is to increase the static route. </p><p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The following is to increase the dynamic routing and dynamic routing to delete an example, the following sub 10.10 .*.*/ that target 24, are using the route 10.0.100.251, where / 24 is that the subnet mask </p>','empty\n'),(302,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/15/1012.html','http://www.ixdba.net','The scope of this patch is quite large impact','The_scope_of_this_patch_is_quite_large_impact','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','We first look at the description of the patch <p></p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Bug 5496862 AIX: Mandatory patch to use Oracle with IBM Technology Level 5 (5300-5)\r\n   Bug 5496862 IO READING PROBLEMS AFTER INSTALLING IBM TECHNOLOGY LEVEL 5 (5300-05)\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Version of essentially all the running in 5305 version 9i and 10g are required to play this patch, and is mandatory to play the patch: </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> All Oracle 9i, 10gR1 and 10gR2 Database Customers running on AIX 5L V5.3\r\n   Technology Level 5 (TL 5300-05) must install an IBM\r\n   AIX fix and an Oracle Database patch to bring the OS and Database environments\r\n   to the correct levels.\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The following is a detailed description </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> This is a mandatory patch needed to use Oracle with\r\n   IBM Technology Level 5 (5300-05). Without it various\r\n   IO errors can be reported such as:\r\n\r\n     ORA-1115: IO error reading block from file? (Block #?)\r\n     ORA-1110: data file #: name\r\n     ORA-27091: skgfqio: unable to queue I / O\r\n     ORA-27072: skgfdisp: I / O error\r\n\r\n     Bad header found during preparing block for write\r\n\r\n     Fractured block found during preparing block for write\r\n\r\n     DBW1: terminating instance due to error ORA-600: [kcbzpb_1]\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The following is a solution, and the need to patch Oracle aix patch, in the new 5305 version, aix patch has hit into default, and if it is not breaking in, you may need to manually to play it. </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Please follow these\r\n   steps:\r\n\r\n   For the IBM AIX fix:\r\n\r\n   After installing AIX 5.3 Technology Level 5, IBM recommends installing the fix for AIX\r\n   APAR IY89080. The fix is available now as an interim fix and will be included\r\n   in the TL5 Service Pack 1\r\n   which is scheduled for release later this month.\r\n\r\n   To obtain the interim fix,\r\n   1. Navigate to http://www14.software.ibm.com/webapp/set2/sas/f/aix.efixmgmt/fixes.html\r\n   2. Select the primary ifix location\r\n   3. Select the ifix for iy89080\r\n\r\n   To obtain the Service Pack (when available)\r\n   1. Navigate to http://www.ibm.com/servers/eserver/support/unixservers/aixfixes.html\r\n   2. Select AIX 5.3 under Fix Bundles\r\n   3. Select Service Pack 5300-05-01\r\n\r\n   For the Oracle fix:\r\n   1. Navigate to http://metalink.oracle.com/ and sign into MetaLink\r\n   2. Select the &quot;Patches &amp; Updates&quot; tab\r\n   3. Select the &quot;Simple Search&quot; link and enter Patch Number 5496862, select\r\n   Platform AIX5L Based Systems (64-bit) and desired Oracle version\r\n   4. Proceed to download the desired patch. \r\n\r\n   Please, note that the patch is not available for all Oracle 9i, 10gR1 and 10gR2\r\n   releases yet.\r\n   If the patch is unavailable for your database version, please contact Oracle Support\r\n   for assistance.\r\n</pre>','empty\n'),(303,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/65/1013.html','http://www.ixdba.net','AIX 5L on the card using the binding (ethe','AIX_5L_on_the_card_using_the_binding_ethe','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','In the AIX operating system, the user can configure multiple EtherChannel (NIC teaming). In AIX 5.2, we can only choose either active / active EtherChannel mode, or can only select active / standby EtherChannel mode of binding of the network card. Therefore, AIX 5.2 introduces a new network card in the reserve mode, the user can specify a backup for the entire EtherChannel network card, when the EtherChannel fails, this card will automatically replace the function of EtherChannel. This is AIX 5.2 backup mode before the EtherChannel card is very different, therefore, can occur after 5.2 more complex binding mode of the composite card. <p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> EtherChannel can have a 2-8 card, an AIX operating system can configure multiple EtherChannel. But remember each EtherChannel is a new Ethernet interface, a user may need to adjust the ifsize no command parameter to ensure the total number of the Ethernet card and EtherChannel does not exceed ifsize, ifsize the default value is 8. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> You can use any card supported by AIX system to build EtherChannel. However, a channel member of the same EtherChannel must be connected to the LAN switch supports EtherChannel, the alternate channel can connect to another switch, taking over for the failure of the main channel. EtherChannel all members of the NIC should be set to the same speed and mode, such as 1000 MB full duplex. Card to be used as EtherChannel members configured IP address can not be, if you have configured, you must configure the EtherChannel to be deleted before the start of these configurations. </p><p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> In Aix5.2 later, we look at three typical configurations </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> 1, dual-channel or multi-channel co-active mode, this mode, all the cards are in active state, that is, each card are in working condition, they share an IP address and MAC address, however, all cards must aim in the same switch, and the corresponding switch port should also bind. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> The greatest advantage of doing so is that, when one card fails, or when a cable failure does not affect the work of the entire network, and only when all channels fail when the network card, network to fail. Moreover, the number of cards at the same time work can increase network bandwidth, however, to note that the default distribution is based on the target machine\'s Ip to allocate which card, if the target machine has only one, is not suitable to use the default settings. In this mode, the biggest problem is that all the cards target must be in the same switch, and bound together, can not prevent the target switch failure. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> 2, active / standby mode, this mode, a network card receives the main switch, a backup switch card receipt, the time when the active channel failure, automatically switches to the standby channel, when the main channel restoration of normal time, and then automatically switch to the main channel (where it switches back, is configurable). The greatest advantage of this approach is that we can prevent the switch failure. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> 3, the composite configuration, in this configuration, combined with the advantages of more than 2 ways. Such as a three card environment, we can configure dual network cards where two active mode to increase the network bandwidth and network reliability, the other a card as a backup mode, then in another switch, the current face 2 card is expired, or in front of two cards, when connected to the switch failure, switch to the backup network card. Figure: </p><p style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: center\"><img alt=\"etherchannel\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/06/etherchannel.jpg\" title=\"etherchannel\" /></p><p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Below, we introduce the detailed steps: </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> If you want to bind or unbind, you can use smit etherchannel completed, as if to bind ent1 and ent2:. </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Chdev-l en1-a netaddr = &quot;-a netmask =&quot;</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Chdev-l en2-a netaddr = &quot;-a netmask =&quot;</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Chdev-l en1-a state = \'detach\'</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Chdev-l en2-a state = \'detach\'</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Note: The above command is necessary, first cancel the existing sub-network card IP address, and must be in the detach state, note that if by en1 or en2 connected to the host, operating more than one command, your network may be suspended immediately Therefore, the operation of the above recommendations be completed by the other network card, or completed in the HMC. Then we started to bind </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> # <font color=\"#0000ff\">Smit etherchannel</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Select </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font color=\"#008000\">Add An EtherChannel / Link Aggregation</font> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IXDBA.NET Technical Community</font></a></font></strong> <br /><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Select card here </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font color=\"#008000\">EtherChannel / Link Aggregation Adapters ent1, ent2</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Enter the Executive: </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Command: OK stdout: yes stderr: no\r\n    Before command completion, additional instructions may appear below.\r\n    ent4 Available\r\n</pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> Finally, prompted the formation of a new network card, this card is available to bind off after the network card. Can view its properties or lsattr lsdev-Cc adapter card to see all the properties. </p>','empty\n'),(304,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/4b/2071.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Distributed File System MFS set notes','Distributed_File_System_MFS_set_notes','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>What is the MFS file system?</strong> <br /> Moose File System is a network with fault-tolerant distributed file system, it will be distributed in the network data on different servers, MooseFS so look through the FUSE is a Unix file system. <br /> MFS file system is individual to understand: the range will be distributed in various computers, the district will not use them to manage the use of a unified file system.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>MFS file system structure:</strong> <br /> Contains 3 roles: <br /> Management server managing server (master) <br /> Data Storage Server data servers (chunkservers)</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>Mount using the client computers client <br /></strong> Personal understanding of the role of 3 characters: <br /> Management Server: responsible for the management of each data storage server, file read and write scheduling, file space, recycling and recovery. Multi-node copy of the data storage server: responsible for the connection management server, follow the schedule management server, providing storage space. <br /> Client: mount the remote management server managed data storage server, by fuse kernel interface. Seems the shared file system and local unix file system uses the same effect. <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>Erection: <br /></strong> Server 2 sets <br /> (At least 2, a server to do the management server, data storage server and the client three kinds of roles, another computer for data storage and client) <br /> Said 1 computer for the A machine, the machine ran three kinds of roles, the first computer, said B-2, run two roles. If your computer can only run if more than one kind of client-side role or the role of data storage, depending on the circumstances decision. <br /> Operating System: FreeBSD6.x or Freebsd 7.x minni install the upgrade ports tree <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>1. A machine installed in the <br /></strong> CODE: <br /> / Sysutils / fusefs-kmod <br /> . / Devel / pkg-config <br /> The two ports package <br /> the results pkg_info <br /> CODE: <br /> b # pkg_info <br /> fusefs-kmod-0.3.9.p1.20080208 Kernel module for fuse <br /> fusefs-libs-2.7.2_1 FUSE allows filesystem implementation in userspace <br /> libiconv-1.9.2_2 A character set conversion library <br /> pkg-config-0.21 A utility to retrieve information about installed libraries <br /> b # <br /> Then add in rc.conf <br /> CODE: <br /> fusefs_enable = &quot;YES&quot; <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>2. In http://www.moosefs.com/index.html Download mfs-1.5.12.tar.gz</strong> <br /> CODE: <br /> # Fetch [url] http://www.moosefs.com/files/mfs-1.5.12.tar.gz [/ url] <br /> 4 times monthly revenue in 2009 - 48 - Received E-mail:</font> <a href=\"mailto:rmzhou@staff.chinaunix.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">rmzhou@staff.chinaunix.net</font> <br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">ChinaUnix.net ----- the world\'s largest Linux / Unix application and development of the Chinese community who <br /> # Tar xvzf mfs-1.5.12.tar.gz <br /> # Cd mfs-1.5.12 <br /> #. / Configure (this produced the bin file and the files and metadata sbin / usr / local / sbin and / usr / local / bin, <br /> Configuration file in / usr / local / etc metadata stored in / usr / local / var / mfs below) the default compiled without any parameters, and can do the data and manage the server. <br /> # Make &amp; &amp; make install the server role to complete the installation of two <br /> ################## The following is compiled in the A drive the implementation of a client file ################# <br /> ################ <br /> CODE: <br /> # Make clean &amp; &amp;. / Configure - prefix = / clien - enable-mfsmount &amp; &amp; make &amp; &amp; make install <br /> Can, in the / client directory to generate a client connection software mfs <br /></font></a> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>2. In B installed on the machine <br /></strong> CODE: <br /> / Sysutils / fusefs-kmod <br /> . / Devel / pkg-config <br /> The two ports package <br /> the results pkg_info <br /> CODE: <br /> b # pkg_info <br /> fusefs-kmod-0.3.9.p1.20080208 Kernel module for fuse <br /> fusefs-libs-2.7.2_1 FUSE allows filesystem implementation in userspace <br /> libiconv-1.9.2_2 A character set conversion library <br /> pkg-config-0.21 A utility to retrieve information about installed libraries <br /> b # <br /> Then add in rc.conf <br /> CODE: <br /> fusefs_enable = &quot;YES&quot; <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>2. In http://www.moosefs.com/index.html Download mfs-1.5.12.tar.gz</strong> <br /> <font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><strong>IXDBA.NET Technical Community</strong></a></font> <br /> CODE: <br /> # Fetch [url] http://www.moosefs.com/files/mfs-1.5.12.tar.gz [/ url] <br /> # Tar xvzf mfs-1.5.12.tar.gz <br /> # Cd mfs-1.5.12</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">#. / Configure - disable-mfsmaster - enable-mfsmount (binary files that can be produced for data storage server and have mfsmount file, the default compiler is not mfsmount\'s).</font> </p>','What is the MFS file system? Moose File System is a network with fault-tolerant distributed file system, it will be distributed in the network data on different servers, MooseFS so look through the FUSE is a Unix file system.  MFS file system is individual to understand: the range will be...'),(305,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/67/2061.html','http://www.ixdba.net','How to set MySQL Sync (mysql hot standby)','How_to_set_MySQL_Sync_mysql_hot_standby','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h3 align=\"center\" style=\"MARGIN: 13pt 0cm; TEXT-ALIGN: center\"> <font size=\"5\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"></span></font> </h3><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">MySQL</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">provides database synchronization, which we have the redundancy of database disaster, backup, restore, load balancing, etc. are of great help. This paper describes a common method of synchronization settings.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\"></span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0\"> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">Synchronization in two forms:</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\"></span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0\"> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">&quot;Master</span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">- <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">slave&quot;,</span> and <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">&quot;Lord</span> - <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Lord.&quot;</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p><h3 style=\"MARGIN: 13pt 0cm; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">A: &quot;Lord</span> - from <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">the&quot;</span> way</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></h3><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0\"> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">1,</span> for the server</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\"></span></font> </p><p style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Between the different versions of</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">MySQL</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">(the</span> binary <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">log)</span></font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">binlog</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">format may be different, so the best combinations is the</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Tahoma\">Master</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT