: \'Times New Roman\'\">Create database</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">instance</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">prepared</span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">Ã‚Â </font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">windows</span> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">platform using</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">oradim</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">tool to create a new <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">instance,</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">unix / linux</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">platform, you can set up a new <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">ORACLE_SID,</span> my platform is <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">linux,</span> you can set the <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">ORACLE_SID.</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">Ã‚Â </font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">Ã‚Â </font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font size=\"2\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">4:</span> ready to prepare the library parameter file</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"></span></strong></font></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">Ã‚Â </font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">The test system was built in two standby databases, while all together if the standby database, then,</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">db_name</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">set the main library <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">name,</span> lock_name_space set to prepare the library name, keeping in mind set</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">DB_FILE_NAME_CONVERT</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">and</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">LOG_FILE_NAME_CONVERT</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">parameters.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\"></span></font></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\">&gt; </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">Several parameters of the main library prepared as follows:</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font></font></strong> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. Log_archive_config = \'DG_CONFIG = (PRIMARY, STANDBY)\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_1 = \'LOCATION = / free / oracle / orabak VALID_FOR = (ALL_LOGFILES, ALL_ROLES) DB_UNIQUE_NAME = STANDBY\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_2 = \'SERVICE = primary VALID_FOR = (ONLINE_LOGFILES, PRIMARY_ROLE) DB_UNIQUE_NAME = PRIMARY LGWR SYNC AFFIRM\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. Db_unique_name = \'STANDBY\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. FAL_CLIENT = \'STANDBY\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. FAL_SERVER = \'PRIMARY\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. Log_archive_dest_state_1 = \'enable\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. Log_archive_dest_state_2 = \'enable\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. STANDBY_ARCHIVE_DEST = \'/ free / oracle / orabak\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. STANDBY_FILE_MANAGEMENT = \'AUTO\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">Ã‚Â </font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">The main library main parameters are as follows:</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font></font></strong> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><font size=\"2\">Ã‚Â </font></strong></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. Log_archive_config = \'DG_CONFIG = (PRIMAYR, STANDBY)\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. DB_UNIQUE_NAME = \'PRIMARY\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_1 = \'LOCATION = / free / oracle / orabak\'</font></span> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><font face=\"Verdana\">#</font></strong></span> *. LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_2 = \'SERVICE = STANDBYVALID_FOR = (ONLINE_LOGFILES, PRIMARY_ROLE) DB_UNIQUE_NAME = STANDBY <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><font face=\"Verdana\">LGWR</font></strong></span> SYNC AFFIRM\' # LGWR</span> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\">way</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">*. LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_2 = \'SERVICE = STAND</font></span>BY DB_UNIQUE_NAME = STANDBY ARCH SYNC REOPEN = 10 <font face=\"Verdana\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">\'#</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">arch</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #333399; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">way</span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">*. LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_STATE_1 = ENABLE</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">*. LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_STATE_2 = ENABLE</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">*. LOG_ARCHIVE_FORMAT = \'arc% s% t% r.arc\'</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">*. FAL_SERVER = \'STANDBY\'</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">*. FAL_CLIENT = \'PRIMARY\'</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">*. STANDBY_FILE_MANAGEMENT = \'AUTO\'</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font size=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">*. Standby_archive_dest = \'/ free / oracle / orabak\'</span></font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><font size=\"2\">Ã‚Â  </font></span> </p>','empty\n'),(309,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/27/2051.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Lvs in Windows as a Real Server','Lvs_in_Windows_as_a_Real_Server','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><h2 align=\"center\" style=\"MARGIN: 13pt 0cm; TEXT-ALIGN: center\"> <span class=\"oblogtext\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%\"><br /> <font face=\"Times New Roman\">Windows</font></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">on the</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span class=\"oblogtext\">increase</span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-hansi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">in</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><span class=\"oblogtext\">MS Lookback Adapter</span> <br /> <span class=\"oblogtext\">Windows</span></span> <span class=\"oblogtext\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">server can also be used as <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">RealServer,</span> the prerequisite is to install</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><span class=\"oblogtext\">MS Lookback <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">Adapter.</span></span> <br /></span> <span class=\"oblogtext\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">You can choose to add new hardware, add network adapters, select <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Microsoft,</span> select</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><span class=\"oblogtext\">Lookback <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">Adapter.</span></span> <br /></span> <span class=\"oblogtext\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">Then add the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">VIP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">(Virtual IP)</span> address of the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">MS Loopback Adapter</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">on</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><br /></span> <span class=\"oblogtext\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">Do not enter the gateway</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">gateway IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">address. However, in</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">MS NT/2K/XP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">subnet mask</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">255.255.255.255</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">will be considered invalid.</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><br /></span>e = <strong>&quot;2&quot;&gt;</strong> IXDBA.NET <strong>Technical Community</strong> <br /> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span class=\"oblogtext\">Can have the following solutions:</span></strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><br /></span> <span class=\"oblogtext\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">In</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">MS</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">NT/2K/XP,</span> the network interface <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">(interfaces)</span> in:</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><br /> <span class=\"oblogtext\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \\ System \\ CurrentControlSet \\ Services \\ Tcpip \\ Parameters \\ Interfaces</span> <br /></span> <span class=\"oblogtext\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">Find the appropriate network interface</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">address, subnet mask changes <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">subnetMask,</span> (note change mode)</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span class=\"oblogtext\">Do not need to reboot, just to re-activate the network interface.</span></span> </p>','Windows on the increase in MS Lookback AdapterWindows server can also be used as RealServer, the prerequisite is to install MS Lookback Adapter. You can choose to add new hardware, add network adapters, select Microsoft, select Lookback Adapter. Then add the VIP (Virtual IP) address of the MS...'),(310,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/97/2036.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Watchdog and Heartbeat in the use of Softdog','Watchdog_and_Heartbeat_in_the_use_of_Softdog','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Core has its own approach to suspend the system, called watchdog, watchdog is just a kernel module, it checks the timer to determine the system is healthy, if the watchdog that the kernel hangs, it may make a fierce response, such as restart the system, If you want to protect your high-availability server configuration, the server hangs when the cause service disruption, Heartbeat also not detected, you should be enabled in your kernel watchdog.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Note: Here we are discussing is not the application server hang problem, Heartbeat (Heartbeat 2 in the preparation of this book is not available the previous version) does not monitor the resources it controls or applications to see whether health - to Monitoring must use another software package, such as the Mon, will be discussed in detail in Part IV it.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Under normal circumstances, the watchdog device connected to the system allows the kernel to determine whether the system hangs (when the kernel can not see the external timer device properly updated, it appears that some mistake.)</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">software watchdog code also supports external hardware replacement timer, the software is called softdog, softdog maintain an internal timer, to write in another process / dev / watchdog device file is updated, if softdog do not see the process of writing / dev / watchdog file, it must be out of the kernel that will boot a kernel panic, under normal circumstances, the kernel panic will cause the system to shut down, but you can change this default behavior, default behavior is to change it to reboot the system.</font> </p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Watchdog is enabled in the kernel</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">To enable in the kernel watchdog, first you need to determine softdog module has been built into the kernel.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Note: In a normal Red Hat or SuSe distributions you do not need the watchdog to the kernel, because the standard release, including Red Hat kernel has been compiled softdog a copy of the module.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">If you compile the kernel from source, from / usr / src / linux directory, run makemenu config command, in the following sub-menu, check or enable the &quot;Software Watchdog&quot; option:</font> </p><table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" bordercolordark=\"#ffffff\" bordercolorlight=\"#000000\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"400\"><tbody><tr><td bgcolor=\"#e6e6e6\" class=\"code\"><pre> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Character DevicesÃ£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€Âcharacter device <br /> Watchdog Cards ---&gt; PlugÃ£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€Âwatchdog <br /> [*] Watchdog Timer SupportÃ£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€Âwatchdog timer support <br /> [M] Software Watchdog (NEW) Ã£Â€Âsoftware watchdog (new)Ã£Â€Â‘\r\n</font> </pre></td></tr></tbody></table><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">If this option is not in the kernel is selected, in accordance with Chapter 3 describes the steps to re-compile and install your new kernel, if you are using Red Hat kernel provides a standard module (or if you just compiled your own kernel, and enable the software watchdog support), enter the following command to determine whether the module is loaded the current running kernel:</font> </p><table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" bordercolordark=\"#ffffff\" bordercolorlight=\"#000000\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"400\"><tbody><tr><td bgcolor=\"#e6e6e6\" class=\"code\"><pre> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"># Insmod softdog <br /> # Lsmod\r\n</font> </pre></td></tr></tbody></table><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">You should see the list of softdog, under normal circumstances, if you / etc / ha.d / ha.cf watchdog support is enabled, Heartbeat switch (init) scripts for you to insert the module, if enabled, watchdog, Now you should remove it from the kernel and allow Heartbeat when it starts you to add, use the following command removed from the kernel softdog:</font> </p><table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" bordercolordark=\"#ffffff\" bordercolorlight=\"#000000\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"400\"><tbody><tr><td bgcolor=\"#e6e6e6\" class=\"code\"><pre> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"># Modprobe-r softdog</font> </pre></td></tr></tbody></table><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Kernel panic - hang or reboot?</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">When the kernel panic and not force the system to restart suspended, need to modify the startup parameters passed to the kernel in the use of LILO boot loader in the system, edit / etc / lilo.conf file, in the &quot;image =&quot; line before the increase in the following this line:</font> </p><table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" bordercolordark=\"#ffffff\" bordercolorlight=\"#000000\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"400\"><tbody><tr><td bgcolor=\"#e6e6e6\" class=\"code\"><pre> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">append = &quot;panic = 60&quot;\r\n</font> </pre></td></tr></tbody></table><p></p><p> <font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><strong>www.ixdba.net</strong></a></font> </p><br /><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Then run:</font> </p><table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" bordercolordark=\"#ffffff\" bordercolorlight=\"#000000\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"400\"><tbody><tr><td bgcolor=\"#e6e6e6\" class=\"code\"><pre> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"># Lilo-v</font> </pre></td></tr></tbody></table><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">You can also use the following command:</font> </p><table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" bordercolordark=\"#ffffff\" bordercolorlight=\"#000000\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"400\"><tbody><tr><td bgcolor=\"#e6e6e6\" class=\"code\"><pre> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"># Echo 60&gt; / proc / sys / kernel / panic</font> </pre></td></tr></tbody></table><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Configuring Heartbeat Support Watchdog</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Addition to that we have just described (as the server part of the normal configuration, the system hangs when upgrading its reliability) softdog timer outside, you can tell Heartbeat update softdog timer, which makes watchdog that Heartbeat is running and very healthy If the timer is not updated, watchdog will notify and enforce the kernel panic, in fact, we are told the watchdog observed Heartbeat.</font> </p>','Core has its own approach to suspend the system, called watchdog, watchdog is just a kernel module, it checks the timer to determine the system is healthy, if the watchdog that the kernel hangs, it may make a fierce response, such as restart the system, If you want to protect your high-availability...'),(311,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/b3/2029.html','http://www.ixdba.net','4 nginx configure load balancing strategy','4_nginx_configure_load_balancing_strategy','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The upstream nginx currently supports the allocation of 4 ways: <br /><br /> 1, the polling (default) <br /> Chronological order for each request individually assigned to different back-end server if out of the back-end server down, can be automatically rejected. <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2, weight <br /> Designated polling probability, weight, and access is proportional to the ratio for the back-end server performance uneven.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For example:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">upstream tomcats { <br /> server 10.1.1.107:88 <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-fareast-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA\">weight = 10;</span> <br /> server 10.1.1.132:80 <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-fareast-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA\">weight = 10;</span> <br /> } <br /> 3, ip_hash <br /> Ip each request to access the hash result by distribution, so that each visitor to access a back-end server fixed, can solve the problem session.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For example:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">upstream tomcats { <br /> ip_hash; <br /> server 10.1.1.107:88; <br /> server 10.1.1.132:80; <br /> }</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> 4, fair (third party) <br /> By the back-end server\'s response time allocation request, response time priority allocation. <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">5, url_hash (third party) <br /> Visit the url of the hash result by allocating the request, so that each url directed to the same back-end server, back-end server for the cache more effective.</font> </p>','The upstream nginx currently supports the allocation of 4 ways:  1, the polling (default)  Chronological order for each request individually assigned to different back-end server if out of the back-end server down, can be automatically rejected....'),(312,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/25/2024.html','http://www.ixdba.net','IPMI tools used to achieve remote management of servers','IPMI_tools_used_to_achieve_remote_management_of_servers','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For network administrators, the server remote management is a very important technology, and in the server remote management, the typical solution is based server operating system software management, but this approach has a fatal flaw lies in high dependence on the operating system, once the system problems would be powerless to affect the daily operation of the server. Today, as we would like to introduce a kind of operating system do not need to rely on remote management - based on Intelligent Platform Management Interface (IPMI), remote management. IPMI defines how administrators monitor system hardware and sensors, control system components and retrieve the log important system events to conduct remote management and recovery. Used that way, users do not need to worry about the state of the operating system, even if the system crashes can easily be machine status, important information such as system logs, but also to achieve the system reboot, shutdown control, very useful. Next, let us take a look at the use of IPMI it.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Understanding of IPMI</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">If you want to use IPMI, let us first come to know about this magical thing, too.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IPMI Intelligent Platform Management Interface is (Intelligent Platform Management Interface) the acronym is the management structure of the enterprise systems based on Intel in the use of peripheral devices used by an industry standard, the standard by Intel, HP, NEC, Dell and the U.S. SuperMicro and other companies to develop. Users can monitor the server using IPMI physical health characteristics, such as temperature, voltage, fan working status, power status. And more importantly, IPMI is an open free standards, users do not need to pay extra to use the standard cost.</font> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"DELL DRAC 5 Ã¨Â¿ÂœÃ§Â¨Â‹Ã¦ÂŽÂ§Ã¥ÂˆÂ¶Ã¥ÂÂ¡\" border=\"0\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/fd/fdceaab384a73047eb74e83a2019a011.jpg\" title=\"DELL DRAC 5 remote control card\" twffan=\"done\" /></font> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">DELL DRAC 5 remote control card</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Since 1998, IPMI IPMI standard forum created dependence, which has been the support of more than 170 suppliers, making it gradually become a complete coverage of servers and other systems (such as storage devices, networking and communications equipment) hardware management practices, present the latest version of the standard IPMI 2.0, the version based on the original with a lot of improvements, including through the serial port, Modem and Lan servers such as remote environmental management systems (including remote switching machine), as well as in security, VLAN and blade support, and so improved.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IPMI for a large number of monitoring, control and auto-reply server operations, providing intelligent management. This standard applies to a different server topology, as well as Windows, Linux, Solaris, Mac or mixed operating system. In addition, IPMI can operate under a different attribute values, even if the server itself is not working correctly, or for any reason unable to provide services, IPMI can still function properly. <br /> IPMI Works</font> </p><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IPMI is the core of a dedicated chip / controller (called the server processor or baseboard management controller (BMC)), it does not depend on the server processor, BIOS or operating system to work, can be described as very independent, is a separate running in the system agentless management subsystem, as long as BMC with IPMI firmware can begin its work, and BMC to install self-love is usually a separate server card on the motherboard, and now have server board provides IPMI support. Characteristics of good self IPMI will overcome the past management of the operating system-based restrictions, such as loading the operating system does not respond or the case can still switch their machines, information extraction and other operations.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">At work, all the IPMI functions are sending commands to the BMC to complete, the command specified using the IPMI specification instruction, BMC received and recorded in the system event log event messages, maintaining the situation described in the sensor system, sensor data records. When you need remote access system, IPMI LAN on the new Serial (SOL) feature is useful. SOL IPMI session to change the course of the direction of the local serial transmission, which provides emergency management services, Windows or Linux dedicated management console for remote access to serial console. BMC LAN through the serial port on the change in the information transmitted to the direction to do so, provides a vendor-independent remote viewing with the launch, the operating system loader or emergency management console to diagnose and repair faults in the standard way.</font> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"IPMIÃ¥ÂŽÂŸÃ§ÂÂ†\" border=\"0\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/f1/f1b62c5a8ec9c672b85e286938f193d5.gif\" title=\"IPMI principle\" twffan=\"done\" /></font> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Community Forums</a></font></strong> <br /><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IPMI Works</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The system text console when you need remote access, Serial Over LAN (SOL) feature is very useful. SOL IPMI session is redirected through the local serial interface that allows remote access to Windows, Emergency Management Console (EMS) Special Administration Console (SAC), or visit the LINUX serial console. This process step is to intercept data IPMI firmware, and then directed through the local area network to re-send the information to the serial port. This provides remote viewing BOOT, OS Loader or Emergency Management consoles to diagnose and fix the standard method of server-related issues, regardless of supplier. It allows the configuration of various components in the boot stage.</font> </p>','For network administrators, the server remote management is a very important technology, and in the server remote management, the typical solution is based server operating system software management, but this approach has a fatal flaw lies in high dependence on the operating system, once the system...'),(313,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/e9/2008.html','http://www.ixdba.net','linux Bonding technology to achieve','linux_Bonding_technology_to_achieve','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\">The Linux bonding Driver provides a method for aggregating multiple Logical Network Interfaces into a single <a class=\"extiw\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.com/wiki/Bonding\" title=\"wikipedia: Bonding\">bonded</a> interface. The behavior of the bonded Interfaces depends upon the mode; generally speaking, modes provide either STANDBY or load Balancing Services Hot. Additionally, Link Integrity Monitoring may be performed.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\">The bonding Driver originally came from <a class=\"extiw\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.com/wiki/Donald_Becker\" title=\"wikipedia: Donald_Becker\">Donald Becker\'s</a> <a class=\"extiw\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.com/wiki/Beowolf_cluster\" title=\"wikipedia: Beowolf_cluster\">Beowulf</a> patches for kernel 2.0. It has changed quite a bit since, and the Original tools from Linux and Beowulf sites Extreme-Will not work with this Version of the Driver.</span></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\">For new versions of the driver, updated userspace tools, and who to ask for help, please follow the links at the end of this file.</span></font> </p><p><table class=\"toc\" id=\"toc\" summary=\"Contents\"><tbody><tr><td><div id=\"toctitle\"><h2> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\">Contents</span></font> </h2> <span class=\"toctoggle\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\">[ <a class=\"internal\" href=\"javascript:toggleToc()\" id=\"togglelink\">hide</a> ]</span></font></span> </div><ul><li class=\"toclevel-1\"> <font color=\"#800080\"><a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Installation\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Installation</span></span></font></a></font> <ul><li class=\"toclevel-2\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Configure_and_build_the_kernel_with_bonding\"><font color=\"#800080\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Configure and build the kernel with bonding</span></span></font></font></a> </li><li class=\"toclevel-2\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Install_ifenslave_Control_Utility\"><font color=\"#800080\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Install ifenslave Control Utility</span></span></font></font></a> </li></ul></li><li class=\"toclevel-1\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Bonding_Driver_Options\"><font color=\"#800080\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bonding Driver Options</span></span></font></font></a> </li><li class=\"toclevel-1\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Configuring_Bonding_Devices\"><font color=\"#800080\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Configuring Bonding Devices</span></span></font></font></a> <ul><li class=\"toclevel-2\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Configuration_with_sysconfig_support\"><font color=\"#800080\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Configuration with sysconfig support</span></span></font></font></a> <ul><li class=\"toclevel-3\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Using_DHCP_with_sysconfig\"><font color=\"#800080\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Using DHCP with sysconfig</span></span></font></font></a> </li><li class=\"toclevel-3\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Configuring_Multiple_Bonds_with_sysconfig\"><font color=\"#800080\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Configuring Multiple Bonds with sysconfig</span></span></font></font></a> </li></ul></li><li class=\"toclevel-2\"> <a href=\"http://www.linuxfoundation.org/en/Net:Bonding#Configu