ancing_LVS_What_is_the_difference','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Hardware load balancers and load balancing LVS What is the difference?</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Answer:</font> </p><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Packet load balancing is a process of re-routing, the general equipment can do Layer 4 load balancing, the Layer 7 load balancing, you need to load the application on the server detected. 7 layer and 4 layers for input and gain perspective, think the 7 layers have little effect. F5 this stuff expensive, so stable, a hardware switch chips, so the throughput than the PC SERVER out of the LVS to do bigger, relative to the back-end servers, front-end load balancing the stability of the more important. A few years ago when F5 is not very popular, but also used the LVS, which we used in the ISP, are basically the F5.</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Answer:</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">lvs applicability of any support for the back-end server can run TCP / IP operating systems, including Linux, various Unix (such as FreeBSD, Sun Solaris, HP Unix, etc.), Mac / OS and Windows NT/2000 and so on. <br /> Load scheduler can support TCP and UDP protocols most: <br /><br /><br /> Agreement <br /> TCP HTTP, FTP, PROXY, SMTP, POP3, IMAP4, DNS, LDAP, HTTPS, SSMTP etc. <br /> UDP DNS, NTP, ICP, video, audio, streaming protocols such as the client and server without any changes, applicable to the majority of Internet services.</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Answer:</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Hardware load balancing performance is relatively good, and I believe that the protocol type of support will be more. But the price is very expensive. <br /><br /> For LVS, the performance will certainly be worse, and what protocol can not support. But victory in the price cheap. <br /><br /> F5 hardware aspects of the conditions I did not do it, but the software side of the LVS, I worked under RHEL5 DR and NAT, you can refer to http://www.redhat.com.cn/docs under <br /> linux cluster / gfs LVS inside the official configuration guide. That\'s what I do according to this, but I am very poor, not so much hardware. All to toss in a virtual machine.</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Answer:</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">F5 former FreeBSD, V9 Linux into the future <br /> NetScaler is a few days before FreeBSD someone to push the A10, F5 and NetScaler than is said to be good performance</font> </div></div><br style=\"CLEAR: both\" /></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Answer:</font> <div class=\"t_msgfont\" id=\"message6579876\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">I have done load balancing, is now running online, the complete set is so constructed. The front is a smart DNS, identification Telecom and China Netcom\'s IP, respectively, with the other lines specify a different field to their room, engine room began to collect the field data is two LVS servers, a backup, call the following SQUID server reverse proxy with SQUID following RealServer server. My QQ: 509447546,509302322, please contact me if want to give help! !</font> </div></div>','Hardware load balancers and load balancing LVS What is the...'),(323,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/ce/999.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Linux RAC OCFS file system and INOD','Linux_RAC_OCFS_file_system_and_INOD','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">ITPUB see in such a <a href=\"http://www.itpub.net/thread-902705-1-1.html\">case</a> , the RAC in a Linux environment, an OCFS volume inode node has been used, but the database still running. <br /> Files can be properly created, several of the system is broadly as follows: <br /></font> <blockquote> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">OS: LINUXAS3 U3 <br /> ORACLE: ORACLE9204 RAC <br /></font> </blockquote> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The following is the specific show, / U04 produce only two-node storage of archive log <br /></font> <blockquote> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">[Root @ db1 /] # cat / etc / issue <br /> Red Hat Enterprise Linux AS release 3 (Taroon Update 3) <br /><br /> [Root @ db1 /] # rpm-qa | grep ocfs <br /> ocfs-support-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-tools-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-2.4.21-EL-smp-1.0.13-1 <br /><br /> [Root @ db1 /] # df-h <br /> Filesystem Size Used Avail Use% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 50G 44M 50G 1% / u04 <br /><br /> [Root @ db1 /] # df-i <br /> Filesystem Inodes IUsed IFree IUse% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 409580 409231 349 100% / u04 <br /><br /></font> </blockquote> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Finally, the author found an explanation from Metalink, that OCFS file system and is usually different, inodes are not here to play the role of the file system normally. <br /> This is the characteristics of OCFS, it is normal. <br /><br /> References that explain the record as follows: <br /></font> <blockquote> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">@ OCFS does not have the concept of inodes, however, for the vfs layer in the <br /> @ Kernel we need to fill out structures. The number returned by df-i is <br /> @ Based on diskspace free. It\'s the number of clusterblocsk in the filesystem <br /> @ We dont \'preallocate inodes like most filesystems do. Nor do we HAVE to do <br /> @ That. Not a bug, expected behaviour, not required to do what any other <br /> @ Filesystem does. <br /></font> </blockquote>','empty\n'),(324,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/a1/1058.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Oracle10g R2 Installing RAC','Oracle10g_R2_Installing_RAC','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Installing Oracle10g R2 RAC <br /> Part1 <br /> - Prerequisites <br /> - Installing / Preparing Guest machine (SuSE10.1) <br /> Prerequisites <br /> This example shows how to install Oracle10g R2 RAC with raw devices (block devices), without using ocfs2 or asmlib, so no other modules need to be downloaded or installed before installing Oracle 10g R2 RAC. <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------ <br /> Hardware requirements: <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------ <br /> Dell PE2850 one <br /> CPU: Intel Xeon 3.6GHz ÃƒÂ— 2 <br /> Memory: 4GB <br /> Hard Drive: 40 -50 GB needed for vitural guests <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------- <br /> Host Operating system and software: <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------- <br /> OS: Windows Server 2003 Enterprise 5.2.3790 <br /> VM: VMWare GSX Server 3.2.1 build-19281 for windows <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------ <br /> Software requirements: <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------ <br /> Guest OS: SuSE Linux Enterprise 10.1 (4cd or 1DVD) <br /> Download Here: <a href=\"http://en.opensuse.org/Released_Version\">http://en.opensuse.org/Released_Version</a></font> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"> </font></p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">$ Uname-a <br /> Linux sles101 2.6.16.21-0.8-smp # 1 SMP Mon Jul 3 18:25:39 UTC 2006 i686 i686 i386 GNU / Linux <br /> DB: Oracle 10gR2 for x86 linux <br /> clusterware: <br /> <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/otn/linux/oracle10g/10201/10201_clusterware_linux32.zip\">http://download.oracle.com/otn/linux/oracle10g/10201/10201_clusterware_linux32.zip</a> <br /> database: <br /> <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/otn/linux/oracle10g/10201/10201_database_linux32.zip\">http://download.oracle.com/otn/linux/oracle10g/10201/10201_database_linux32.zip</a></font> <br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">-------------------------------------------------- ------------ <br /> Configuring VMWare virtual Networks: <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------ <br /> Start -&gt; Programs -&gt; VMware -&gt; VMware GSX Server -&gt; Manage Virtual Networks <br /> From Virtual Network Editor, Select Host Virtual Network Mapping: <br /> The public address is using &quot;Bridged&quot; mode to utilize the physical subnets (172.16.2.0/24, on same subnet with the host machine. <br /> VMnet1\'s subnet address is 192.168.235.0/24 (use &quot;host-only&quot; mode) - as private address for the 2 nodes. <br /> Installing / Preparing Guest machine (SuSE10.1) <br /> -------------------------------------------------- --------------------------- <br /> Creating Guest machine (SuSE10.1) in VMWare <br /> -------------------------------------------------- --------------------------- <br /> 1. Open VMware Virtual Machine Console <br /> 2. Click New Virtual Machine <br /> 3. Select the Appropriate Configuration: <br /> Select Custom, click [Next] <br /> 4.Select a Guest Operating System: <br /> Select Linux, Version SuSE Enterprise Linux, click [Next] <br /> 5.Name the Virtual Machine: <br /> SLES101, location d: \\ sles101, click [Next] <br /> 6.Set Access Rights: <br /> Use default, click [Next] <br /> 7.Startup / Shutdown Options: <br /> Use default, User that powers on the virtual machine, click [Next] <br /> 8.Memory for the Virtual Machine: <br /> 1024MB, click [Next] <br /> 9.Network Type: <br /> select Do not use a network connection, click [Next] (configure later) <br /> 10.Select I / O Adapter Types: <br /> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\">IXDBA.NET Technical Community</a></font></strong> <br /> select LSI Logic, Click [Next] <br /> 11.Select a Disk: <br /> select Create a new virtual disk, click [Next] <br /> 12.Select a Disk Type: <br /> select SCSI, click [Next] <br /> 13.Specify Disk Capacity: <br /> Enter 8GB, select Allocate all disk space now, deselect Split disk into 2GB files, <br /> click [Next] <br /> 14.Specify Disk File: <br /> d: \\ sles101 \\ system.vmdk, click [Finish] <br /> 15.Info: <br /> Creating pre-allocated virtual disk ... <br /> 16. Hardware Type: <br /> select Ethernet Adapter, click [Next] <br /> 17. Network Type: <br /> select Custom, select &quot;Bridged&quot;, Connect at power on, click [Finish] <br /> 18. Add one more NIC: <br /> click [Add] <br /> 19. Hardware Type: <br /> select Ethernet Adapter, click [Next] <br /> 20. Network Type: <br /> select Custom, &quot;Host-only&quot;, Connect at power on, click [Finish] <br /> 22. Exit VMware Virtual Machine Console: <br /> I will use the first node to clone the second node. <br /> -----------------------------</font>------------- <br /> Create additional disks: <br /> ------------------------------------------ <br /> 1. On Window Host machine, Open Command Prompt. <br /> 2. Change to GSX Installation directory, c: \\ program files \\ vmware \\ vmware gsx server: <br /> 3. Run DOS command to create OCR + CRS voting disks, <br /> vmware-vdiskmanager-c-s 500Mb-a lsilogic-t 2 d: \\ sles101 \\ ocr.vmdk <br /> vmware-vdiskmanager-c-s 500Mb-a lsilogic-t 2 d: \\ sles101 \\ css.vmdk <br /> [OCR and CSS partition could be on the same virtual disk, and you can also create mirror disk (1 for OCR, 2 for CSS) if neccessary, each OCR or CSS partition need&gt; 256MB disk space.] <br /><br /> 4. Create 1 Oracle product disk&gt; 4GB, used for local disk on both nodes <br /> vmware-vdiskmanager-c-s 4Gb-a lsilogic-t 2 d: \\ sles101 \\ u01.vmdk <br /> 5. Create 4 ASM disks for Oracle data &amp; flash recovery area: <br /> vmware-vdiskmanager-c-s 2Gb-a lsilogic-t 2 d: \\ sles101 \\ asm1.vmdk <br /> vmware-vdiskmanager-c-s 2Gb-a lsilogic-t 2 d: \\ sles101 \\ asm2.vmdk <br /> vmware-vdiskmanager-c-s 2Gb-a lsilogic-t 2 d: \\ sles101 \\ asm3.vmdk <br /> vmware-vdiskmanager-c-s 2Gb-a lsilogic-t 2 d: \\ sles101 \\ asm4.vmdk <br /> 6. Edit (do not use notepad) d: \\ sles101 \\ system.vmx and d: \\ sles102 \\ system.vmx (after cloned from sles101), add the following lines: <br /> scsi1.present = &quot;TRUE&quot; <br /> scsi1.virtualDev = &quot;lsilogic&quot; <br /> scsi1.sharedBus = &quot;virtual&quot; <br /> scsi1: 1.present = &quot;TRUE&quot; <br /> scsi1: 1.mode = &quot;independent-persistent&quot; <br /> scsi1: 1.filename = &quot;d: \\ sles101 \\ ocr.vmdk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 1.deviceType = &quot;plainDisk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 2.present = &quot;TRUE&quot; <br /> scsi1: 2.mode = &quot;independent-persistent&quot; <br /> scsi1: 2.filename = &quot;d: \\ sles101 \\ css.vmdk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 2.deviceType = &quot;plainDisk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 3. present = &quot;TRUE&quot; <br /> scsi1: 3.mode = &quot;independent-persistent&quot; <br /> scsi1: 3.filename = &quot;d: \\ sles101 \\ asm1.vmdk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 3.deviceType = &quot;plainDisk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 4. present = &quot;TRUE&quot; <br /> scsi1: 4.mode = &quot;independent-persistent&quot; <br /> scsi1: 4.filename = &quot;d: \\ sles101 \\ asm2.vmdk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 4.deviceType = &quot;plainDisk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 5.present = &quot;TRUE&quot; <br /> scsi1: 5.mode = &quot;independent-persistent&quot; <br /> scsi1: 5.filename = &quot;d: \\ sles101 \\ asm3.vmdk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 5.deviceType = &quot;plainDisk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 6.present = &quot;TRUE&quot; <br /> scsi1: 6.mode = &quot;independent-persistent&quot; <br /> scsi1: 6.filename = &quot;d: \\ sles101 \\ asm4.vmdk&quot; <br /> scsi1: 6.deviceType = &quot;plainDisk&quot; <br /> disk.locking = &quot;FALSE&quot; <br /> diskLib.dataCacheMaxSize = &quot;0&quot; <br /> diskLib.dataCacheMaxReadAheadSize = &quot;0&quot; <br /> diskLib.dataCacheMinReadAheadSize = &quot;0&quot; <br /> diskLib.dataCachePageSize = &quot;4096&quot; <br /> diskLib.maxUnsyncedWrites = &quot;0&quot; <br /> save and exit. </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">[If the vitual machines will be installed on VMWare ESX server, use &quot;LSI Logic&quot; for the SCSI Controller type. If you use &quot;Bus Logic&quot;, the drivers could not be loaded and no hard drive will be located for installation.] <br /><br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------ <br /> Install SuSE Linux 10.1 (sles) on first node <br /> -------------------------------------------------- ------------------ <br /> Please refer to the following Novell official website for the installation guide: <br /> Installing Oracle10g R2 Database on SLES10 for i386 - step by step <br /> Partition Settings <br /> For &quot;partitioning&quot; of the Installation Settings screen, create LVM partitions for &quot;/&quot;, &quot;/ tmp&quot;, swap, &quot;/ u01&quot; (the oracle product location). Create with this sequence: PV-&gt; VG-&gt; LV <br /> Create Physical Volume from raw partition (primary partition) first, then create new Volume Group and add Physical Volumes to the group, at last mount the Volume Group to the mounting points with format option. <br /> The reason to use LVM is that it is easy to extend the size in case not sufficient later. For example, the following results showed that the &quot;swap&quot; space was extended from 1GB up to 1.89GB by adding 2 partitions (/ dev/sdc1 and / dev/sdc2) to the first partition (/ dev/sda3) which are all in the VG &quot;swapvg&quot;.</font> </p>','Installing Oracle10g R2 RAC  Part1  - Prerequisites  - Installing / Preparing Guest machine (SuSE10.1)  Prerequisites  This example shows how to install Oracle10g R2 RAC with raw devices (block devices), without using ocfs2 or asmlib, so no other modules need to be downloaded or installed before...'),(325,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/b7/1210.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Linux Server Cluster System (lvs)','Linux_Server_Cluster_System_lvs','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">This article describes the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span> server cluster <span lang=\"EN-US\">DDLVS (Linux Virtual Server)</span> project background and objectives, and describes the framework and the <span lang=\"EN-US\">LVS</span> server cluster software is now available, lists the characteristics of <span lang=\"EN-US\">LVS</span> cluster system and some practical applications, and finally, the paper about the <span lang=\"EN-US\">LVS</span> project development progress and development of thoughts and feelings. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Ã‚Â </span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <strong><a name=\"1\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Background</span></a></strong> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: 1\"></span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Today\'s computer technology has entered a period of network-centric computing. As client <span lang=\"EN-US\">/</span> server model of simplicity, manageability and ease of maintenance, client <span lang=\"EN-US\">/</span> server computing model on the Internet is widely adopted. In the mid-nineties, the World Wide Web <span lang=\"EN-US\">(World Wide Web)</span> the emergence of its simple mode of operation will be illustrated on-line message to the general public, <span lang=\"EN-US\">Web</span> content is being sent from a mechanism as a service platform, a large number of services and applications ( such as news services, online banking, e-commerce, etc.) are conducted around the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Web.</span> This promotes growth of <span lang=\"EN-US\">Internet</span> users and <span lang=\"EN-US\">Internet</span> traffic dramatic explosion in growth.</span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">The rapid development of</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Internet</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">network bandwidth and server enormous challenges. From the perspective of the development of network technology, network bandwidth is much higher than the growth in processor speed and memory access rate of growth, such as the <span lang=\"EN-US\">100M Ethernet, ATM, Gigabit Ethernet</span> and other constantly <span lang=\"EN-US\">emerging,</span> 10Gigabit <span lang=\"EN-US\">Ethernet</span> is about to place in the dense wavelength division multiplexing backbone with <span lang=\"EN-US\">(DWDM)</span> will become the mainstream of broadband <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> technology <span lang=\"EN-US\">[2,3], Lucent</span> has introduced a fiber run <span lang=\"EN-US\">800Gigabit</span> the <span lang=\"EN-US\">WaveStar? OLS 800G</span> products <span lang=\"EN-US\">[4].</span> Therefore, we believe there will be more and more bottlenecks on the server side. Many studies have shown that <span lang=\"EN-US\">Gigabit Ethernet</span> server throughput makes it difficult to reach <span lang=\"EN-US\">1Gb / s</span> because the protocol stack <span lang=\"EN-US\">(TCP / IP)</span> and the operating system, inefficient, and inefficient processor, which requires the agreement approach operating system scheduling and handling of <span lang=\"EN-US\">IO</span> for more in-depth study. High-speed network, re-design the network on a single server service program is also an important issue. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p> <font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\"><strong>IXDBA.NET Community Forums</strong></a></font> <br /><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">The site will attract more popular unprecedented access to traffic, for example, according to <span lang=\"EN-US\">Yahoo\'s</span> press release, <span lang=\"EN-US\">Yahoo</span> has sent <span lang=\"EN-US\">625</span> million pages per day <span lang=\"EN-US\">[5].</span> Network Services also received a large number of the flow, such as <span lang=\"EN-US\">American Online\'s Web Cache</span> system handled <span lang=\"EN-US\">5.02</span> billion daily <span lang=\"EN-US\">Web</span> requests for user access, the average response to each request length <span lang=\"EN-US\">5.5Kbytes.</span> At the same time, many network services as the number of visits to the explosive growth overwhelmed and can not handle user\'s request, causing users to wait a long time, greatly reducing the quality of service. How to build scalable network services to meet the growing load demand has become a pressing issue. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"><html> 0pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt &quot;&gt; Most sites are required to provide <span lang=\"EN-US\">24</span> hours a day service <span lang=\"EN-US\">7</span> days a week, especially on e-commerce website and any service interruptions and critical data loss will cause direct loss of business. For example, according to <span lang=\"EN-US\">Dell\'s</span> press release <span lang=\"EN-US\">[6], Dell</span> is now on the site each day trading income for the fourteen million U.S. dollars, a one-hour service outage will result in the loss of an average of five hundred and eighty thousand U.S. dollars. So, that the reliability of network services higher and higher requirements. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Web</span> services is the increasing use of <span lang=\"EN-US\">CGI,</span> dynamic home page, <span lang=\"EN-US\">CPU-intensive</span> applications, which have higher performance on the server requirements. Future network services will provide richer content and better interaction, better security and so on, requires a server with more <span lang=\"EN-US\">CPU</span> and <span lang=\"EN-US\">I / O</span> processing capabilities. For example, by <span lang=\"EN-US\">HTTPS (Secure HTTP)</span> to take a static page than the processing performance required by an order of magnitude <span lang=\"EN-US\">high-HTTP, HTTPS</span> is being widely used e-commerce site. Therefore, the network traffic and can not explain all the problems, taking into account the development needs of the application itself more and more powerful processing performance. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Therefore, the hardware and software methods used to achieve highly scalable, highly available network services to the growing demand, this demand can be attributed to the following: <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l6 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Scalability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Scalability),</span> when the service load growth, the system can be expanded to meet demand, and does not reduce the quality of service. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l6 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">High Availability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Availability),</span> though some of the hardware and software malfunction, the entire system of service must be <span lang=\"EN-US\">24</span> hours a day <span lang=\"EN-US\">7</span> days a week available. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l6 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Manageability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Manageability),</span> the system may be physically large, but it should be easy to manage. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Price validity <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Cost-effectiveness),</span> the system implementation is economical, easy to pay. <a name=\"2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></a></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: 2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </p>T: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan &quot;&gt; <span style=\"mso-bookmark: 2\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong><span style=\"mso-bookmark: 2\">Server Cluster System</span></strong></span> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: 2\"></span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Symmetric multiprocessing <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Symmetric Multi-Processor,</span> referred to as <span lang=\"EN-US\">SMP)</span> by a number of symmetrical processors, and shared memory through the bus and <span lang=\"EN-US\">I / O</span> components consisting of a computer system. <span lang=\"EN-US\">SMP</span> is a low degree of parallelism of the structure, is commonly referred to as <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;tightly</span> coupled multi-processing <span lang=\"EN-US\">system&quot;,</span> and its scalability is limited, but the advantages of a single <span lang=\"EN-US\">SMP</span> system images <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Single System Image),</span> a shared memory and <span lang=\"EN-US\">I / O,</span> and easy programming. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Because the limited capacity of <span lang=\"EN-US\">SMP</span> scalability, <span lang=\"EN-US\">SMP</span> server obviously does not meet the highly scalable, highly available network services in the growing demand for load handling capacity. With the increasing load will cause the server to continually upgrade. The server upgrade has the following disadvantages: First, complicated upgrade process, the machine will switch the temporary suspension, and result in waste of existing computing resources; the second is more to the high-end server, the greater the price to pay; third <span lang=\"EN-US\">SMP</span> server a single point of failure <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Single Point of Failure),</span> once the server or application software failure, will lead the service interruption. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">High-performance local area network or Internet through the server cluster is a high scalable, highly available network services, effective structure. The loosely coupled structure of the server cluster system has the following advantages: <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Performance <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> Workloads for network services is usually a large number of independent tasks, by a group of servers to divide and rule, can achieve high overall performance. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Performance <span lang=\"EN-US\">/</span> price ratio <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /> PC</span> cluster system composed of servers, or <span lang=\"EN-US\">RISC</span> servers and standard network equipment for mass production to reduce costs, low prices, with the highest performance <span lang=\"EN-US\">/</span> price ratio. If the overall performance of the growth nodes with near linear increase, the system performance <span lang=\"EN-US\">/</span> price ratio closer to <span lang=\"EN-US\">PC</span> servers. Therefore, this loosely coupled structure than the tightly coupled multi-processor system has better performance <span lang=\"EN-US\">/</span> price ratio. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">*</span></span> </spa<html> n&gt; <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Scalability <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> Nodes in the cluster number can grow to thousands, even tens of thousands, and its scalability is far more than a single supercomputer. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">High Availability <span lang=\"EN-US\"><br /></span> Both in hardware and software redundancy, by detecting the hardware and software failures, the fault mask, by the surviving nodes to provide services for high availability. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Of course, with a server cluster system to achieve scalable network services, there are many challenging tasks: <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l4 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Transparency <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Transparency) <br /></span> How to efficiently make multiple independent computer cluster composed of loose coupling system constitutes a virtual server; client applications interact with the cluster system, like with a high-performance, highly available server interaction, the client need not any changes. Some servers will not be interrupted cut and cut services, which is transparent to the user. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l4 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Performance <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Performance) <br /></span> Performance to be close to linear speedup, which requires well-designed hardware and software architecture, eliminate bottlenecks that may exist in the system. Scheduling will be more balanced load to each server. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l4 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">High Availability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Availability) <br /></span> Need to design and implement a good system resources and fault monitoring and handling systems. When they find a module fails, this module to migrate the services provided to other modules. In the ideal case, this migration is immediate and automatic. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l4 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Manageability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Manageability) <br /></span> For cluster systems have become easy to manage, like management system as a single image. In the ideal case, the hardware and software modules can be inserted into plug <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Plug &amp; Play).</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"><html> SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt &quot;&gt; programmable <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Programmability) <br /></span> In the cluster system, easy to develop applications. <a name=\"3\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></a> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: 3\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <strong><span style=\"mso-bookmark: 3\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Linux Virtual Server</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Project</span></span></strong> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: 3\"></span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">For highly scalable, highly available network services needs, we give the <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP-based</span> distribution layer and content-based load balancing scheduling request solution, and in the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span> kernel implements these methods to form a realization of a scalable server , and highly available network services virtual server. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Virtual server architecture shown in Figure <span lang=\"EN-US\">2,</span> a group of servers through high-speed LAN or WAN geographical distribution of interconnected at their front end has a load scheduler <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Load Balancer).</span> Load scheduler can request scheduling the network seamlessly to the real server, which makes the structure of the server cluster is transparent to customers, clients access the cluster system to provide network services like access to a high-performance, highly available server. Client from the server of the cluster without any changes. Scalability of the system in the service cluster by transparently adding and deleting a node to achieve, by detecting node or service process failures and properly reset the system to achieve high availability. Because of our load scheduling technology is implemented in the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span> kernel, which we call <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span> Virtual Server <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Linux Virtual Server).</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> <a name=\"N100E6\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>Figure <span lang=\"EN-US\">2:</span> Structure of the virtual server</strong></span></a> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: N100E6\"></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">In May <span lang=\"EN-US\">1998,</span> I set up a <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux Virtual Server</span> for free software projects, the development of <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span> server clusters. Meanwhile, <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux Virtual Server</span> Project is the first appearance of free software projects. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Linux Virtual Server</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">project aims: to use cluster technology and <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span> operating systems to achieve a high-performance, high availability servers, it has very good scalability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Scalability),</span> reliability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Reliability)</span> and manageability <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Manageability).</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"><html> bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt &quot;&gt; Currently, <span lang=\"EN-US\">LVS</span> project has provided a scalable network services implementation <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux Virtual Server</span> framework, shown in Figure <span lang=\"EN-US\">3.</span> in the <span lang=\"EN-US\">LVS</span> framework, provided with three kinds of <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> load balancing technology, <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> virtual server software <span lang=\"EN-US\">IPVS,</span> content-based request distribution of the core <span lang=\"EN-US\">Layer-7</span> switch <span lang=\"EN-US\">KTCPVS</span> and cluster management software. <span lang=\"EN-US\">LVS</span> framework can be used to achieve highly scalable, highly available <span lang=\"EN-US\">Web, Cache, Mail,</span> and <span lang=\"EN-US\">Media,</span> etc. network services; on this basis, can be developed to support a large number of users, highly scalable, highly available e-commerce applications. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /><br /></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <strong><a name=\"N1010B\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">3.1 IP</span></a> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: N1010B\">virtual server software <span lang=\"EN-US\">IPVS</span></span></span></strong> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: N1010B\"></span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Implementation of the scheduler technology, <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> load balancing technology is the most efficient. In the existing <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> load balancing technology with network address translation <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Network Address Translation)</span> to a group of servers to form a high-performance, highly available virtual servers, which we call <span lang=\"EN-US\">VS / NAT</span> technologies <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Virtual Server via Network Address Translation</span> ), most of the commercialization of <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> load balancing scheduler products are using this method, such as <span lang=\"EN-US\">Cisco\'s LocalDirector, F5\'s Big / IP,</span> and <span lang=\"EN-US\">Alteon\'s ACEDirector.</span> In the analysis of <span lang=\"EN-US\">VS / NAT</span> shortcomings and network services on the basis of non-symmetry, we propose a virtual server via <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> tunneling approach <span lang=\"EN-US\">VS / TUN (Virtual Server via IP Tunneling),</span> and the virtual server via direct routing method of <span lang=\"EN-US\">VS / DR (Virtual Server via Direct Routing),</span> which can greatly improve system scalability. Therefore, <span lang=\"EN-US\">IPVS</span> software <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> load balancing of these three technologies, they generally works as follows (we will work in other chapters of their detailed description of principle), <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">1. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Virtual Server via Network Address Translation</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(VS / NAT)</span></span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Network address translation, packet scheduler rewrite the destination address of the request, according to the default scheduling algorithm, the request to be assigned to the real back-end server; the real server\'s response message through the scheduler, the packet source address is rewritten , and then returned to the client to complete the whole load scheduling process. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"><html> Ignore &quot;&gt; 2. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> <strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Virtual Server via IP Tunneling</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">(VS / TUN)</span></span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Using <span lang=\"EN-US\">NAT</span> technology, the request and response packets through the scheduler must address rewriting, when the client requests rises, the scheduler\'s processing capacity will become a bottleneck. To solve this problem, the scheduler via the <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> tunnel request message forwarded to the real server, and the real server will respond directly back to the customer, so the scheduler only processes the request message. Because most Internet service response much larger than the request message, using <span lang=\"EN-US\">VS / TUN</span> technology, the cluster system can increase the maximum throughput of <span lang=\"EN-US\">10</span> times. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">3. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Virtual Server via Direct Routing</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">(VS / DR)</span></span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /> VS / DR</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">packet by rewriting the <span lang=\"EN-US\">MAC</span> address of the request, the request is sent to the real server, and the real server will respond directly back to the customer. With <span lang=\"EN-US\">VS / TUN</span> techniques like, <span lang=\"EN-US\">VS / DR</span> technology can greatly improve the scalability of cluster system. This method does not <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> tunneling overhead, the real server on the cluster and no <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> tunneling protocol must support the request, but requires the scheduler and the real server has a network card connected to the same physical network segment. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Demand for different network services and server configuration, <span lang=\"EN-US\">IPVS</span> scheduler to achieve the following eight load scheduling algorithms: <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">1. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>Round-robin <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Round Robin)</span></strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Scheduler through the <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;round-robin&quot;</span> scheduling algorithm in order to turn the external requests assigned to the real server in the cluster, which equally treat each server, regardless of the actual number of connections on the server and system load. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">2. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>Weighted round-robin <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Weighted Round Robin)</span></strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span><html> = &quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt&quot;&gt; scheduler through the <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;weighted</span> round-robin <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;scheduling</span> algorithm based on the real server to schedule the different processing access requests. This will ensure a strong capacity to handle more traffic to the server. Real scheduler queries the server can automatically load and dynamically adjust their weights. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">3. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>At least link <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Least Connections)</span></strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Scheduler through the <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;least connected&quot;</span> scheduling algorithm to dynamically schedule the network request to have the least number of links created on the server. If the real server cluster have similar performance, the <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;minimum connection&quot;</span> scheduling algorithm can better balance the load. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">4. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>Weighted minimum link <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Weighted Least Connections)</span></strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">In the cluster system quite different in the case of server performance, the scheduler uses <span lang=\"EN-US\">the &quot;weighted</span> minimum <span lang=\"EN-US\">link&quot;</span> scheduling algorithm to optimize load balancing performance, with higher weight server will bear a large proportion of the activities of connected load. Real scheduler queries the server can automatically load and dynamically adjust their weights. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">5. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>Based on at least a partial link <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Locality-Based Least Connections)</span></strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">&quot;Based</span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">on at least a partial link <span lang=\"EN-US\">to&quot;</span> scheduling algorithm is for the target <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address load balancing, the key for the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Cache</span> Cluster. The algorithm based on the <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address of the requested target <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address of the target to find the most recently used server, if the server is available and there is no overloading, the request is sent to the server; if the server does not exist, or the server is overloaded and there are servers in the half workload, the use of <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;at</span> least <span lang=\"EN-US\">link&quot;</span> principle, elected one of the available server, the request is sent to the server. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">6. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>With at least copy the link based on locality <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Locality-Based Least Connections with Replication)</span></strong></span><html> ly: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt &quot;&gt;&quot; <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">with a copy of at least based on partial link <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;scheduling</span> algorithm is also the target <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address for load balancing, the key for the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Cache</span> Cluster. It <span lang=\"EN-US\">LBLC</span> the difference between the algorithm is it to maintain a target from a group of servers <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address to map, and <span lang=\"EN-US\">LBLC</span> algorithm to maintain a target from the <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address to a server mapping. The algorithm, upon request, to find the target <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address corresponding to the target server group by <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;minimum connection&quot;</span> principle selected from the server a server group, if the server is not overloaded, the request is sent to the server, if the server is overloaded; press the <span lang=\"EN-US\">&quot;minimum connection&quot;</span> principle selected from this cluster one server, the servers into a server group, the request is sent to the server. Meanwhile, when the server group has not been modified over time, will be the most busy server group deleted from the server to reduce the extent of replication. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">7. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <strong><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Destination address hash <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Destination Hashing)</span></span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">&quot;Destination</span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">address <span lang=\"EN-US\">hash&quot;</span> scheduling algorithm based on the requested target <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address as the hash key <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Hash Key)</span> static allocation of the hash table from the corresponding server to find out if the server is available and not overloaded, the request is sent to the server, otherwise returns null. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">8. <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <strong><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Source address hashing <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Source Hashing)</span></span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">&quot;Source</span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">address <span lang=\"EN-US\">hashing,&quot;</span> Scheduling algorithm based on the source <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address of the request, as the hash key <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Hash Key)</span> static allocation of the hash table from the corresponding server to find out if the server is available and not overloaded, the request is sent to the server, otherwise returns null. <span lang=\"EN-US\"> </span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <strong><a name=\"N10196\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">3.2</span></a> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: N10196\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Kernel <span lang=\"EN-US\">Layer-7</span> switch <span lang=\"EN-US\">KTCPVS</span></span></span></strong> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: N10196\"></span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"></span></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Load dispatch based on <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> technology, a <span lang=\"EN-US\">TCP</span> connection when the initial <span lang=\"EN-US\">SYN</span> packet arrives, the scheduler to select a server forwards the packet to it. After the text by checking the transmitter and the <span lang=\"EN-US\">TCP</span> header <span lang=\"EN-US\">IP</span> address, to ensure that subsequent packets for this connection is forwarded to the server. This, <span lang=\"EN-US\">IPVS</span> can not check the contents of the request and then select the server, which requires back-end server group to provide the same service, regardless of which server the request is sent to return the same result. However, in some applications, different back-end server features, and some provide <span lang=\"EN-US\">HTML</span> documents, and some provide pictures, and some provide <span lang=\"EN-US\">CGI,</span> which requires content-based scheduling <span lang=\"EN-US\">(Content-Based Scheduling).</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><html> 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan &quot;&gt; <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">the user space <span lang=\"EN-US\">TCP Gateway\'s</span> overhead is too large, we propose in the operating system implemented in the kernel <span lang=\"EN-US\">Layer-7</span> switching method, to avoid the user space and kernel space switching and memory copying overhead. in the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Linux</span> operating system kernel, we realized the <span lang=\"EN-US\">Layer-7</span> switching, called <span lang=\"EN-US\">KTCPVS (Kernel TCP Virtual Server)</span> . At <span lang=\"EN-US\">present,</span> KTCPVS <span lang=\"EN-US\">HTTP</span> requests have been able to content-based scheduling, but it is not very mature in its scheduling algorithms and features support various protocols, there were a lot of work to be done. <span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Although the application layer exchange complex, and its scalability is limited, but the application layer switching provides the following benefits: <a name=\"4\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"></span></a></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list 36.0pt\"> <span style=\"mso-bookmark: 4\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol\">* <span style=\"FONT: 7pt \"Times New Roman\"\">Ã‚Â  </span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">The same page request is sent to the same server, you can improve a single server\'s</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Cache</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; ms