run different types of services, such as document services, photo services,</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">CGI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">services and database services.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"></span></span> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 20.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <strong><span style=\"mso-bookmark: 4\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">Ã‚Â </span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Characteristics of</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-','This article describes the Linux server cluster DDLVS (Linux Virtual Server) project background and objectives, and describes the framework and the LVS server cluster software is now available, lists the characteristics of LVS cluster system and some practical applications, and finally, the paper...'),(326,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/02/1211.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Linux file system on the storage technology architecture','Linux_file_system_on_the_storage_technology_architecture','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <a name=\"N10040\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong><span class=\"atitle2\">I. Introduction</span></strong></font> <br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Host high-performance computing has been the traditional way of gradually evolving to the cluster approach, such as the TOP500 in 1998, only 2 sets of systems are clustered, rather than 208 units in 2003 for the cluster. With the development of high performance computing architecture changes, the traditional host-based storage architecture has become the new bottleneck, the system can not meet the needs of the cluster. Clustered storage system must solve two major problems: (1) to provide shared access to data, ease of preparation of the application cluster and storage load balancing; (2) to provide high-performance storage, the I / O-level and data throughput Hundreds of units to meet the terms of the scale Linux cluster servers aggregate demand access. Currently, network storage has become a high-performance storage cluster system to solve the effective technical approach.</font></a> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">There are two major international network storage architecture, they are the commands to distinguish the difference. The first is SAN (Storage Area Network) structure, it uses SCSI block I / O command set, through the disk or FC (Fiber Channel) provides high performance data access class random I / O and data throughput, it high bandwidth, low latency advantages in high-performance computing in a place, such as SGI\'s CXFS SAN file system is based on high performance file storage, but due to the higher price of SAN systems, and poor scalability, has CPU does not meet the scale of tens of thousands of systems. The second category is NAS (Network Attached Storage) structure, it uses NFS or CIFS command set to access data to file transfer protocol, through the TCP / IP networked storage, scalability, and the prices are cheap, easy to manage users, such as At present the application of cluster computing more NFS file system, but because of the high cost of NAS protocols, low-bandwidth, delay, it is not conducive to high-performance cluster applications.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Linux clusters for high-performance storage systems and data sharing needs, has begun to study abroad, a new storage architecture and a new file system, hoping to effectively combine the advantages of SAN and NAS systems to support direct access to disk to improve performance by sharing documents and metadata to simplify the management, the current object storage file system has become a high-performance Linux cluster file system, the research focus, such as Cluster File Systems\'s Lustre, Panasas\'s ActiveScale file system. Lustre file system using object-based storage technology, which comes from the Coda project at Carnegie Mellon University study, released in December 2003 Lustre 1.0 version, expected in 2005 will release version 2.0. Lustre in the United States Department of Energy (USDepartment of Energy: DOE), Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory, Los Alamos National Laboratory, Sandia National Laboratory, Pacific Northwest National Laboratory\'s high-performance computing system applications have been initially, IBM is developed the Blue Gene system will also be used to achieve its high performance Lustre file system storage. ActiveScale file system technology from Carnegie Mellon University Dr. Garth Gibson, was first supported by the DARPA NASD (Network Attached Secure Disks) project, is already the industry\'s more influential object storage file system, was awarded the ComputerWorld 2004 Innovative Technology Award.</font> </p><p> <a name=\"N1004F\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong><span class=\"atitle2\">Second, the object storage file system</span></strong></font> <br /></a> </p><p> <a name=\"N10055\"><span class=\"atitle3\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2.1 The object storage file system architecture</font></span> <br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Object storage file system is the core of the data access (data read or write) and the control channel (metadata) separation, and object-based storage devices (Object-based Storage Device, OSD) build storage systems, storage devices, each object has a certain intelligent, able to automatically manage the data on the distribution of object storage file system usually has the following components.</font></a> </p><p> <strong xmlns:dw=\"http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">1 object</font></font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">System object is the basic unit of data storage, an object is actually a set of file data and a combination of attributes, these attributes can be defined file-based RAID parameters, data distribution and quality of service, using the traditional file storage system or block as the basic unit of storage in the block storage systems also need to always follow the system the attributes of each block, objects communicate with the storage system to protect their property. In the storage device, all objects have an object identified by object identifier to access the OSD command object. There are many types of objects are usually stored on the device\'s root object identifier storage device and the device\'s various properties of objects is shared storage resource management strategies on the collection of objects and so on.</font> </p><p> <a name=\"N10067\"><span class=\"atitle3\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2, object storage devices</font></span> <br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Object storage devices have some intelligence, it has its own CPU, memory, network and disk systems, the current international structure commonly used blade storage devices to achieve the object. OSD provides three main functions:</font></a> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(1) data storage. OSD object data management, and place them in the standard disk system, OSD does not provide block interface access method, Client requests for data, the object ID, offset data read and write.</font> </p>','I. IntroductionHost high-performance computing has been the traditional way of gradually evolving to the cluster approach, such as the TOP500 in 1998, only 2 sets of systems are clustered, rather than 208 units in 2003 for the cluster. With the development of high performance computing architecture...'),(327,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/00/1209.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Introduction to linux cluster file system used','Introduction_to_linux_cluster_file_system_used','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<span class=\"parahead1\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Application procedures for the cluster</font></font></span> <p></p> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Cluster applications with a variety of levels of maturity and functionality. They include:</font></font></span> <ul><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><em>High Performance</em> Cluster, also known as parallel computing cluster or clusters, usually for those who support a large number of computing systems. In these clusters, parallel file system, allocation of processing resources between the nodes, thus allowing concurrent read and write by each node to access the same file simultaneously. NASA developed in the early nineties of the twentieth century\'s Beowulf Linux cluster is the most common example.</font></font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><em>High Availability</em> (HA) cluster specifically designed for fault tolerance or redundancy. Because these clusters typically use one or more servers for processing, so when one or more server downtime, these servers can take on other servers handling duties.</font></font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Cluster <em>load balancing</em> or <em>load balancing</em> across multiple servers (usually web servers) distributed as evenly as possible between the load.</font></font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">SAN <em>storage</em> cluster for different operating systems and servers, providing common data storage medium block of shared access.</font></font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Oracle RAC <em>database</em> cluster will be as a platform to introduce many cluster file system features into the application itself.</font></font> </li></ul> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">The application of these clusters have overlapping features, one or more of the characteristics usually clustered in a single application can be found - especially in the HA and load balancing cluster. For example, Oracle RAC can be installed in the HA cluster file system, which will introduce the advantages of HA database cluster cluster applications, such as:</font></font></span> <ul><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Sharing resources - including data, memory, hard disk and metadata - so that multiple nodes look like a single file system. They allow both read and write to all members of the cluster file system.</font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Collection of the storage devices into a single disk volume, thus no need for data replication for improved performance</font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Scalable capacity, bandwidth and connectivity</font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Single system image, providing the same for all nodes in the data view.</font> </li></ul> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Now let\'s look at some of the support can be used with Oracle RAC and Linux cluster-aware file system, and how they improve the function of Oracle RAC.</font></font></span> <p></p> <span class=\"parahead1\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">You can run Oracle\'s Cluster File System</font></font></span> <p></p> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Oracle RAC technology has provided, such as load balancing, redundancy, failover, scalability, cache and lock and other features, so when the Oracle data files are located in the traditional Linux file systems (such as ext2/ext3) when the block device there will be duplication of function. In this case, reduced performance, because Oracle and file system cache consumes memory resources.</font></font></span> <p> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">To write this article so far, in addition to third-party cluster file system, there are four kinds of optional file system running Oracle RAC. Recommended by Oracle in order, they were:</font></font></span> </p><ol><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle Automatic Storage Management</font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle Cluster File System</font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Network File System</font> </li><li class=\"bodycopy\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Original equipment.</font> </li></ol> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><strong>Oracle Automatic Storage Management (ASM)</strong> Oracle is a feature, no matter what environment it is running, once you get an Oracle API, then all the appearance, experience and operations are the same. Oracle ASM, Oracle Database 10 <em>g</em> of a feature that will extend this line to the storage management environment, using SQL statements, Oracle Enterprise Manager Grid Control or Database Configuration Assistant program to create and manage store content and metadata. The ASM for Oracle Database 10 <em>g</em> data file storage is considered to be the best method.</font></font></span> <p></p> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">The basic data structure in ASM is the disk group, which consists of one or more disks. In this context, the &quot;disk&quot; can be a disk partition, an entire disk, a cascade disk partition or a storage device a complete storage device.</font></font></span> <p> <font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://bbs.ixdba.net\"><strong>IXDBA.NET Community Forums</strong></a></font> <br /> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Must understand that, ASM is not a general-purpose cluster file systems. In contrast, ASM is a cluster aware file system designed to handle Oracle database files, control files and log files and design. ASM should not logical volume manager (LVM) shared, because the latter make the ASM does not recognize the disk.</font></font></span> </p><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">ASM performs the following functions:</font></font></span> <ul><li> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Through the disk head in the ASM ID identification disk.</font></font></span> </li><li> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">In the disk group, dynamically allocated among all the memory data, with optional redundant protection, and has a cluster-aware.</font></font></span> </li><li> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Allows the Oracle database is fully operational state, the primary storage operation - no downtime can add, delete, or move to a new disk storage array group (although rare)</font></font></span> </li><li> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">When you add or remove disk, automatic load balancing and re-balancing</font></font></span> </li><li> <span class=\"bodycopy\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Through the use of failure groups, providing additional redundancy protection</font></font></span> </li></ul>','empty\n'),(328,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/f9/1192.html','http://www.ixdba.net','How to choose the two machines and clustering software','How_to_choose_the_two_machines_and_clustering_software','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This said, the two machines and clustering software, all that needs to write the data situation, such as databases. If only the application server, you should choose load balancing software.</font> </p><p> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><strong>SCO UNIX:</strong> Only LanderCluster support.</font></font> </p><p align=\"left\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">LanderCluster For Windows2000 is a high availability cluster software package, currently supported operating system Windows2000, Windows2003, Linux, SCO OpenServer/UnixWare7 environments.</font> </p><p align=\"left\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In this system, each host runs its own applications, user data stored in the shared storage subsystem. LanderCluster EtherNet monitoring daemon by running the whole cluster. By the PC server, shared cluster disk array subsystem and LanderCluster high availability software package composed of an effective cluster system.</font> </p><p align=\"left\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">LanderCluster products into LanderCluster-DN and LanderCluster-MN:</font> </p><ul><li> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">LanderCluster-DN Dual high availability products: a cluster Products LanderCluster the mainstream products. Support Windows / Linux / SCO Unix operating systems platform, a stable, reliable, easy to manage, open and strong, cost-effective features, while supporting multiple languages, support for remote management and other functions, is necessary for you to build highly available environment, selection.</font> </li></ul><ul><li> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">LanderCluster-MN multi-node cluster products: a LanderCluster cluster flagship product line. Support more than two node cluster environment to support Windows Server / Linux / SCO Unix operating systems platform, a stable, reliable, easy to manage, flexible and diverse redundancy, scalability strong nodes and the task to protect user investment, integration and optimization user\'s system environment, support including ISCSI storage environment and so on. The product can support more than eight node cluster environment.</font> </li></ul><p> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><strong>SUN Solaris:</strong> Only PCL support</font></font> </p><div align=\"left\"><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">PrimeCluster HA (PCL HA) is a German Fujitsu - Siemens Computers (Fujitsu-Siemens Computers) provides industry-leading support hot standby and high availability multi-node cluster management software.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">PCL HA is a high-availability applications and systems (High Availability) Manager. It is critical business applications and related resources can continue to provide access to the platform. PCL HA can be any type of applications, services or data to provide the most versatile high-availability environment. The main advantage of automatic identification system failures and component failures, and has a resume or application, such as a transparent local failover (Failover) and other appropriate restoration measures. PCL HA failover capabilities with multi-direction - any node within the cluster can take over the function of other nodes. If a particular server fails, it runs the rest of the application will be allocated to the normal operation of the server, allowing administrators the flexibility of resources and effective application system. Through management intervention as applied to other servers, allowing uninterrupted operation in the case of the expansion of the cluster.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">PCL HA for Linux with the rest of the market based on open source software 