t> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"> </font></li><li> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Disk array-based counters, multiple servers, the choice of including: LanderCluster, LifeKeeper</font> </li></ul><ul><li> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Disk array-based cabinet, two servers: Almost all products are supported, including, <a class=\"Ã§ÂÂ°Ã¨Â‰Â²Ã¦Â Â‡Ã¦Â³Â¨\" href=\"http://www.ha999.com/roseha/roseha.htm\">ROSE HA</a> reasonable price, but to prevent non-formal channels for products to buy; <a class=\"Ã§ÂÂ°Ã¨Â‰Â²Ã¦Â Â‡Ã¦Â³Â¨\" href=\"http://stor.51cto.com/art/200609/32301.htm\">LifeKeeper</a> more expensive (because of its price and the pure soft-mode, multi-point version no difference), there is no local support; <a class=\"Ã§ÂÂ°Ã¨Â‰Â²Ã¦Â Â‡Ã¦Â³Â¨\" href=\"http://stor.51cto.com/art/200609/32288.htm\">LanderCluster</a></font> </li></ul></ul>','This said, the two machines and clustering software, all that needs to write the data situation, such as databases. If only the application server, you should choose load balancing...'),(329,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/e6/1193.html','http://www.ixdba.net','LifeKeeper Software','LifeKeeper_Software','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SteelEye\'s LifeKeeper the United States is supporting a variety of soft (WindowNT, Windows2000, various Linux, etc.), high-performance fault-tolerant hardware platform, software can support up to 16 servers clustered. Lifekeeper software from NCR Corporation and the leading U.S. AT &amp; T Bell Labs. For enterprises, banks and government information services, business services, government services, providing high availability solutions.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">LifeKeeper high availability fault-tolerant cluster software is running on NT, Windows 2000, Linux and NCR Unix platforms. Way to support both software-mirrored disk array cabinets and shared approach and real-time replication to support remote disaster backup and recovery system. So that the user\'s servers, operating systems, database systems and critical data and applications remain seven days ÃƒÂ— 24 hours of continuous uninterrupted, providing 99.99% availability. Software includes a number of core parts and for different applications ARK.</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#3366ff\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>The key features of LifeKeeper</strong></font> </p><p> <font color=\"#3366ff\"><strong><br /></strong></font> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1. Without any additional investment in hardware, pure software approach to achieve Fault-tolerant, and to the preparation machine without hardware configuration requirements. <br /><br /> 2. Support for Notes, Exchange, SQL Server, Sybase, Informix, Oracle, SAP and other application-level heat recovery system. <br /><br /> 3. Is the world\'s first set of NT-based operating system supports fault-tolerant software and LINUX platforms. Remote disaster recovery. <br /><br /> 4. Support the expansion of shared disk array cabinets and mirrors in two ways, give users the flexibility to choose, but also to adapt to a variety of models, network architecture, software platforms and applications. <br /><br /> 5. LifeKeeper in shared disk array mirrored or extended any way, can achieve two servers running different applications and their mutual hot backup, the dual Active operation mode. <br /><br /> 6. Shared disk array cabinet mode, can support up to 16 nodes, much larger than other similar systems are supported by two nodes. <br /><br /> 7. Maximize the protection of the client application continuity. The user\'s hardware resources (such as network cards), software resources (such as the NT operating system, database management systems, database applications, e-mail systems, etc.) can in under LifeKeeper protection, conservation of resources when these are a technical failure, LifeKeeper implementation of system resources can be switched at any time. So, LifeKeeper truly a user\'s hardware or software failure of the system resources and application-layer switch on the hot line. <br /><br /> 8. LifeKeeper minimal system resources, without increasing network load, and do not disturb any specific application of any operation. <br /><br /> 9. LifeKeeper truly unattended, automatic application of resources to achieve change, and the graphics interface operation, simple and convenient. <br /><br /> 10. Since put into use, has undergone a large number of transactions the actual peak of the test, its implementation is very efficient and reliable operation, the global market share first.</font> </p>','SteelEye\'s LifeKeeper the United States is supporting a variety of soft (WindowNT, Windows2000, various Linux, etc.), high-performance fault-tolerant hardware platform, software can support up to 16 servers clustered. Lifekeeper software from NCR Corporation and the leading U.S. AT & T Bell Labs....'),(330,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/a4/1194.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Pure software mode hot standby solution depth','Pure_software_mode_hot_standby_solution_depth','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Database dual hot with two typical methods for a standard of comparison, the two servers via a shared storage device (usually a shared disk array or storage area network SAN), and install the software, double, dual hot standby, known as the shared way. Another way is through pure software approach, commonly referred to as pure software or in mirror mode (Mirror).</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For shared mode, the database on a shared storage device. When a server provides services directly in the storage device to read and write. When the system switch, another server also reads the data on the storage device.</font> </p><p> <span class=\"postbody\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For pure software approach, through the mirroring software, the data can be copied to another server in real time, so that the same data on the existence of a two servers, if one server fails, you can switch to another time servers.</font></span> </p><p> <span class=\"postbody\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Pure software approach to a certain extent, reduce costs, but it also has very significant disadvantages:</font></span> </p><p><span class=\"postbody\"></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1. Reliability is relatively poor, the two real-time replication of data between servers is a relatively weak link.</font> </p><p> <span class=\"postbody\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2. Once a server interruption, even after the resumption for more sophisticated data synchronization recovery. And, this time the system is not protected.</font></span> </p><p><span class=\"postbody\"></span> <span class=\"postbody\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">3. There is no transaction mechanism, because of its replication is in the file and disk layer, and copy the database transaction will not affect the success of operations, it is a complete change of data is not the case, there is considerable risk in this.</font></span> </p><p><span class=\"postbody\"></span> <strong><span class=\"postbody\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Therefore, it is recommended unless a last resort, do not choose a software program.</font></span></strong> </p><p><span class=\"postbody\"></span> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">On the other hand, there is a parallel database solution, it is not in the file or to copy the disk layer, but directly in front of the routing database operations distributed transaction mechanisms in parallel in order to complete the database update, the database also provides parallel service. In this way the current application for SQL SERVER very successful, much better than shared memory mode + dual machine software</font> </p>','Database dual hot with two typical methods for a standard of comparison, the two servers via a shared storage device (usually a shared disk array or storage area network SAN), and install the software, double, dual hot standby, known as the shared way. Another way is through pure software approach,...'),(331,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/08/1195.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Hot Standby: pure software-based shared memory','Hot_Standby_pure_softwarebased_shared_memory','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Dual hot with two implementation modes, one is based on shared storage devices, the other one is not the way the shared storage device, commonly referred to as pure software approach.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Based on storage shared hot standby is hot standby of the most standard programs.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For this method, the use of two servers, the use of shared storage devices (disk array cabinet or storage area network SAN). Two servers can be prepared by each other, master and slave, parallel and other different ways. In the course of their work, both servers will be a virtual IP address of external services, according to the different ways of working, the service request is sent to take one of the servers. At the same time, the server heartbeat (now often used to establish the way private network) to detect the working condition of another server. When a server fails, another server heartbeat detection under the circumstances to make judgments, and switch to take over the service. For users, this process is fully automated, in a very short time, thus no impact on the business. The use of shared storage devices, is actually two servers using the same data by two-machine or cluster software to manage them.</font> </p><p> <span class=\"postbody\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For pure software approach, it is mirrored by supporting dual-machine software, the data can be copied to another server in real time, so that the same data on the existence of a two servers, if one server fails, a timely switch to another server.</font></span> </p><p><span class=\"postbody\"></span> <span class=\"postbody\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">There is another software-only approach a situation in which the server provides application services only, and not save the data (for example, only for certain calculations, as the application server uses). In this case also does not need to use the shared storage device, this field should be included in load balancing,</font></span> </p>','Dual hot with two implementation modes, one is based on shared storage devices, the other one is not the way the shared storage device, commonly referred to as pure software...'),(332,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/cf/1196.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Hot Standby with the data backup, data security','Hot_Standby_with_the_data_backup_data_security','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Some users in the planning or dual hot standby backup, there will be such a problem: I already have a RAID, and tape backup, there must be two-machine? Or, if I did a double backup, there is a need to do a tape backup?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">RAID and data backup should be said are very important. However, RAID technology can only solve the problem of hard disk, backup can only solve the problem in the system after the recovery. Once the server is itself a problem, whether it is equipment, hardware problem or software problem, can cause service interruptions. Therefore, RAID and data backup technology can not solve the problem of avoiding service interruption. The need to sustain a reliable system to provide application services, double or very important. Just think, if your server was down, how much time you will restore it to work properly, your users can tolerate long recovery time will be able to understand the importance of the double.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">From the other side, RAID and tape backup is very necessary. For the RAID, the low cost can be greatly improve system reliability, and its complexity is much lower than the double. After all, the mechanical operation of the hard disk is the system most frequently, the highest rate of vulnerable components, if using RAID, you can make the system failure is very easy to fix, but also reduce the number of server downtime to switch.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Data backup is essential measures. Because whether or Dual RAID, is a real-time backup. Any software errors, virus impact, misuse, etc., will simultaneously occur in multiple copies of data. Therefore, be sure to backup data (regardless of what media are recommended at least an offline backup) in order to be able to data corruption, to restore lost</font> </p>','Some users in the planning or dual hot standby backup, there will be such a problem: I already have a RAID, and tape backup, there must be two-machine? Or, if I did a double backup, there is a need to do a tape...'),(333,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/38/1197.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Hot Standby FAQ doubts','Hot_Standby_FAQ_doubts','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Important applications for enterprise systems, to ensure that the system can be sustained and reliable service is very important, so there have been demands for high availability and high availability solutions.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">For how to select high-availability solutions, particularly on hot standby scheme selection, common are the following:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Q: high-availability solution for what?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A: Broadly speaking, high-availability systems, including all services to avoid disruption of the technology. The general said the system high availability, often double or more specific to the server hot standby / failover.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Q: When do you need hot standby?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A: Deciding whether to use hot standby, the correct way is to analyze the importance of the system and the degree of tolerance of service interruptions in order to decide whether to use Hot Standby. That is, your users can tolerate long recovery service, if service can not be restored will cause much impact.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Q: hot standby program with the difference between the cluster?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A: Conceptually, hot standby is a cluster (Cluster) of the kind. Clusters generally include two kinds, one is pure application server cluster, each application server to access centralized database server, but he does not need some shared storage, this cluster is relatively simple, and often provide services to each server\'s way, and often while using load balancing technology. There is another type of database server (or other systems that require access to stored data, such as Exchange, Notes) of the cluster. Cluster may include multiple servers. In addition to supporting two-machine cluster software work, but also can support multiple servers (Multi Node) work, the simultaneous deployment of multiple applications and the flexibility to set up multiple servers over strategy.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Q: high-availability database services There are several ways?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A: The most simple way is to use prepared machine. This fact does not belong to the scope of high availability, but you can restore service after the failure of the time control in the order of tens of minutes, and prepare machines usually also available for other purposes. This approach is a simple low-cost solution is not very important for the application of more suitable. It does not apply to important applications, but unless you stop for a few days the application does not matter, or at least this level of protection.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The second way is through the software to achieve hot standby. That is, not using a shared storage device, but the data is no longer a single point of storage, the machine data can be made to multiple hosts real-time data replication. This approach has the advantage of saving expensive storage equipment investment. The disadvantage is, or will produce different data, or will affect the speed of the database. For example, if the interruption in service to switch to the backup machine, you may have a small amount of the transaction has been completed on the host machine not yet been achieved in the preparation. Backup data recovery with the different preparation machine starts, follow-up operation has been carried out, so the transaction is lost is difficult to fill. Therefore, this method is applicable for the loss of a small amount of data is not very sensitive system.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The third is based on the shared storage devices and software implementation of double hot standby. This is the standard method, to the case of unattended switch to provide second level, and will not lose data. Of course, the investment will be higher.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Q: When hot standby database, double the same time work?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A: In general the small and medium-scale applications, database, Hot Standby is active / standby mode, the main server to wait for another job, in the main server fails with dual machine software automatically switch to another server. And some large-scale application for the full use of equipment, the way services can be used in parallel, two servers provide services such as Oracle\'s RAC (Oracle Real Application Cluster), and support for SQL Server database, parallel services router software ICX</font> </p>','Important applications for enterprise systems, to ensure that the system can be sustained and reliable service is very important, so there have been demands for high availability and high availability...'),(334,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/d9/2175.html','http://www.ixdba.net','MySQL second change of ownership, the road was more difficult','MySQL_second_change_of_ownership_the_road_was_more_difficult','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=Sun\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Sun</span> Wen, after the acquisition of bone, MySQL\'s development prospects have been closely watched by all sides. Recently, some MySQL <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%D3%C3%BB%A7\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">users</span> long-term approach to migration of other <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CF%B5%CD%B3\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">systems</span> for the future of MySQL adds pessimistic expectations. <br /><br /> Preceding <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CA%B1%BC%E4\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">time,</span> Twitter announced that it would phase out the existing MySQL systems in favor of Cassandra <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%B9%DC%C0%ED\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">management</span> information. Cassandra is a distributed by the Apache Foundation\'s open source <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CA%FD%BE%DD%BF%E2\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">database,</span> mainly for the huge amounts of <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CA%FD%BE%DD\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">data</span> distributed to a large number of low-cost <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%B7%FE%CE%F1%C6%F7\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">servers,</span> and then piece together a single point of failure-free information management clusters. Prior to in Twitter, Facebook, Digg has started using Cassandra, <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CB%BC%BF%C6\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Cisco</span> WebEx has also been used to collect user feedback Cassandra. <br /><br /> Once upon a time, MySQL as the darling of the Internet and open source <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%C8%ED%BC%FE\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">software,</span> the standard-bearer, much the favor various types of Internet <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%D3%A6%D3%C3\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">applications.</span> However, as Sun acquired MySQL, it has bright light slowly faded. For many users, MySQL has become a profitable commercial product, the future development of great uncertainty. In addition, with the continuous expansion of Web 2.0 applications, many <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%C6%F3%D2%B5\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">companies</span> find that the cost of using the MySQL data will be accompanied by the expansion of the exponential growth of centralized data storage more difficult to achieve efficiency and effectiveness of the organic balance. <br /><p style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 30px; TEXT-INDENT: 2em\"> <span id=\"attach_615015\" onmouseover=\"showMenu({\'ctrlid\':this.id,\'pos\':\'13\'})\" style=\"POSITION: absolute; DISPLAY: none\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://www.ixpub.net/images/default/attachimg.gif\" /></span> <img alt=\"1524331457-0.png\" file=\"http://files.ixpub.net/day_100320/1003201302207a925d64da8523.png\" id=\"aimg_615015\" initialized=\"true\" outfunc=\"null\" src=\"http://files.ixpub.net/day_100320/1003201302207a925d64da8523.png\" status=\"2\" unselectable=\"true\" width=\"202\" /></p><div cache=\"1\" class=\"t_attach\" cover=\"0\" ctrlkey=\"aimg_615015\" fade=\"false\" id=\"aimg_615015_menu\" initialized=\"true\" layer=\"1\" mtype=\"menu\" style=\"Z-INDEX: 301; POSITION: absolute; FILTER: progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Alpha(opacity=100); DISPLAY: none; TOP: 723px; LEFT: 587px; opacity: 1\"> <font color=\"#0066cc\"><span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CF%C2%D4%D8\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\"><strong>Download</strong></span></font> (17.04 KB) <br /><div class=\"t_smallfont\"> <span title=\"2010-3-20 13:02\">The day before yesterday 13:02</span> </div></div><p></p><br /> In addition, the recent rise of the No-SQL movement to the IT industry has brought new choices. In addition to Cassandra addition, No-SQL campaign representatives, including Hadoop, Google\'s Big Table, MemCacheDB, Voldemort, CouchDB and MongoDB. In this context, not only include large Internet companies began to give up the relational database, including MySQL, even some of the enterprise\'s internal applications, taking into account the multi-media, e-mail, spatial and geographic information increases, are beginning to use non-relational database <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%B7%BD%B0%B8\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">programs.</span> <br /><br /> Cassandra official Twitter some of the comments seem more telling. Twitter said: &quot;Cassandra does not exist a single point of failure; came from Facebook, born as a mass of data design; for a large number of distributed write operations; relying on the support of a healthy community.&quot; For those who built on top of relational database systems Yan, Cassandra offers from other relational database tools for loading data, which means that potential users may consider &quot;try&quot; to its system for Cassandra, but Twitter is also to do so. Twitter plans to let the first two systems in parallel for some time, and stable <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%D4%CB%D0%D0\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">operation of</span> the new system to be determined after the MySQL eliminated. <br /><br /> MySQL today have to face many problems, it is large-scale applications in the low adoption rate, while PostgreSQL is facing a strong competitors. In addition, MySQL version are thriving grass-roots, as opposed to the official Enterprise and Community Edition, MySQL seems to be the branch products more community support. Moreover, the acquisition has not really settled. Although Oracle\'s acquisition of the Sun has received recognition in the U.S. and the EU, but whether China and Russia through the review of anti-monopoly authorities still need time.','...'),(335,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/13/2174.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Who is the largest contribution to the open source world?','Who_is_the_largest_contribution_to_the_open_source_world','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Open-source collaboration company MindTouch 3 17 in open source business conference this year, released their Twitter according to Google Trends and a variety of analysis <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%B9%A4%BE%DF\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">tools to identify</span> the most influential opinion leaders in open source list.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\"><br /><font size=\"2\"></font></font> </p><p align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/3b/3b7cb4c8d09ee7c48f9d01dfbd948579.jpg\" /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Among them, the leading <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%BC%BC%CA%F5\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">technology</span> publishing company O\'Reilly Tim O\'Reilly, founder of Twitter, because of its 1.43 million followers and tops the list. Although the father of <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=Linux\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Linux</span> Linus Torvalds little on Twitter, blog is not updated frequently, but mostly write their own private activities, still unparalleled strength and a strong second place. Other opinion leaders in the top 10 include: Google\'s open-source advocates Chris Messina, <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=Sun\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">Sun\'s</span> former CEO Jonathan Schwartz, Mono founder Miguel de Icaza, leading Drupal design and <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%BF%AA%B7%A2\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">development</span> company ImageX Media founder Glenn Hilton, technical writers, open Source book &quot;Rebel Code&quot; author Glyn Moody, Ubuntu developer Canoni