source products. Roger believes that the current economic situation will encourage enterprises to adopt open source products, and once from open source software companies have tasted the sweetness, will adopt more open source software. <br /><br /> In fact, according to report, open source software adoption rates in China\'s enterprises in a steady upward trend, the statistics from the relevant agencies, the current Linux has accounted for more than 30% of worldwide server market share in the grid, high performance computing and many other fields, open source software and even become mainstream. Open-source alliance from our statistics show that the Chinese market in 2007 totaled 2.7 billion yuan, an increase of 27% in 2006. The major open-source software vendors, including Novell, Red Hat, also are increasing the investment in the Chinese market. <br /><br /> &quot;Novell is increasing more recent R &amp; D staff in China to expand from the current 35 to 70, the next few years will continue to expand the team, which is the main purpose of my current one to China.&quot; Roger told reporters. <br /><br /> However, Roger denied the plans and directly related to the current economic situation, he said: &quot;Novell plans to expand R &amp; D Centre Beijing and not directly related to the economic situation. In fact, we have R &amp; D centers in China for some time, research and development covering server, desktop and other technology, its R &amp; D results will also contribute to global customers. &quot;Roger said, as Chinese companies authorized to open source software, Novell\'s business in the Chinese market is also expanding. R &amp; D team behind this expansion is because Novell signed a number of new business contracts, such as with Lenovo, Dell, HP and other vendors of desktop systems preloaded with the cooperation of the work. <br /><br /> Roger also pointed out that at present the main issues facing open source software, including version too, and standardized enough. &quot;Because there are different versions of application software providers need to be certified for each, also need to work closely with hardware manufacturers. This will hinder application innovation.&quot; <br /><br /> During the interview, as general manager of Open Platform Solutions Division, Roger repeatedly showing appreciation to the Chinese engineers, he said: &quot;I see China has a lot of very good engineers, they have a strong technical background, there is a high R &amp; D passion, many people contacted in the University of Linux, open source contacted by the personnel of such a strong R &amp; D team will be Novell to provide good customer service basis. &quot;</font> <div style=\"DISPLAY: none\"></div>','empty\n'),(350,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/50/994.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Microsoft, Yahoo, Google to find external resistance or Ping','Microsoft_Yahoo_Google_to_find_external_resistance_or_Ping','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Beijing February 4, according to foreign media reports, sources said Google CEO Eric Schmidt (Eric Schmidt) Yahoo CEO Jerry Yang specifically call, hoping to provide help for Yahoo against Microsoft\'s &quot;hostile&quot; takeover.</font> </p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Google initiative to provide assistance</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Microsoft on Friday announced it has submitted a bid to Yahoo\'s board, plans to acquire $ 31 per share, which all the issued ordinary shares, the total transaction value of approximately $ 44,600,000,000. Yahoo said later, take a long time to evaluate Microsoft\'s acquisition of the request. Over the past three days, the deal in the media and technology industry firestorm. According to sources, so far, no clear position on Yahoo\'s board of directors, and no other potential bidders surfaced.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The industry believes that Google directly is almost no possibility to buy Yahoo because the two companies accounted for Web search and advertising market share in the vast majority of such transactions can not antitrust regulatory approval. However, sources said, Google can help other companies bid for Yahoo and Microsoft, or to help Yahoo remain independent. For example, Google may provide funds, or with Yahoo sign advertising outsourcing revenue assurance contract. Of course, even Google to take this compromise means, can be subject to antitrust scrutiny because regulators worried about competition in the Internet market has been weakened.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">So far, Google spokesman was not on whether the company intends to bid for a contract with Yahoo, Yahoo or comment. Google said in a blog post on Sunday, Microsoft acquisition of Yahoo would trigger some serious problems, because the deal will give Microsoft access to too much monopoly hegemony, and is used to combat competitors. Microsoft said it enough by building a Web search and advertising market with Google competing service providers, allowing the market more competitive.</font> </p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Is hard for bidders</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A source said that since Friday have been a number of technology, media and financial companies and their advisers to contact Yahoo and expressed interest in bidding with Microsoft. But so far, none of the companies to submit a formal offer. Industry speculation, AT &amp; T, News Corp and Time Warner are all potential bidders. However, according to sources, the three companies do not plan to buy Yahoo. Although they may change position, but unlikely.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Yahoo said earlier that its board will carefully study the request and Microsoft\'s acquisition of other alternatives, including continuing to remain independent. Yahoo said in a statement: &quot;We will find the best solution, the goal is to maximize long-term value for shareholders. However, the uncertainty assessment process, and may last for a long time.&quot; Sources said Yahoo has been in recent weeks negotiations with Google, hoping to outsource Web search advertising in Europe to the latter. Since last year, many investors have called for Yahoo to abandon its own search advertising system in favor of Google system to get more revenue.</font> </p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Search outsourcing negotiations continue</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">A source said the outsourcing of search advertising business in Europe may be Yahoo\'s talks with Google to carry out comprehensive cooperation in the first step in outsourcing. While Microsoft has submitted purchase request, but negotiations between the two sides will continue. Another source said that Yahoo and Google recently faced the issue of revenue sharing had serious differences. Citigroup Global Markets analyst Mark Mahaney (Mark Mahaney) on Friday said in a report, through the outsourcing to Google search advertising business, Yahoo\'s cash flow each year will increase by 25% or more.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">It is said that the strategic review conducted last year, Yahoo executives have to consider outsourcing search advertising to Google. However, in October last year, Yang made the opposite decision. He was at the analyst meeting, said: &quot;We believe that the development of search and display ads while Yahoo is very important to help us create long-term value for shareholders.&quot; Of course, Yahoo\'s recent poor performance, including stock price continued to fall, and disappointing 2008 results are expected, may force the introduction of more aggressive Yang initiatives, including with major competitors, Google co-operation.</font> </p><p> <strong><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Microsoft, Google struggled</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\"