wei R &amp; D base has an employee after falling from the third floor cafeteria Huawei died. Then the situation on their cause of death has not been so public. Southern Metropolis Daily reporter 18:14 Report: Longgang police official said the preliminary investigation, Huawei Zhang staff suicide, but jumping is not clear why, at present, is investigating the reasons for suicide.</font> <p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This has happened the past year, Huawei\'s internal staff from at least the fifth case of unnatural death; and internal staff, according to Huawei, said that Huawei has been the recent death of non-normal first 38 cases of it!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This occurred in less than 10 days before the February 26,</font> <font color=\"#0000ff\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Lidong Bing Huawei staff from the Chengdu R &amp; D center of Huawei floor jump, died on the <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">spot,</font></font> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">was certified systems problems with personal feelings, the official also did not disclose more information.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">December 5, 2007 morning, to work in Shenzhen Huawei</font> <font color=\"#0000ff\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Qiaoxiang Ying toiletries in the bathroom when you get down after <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">death.</font></font> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">It is said, December 5, 2007 morning, the project work in Shenzhen Huawei Technology Qiaoxiang Ying into the toilet in the dorm toilet after getting up suddenly inexplicable fall. But this is an error message after the requirements of Huawei, said the media removed, has not been formally confirmed.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">At 17:30 on August 11, 2007, the League of Nations in Changchun area,</font> <font color=\"#0000ff\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Huawei Zhao Bing Changchun office staff</font> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">arguing with people on the phone 20 minutes later, caught jumped from the 7th floor, dead. However, due to various reasons, this was later played down the media.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">July 18, 2007 afternoon, the age of 26</font> <font color=\"#0000ff\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Zhang Rui <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Huawei</font> employees of a district in Shenzhen Meilin Ziyishenwang within the <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">corridor.</font></font> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Huawei is only 60 days into his, who had been repeatedly expressed to the family too much pressure of work, and want to quit twice, for deep twice to visit his father to persuade. But the second time in his father came to Shenzhen, Rui chosen in this way and their loved ones goodbye.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The night of 28 May 2006,</font> <font color=\"#0000ff\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">25-year-old Hu Xinyu, died due to illness was diagnosed viral <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">encephalitis.</font></font> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">After graduating in 2005 Master Hu Xinyu directly to Shenzhen Huawei R &amp; D work, often in the company overtime, play ground floor overnight. April 28, Hu Xinyu, extreme physical discomfort, he took leave of absence to the hospital eventually died.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Huawei frequent unnatural deaths, has caused widespread concern in the industry. After last week Zisha Chengdu Lidong Bing, 51CTO.com held on &quot;whether the enterprise workers killed themselves bear the main responsibility&quot; of the survey, 65% of the readers that the main responsibility should be in the business, reflecting the user to query the corporate culture of Huawei.</font> </p>','This has happened the past year, Huawei\'s internal staff from at least the fifth case of unnatural death; and internal staff, according to Huawei, said that Huawei has been the recent death of non-normal first 38 cases of...'),(359,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/c0/1999.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Greater than 2T partitioned the disk using the GPT','Greater_than_2T_partitioned_the_disk_using_the_GPT','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The ISCSI a MD1000 storage, a 15T space in the sub-space, more than 2T for nothing, can not use common partition. Can only use the GPT method. Checks the introduction of GPT. Introduced speaking, only in 2TB, the ordinary pc\'s BIOS to recognize the partition table. More than 2TB of disk must use the GPT partition table. <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Here are some of its introduction <br /> Acronym for GUID Partition Table</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">GPT was introduced for iA64 systems, to get around a fixed 32 bit issue (2 to the power of 32 is 4 billion times a 512 byte block equals 2 Terabytes) in the PC-BIOS Partition table. Partitions larger than 2 TB require using a GPT disklabel, which differs from the PC-BIOS Partition table in a number of ways:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">* Is easily extensible. <br /> * Can contain up to 128 primary partitions, as opposed to 4, so there\'s no need for extended partitions. <br /> * Allows Partitions larger than 2 TB. <br /> * Identifies Partitions with a GUID so you can reference that Partition even if disks are moved around. <br /> * Identifies Partition type with a GUID, thus avoiding the type conflicts that plague the PC-BIOS Partition table format. <br /> * Provides a 46 (?) Character UTF-16 partition label to identify Partitions. <br /> * Has a &quot;fake&quot; MBR for backwards compatibility. <br /> * Includes a CRC32 to detect corrupt Partition tables. <br /> * Stores a backup Partition table at the end of the disk.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Most partitioning tools under Linux will fail to do anything sensible with a&gt; 2 TB Partition. As of this writing, parted (8) is the only one that understands them and will let you set the GPT label on the disk.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">There is a lot of information stating that you cannot boot off a GPT enabled device. Most of the claims imply that the fault is with LILO or GRUB not understanding GPT devices. We\'ve not tested this, but GPT and traditional MBRs will coexist.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">See also:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">* Disk Sectors on GPT Disks from the MS Knowledge Base</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Therefore, more than 2TB, I can not use the Fdisk command to interact well, only converted to GPT format disks. GPT format disks as the equivalent of the original disk to retain the original MBR partition table 4 4 * 16 bytes, leaving only the first 16 bytes, the other is similar to the extended partition, the real in the 512-byte partition table after So in terms of GPT disk table is not limited to four primary partitions.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">GPT partition table of the operation, we have to use the parted command. In fact parted very powerful, it can be the same as fdisk can also be used with an interactive command line. <br /> Here we have to practice it, parted at the prompt, enter the interactive mode will be entered</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"># Parted / dev / sdb <br /> GNU Parted 1.8.1 <br /> Using / dev / sdb <br /> Welcome to GNU Parted! Type \'help\' to view a list of commands.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(Parted) mklable gpt <br /> GPT to MBR disk is formatted as</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(Parted) mkpart primary 0 100 <br /> 0 by a starting position of the primary partition size 100M</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(Parted) mkpart primary 100 200 <br /> 100M division of a starting position for the primary partition size 100M</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(Parted) mkpart primary 0 -1</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">All the space to a partition by</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(Parted) print <br /> Print the current partition</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(Parted) quit</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Some commands may also be used</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">(Parted) mklable msdos <br /> If you want to turn. Will be converted to MBR disks GPT disk</font> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IXDBA.NET Technical Community</font></a></font></strong> <br /><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">End points in this partition, but also the use mkfs.ext3 to format <br /> # Partprobe</font> </p>','The ISCSI a MD1000 storage, a 15T space in the sub-space, more than 2T for nothing, can not use common partition. Can only use the GPT method. Checks the introduction of GPT. Introduced speaking, only in 2TB, the ordinary pc\'s BIOS to recognize the partition table. More than 2TB of disk must use...'),(360,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/83/1886.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Intel motherboard RAID1 recovery methods and illustrations','Intel_motherboard_RAID1_recovery_methods_and_illustrations','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font color=\"#000000\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\">Test to EP-5LDA + GLI, for example, the first with 2 Seagate 80G SATAII <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%D3%B2%C5%CC\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">hard</span> group &amp; RAID1. When installing the drivers in addition to <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%D6%F7%B0%E5\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">the motherboard</span> chipset, sound card, network card, graphics driver, you must also load the &quot;Intel <br /> Application Accelerator Raid edition V5.10.1022 full Version &quot;drive, Intel motherboard, mainly through the driver to complete the RAID mirror restoration. Following is a RAID damage and recovery of the whole process, please refer to:</font></font></font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><br /></font></font> <div class=\"t_msgfont\"> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\">1. First, unplug one of the hard drive, boot the second screen is displayed as an incomplete (Degraded) RAID1 (pictured), into <br /> <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%CF%B5%CD%B3\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">System.</span> Click on Start menu-Intel (R) Matrix Storage manager-Intel (R) Matrix Storage Console, view the status of the hard drive and RAID clues &quot;lost a hard drive, RAID performance degradation volume&quot; RAID1 that has been damaged.</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onload=\"attachimg(this, \'load\')\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/f0/f0191cc3b1d4b26d7c024f9a466eb8ff.jpg\" /></font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"502\" onload=\"attachimg(this, \'load\')\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/bc/bc15b93306c5f2ad2e8c13960f11af26.jpg\" width=\"607\" /></font> <br /><font color=\"#000000\"></font><br /><br /> <font color=\"#000000\">2. Add a SAMSUNG 80G SATAII disk space, access to the system to open Intel (R) Matrix Storage Console</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\">Dialog box, click the &quot;Restore RAID1 data protection&quot; before the icon.</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"509\" onload=\"attachimg(this, \'load\')\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/8a/8ae3f90710d84e31cab686bc9ddd2ebc.jpg\" width=\"611\" /></font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\">3. Then click on &quot;Reconstruction now RAID volumes.&quot;</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"495\" onload=\"attachimg(this, \'load\')\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/96/96be3b4828617dbb6af032754e0eaff8.jpg\" width=\"613\" /></font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\">4. View hard drive and RAID status prompted &quot;a RAID volume is rebuilding.&quot;</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"491\" onload=\"attachimg(this, \'load\')\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/f2/f2587adbab47e010d2f03df85a9bc6c5.jpg\" width=\"617\" /></font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\">5. Reconstruction process will take some time, until the prompt &quot;All the hard drives and RAID volumes are normal,&quot; said RAID1 has been restored.</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"499\" onload=\"attachimg(this, \'load\')\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/40/40c5f789978ebd4ae692f3e069b4f6cb.jpg\" width=\"618\" /></font> <br /><br /> <font color=\"#000000\">6. Reboot, the boot screen also displays an &quot;Nomal&quot; RAID1</font> <br /> <font color=\"#000000\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"375\" onload=\"attachimg(this, \'load\')\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/95/95bd8c8063d1f1353a90d1c77d682681.jpg\" width=\"622\" /></font></font></font> </div></div><font color=\"#000000\"></font>','empty\n'),(361,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/0f/1857.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Three major comparative analysis of iSCSI Initiator software','Three_major_comparative_analysis_of_iSCSI_Initiator_software','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">To implement</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">read and write, in addition to the use of specific hardware devices, but also by software methods, the server-side simulation for the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">initiator or target side, the use of existing processor card with ordinary Ethernet</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">connectivity resources to achieve .</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">is</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">internet</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">SCSI,</span> is the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">IETF</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">developed a storage transport protocol standard for the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">SCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">data block image as the Ethernet data packets.</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">protocol is essentially a</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">SCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">across the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">IP</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">network to transmit data block approach, read and write requests initiated by the source of equipment called the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Initiator</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">(initiator), the requested destination device is known as <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Target.</span> In this way the network in</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">IP</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">mode on a block-level access to large amounts of data.</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Ã‚Â </span></p><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">To implement</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">read and write, in addition to using specific hardware device, but also through software means, the server-side simulation for the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">initiator or target side, the use of existing processor card with ordinary Ethernet</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">connectivity resources to achieve . At present, most of the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI Target</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">simulation software to be paid more for the commercial software, but there are many free</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI initiator</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">software is available for selection.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IXDBA.NET Technical Community</font></a></font></strong> <br /><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>Microsoft iSCSI Initiator</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Microsoft</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">provides software initiated</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">that allows</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Windows</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">client initiated</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">Ethernet card into a device simulation for</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">on the network</span></font><html> ly: Verdana &quot;&gt; <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">target device initiates access requirements, the establishment of</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">online.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">The latest version of</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Microsoft iSCSI Initiator</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">version <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">2.04,</span> supports</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Windows 2000/XP/Server 2003</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">and other Microsoft operating environment, and the respective support <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">x64, IA64,</span></font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">x86</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">processor platforms such as the version. Download the installation is complete, the</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Discovery</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">menu, enter the</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">target device or</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iqn IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">address, you can choose the</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Target</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">menu to establish a connection with the</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">device, through the</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">network to access</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">storage devices, also supports multi-path transmission.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>Linux-iSCSI</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">There are two versions of</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Linux kernel <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">2.4/2.6\'s</font></span> iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Initiator,</span> in use, the system must be ready <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">kernel-source, kernel, gcc, perl, Apache,</span> and other related files. Download and complete the compilation, the first</font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">/ etc / iscsi.conf iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">configuration within the configuration, to meet the currently used</font></span>pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana &quot;&gt; iSCSI <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">target device the correct URL, user name and password, next to</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"># / etc / init.d / iscsi start</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">start the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">device, and the disk partition</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">fdisk</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">command, and finally with the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">mkdir</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">and</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">mount</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">command to mount the disk drive.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>Solaris iSCSI Initiator</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Solaris 10</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">has built-in</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI Initiator</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">software, including</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">SPARC <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">64,</span></font> x64</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">and</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">IA-32</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">and other processor platforms can support.</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Sun</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">related to the</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">driver integrated</span></font> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI Device Driver and Utilities</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">updates, the current version has been updated to <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">5.10.</span></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </p><p> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt\"><font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">Use, first with the <span lang=\"EN-US\">svcadm enable svc: / network / iscsi_initiator</span> first startup instruction format</font> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iSCSI</span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"> </font></span> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Initiator,</span></span> the operation mainly depends on the next <span lang=\"EN-US\">iscsiadm</span> command, first to <span lang=\"EN-US\">iscsiadm add discovery-address</span> command to set the target device address, and then <span lang=\"EN-US\">iscsiadm modify <span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">initiator-node</span></span> changes the connection between the target device settings, and then use <span lang=\"EN-US\">devfsadm-c</span> sequence <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iscsi,</span> format, newfs</span> command to create a new disk and other areas, the final disk area and then <span lang=\"EN-US\">mount</span> command to mount <span lang=\"EN-US\">up.</span></font></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p>','To implement iSCSI read and write, in addition to the use of specific hardware devices, but also by software methods, the server-side simulation for the iSCSI initiator or target side, the use of existing processor card with ordinary Ethernet iSCSI connectivity resources to achieve ....'),(362,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/4c/1856.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Red Hat linux iSCSI initiator configuration','Red_Hat_linux_iSCSI_initiator_configuration','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><u><strong>Red Hat <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/d4/444.html\">Linux</a> iSCSI Configuration</strong></u></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><u><strong>Supported iSCSI Initiators:</strong></u></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>Enterprise Linux (ES or AS) 3 Update 6:</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Disc 2 of 4:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iscsi-initiator-utils-3.6.3-3.i386.rpm</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">linux-iscsi 3.4.x: Minimum kernel release: 2.4.21</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">linux-iscsi 3.6.x: Minimum kernel release: 2.4.21</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>NOTE:</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Versions of the linux-iscsi Initiator above 3.x are not compatible with the 2.4.x and below kernel release.</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>Enterprise Linux (ES or AS) 4 Update 2:</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Disc 4 of 4:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iscsi-initiator-utils-4.0.3.0-2.i386.rpm</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">linux-iscsi:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">4.0.2 - Mnimum kernel release: 2.6.10</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">4.0.1 - minimum kernel Release: 2.6.0</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>NOTE:</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Versions of the linux-iscsi Initiator below 4.x are not compatible with the 2.6.x and higher kernel release.</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>NOTE:</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">The linux-iscsi version 5.x and higher has yet to be successfully tested by UIT.</span> </p> <font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>IXDBA.NET Technical Community</strong></font></a></font> <br /><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><u><strong>Installation Instructions:</strong></u></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>Red Hat Supplied iSCSI Initiator:</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Regardless of whether Enterprise <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/d4/444.html\">Linux</a> 3 or 4 is being run, you Simply Find the RPM on the Red Hat Media, then install using the rpm-ivh IT command as follows:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"># Rpm-ivh iscsi-initiator-utils-4.0.3.0-2.i386.rpm</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><strong>NOTE:</strong></span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">This is the version for Enterprise Linux ES 4 Update 2. Your version may differ.</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">An alternative to installing this package manually in Red Hat Enterprise Linux (ES or AS) 4 Update 2 or greater is to use the &quot;Add / Remove Applications&quot; menu item in the &quot;System Settings&quot; menu. In the details for the &quot;Network Servers &quot;package list, the iscsi-initiator-utils is one of the packages listed. This same choice is available in the same location during the initial instal</span>l of Red Hat, so this can also be done at that time. </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Once installed, there will be a file in the / etc directory named iscsi.conf. If this file does not exist this may indicate a problem with the installation. This file can be created with the following minimal entries:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">DiscoveryAddress = &lt;IP Address&gt;</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">This needs to be set to the Group IP Address of your UIT Array.</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">SendAsyncText = yes</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">For the initiator to receive Vendor Specific async events from the target.</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Continuous = yes</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">To globally specify that all discovery sessions be kept open.</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Within the iscsi.conf file itself there are many more options available that can be set. You can look through the iscsi.conf file for information on what these variables are and what they are used for.</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">Once these values are either placed in a newly created / etc / iscsi.conf file, or the respective lines are uncommented and edited where necessary, the iscsi service can be started:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"># Service iscsi start</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">To verify that the iscsi service will be started at boot time, the chkconfig command can be used as follows:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"># Chkconfig-list iscsi</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">iscsi 0: off 1: off 2: off 3: off 4: off 5: off 6: off</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">By default, the newly added iscsi initiator is not enabled at boot which is the reason for each of the run levels listed to have the service set to off. To enable this at boot, again use the chkconfig command as follows:</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"># Chkconfig-add iscsi</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"># Chkconfig iscsi on</span> </p><p> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\">The above two commands first checks to be sure there are the necessary scripts to start and stop the service, then it sets this service to be on for the appropriate runlevels.</span> </p>','Red Hat Linux iSCSI Configuration...'),(363,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/1b/1855.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Several host and ISCSI connection between devices','Several_host_and_ISCSI_connection_between_devices','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><h1 style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\"></span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana\"></span></font> </h1><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto\"> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Storage devices and hosts connected via Ethernet cable to an Ethernet network switch, through the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">network to achieve the transmission of</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">SCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">protocol.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">ISCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">host connections between devices in three ways:</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /><br /></span> <strong><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">The first: Ethernet card</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">+</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">software way.</span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /><br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Host a standard Ethernet card, install the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Initiator</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Software</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Initiator</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">software through a virtual Ethernet card for the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">ISCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-famil