; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">packet conversion elements of the text as part of the host-side resources.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /></span> </p><p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\">www.ixdba.net</a></font></strong> </p><br /><br /> <strong><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">The second:</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">TOE</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">NIC hardware implementations.</span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong><br /></strong> <br /></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">In this way, the host using</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">TOE (TCP / IP Offloading Engine)</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">card to connect to the network,</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">TCP / IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">protocol stack by the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">TOE</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">cards feature complete, and</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">layer functions still to be completed by the host.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">TOE</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">cards can also use the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">TCP / IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">protocol, the equivalent of a high-performance Ethernet card, so the second approach can also be seen as the first connection of the special circumstances.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /><br /></span>&quot;&gt; The third is the <strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">iSCSI HBA</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">card implementation.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><br /><br /></span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Using the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">storage adapter to complete the server</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">layer and the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">TCP / IP</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">protocol stack functionality. This approach makes the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">CPU</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">do not need to consider the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">iSCSI</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">server, and network configuration, in terms of server,</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">iSCSI HBA</span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Adapter is a memory device, and the server has nothing to do with the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"COLOR: #000099; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; TEXT-DECORATION: none; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; text-underline: none\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">operating <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">system.</span></span></span></span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">This way the best performance, but the price is also the most expensive.</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"> </span><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; TEXT-ALIGN: left; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span> <span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; LINE-HEIGHT: 160%; FONT-FAMILY: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">In the latter two methods require special hardware installed on th