ead to loss of RAID disk array:</font> <p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1. The hard disk in order messed up, causing the boot disk array is not up</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2. Array disks dropped to two or two more, the collapse of the array</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">3. Expansion of the disk array is not yet complete when the go out into the write data, resulting in the collapse of the array</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">4. Dropped a hard drive, put a good plate Rebuild, cause data is not normal</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">5. Disk physical failure, such as: bad circuit board, heads damage, bad disk, bad sectors, etc.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">6. In the absence of any exceptional circumstances, the array is not normal boot</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">7. A sudden power outage caused by RAID disk array card information loss</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">8. The hard drive in the wrong order, start the system, or change the configuration;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">If you find raid disk array failure. Please take the following action.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">1, the system power off, the hard drive in order of number</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2, will report to the disk array disk array vendor or professional data recovery company</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">3, non-professionals do not try to Rebuild, initialization, synchronization, data recovery attempt to action</font> </p>','1. The hard disk in order messed up, causing the boot disk array is not...'),(367,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/26/1545.html','http://www.ixdba.net','IDE / ATA, SCSI, Fibre Channel technology Detailed','IDE__ATA_SCSI_Fibre_Channel_technology_Detailed','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div class=\"t_msgfont\" id=\"message634880\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This article about the IDE / ATA, SCSI, Fibre Channel technology, suitable for beginners! <br /> 1, IDE / ATA <br /><br /> 1.1 Overview <br /> IDE or Integrated Drive Electronics, it is intended to refer to the integrated controller and disk physical hard drive, we have often said IDE interface, also known as ATA (Advanced Technology Attachment) interface, now PC, most of them hard to use is IDE compatible, just with a cable with the motherboard or interface card are connected together on it. <br /> Western Digital IDE interface is with COMPAQ Computer shared by the two companies developed the interface. Because the technology continues to improve, a new generation of Enhanced IDE (Enhanced IDE, referred to as EIDE) maximum transfer rate of up to 100MB / s (Ultra ATA/100). <br /> IDE interface has two main advantages: ease of use and low cost, become the most popular after the advent of the disk interface. However, with the faster CPU speed and application software and the increasing complexity of the environment, IDE\'s shortcomings began to slowly emerge. Enhanced IDE Western Digital Corporation is the interface for the shortcomings of the traditional IDE to improve after the introduction of new interfaces. Enhanced IDE using the expansion of CHS (Cylinder-Head-Sector) or LBA (Logical Block Addressing) address ways to break through 528MB of capacity constraints, can successfully make use of the capacity to reach levels of tens of GB IDE hard drive. <br /> In the PC, I / O devices such as hard disk drives, the system is not directly connected to the central bus (AT bus AT system, or after the PCI bus system). The I / O devices and interface chip connected to the interface chip and system bus connections. <br /> Composition of the interface chip I / O devices and system bus bridge, in the system bus protocols (PCI or AT) and the I / O device protocol (such as IDE or SCSI) to translate between. This makes I / O devices can be independent of the system bus protocol. <br /> The following figure shows the basic system structure of PC workstation, showing the remaining part of the IDE devices and systems relations. <br /><br /><br /> 1.2 IDE Transfer Mode <br /> IDE hard disk interface of several transport modes are apparently different. IDE interface hard disk transfer mode, experienced three different technological changes, the PIO (Programmed I / O) mode, DMA (Direct Memory Access) mode, until the current Ultra DMA modes (referred to as UDMA). <br /> PIO (Programmed I / O) modes biggest shortcoming is the very large consumption of CPU resources, yet to DMA mode in the previous drive when the drive is in PIO mode. You may remember that the CD player with VCD, Coupled with software decompression, even with Pentium 166, his fluency is not ideal, this is a large number of processors occupied by long-term reason. To the IDE PIO mode interface, data transfer rate of 3.3MB / s (PIO mode 0) to 16. MB / sec (PIO mode 4) months. Later, with the Fast ATA / DMA mode there, IDE interface and devices are beginning to have DMA support, DMA mode is divided into Single-Word DMA and Multi - Word DMA two, with the biggest difference is the PIO mode: DMA mode and without over-reliance on the running CPU instructions can be achieved by saving resources, the effect of the processor is running. However, the later emergence of the Ultra DMA mode and the rate determining popularity. The two models will only be short-lived, shortly thereafter replaced by UDMA. Single-Word DMA Mode maximum transfer rate of 8.33MB / s, Multi-Word DMA (Double Word) is up to 16.66MB / sec. <br /> The Ultra DMA mode (Ultra ATA standard, a standard under the reference) of the universal, UDMA mode on the whole to 16-bit Multi-Word DMA mode as a benchmark. One of the advantages is that it UDMA in addition has the advantages of DMA mode, but also the application of CRC (Cyclic Redundancy Check) technology to enhance the data transfer process in terms of debugging and performance debugging. Specifications developed in the first UATA/33, in order to retain maximum compatibility with IDE systems, so the design of the hardware did not make too much changes, not only fully backward compatible with older ATA devices, and need not change the connector hardware manufacturers and signal connection design. Ultra ATA standards since its inception, its interface will be applied to DDR (Double Data Rate) technology will be doubling the speed of transmission, has been developed to Ultra ATA/100, and its transmission speed of up to 100MB / sec. <br /> Ultra DMA/66/100 hard drive cable and a dedicated 40-pin connector in general be different. Quantum in the development of Ultra ATA/66 the same time, the old IDE cable specifications with minor modifications. In addition to the core of the IDE connector 40 in use, the 80-pin ribbon cable replaced, the original 40-pin ribbon cable between each line of the core are separated by a line more, and this new line with the original 40-core cable 40 ground among the original seven linked to the phenomenon of electromagnetic form filter away Crosstalk increases the stability of data transmission (in the high-speed electronic signal transmission, when a lot of wires with high-frequency signals close to each other together When the signal line will interfere with each other electromagnetic waves emitted, which is the so-called &quot;Crosstalk&quot; phenomenon). Ultra ATA/66/100 cable\'s basic specifications are irresolute line length does not exceed 18 inches. Ultra DMA/66 to really play that high-speed transmission is to be hard, with the row line, of course, if the core with 40 general cable, Ultra DMA/66 interface is backward-compatible hard drive is still able to work the way but can not use the Ultra DMA/66 Bale.</font> </div><br /><br /><center> <b><font color=\"red\">Read more:</font> <font color=\"red\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">1</font></b> <a href=\"/article/26/1545$2.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">2</a> * <a href=\"/article/26/1545$3.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">3</a> * <a href=\"/article/26/1545$4.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">4</a> * <a href=\"/article/26/1545$2.html\" Ã£ÂƒÂ»=\"Ã£ÂƒÂ»\">Next&gt;&gt;</a> </center><br />','empty\n'),(368,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/93/1488.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Store experience: on the selection of ESS and FastT','Store_experience_on_the_selection_of_ESS_and_FastT','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div id=\"art\" style=\"MARGIN: 15px\"><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Store experience: on the selection of ESS and FastT</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Environmental FastT, SAN, ESS <br /> Product: FastT, ESS <br /> Host Platform: Cross Platform, p / x / i / z <br /> Operating system: irrelevant</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Question: summarizes the IBM ESS Enterprise Storage Server and FastT high-end products (FastT700, FastT900) Comparison between the features. <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Answer: IBM ESS Enterprise Storage Server is to use the IBM server and storage technologies mature created by the storage server. Internal hard drive for high-bandwidth and high availability of SSA disks, using the same architecture with the IBM pSeries as the central processing unit controller, and offers a variety of external data access channel (SCSI, FC, etc.), and a wealth of complete storage management solutions. <br /> IBM FastT optical storage disk array is completely SAN technology using optical fiber and disk storage devices. Can be flexibly used in a variety of environments in the SAN disk storage requirements. Mainly based on the expansion of storage capacity of users and I / O ability to select different low , in the high-end products FastT. SAN storage management solutions needs FastT management software, SAN Switch management software, SVC management software, Tivoli SAN storage management software to achieve synergy. <br /> * ESS storage servers can also be connected into the SAN environment, as part of SAN solutions. <br /> The following table summarizes the IBM ESS Enterprise Storage Server and FastT high-end products (FastT700, FastT900) Comparison between the features.</font> </p><div align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>500)this.width=500;\" src=\"/hbcms/upload/image/big/3d/3d8fdf6b70e878edc44ed0560bb0d199.jpg\" width=\"500\" /></font> </div></div>','Store experience: on the selection of ESS and...'),(369,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/2a/1487.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Introduction of several common storage backup systems','Introduction_of_several_common_storage_backup_systems','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Common data backup systems are Host-Base, LAN-Base Structure-based SAN LAN-Free, Server-Free and other structures. <br /><br /> Host-Based backup: <br /><br /> Host-Based is the traditional structure of the data backup tape library in this structure directly connected to the server, and only data backup service for servers. In most cases, the backup server comes with most of the tape drive, the backup operation is by manual operation is often conducted in a way. <br /><br /> Host-Based backup structure has the advantage of fast data transfer, backup and simple management; disadvantage is not conducive to the sharing of backup system is not suitable for large data backup requirements now. <br /><br /> LAN-Based backup: <br /><br /> LAN-Based backup data in the system is web-based transmission. Which to configure a server as backup server, which will be responsible for the entire system backup operations. Tape library is connected to a server, data backup backup object in the data over the network to implement a backup tape library. <br /><br /> LAN-Based backup structure has the advantage of saving investment, tape library sharing, centralized backup management; its disadvantage is that pressure on the network transmission. <br /><br /> LAN-Free backup: <br /><br /> LAN-Free and Server-Free Backup System is based on SAN (Storage Area Network) based on its structure as shown below. SAN-based backup is a complete backup solution needs to occupy the traditional LAN-bandwidth solution to the problem. It uses a new architecture, the tape library and disk array of fiber each node as an independent, multi-host shared tape library backup, data flow through the network no longer directly transmitted from the disk array, tape library, network bandwidth is a need (LAN-Free) solutions. <br /><br /> With the current SAN technology continues to progress, LAN-Free structure is already quite mature, and Server-Free backup structure is not mature enough. <br /><br /> LAN-Free has the advantage of unified management of data backup, backup speed, network transmission pressure is small, tape library resource sharing; disadvantage is that high investment. <br /><br /> Using IBM Tivoly Storage Manager software, with IBM LTO tape library, etc., can achieve all of these backups. <br /><br /><br /><br /> <strong>other</strong> <br /> The choice of data backup <br /><br /> The main ways of the current data backup: LAN backup, LAN Free backup and SAN Server-Free backup of three. LAN backup for all storage types are available, LAN Free backup and SAN Server-Free backup for SAN-based storage only. <br /><br /> Traditional LAN-based backup requires the backup on each host to install a tape backup on the local system, using LAN backup strategy, when the data is not very big, centralized backup can be used. A central backup server will be installed in the LAN, and then the application server and workstation configured as a backup server to the client. Accept the central backup server running the backup on the client agent\'s request, the data passed to it through the management LAN, connected to a local tape drive resources. This approach provides a centralized, easy to manage backup program, and through the sharing of tape drives in the network resource efficiency. <br /><br /> LAN-Free backup of the data transmitted through the LAN, when a larger amount of data to backup, backup tight time window, the network prone to clogging. In the SAN environment, can be stored in the network LAN-Free backup, you need to backup the server through the SAN to connect to the tape machine, the LAN-Free backup client software trigger, the read data to back up, back up through the SAN to a shared the tape drive. This independent network LAN traffic can not be transferred, and its CPU resources required to operate way below the LAN, because the fiber channel connection does not require the server\'s TCP / IP stack, and some level of error checking can be within the Fibre Channel hardware to complete. In many solutions require a host to manage the shared storage devices and data used to find and restore the backup database. <br /><br /> SAN Server-Free Backup LAN Free backup on the need to take back the host CPU resources, if the backup process can be completed within the SAN, and a large number of data streams without flow through the server, you can greatly reduce the backup of the production system. SAN Server-Free backup is one such technology. <br /><br /> Backup the current mainstream software, such as IBM Tivoli, Veritas, were in support of the three backup programs. Three scenarios, LAN backup of the minimum amount of data, most of the server resource consumption, the lowest cost; LAN free backup data volume number, smaller footprint on the server, the cost higher; SAN Server-free backup solution to backup in a short time large amounts of data, at least on the server resource consumption, but the highest cost. Small customers can choose according to the actual situation.</font> </p>','empty\n'),(370,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/80/1486.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Fiber array: IBM optical disk array product summary','Fiber_array_IBM_optical_disk_array_product_summary','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">IBM to provide &quot;the SAN becomes simple&quot; package contains a IBM TotalStorage Fibre Array Storage Technology (FAStT) array, a host adapter, FC SW GBIC, Hot swap HDD, FC SW Cable and power cord. IBM TotalStorage FAStT family of disk subsystem is to support the large and growing data storage needs of critical applications and design, but also laid the foundation for the future of SAN. SMEs demand for storage solutions along with the rapid development of its own rapid growth, this, IBM introduced a tailor-made for SMEs, the low-end storage products and solutions and channel support measures. IBM introduced the &quot;simple storage&quot; development strategy, which consists of four parts, including open storage, self storage, integrated storage and virtual storage. At the same time in the &quot;simple storage&quot; strategy support, IBM also introduced for the storage needs of SMEs in the following two storage solution.</font> <p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#008080\">The first PowerPac solution:</font> eight-way UNIX server using IBM\'s p650, SAN Fibre Channel switch for core equipment to FAStT600/700 for SAN disk arrays and using LTO tape library for data backup, all storage devices are used for Fibre Channel SAN architecture connection.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#008080\">The second X-File Pac Solution:</font> Based on the Intel platform and the PC server is IBM xSeries and FAStT products, combined with open and &quot;on-demand&quot; capacity, fully embodies the high-performance, high reliability and high availability characteristics.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The two programs above are using FAStT disk array products. Therefore, we should be based on the actual needs of enterprise storage, optical disk array to determine the grade of choice. FAStT200 for workgroup and departmental servers cost-effective RAID storage solutions; FAStT600 focused on scalable computing environments demand high-performance storage devices; FAStT700 2Gbps Fibre Channel technology through the provision of superior performance; FAStT900 is targeted with Strain computing environment to be scalable high-performance storage devices. <br /> IBM storage systems market for SME customers a &quot;SME SAN slimming plan&quot; around the plans to introduce a series of solutions in a easy to integrate, simple and easy to operate, reasonably priced, and the principle of integrated application built to help small and medium SAN enterprise market customers storage management solution for business efficiency and business continuity issues. &quot;Amazing Dolphin&quot; - IBM FAStT storage array is IBM &quot;SME SAN fitness program,&quot; the core product. As with a Fibre Channel host and drive, IBM FAStT storage arrays provide flexible, affordable optical storage, is designed for the need for external storage solutions for organizations and departments of the server design is a web-based, integrated storage management tool .</font> </p></div>','The first PowerPac solution: eight-way UNIX server using IBM\'s p650, SAN Fibre Channel switch for core equipment to FAStT600/700 for SAN disk arrays and using LTO tape library for data backup, all storage devices are used for Fibre Channel SAN architecture...'),(371,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/e9/1484.html','http://www.ixdba.net','SAN, NAS, DAS distinction between meaning and structure','SAN_NAS_DAS_distinction_between_meaning_and_structure','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font size=\"2\"><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 13px\">With the development of computer technology and extensive application of storage technology has been applied in various areas of industry and professional attention. The rapid growth of data for enterprise development is put forward new problems and requirements, how to ensure data consistency, security and reliability, how to implement centralized management of different data, how to achieve centralized access to data on the network, how to achieve different main types of data access and protection and so on. All this calls for a new network storage technology and its products appear. <br /><br /> SAN and NAS technologies and products, the emergence of not only expand the space for network development and, more importantly, they will be stored in network technology and the emerging field of organically combine the process of development in the IT industry plays a vital role. <br /><br /> SAN and NAS are often seen as two competing technologies, in fact, the two complement each other very well also be able to provide access to different types of data. SAN for the massive, block-oriented data transfer, while the NAS provides file-level data access features. <br /><br /> Both techniques will not only meet the needs of flexible storage access, and SAN and NAS are based on open, industry-standard network protocols: protocol for Fibre Channel SAN and NAS network protocol used (such as TCP / IP). SAN broader range of applications, but also provide storage on NAS devices, and NAS file-level data generally limited access applications. If you do not take into account the differences between them, SAN and NAS storage in the enterprise today are playing an important role, than the traditional server-attached storage has more advantages. <br /><br /> SAN and NAS in the data center on the traditional server-attached storage is a strong complementary and alternative. Thus, enterprise customers come to realize its many advantages, including improved flexibility, more convenient storage deployment, and lower total cost of ownership. Although SAN and NAS technology can provide a competitive advantage, but they are for the specific environment and application and design. <br /><br /> Key features SAN <br /><br /> SAN as a network infrastructure to provide flexible, high performance and highly scalable storage environment and design. SAN through the server and storage devices (such as disk storage systems and tape libraries) connection between this purpose. <br /><br /> High-performance Fibre Channel switches and Fibre Channel network protocols can ensure reliable and effective devices. These connections to the local fiber or SCSI (via SCSI-to-Fibre Channel switch, or gateway) basis. One or more Fibre Channel switches in the network topology (SAN architecture) in the form of host servers and storage devices connected. <br /><br /> Because the SAN is transferred between servers and storage devices optimized for large data, so application of SAN is ideal for the following choice: <br /><br /> Mission-critical database applications, which can be expected response time, availability and scalability are the basic elements. <br /> Centralized storage and backup, including performance, data consistency and reliability to ensure the security of business-critical data. <br /> High availability and failover environment to ensure a lower cost, higher application level. <br /> Scalable storage virtualization, storage and can connect directly to the host phase separation, and to ensure dynamic storage partition. <br /> Improved disaster tolerance characteristics of the host server and its connected devices to provide high performance and scalable Fibre Channel distance (150 km). <br /> The main strengths of SAN <br /><br /> The face of rapidly growing data storage needs, large enterprises and service providers beginning to select the SAN as a network infrastructure, because the SAN with excellent scalability. Indeed, SAN storage architecture than the traditional advantages have more significant. For example, the traditional server-attached storage is often difficult to update or centralized management. Each server must be shut down to add and configure the new storage. In comparison, SAN without downtime and disruption will increase the connection to the server storage. Data can be centrally managed SAN, reducing total cost of ownership. <br /><br /> Using Fibre Channel technology, SAN can effectively transmit data block. By supporting the storage and transfer huge amounts of data blocks between servers, SAN provides an effective way of data backup. Thus, traditionally used for data backup can save network bandwidth for other applications down. <br /><br /> Open, industry-standard Fibre Channel SAN technology also enables very flexible. SAN overcome the traditional limitations with the SCSI cable connected to greatly expand the distance between servers and storage, thus increasing the possibility of more connections. Improved server scalability also simplifies deployment and upgrades, protecting the original hardware investment. <br /><br /> In addition, SAN storage network can better control the environment for transaction-based system in which performance and availability requirements. SAN using highly reliable and high-performance Fibre Channel protocol to meet this need. <br /><br /> Another merit of SAN block transfer data to the enterprise the ability to data-intensive applications. In the data transmission process, SAN nodes in the communication (especially servers) on the treatment costs less overhead, because the data transmission is divided into smaller blocks of data. Therefore, the Fibre Channel SAN in the transmission of large data blocks are very effective, making it ideal for Fibre Channel storage-intensive environments.</span></font>','empty\n'),(372,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/c2/1483.html','http://www.ixdba.net','IBM Tivoli Storage Manager implementation and installation configuration principle','IBM_Tivoli_Storage_Manager_implementation_and_installation_configuration_principle','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Backup Software: Tivoli</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> Tivoli storage manage <br /> Tivoli Storage Manager Functional Description <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">TSM technical parameters</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> TSM version: 5.1 <br /> TSM5.1 server software operating platform: IBM AIX 4.3.2, 4.3.3., 5l Sun Solaris 2.6, 7, 8. HP-UX 11.0. Microsoft Windows NT/2000 Workstation or Server Version 4.0, SP3, SP4, SP5 , SP6 or SP6a. <br /> TSM client software: supports almost all popular operating system platforms. Such as IBM, all operating systems, Windows, Apple, Novell, DEC, HP, SUN, SCO, SGI, Linux and so on. <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Tivoli Data Protection for Oracle 2.2: implementation of Oracle database online backup and recovery. <br /> Oracle server can run on platforms including Windows NT/2000, AIX, HP-UX, Solaris.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> Tivoli TSM product features details:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> Tivoli TSM (Tivoli Storage Manager) is an enterprise-level Client / Server structure, cross-platform network backup, recovery and storage management software. TSM Client main function is to provide the necessary backup to the TSM Server data, or obtain the TSM Server backup data and archive data has been to Client restore the data. TSM Server TSM Client is responsible for managing backup data, backup strategy and management connected to the TSM Server on the various types of storage products.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> Automatic backup and restore TSM</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> Once the setup is complete the entire backup system, each application server will need to back up the specified time to the data sent to the TSM server in the centralized storage. If you need to recover data, TSM Client-side through the very simple to use as long as the graphical interface or by the application which issued a directive that an object file restore, TSM Server automatically remove files from the tape library, to the TSM Client. If the backup tape is not in the tape library, TSM Server prompts the system administrator into a tape. <br /> TSM is a complete online backup software. The database, TSM backup through TSM Connect Agent is an open database. The general file system files, TSM\'s Client-side can back up open files, and can even backup files being modified. TSM encountered when the backup files to be backed up when being changed, there are four approaches:</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> Do not back up, while leaving a mark in the log; <br /> Back up again several times at once (the number of scheduled by the user), such as files are still in the edit, no backup, to log; <br /> Retry several times (the number of pre-specified by the user), the last time regardless of the file changes at rest or still have the backup of the file.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">TSM backup software to consider than the more similar is the data recovery capabilities. TSM concept is: the purpose is to restore the backup. Therefore, the evaluation of the backup software, backup speed advantage of TSM is not obvious, but the speed of recovery is often several times more than other software.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> TSM This amazing recovery speed, and many other unique features mainly depends on a strong core TSM, TSM is a relational database engine. So far no other backup software is a relational database used for the core. Relational database processing power and speed of TSM performance search using the index file over other backup software as the main engine. TSM perfect media management capabilities also benefit from this database engine.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> TSM backup and recovery process of the fault tolerance</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> TSM is the only backup using the database management software as the core, each backup object as a transaction (Transaction) to deal with. Therefore, a strong fault tolerance TSM, TSM data transmission principle is: try to avoid unnecessary duplication of data transmission network bandwidth. When a backup or restore process because of network outages or machine failures and unexpected termination of the next re-submitted when the backup or restore process, TSM will continue to transfer from the point of interruption, rather than starting from scratch (many backup software have to be redone from scratch .) Because the TSM backup completed or not each object has a log record of each transaction as the banking system has been recorded as completed or not. <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">TSM incremental backup forever</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /> TSM support for a comprehensive backup and unique &quot;permanent incremental backup&quot; approach. Permanent incremental backup is: do all the initial data files when the overall backup, after backup only new or changed files. This approach reduces backup times and required storage capacity and reduce the network burden. In this way because TSM backup of each object as a transaction record in its relational database, each object corresponds to the file system backup of a file. When users need to restore the file system, TSM find all belong to the original backup file system objects to the user. Therefore, TSM can do incremental backups forever.</font> </p>','Backup Software:...'),(373,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/62/1477.html','http://www.ixdba.net','IBM DS300 for iSCSI configuration','IBM_DS300_for_iSCSI_configuration','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">iSCSI is a popular new technology in recent years, the use of iSCSI technology, not only saving the cost of the project, while the performance of iSCSI performance is also very good!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">This document briefly describes how the Red Flag 4.1 series and RedFlag 5.0 series of iSCSI-initiator-side configuration, and the third-party iSCSI target-side connection. Here to IBM DS300 example for the target side. <br /><br /> What is iSCSI <br /> iSCSI (internet SCSI) is a set defined in the TCP / IP network protocol on the transport SCSI commands. He will be the definition of SCSI Initiator (initiator) and target side (target) from the SCSI bus connection to the internet on the expansion, breaking the SCSI storage from the definition of the limits. The following brief description of the icon to iSCSI works. <br /></font> <a name=\"entrymore\"><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Red Flag products currently contains only the initiator driver, he can support the iSCSI protocol standard connection to any of the target device. <br /> Product configuration in the red flag iSCSI Initiator 4.1 series of default does not include iSCSI initiator driver, but you can go to red flag the official support site to download the relevant drivers. Red Flag 5.0 for the series, the default is to include the iSCSI initiator driver. The following configurations are red DC5.0 example. Configuration, we need to use the following three files: <br /> File description <br /> / Etc / iscsi.conf initiator parameter definition, which is the core configuration file <br /> / Etc / initiatorname.iscsi initiator name definition file and the target for communication, some of the target must be specified initiator name <br /> / Etc / fstab.iscsi defined automatically mount the file, similar to the system / etc / fstab file, which is optional <br /><br /> Here we go step by step configuration First, open the / etc / iscsi.conf file, found about 69 lines, this line like the following <br /> # DiscoveryAddress = 172.16.81.195 <br /> Remove the front of the \\ # Note, fill in the target side of the IP address of \\ footnote {Here is the default port used by iSCSI protocol defined in 3260, if you use another port, use the ip: port way to define}. <br /> Then open / etc / initiatorname.iscsi files, comment below this line <br /> InitiatorName = / sbin / iscsi-iname <br /> And add this line below <br /> InitiatorName = iqn.192.168.5.1.iscsi.1 <br /> There are two iSCSI node name formats, iqn (iSCSI check character name) format and meet the IEEE-EUI format. iqn the iSCSI names are as follows: <br /> iqn.yyyy-mm.backward_naming_authority: unique_device_name <br /> Such as <br /> iqn.2006-02.com.redflag-linux: e2d4edf37 <br /> Through the above two steps, iSCSI initiator configuration basically completed. Next you need to configure the target, the following example we IBM DS300. <br /> First, you need to complete the basic configuration DS300, including the configuration of RAID, LVM configuration and so on. <br /> Open the IBM ServeRAID Manager, switch to the following screen, click the Add button, pop-up box on the exchange are required to complete two rows, one is the initiator IQN, is that when we configure the iSCSI initiator configuration iCSI Name, or iqn.192.168.5.1. iscsi.1; fill in the initiator iSCSI initiator alias host name, host name is not here the full name, such as your host name is ora1.redflag-linux.com, you only need to fill ora1. <br /><br /> Click OK to complete the configuration of an initiator, you can use the same method to join the other initiator. <br /><br /> Click Next, the following screen appears <br /><br /> The figure in the left column is configured to use the name of a valid storage device, select the one you need to add the device name, the right column select ora1, said it would use the device assigned to the ora1. Click the button to add it to the right column The results as shown below <br /><br /> Can repeat the above steps to add other storage devices in, click the Next button, the following interface <br /><br /><br /> Click the Apply button, ServRAID will modify the configuration of DS300. Before changes will give an OK dialog box, click the Yes button. <br /><br /> ServRAID start applying the new configuration <br /><br /> Finally, the interface is as follows <br /><br /> Here so far, DC300\'s configured, and then back to iSCSI initiator host, at the command line, type the following command to start the iSCSI service <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsi start <br /> After approximately 30 seconds, use the dmesg command to view the system log, you should see information similar to the following <br /> ************************************************** *************** <br /> Vendor: SEAGATE Model: ST39103FC Rev: 0002 <br /> Type: Direct-Access ANSI SCSI revision: 02</font></a> </p>','iSCSI is a popular new technology in recent years, the use of iSCSI technology, not only saving the cost of the project, while the performance of iSCSI performance is also very...'),(374,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/bd/1469.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Os sharing on multi-lun, and file systems, databases discussions!','Os_sharing_on_multilun_and_file_systems_databases_discussions','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h2> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Discuss the multi-os shared lun, and the file system, database problems!</font> </h2><div class=\"t_msgfont\" id=\"postmessage_330717\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">os do not write on what information it raw lun, no os will automatically recognize that the raw lun his format If so, why not share a number of os raw lun? <br /> Environment in oracle rac, oracle will write his own raw lun fs, such as cluster fs, os does not recognize the fs, still be considered to be a raw lun <br /> Read and write arbitration by the oracel do, do not need to do os, os can share raw lun <br /><br /> Actually can not, then I will have problems, please understand that heroes are the problems younger brother, thank you! <br /></font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><div class=\"t_msgfont\" id=\"postmessage_330722\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"