 /></font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><div class=\"t_msgfont\" id=\"postmessage_361192\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">You say the drive is initiator, NIC is responsible for the TCP / IP protocol parsing out, and then systems software initiator package to package content from ISCSI resolve it. Software initiator using a host CPU, CACHE, the host will have some impact, but as you said, the computer CPU upgrade so little impact. <br /> Add ISCSI card, of course, better, that is, all packets are in the ISCSI card resolution process is complete.</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><div class=\"t_msgfont\" id=\"postmessage_361324\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">iSCSI cards, TOE-EQUIPPED NIC, also according to the functional size of two ways: <br /> Full TCP / IP offload <br /> - Fragmentation, out of order packets handled by TOE <br /> - Increased memory / processing requirements <br /> - ISCSI &amp; SCSI handled by host <br /> Full TCP / IP + iSCSI / SCSI <br /> - Completes storage connection <br /> - Runs all layers on TOE (HBA) <br /> The more full, the price is more expensive</font> </div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_msgfont\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></div><div class=\"t_