INSERT INTO `entries` VALUES (380,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/29/987.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Illustrated: Configuring RAID disk array (s','Illustrated_Configuring_RAID_disk_array_s','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Note: Please pre-backup data on your server, configure the disk array, the process will delete all your data on your hard disk! <br /><br /> First, why do you want to create logical disks? <br /> When the hard drive connected to the array card (RAID) on the operating system will not directly see the physical disk, so you need to create into a one set to RAID0, 1 and 5 so the logical disks (also called <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/29/987.html\">containers</a> ), so the system can correctly identify it. <br /> Logical Disk (Logic Drive), <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/29/987.html\">container</a> (Container) or virtual disk (Virtual Drive) expressed a meaning, they are just different array of different name for card manufacturers. <br /><br /> Second, create a logical disk array cards use their own configuration tool, that the array card BIOS. (Generally used for reinstalling the system or install an operating system is not going to create <a class=\"kw\" href=\"/article/29/987.html\">the container</a> (Adaptec RAID Card) / logical drive (AMI / LSI array of cards). <br /> Use the configuration tools provided by third parties to achieve the management of the array cards. Such as the Dell Array Manager. (The software has been installed for the server operating system) <br /><br /> Third, correctly identify the type of your array of cards to identify your disk array controller (disk array controller is optional, if you did not purchase the disk array controller, then to the step can save) <br /> If you have an Adaptec RAID controller (PERC 2, PERC2/SI, PERC3/SI, PERC3/DI), you will see the following information: <br /> Dell PowerEdge Expandable RAID Controller 3/Di, BIOS V2.7-x [Build xxxx] (c) 1998-2002 Adaptec, Inc. All Rights Reserved. &lt;&lt;&lt;Press CTRL + A for Configuration Utility!&gt;&gt;&gt; <br /> This section of the configuration array reference card is as follows: <br /> Create a container step (here we focus on the card itself to use the array configuration tool with a four-channel configuration PERC2 card, so may your array of cards because the channels for different reasons, with it slightly different) <br /><br /> Note: Please pre-backup data on your server, configure the disk array, the process will delete all your data on your hard disk! <br /><br /> 1) First, when the system appears in the process of self-what prompted, press &quot;Ctrl + A&quot; key: <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_01_2005_9_14_12_10_31.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"78\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_01_2005_9_14_12_10_31.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2) enter the array card configuration program, then select the &quot;Container configuration utility&quot;. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_02_2005_9_14_12_10_50.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"51\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_02_2005_9_14_12_10_50.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">3) into the &quot;Container configuration utility&quot;, this time, you will want to select &quot;Initialize Drivers&quot; option to the new or the need to re-initialize the hard disk to create the container. (Note: If the original hard disk will delete all data on the current hard drive) <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_03_2005_9_14_12_11_5.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"32\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_03_2005_9_14_12_11_5.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">4) window will appear and the channel RAID card connected to the channel on the hard disk, you can use the &quot;Insert&quot; key to select the hard disk needs to be initialized. Please note the following help tips window. <br /></font> <p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">www.ixdba.net</font></a></font></strong> </p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_04_2005_9_14_12_11_17.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"107\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_04_2005_9_14_12_11_17.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">5) When you select Finish and press &quot;Enter&quot; key, the system key appears about warnings. If you confirm, select &quot;Y&quot; can be. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_05_2005_9_14_12_11_28.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"24\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_05_2005_9_14_12_11_28.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">6) after initializing the hard disk can be created according to your needs the appropriate level (RAID1, RAID0, etc.) of the container. Here we take an example to illustrate how to create RAID5 it. In the main menu (Main Menu) select &quot;Create container&quot; and press Enter. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_06_2005_9_14_12_11_39.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"57\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_06_2005_9_14_12_11_39.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br />&quot;Size =&quot; 2 &quot;&gt; 7) with the&quot; insert &quot;key to select the hard disk needs to be used to create Container list to the right. Press&quot; Enter &quot;. <br /><div align=\"center\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_07_2005_9_14_12_11_52.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"107\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clie