 the &quot;Container&quot; in the &quot;Status&quot; as &quot;Scrub&quot;. When it becomes &quot;Ok&quot;. The new Container is created it will have a redundant function (if this Container supports redundant. Scrub will be a need for a long time process, in the Scrub of the process, you can exit the administrative interface, restart, or your operating system. Container not during this time in a redundant state) <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_11_2005_9_14_12_12_29.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"112\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_11_2005_9_14_12_12_29.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">11) Containers created. Use the &quot;ESC&quot; key to launch and restart the computer. <br /></font>','empty\n'),(381,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/48/988.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Illustrated RAID: RAID disk array configuration','Illustrated_RAID_RAID_disk_array_configuration','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<html><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Third, correctly identify the type of your array of cards to identify your disk array controller (disk array controller is optional, if you did not purchase the disk array controller, then to the step can save) <br /><br /> If you have an AMI / LSI RAID controller (PERC2/SC, PERC2/DC, PERC3/SC, PERC3/DC, PERC4/DI, PERC4/DC), when the system POST you will see the following information : <br /> Dell PowerEdge Expandable RAID Controller BIOS X. XX Jun 26.2001</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Copyright (C) AMERICAN MEGATRENDS INC. <br /> Press CTRL + M to Run Configuration Utility or Press CTRL + H for WebBios <br /> Or PowerEdge Expandable RAID Controller BIOS X. XX Feb 03,2003 Copyright (C) LSI Logic Corp. <br /> Press CTRL + M to Run Configuration Utility or Press CTRL + H for WebBios <br /> This section of the configuration array card, please refer to the following: <br /><br /> In the AIM / LSI RAID controller to create Logical Drive (logical disk) <br /> --- PERC2/SC, PERC2/DC, PERC3/SC, PERC3/DC, PERC3/DCL <br /> --- PERC4 DI / DC (slightly different, please read the following documents) <br /><br /> * Note: Please pre-backup data on your server, configure the disk array, the process will delete all your data on your hard disk! <br /><br /> 1) In the self-test process, when prompted to press the &lt;Control&gt; &lt;M&gt; button, press and enter the RAID configuration interface. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_12_2005_9_14_12_16_49.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"38\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_12_2005_9_14_12_16_49.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">2) If the server in the Cluster mode, the following information will be displayed &quot;Press any key to continue.&quot; <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_13_2005_9_14_12_17_1.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"98\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_13_2005_9_14_12_17_1.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">3) Select Configure, and press Enter. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_14_2005_9_14_12_17_12.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"98\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_14_2005_9_14_12_17_12.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div></p><p><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">4) If you need to configure a RAID, select New Configuration, and press Enter. <br /> If there is already a logical disk can be used, select the View / Add Configuration, and press Enter. <br /> In this paper, we will select &quot;New Configuration&quot; as an example (Note: Selecting New Configuration will</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Deleting the existing configuration information on disk array) <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_15_2005_9_14_12_17_22.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"99\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_15_2005_9_14_12_17_22.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /></p><p> <strong><font color=\"#ecf4f5\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net\">www.ixdba.net</a></font></strong> </p><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">5) Select YES, and press Enter. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\