l drive. <br /> Select Accept, and press Enter. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_21_2005_9_14_12_18_29.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"99\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_21_2005_9_14_12_18_29.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">13) Press ESC key to return, select YES, and press Enter. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_23_2005_9_14_12_19_0.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"99\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_23_2005_9_14_12_19_0.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">14) Press any key to continue. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_24_2005_9_14_12_19_9.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"99\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_24_2005_9_14_12_19_9.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">15) Initialize Logical Disk (Logical driver) (just created a logical disk to go through initialization, can be used) <br /> Press ESC button to return to the main menu, select Initialize, and press Enter. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_25_2005_9_14_12_19_20.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"99\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_25_2005_9_14_12_19_20.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">16) need to initialize the selected logical disk, and press the space bar to accept. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_26_2005_9_14_12_19_30.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"99\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_26_2005_9_14_12_19_30.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">17) Select YES, and press Enter. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\">/ This.width; this.width = document.body.clientWidth-450} &quot;src =&quot; http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_27_2005_9_14_12_19_40.gif &quot;width =&quot; 210 &quot;/&gt; </div><br /> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">18) Press any key to continue, and reboot the system, RAID configured. <br /></font> <div align=\"center\"> <a href=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_28_2005_9_14_12_19_51.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><img alt=\"Click here to view pictures in a new window\" border=\"0\" height=\"99\" onload=\"javascript:if(this.width>document.body.clientWidth-450) {this.height=(document.body.clientWidth-450)*this.height/this.width;this.width=document.body.clientWidth-450}\" src=\"http://www.serverol.com/upimages/tech/config_a_raid_28_2005_9_14_12_19_51.gif\" width=\"210\" /></font></a> </div><br />','Third, correctly identify the type of your array of cards to identify your disk array controller (disk array controller is optional, if you did not purchase the disk array controller, then to the step can save)  If you have an AMI / LSI RAID controller (PERC2/SC, PERC2/DC, PERC3/SC, PERC3/DC,...'),(382,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/7e/1202.html','http://www.ixdba.net','How to choose the right RAID level?','How_to_choose_the_right_RAID_level','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">How to choose the right RAID level?</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">There are different RAID configuration or &quot;class&quot;, each level has its own unique advantages. Understanding will enable you to determine the RAID level server reliability, data availability and storage performance in the right combination to meet specific e-business needs. Intel Integrated RAID software supports the most widely used RAID level: 0,1,5, and 10.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">RAID 0 level will be assigned to the data base with more than one disk, there is no redundancy or parity. The main features of the RAID level is extremely high data throughput speeds. Data access to multiple disks make disk access more efficient, which improves read performance data. Any one disk fails the data stored will be lost</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Copy using two hard drives store data, we implemented a RAID1-level (called disk mirroring), in most cases through the software. If a hard disk fails, it will be all the data (and software applications) to save to another hard disk. Although it provides maximum fault tolerance, but requires twice the disk number, so RAID1 level is extremely expensive option. With the declining cost of disk technology, RAID1-level optimization of data availability has become a viable option.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">RAID 5 level will baseband section and the &quot;parity&quot; the combination together, this case, the data distribution in the online group\'s hard drive. Parity RAID controller data to understand the data stored on your hard drive. Suppose that a hard disk fails, the controller can use the parity information to re-create the lost data. RAID5-level data to allow both read and write, which is data-intensive applications that require high performance provided support. You can adjust the size of the baseband section to optimize performance, the Intel Integrated RAID software support this feature. RAID5 reasonable price level provides the best performance and data security, so far it is very popular.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">RAID 10 level (0 +1) is a RAID0 and RAID1-level combination of grade, it will mirror the baseband section, and together the disk. 0 RAID10 level provides a fast performance and data protection features. In this configuration, the data is distributed across several hard disk (which is similar with the 0 level), and the data of each disk are copied to another disk, thereby protecting the data. We recommend that the best performance and data availability requirements of a small network with 10.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">From large databases to e-mail systems and Web servers, they all select the appropriate RAID configuration are required to provide all the e-commerce data protection, server reliability and storage performance.</font> </p>','How to choose the right RAID...'),(383,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/48/1034.html','http://www.ixdba.net','SUN CMT, CPU market by ramming paste','SUN_CMT_CPU_market_by_ramming_paste','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">If you later buy a server, just ask the machine to support the number of CPU, that is, processor, may need to be careful, because you might buy a cpu, the results of several cpu to pay the license.</font> <p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Not impossible, in fact, already have such a situation, that is, SUN CMT appearance, making processor, that is, cpu, began to be a vague concept, and core (kernel) may replace the cpu become the new inspection standards .</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">SUN CMT but it is still a good thing, in a single chip, integrating a number of Core, now, can support the UltraSPARC architecture 8 core, however, SUN that this chip is a CPU, that is, a processor, such as a UltraSPARC T1 CPU, there may be 8 core.</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">However, other vendors such as IBM, ADM / Intel, and so, if the CPU module also integrates a number of Core, but they think this is the number of CPU, that is, multiple processor, such as IBM\'s Power5 multi-core CPU module If multiple core, IBM believes that he is more than CPU.</font> </p><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The greatest impact, it should be that software vendors charge by the cpu, such as Oracle, therefore, Oracle is not in accordance with the cpu started to charge, but in accordance with the core to charge different is that different vendors may not like the price discount, the following is discount percentage of a public</font> </p><pre style=\"BACKGROUND: #e6e6e6; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Oracle Processor Licensing Cores Processor Factor\r\n    UltraSPARC T1 8 0.25\r\n    AMD / Intel 2 0.5\r\n    All other Multi-core Chips (IBM Pseries, SM USIV, etc.) 2 0.75\r\n    Single Core Servers 1 1.00\r\n</font> </pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">According to this standard, an UltraSPARC T1\'s cpu, China announced a cpu, although the discount is very low, but, but need to buy 8 * 0.25 = 2 cpu license, a dual-core of the AMD / Intel chips, including two core, outside is 2 cpu, but only need to buy 2 * 0.5 = 1 cpu license.</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">In addition, IBM also supports multi-core though, such as 8-way of the CPU module, but from internal structure, is equal to 4 dual-core. Therefore, the multiple of the charges IBM\'s power cpu cpu simply put the number of * 0.75 to buy license.</font> </p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Finally, you may see is, SUN cpu how to buy a few license, while others only buy a few cpu license. Not surprisingly, this is the new standard.</font> </p>','empty\n'),(384,'BLOG','BLOG','en','/article/ad/1036.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Or cx series, how to add / replace the host','Or_cx_series_how_to_add__replace_the_host','2010-11-12','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The article said, the story of a cx700 and powerpath, as written, then also write down the story to another, personal feeling, this story is a story perhaps more interesting than the previous, and more reference, because in practice, may often encountered.</font> <p></p><p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The origin of the story is that our HA, aix host, previously only a card through a fiber optical switch connected to the cx700. Now, looking to buy a piece of IBM Fibre card, ready to install up by another optical switch connected to the cx700, expand